job_description.0: International Tourism And Transport Company  ASX 200 Listed with 11,000+ employees globally  About Us  Competitive salary and benefits package  Kelsian Group Limited (Kelsian) is an ASX200 listed business with over 11,000 employees across Australia, Singapore, United Kingdom and United States of America.  At Kelsian Group Limited, we are more than just a company – we are a team of dedicated professionals committed to innovation, growth, and positive change. With a strong commitment to our employees and a vision for a brighter future, we're poised for continued success in the years ahead.  About the Role - Bridge the Gap between Data & Business Insights  We are on the hunt for a unique blend of technical prowess and business insight - a data professional who thrives on solving complex challenges and influencing key stakeholders. This position offers the opportunity to work hand-in-hand with our Group CEO and senior leadership team, directly addressing their most pressing data concerns. Additionally, you will work closely with our data team to play a pivotal role in furthering our long-term data agenda.  Reporting To • Group CEO (2 days a week) • D&A Lead (3 days a week)  Your Role Entails • Engage in consultations with business users to grasp their reporting needs and translate them into actionable solutions. • Collaborate with and influence other teams to encourage sound and practical data capture and reporting processes. • Design, develop, and deploy reports utilizing a range of tools, especially Incorta and Excel. • Dive deep into data sources, understanding their intricacies and ensuring their optimal use. • Empower and coach business users, enhancing their data literacy and promoting the use of the developed solutions. • Collaborate with the data team, contributing to larger projects. • Consistently create and update vital documentation, ensuring clarity and accessibility.  Essential Traits  What Sets You Apart: • Rapid adaptability to new tools and data sources. • An unyielding commitment to customer service. • Hands-on experience with BI toolsets (such as Incorta, SQL, PowerBI, Tableau). • Profound understanding of the art of science of data visualisation and metrics. • Demonstrated ability to manage time effectively amidst competing priorities.  Desirable Traits • Direct experience with Incorta. • Expertise in data modelling and architecture. • Fluency in BI-related languages (e.g. Python). • Familiarity with cloud technologies, particularly AWS. • Proven record of positively influencing, coaching, and guiding non-technical stakeholders.  Why Join Us  This is a unique opportunity to work directly with our most senior leaders, influence key business decisions, and be at the forefront of a data-driven transformation. With dual reporting lines, your work will have immediate visibility and impact, offering you a platform for unparalleled professional growth.  If you have a background in data and computer science, a consulting mindset, and are looking to make waves in a dynamic environment, we want to hear from you!  How To Apply  We are requesting your resume and a cover letter explaining why you are the best person for this position.  Click APPLY and fill in as much information as you can in the track record section of the application, paying close attention to each question.  Applicants must have the appropriate work visa and must not have any restrictions to their entitlement to work.  Don't miss this opportunity to lead the charge in shaping our future. Apply today and be a part of something extraordinary!  Applications close by 5pm Monday 23 October 2023  Kelsian Group is committed to providing equal employment opportunities and embracing diversity to the benefit of all. We actively encourage applications from any background. We strongly encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people.

job_description.2: You shall find the IDA team very self-motivated, high standard and forward thinking focused, and highly hands-on.  Responsibilities • Collaborate with team leader and senior data scientists, as well as clients and internal stakeholders to understand and document their business requirements, problems and objectives. • Understand data structures and business and extract and integrate required data sources for analysis according to business requirements. • Develop and evaluate data analytics models, algorithms, systems and solutions, including undertaking data extraction, pre-processing, modeling, evaluation, deployment, and maintenance. • Collaborate with senior data scientists and team leader and clients to productise and pilot analytical models for production and insight per clients required. • Undertake cost-benefit, forecasting and impact analysis by effective presentations of data-driven findings to clients and stakeholders. • Document and communicate all relevant work and work outcomes.  Qualifications • Solid background, knowledge and capabilities in statistics, mathematics, computer science, informatics, computing, or closely relevant scientific field. • Experienced in data-driven analytics hands-on experience with deep know-how of predictive modeling, machine learning and data mining, and relevant modeling approaches and algorithms. • Demonstrated capabilities to develop and evaluate statistical analysis and modeling algorithms and apply these algorithms for data-driven solutions to problems in new domains. • Demonstrated knowledge of SQL (data extraction and manipulation), expertise in SAS programming, and software development skills in one to several scripting languages (Python/R). • Demonstrated capabilities to communicate and engage with a range of stakeholder groups and technical project teams. • Demonstrated capabilities to work effectively as a member of a data science project team. • Demonstrated experience for independent problem-solving and self-motivated innovation, education and services. job_description.3: • ASX Listed Energy Company - Adelaide Head Office • Competitive package + bonus + benefits + flexibility • Mid-size company: big enough for opportunities, small enough to get things done.  At Beach Energy, we are dedicated to advancing exploration and subsurface technologies and we are committed to pushing the boundaries of what is possible in our field, and we are now seeking a talented Data Analyst to join our Exploration and Subsurface (E&S) team.  About the Role  You will play a crucial role in transforming raw data into actionable insights through data engineering techniques. Leveraging your expertise in SQL and Python, you will collaborate closely with our multidisciplinary team to engineer, integrate, analyse, and interpret data, contribute to decision-making processes, and drive the success of our exploration and subsurface projects.  Key responsibilities will include: • Utilising a strong skill set in working with SQL Server, including data manipulation, advanced SQL query-building, spatial geometry management, and CRS (coordinate reference system) management in datasets. • Developing ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) processes to automate data transformation workflows, addressing critical information needs and enhancing efficiency. • Collaborating with cross-functional teams to understand data requirements and develop effective solutions using on-prem and cloud technologies. • Demonstrating competency in developing data models spanning from conceptual to physical, crucial for implementing business information workflows. • Managing and overseeing SQL databases, ensuring smooth operation, high availability, and optimal performance.  About You  Success in our multidisciplinary team environment requires effective collaboration. The ideal candidate should be a team player, capable of communicating complex technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders and working seamlessly with professionals from diverse backgrounds.  A solid foundation in SQL and Python is essential for this role. The candidate should demonstrate expertise in writing logical SQL queries and effective Python scripting according to the industry standards. Familiarity with data visualisation tools will be advantageous.  You will need: • Effective communication skills with the ability to understand business information requirements and present complex data insights in a clear and understandable manner. • Excellent problem-solving and critical-thinking skills. • Experience with data visualisation tools (e.g., Spotfire, Power BI and ArcGIS Portal) is a plus. • Knowledge of geoscience concepts and terminology is desirable but not mandatory.  About Us  Beach Energy is an ASX listed oil and gas exploration and production company. Founded in 1961, our head office is in Adelaide, and we operate in several locations in Australia and in New Zealand.  Beach’s purpose is to ‘sustainably deliver energy for communities. That means we are committed to a just and sustainable energy transition whilst maintaining high health, safety, and environmental standards. See our actions and plans in our Sustainability Report.  How to Apply  Beach is committed to improving gender diversity and Indigenous participation; we encourage all applications.  Please submit your application, cover letter and updated CV by 19 October 2023.  For this opportunity you must be eligible to work in Australia.
job_description.4: Careers that Change Lives  Join the Global Operations & Supply Chain organization as a Principle Advanced Analytics Analyst for the Supplier Transfer Optimization Program (STOP), an Enterprise-wide strategic program to strengthen Medtronics supply base excellence through strategic negotiation and transfers to preferred suppliers.  Through this program, you will help build a pipeline of supplier transfer activities that will improve supplier performance and quality while delivering margin expansion across Medtronic. This role will partner with business stakeholders to understand and solve business problems.  Primarily they are responsible for building insights and analytics while providing subject matter expertise, technical knowledge, and analytic product ownership. They will create user workflows analytics and insights and bring them to life. The role supports Centers of Excellence (COE) as well as tactical business users.  The mission of this role is to contribute to the building of GO&SC INSIGHTS to drive for best-in-class practices and tools for Global Operations & Supply Chain.  The role will also need to work hand in hand with the Analytics Development Team & the Data Services Team to manage the creation and deployment of solutions that simplify our customers processes and generate insights that align with our customers goals. This role requires you to be the user of your tools and generate insights to share with the business.  This role needs to provide excellent customer service in a way that helps our stakeholders perform at their very best. This role needs to empower our stakeholders to perform at their very best.  The role will move with decisiveness and courage, drive experimentation and calculated risk taking to create solutions that are simple and innovative that are the best possible for our stakeholders.  Furthermore, the role needs to seek out best practices, educate our stakeholders, and be an agent of change within the organization to educate and drive data-based decisions and workflows for our stakeholders.  Open to fully remote for the right candidate, but we prefer location near any US based Medtronic facility.  A Day in the Life • Lead ideation and creation of analytical solutions for STOP. • Capture requirements and enhance analytical processes as the primary business liaison. • Collaborate across cross-functional teams. • Drive development and deployment of analytics for productivity, decision-making, and competitiveness. • Ensure alignment with End-to-End supply chain focus and business objectives. • Support and drive analytics initiatives. • Promote adoption and usage of analytics tools. • Support tool training. • Ensure timely delivery of solutions. • Generate insights for business use cases. • Travel: Up to 25% or quarterly. _To be considered for this role, please ensure the minimum requirements are evident in your applicant profile._  Must Have: Minimum Requirements • Bachelor's degree. • 7 years of supply chain and operations analytics experience (or 5 years with an advanced degree).  Nice to Have • SQL or Oracle Developer experience • PowerBI visualization experience. • PowerApps and Power Automate experience. • Agile environment experience. • Regulated industry experience (e.g., Medical Device). • Strong ability to influence and drive projects to completion.  About Medtronic Together, we can change healthcare worldwide.  At Medtronic, we push the limits of what technology, therapies and services can do to help alleviate pain, restore health, and extend life. We challenge ourselves and each other to make tomorrow better than yesterday. It is what makes this an exciting and rewarding place to be.  We want to accelerate and advance our ability to create meaningful innovations - but we will only succeed with the right people on our team. Lets work together to address universal healthcare needs and improve patients lives. Help us shape the future. job_description.6: • A position that's professionally rewarding | Commencing January 2024 • Access to Mentoring, Coaching and Industry Expertise • Full Time, 2-Year Fixed Term Graduate Program Opportunity. Requests for part-time hours may be considered.  About the Opportunity  As part of the Adelaide Economic Development Agency (AEDA), you will learn and develop on the job and through a tailored development program, while making a tangible contribution to our team and the City of Adelaide (CoA) more broadly. You will review macroeconomic conditions as well as activity levels in the city including consumer expenditure behaviour, foot-traffic, public transport usage, e-scooter trips, as well as parking and other indicators.  Some of the things you'll see yourself doing with us are: • Analysing qualitative and quantitative data using Excel or other programs such as PowerBI, Tableau, R, ai, etc. • Compiling high quality, robust and professional designed reports and briefing notes. • Assisting in producing or maintaining statistical models, and assisting in designing data visualisations. • Participating in and contributing to all graduate program projects, training, and other undertakings.  Why Our Graduate Program?  Our graduate program gives you a great opportunity to start building your career, while having our genuine impact on our City and our communities. As a capital city council, we have wide-ranging responsibilities, so you'll be exposed to many different industries. This includes everything from community wellbeing to urban planning, events to infrastructure, lifestyle experiences to heritage, economic development to climate action, corporate services and many more.  Apart from gaining valuable insight into what makes our community unique, you will also have access to a wide range of benefits such as: • Flexible work arrangements • A range of health & wellbeing offerings • On-site gym and chill-out areas • Social Club events where you get to connect with other colleagues  For more information about what it's like to work for the City of Adelaide, including the benefits, please visit www.cityofadelaide.com.au/careers  About You  To be successful in this role you will have: • Graduated within approximately the last 2 years or are expecting to graduate within approximately the next 6 months, with a degree in Economics, Data Science, Commerce, Mathematics or related field. • An understanding of economic indicators at a council level. • Ability to analyse data, find insights and present information concisely. • Well-developed verbal and written skills to be able to construct high quality written work/reports. • Strong organisational skills, the ability to successfully manage competing priorities, maintain attention to detail and meet deadlines. • A commitment to ongoing professional development, continuous learning, and to building your career.  About Us  Located in the geographic heart of Kaurna Country, the City of Adelaide celebrates its cultural heritage, unique natural surrounds and structures its footprint in a way that allows it to adapt to the changing needs of the community and a dynamic global landscape. Our focus is on our community's wellbeing and quality of life - investing in city improvements and on future planning, so we continue to design a liveable city where future generations can continue to live authentic and meaningful lives. This is an exciting opportunity to join our team and be a bigger part of our amazing city!  To find out what our people love about what they do please watch this video.  AEDA works closely with businesses, industry groups, the state government and other relevant organisations to deliver a range of programs designed to stimulate the city's economic growth. AEDA's focus is investment attraction, growing our visitor economy, residential growth, marketing the city as a whole and promoting Rundle Mall as Adelaide's premier shopping destination.  At the City of Adelaide, we thrive in an environment that is welcoming, inclusive and safe, and celebrates difference. We value and embrace our diverse perspectives and recognise the value diversity has in fuelling innovation and enabling brilliant experiences for our diverse community.  For Further Enquiries & How to Apply  All enquiries regarding this position will remain private and confidential and can be directed to Jordon Tomopoulos on 08 8203 7563.  Please submit a Resume, a copy of your academic transcript, and a Cover Letter expressing the skills, experience and qualities you can bring to this position addressed to Jordon Tomopoulos, Economic Research & Data Analyst.  Please review the position description prior to submitting an application by following the prompts to apply.  Applications close at 11.59pm, 15 October 2023.  Please be advised this is a full-time, two-year fixed term opportunity with a starting salary at the Level 3 Classification commencing at $77,210 11% superannuation.  We encourage Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander People, and people living with disability to apply.  We are committed to making reasonable adjustments to provide a positive, barrier-free recruitment process and supportive workplace. If you require assistance with our recruitment process, please call our People Services team on (08) 8203 7333.
job_description.7: If we inspire you to do the work you love, will you still call it work?  What's in it for you?  We are seeking a Data Analyst to join our EY Data and Analytics team ideally in our Melbourne and Sydney offices but can also be based in any of the major Australian cities. Working with a number of high profile clients this role is offered on a flexible, full-time basis.  You will help shape, change, and deliver a data management roadmap to improve and enhance the value and re-usability of data, through modern and evolving data management practices and frameworks.  As a Data Analyst, you will support our clients in defining and implementing a data journey aligned with their strategic objectives, you will work with a diverse range of stakeholders and data teams to uplift the current data quality management capabilities of a number of different high profile client groups.  What We're Looking For  Translating business questions to data and analysis requirements; carry out analysis, visualization and presentation.  Performing ad-hoc analysis to solve business problems and support decisions.  Design and build data products, such as Power BI dashboards, including defining the data models.  Surfacing and sharing insights, typically from internal corporate data, using a dashboard.  Run human centred design sessions with end-users.  Communicating and influencing stakeholders.  Coaching non-data experts how to use data.  Skills And Attributes For Success  Experience in a hands-on role interpreting and telling stories with data.  Curious and business outcome focused with an ability to break down a complex problem and work out how to solve it.  Evidence of numerical and technical aptitude strong collaboration skills having worked with business stakeholders at different levels of seniority.  Comfortable working across a wide range of data sets and systems.  Expertise in cleansing, combining and processing data.  Have knowledge of SQL, with knowledge of Python an advantage.  Familiarity with Power BI and ideally data manipulation tools (e.g. Alteryx and Daraiku).  The preferred applicant will be subject to employment screening by EY or by their external third party provider. Regarding this role, the minimum salary is $90,000 including 11% superannuation.
job_description.8: Join an organisation with strong values, a community focus and a great culture!  About the Team  The Lending Quality Team is responsible for reviewing the accuracy of all inputs to Credit Ratings and Security Ratings prior to approval and reviewing and providing coaching and feedback on credit submissions processed via the Business and Agribusiness teams. The focus of the team is a proactive measure to: • Support the Bank to ensure well managed portfolios are maintained. • Ensure ongoing quality of the non-retail portfolio; and • Generate a circle of continuous improvement through sharing of best practice.  About the role:  As the Lending Quality and Data Analyst you will be responsible for collating quantitative data of reviewed applications within the business customer portfolio and identifying trends for process and capability uplift opportunities.  Key responsibilities will include: • Providing feedback to the Lending Quality Coaches, your leader, and other key stakeholders in analysis by identifying and making recommendations to the broader business on opportunities to address capability gaps and education needs. • Developing insights and providing future strategies to key stakeholders based on findings and observations from the quantitative quality review data. • Advocating for changes and ensuring change is adhered to, this may be procedural, system or people related. • Completing remediation activities in line with the defined instructions provided to uplift the overall quality of data in the environment.  The data quality process is a governed activity enabling insights and trends across our business, detailing areas of focus to increase capability, unblock bottlenecks in teams and identify themes of focus for continuous improvement.  Does this sound like you? • Demonstrated experience in statistical visualisation and interpretation of data. • Strong strategic application of data and insights, with the ability to translate complex analytics into actionable insights. • Proficiency with using Microsoft Office products specifically advanced in Excel & Word. • Ability to develop and maintain relationships with Business Banking and Credit Risk team members, to provide an understanding of key risks identified within reviews and follow up that recommended remediation has occurred. • Critical thinking analysis and ability to communicate outcomes. • Ability to work as part of a remote team  About Bendigo Bank  With more than 160 years of history, we are proud of our position in the community with more satisfied customers than any other Australian bank. Every day, we work hard to bring our company purpose to life; feeding into the success of our customers and communities and not off it.  We're more than just a bank with banking products. We change the lives of customers and communities. Commercial actions with heart!  Our time is now. We are challenging the status quo and we're excited about our future!  Why us?  There's so much more to a career with Bendigo and Adelaide Bank than just banking.  Get real benefits, work life balance and flexibility. You bring your brilliant mind, and we’ll help you take your learning to the next level with on-the-job training and external development opportunities - we want you to shine. After all, YOU are the difference that makes us the better big bank.  We believe a diverse workforce supported by an inclusive culture is central to our success and we actively encourage applications from those who bring diversity of thought to our business. We support candidate requests for adjustment to accommodate an illness, injury or disability to equitably participate in the selection process.  So, if you’re excited to be part of an organisation with strong values and a community focus apply now!
job_description.9: Data Engineer - Sterling  Westpac Group has a rich heritage and offers employees a multitude of opportunities. We aim to attract the best people inside and outside of the business building an organisation where the best talent thrives.  The Westpac Group has been proudly advancing Australia for two centuries. Our success is built upon both our heritage and our ability to evolve.  We’re setting ourselves up to be Australia’s No. 1 Bank and we have an exciting change agenda ahead.  What we are looking for?  As a part of the Data Platforms Insourcing Strategy, this role will predominantly be responsible to engage with business and Architecture on the technical aspects of the Data Quality Capability and onboarding.  Drive the platform roadmap, including the decommission of the legacy Platform. Level 4 technical support as required and to ensure ongoing optimal utilisation of the platform to minimise Westpac operational costs. • The ideal candidate(s) should have 6-10 years of hands-on experience in building a data ingestion and file transfer framework along with data engineering expertise. • Working experience on Data Lake Implementations on Azure cloud / BigData technologies • Cloud experience in one or more of Azure, AWS or GCP environment • Expertise with modern file transfer tools • Should be able to tune file Transfer jobs for performance. • Deep understanding of distributed computing systems • Able to stitch together an end-to-end file transfer solution using a range of techniques. • Good knowledge in File transfer data technologies, preferably Sterling Business Integrator • Good temperament - buildings relationships and stakeholder management skills with an ability to interact with a diverse group of stakeholders and proactively provide actionable data. • Familiar working with DevSecOps tools, methodologies - CI / CD (i.e., Jenkins, bitbucket, GitHub), Azure DevOps i.e., best practices for code deployment • Working knowledge in job Orchestration (Control-M, ESP) • Work with Architects, Technical Leads and Business Teams and contributes to the development of technical designs. • Strong knowledge of various data structures and the ability to extract data from various data sources. • Provides technical database consultation on application development and other database administration efforts related to specific DBMS. • Experience in writing complex SQL queries preferred. • Ability to conduct data profiling, cataloguing, and mapping for technical design and construction of technical data flows.  What’s in it for me?  You will play an important and significant part in the future of a business that has been around for 200 years. Our purpose is to create better futures together.  So, we will back you in the development of your career, with internal career prospects and flexible working. You will also be backed by a fantastic team of people in a can-do, supportive structure.  What’s it like to work there?  As well as competitive remuneration and a great culture, joining the Westpac family means you will get some of the best banking, wealth and insurance benefits in the market.  We back our employees by helping them work towards industry-recognised qualifications, using online learning, training modules and career planning tools for you to grow with us.  We will even pay you to do volunteer or community work.  As an equal opportunity employer, we are proud to have created a culture and work environment that values diversity and flexibility and champions inclusion.  How do I Apply?  Start here. Just click on the APPLY button.  As part of our commitment to creating a diverse and inclusive workplace, this role is open to experienced candidates seeking a discussion around workplace flexibility.  We invite candidates of all ages, genders, sexual orientation, cultural backgrounds, people with disability, neurodiverse individuals, and Indigenous Australians to apply. job_description.11: • Closing Date: 13 October 2023, 9:00 AM  face2face reference: 591408  Location: Nationwide - Remote  Hours: Full-time  Contract length: 12 Months Contract + 3 x 1 Month (Pending approval)  Entry requirements: Australian Citizen + Ability to obtain Baseline  Pay range: $95.00 – 115.00 p/h inc super  About the role:  The Tertiary Skills and Pathways team is responsible for the unit mapping project, as part of its program of work. Unit mapping uses natural language processing techniques to create a connection between tertiary education learning materials (VET and HE units), and skills taxonomies. Unit mapping helps to identify skills taught in tertiary education, and their potential relationship to occupations and the labour market, to assist in analysis and advice on tertiary education delivery.  The team is working on a demonstration project basis with five key projects to design the end to end process of unit mapping, to continually refine the data science model, and to generate insights on the potential use of mapping outputs. The outputs of models are large, for example one university with approximately 3,000 units can have an output of approximately 30,000 skills mapped. Validation of outputs is a critical part of the mapping process to produce a model and results that are highly accurate.  Duties: • Developing of a comprehensive internal and external validation process for very large data sets, to support improvement of data science models, and the quality of output data sent to partners. This may require an ensemble of approaches, for example statistical sampling, manual and automated approaches to validation. • Managing internal validation processes before outputs are sent to project partners. • Working closely with the data science team to provide feedback for the mapping model development. • Analysing complex model outputs, to derive valuable insights for reporting to project partners, including visualisation techniques. • Providing advice to technical services on interface design for a validation application for project partners.  Required experience/skills: • Demonstrated experience in data analysis and process design, to create replicable data validation processes to improve data output quality. • Excellent analytical skills, with strong attention to detail, and the ability to synthesise and critically analyse large volumes of structured and unstructured data. • Strong skills and experience in data management, in particular how data can be effectively structured, analysed, presented and communicated, to achieve high-quality outcomes. • Excellent communication skills, including the ability to effectively communicate key data insights visually and in written form to a range of diverse stakeholders • Well-developed interpersonal skills, including the ability to work effectively in a multidisciplinary setting.  Desirable experience skills: • Experience in R Shiny, Python, SQL, anduser experience design. • Understanding of, and experience working with tertiary education (HE and/or VET) and/or occupation and labour market data. • Understanding and experience in data science, or related fields. • Experience operating in a policy environment. We bring together extraordinary people, like you, to build a better working world.  The opportunity  Due to continued success and growth, an exciting opportunity exists for a Data Analytics Senior Consultant or Manager to join our highly regarded People Advisory Services team.  Our team works as a well-integrated national team, where you’ll have the opportunity to work with Australian-based and multinational clients across the country, therefore offering you the ability to work with large corporates, and a diverse range of industries. In this role, you will have access to training, coaching and support that’s available to help grow your career even further!  This role is open to various locations - Melbourne, Sydney, Brisbane, Adelaide, and Perth.  What’s in it for you?  As our Data Analytics Senior Consultant or Manager - your responsibilities will include: • Modelling of various Industrial Instrument (including Enterprise Bargaining Agreements, Industry Awards etc.) for wage compliance projects; • Modelling of superannuation and Pay-As-You-Go Withholding data modelling projects (including the preparation of superannuation guarantee charge statements and voluntary disclosure letters); • Liaise directly with clients and other regulatory authorities (e.g. Australian Taxation Office, Fair Work Australia etc.) in the delivery of data projects; • Work with different parts of the business in driving growth in the global mobility data analytics practice; • Preparing & presenting training seminars to both clients and team members. We’re interested in your strengths, what you want to learn, and how far you want to go. • Degree in Data Analytics/Commerce, or similar; • Between 1-5 years’ experience in a data analytics discipline (focused towards wage compliance and employment taxes remediation); • Experience with Alteryx at the intermediate or advanced level; • Experience with data visualisation software such as Power BI and Tableau; • Experience with SQL, Python, and other database/coding languages [preferred]; • Ability to lead and mentor junior members of our team; • Commitment to excellence in client service, with the ability to work both autonomously and as part of a team. job_description.15: • ASX Listed Energy Company - Adelaide Head Office • Unique Adelaide based accounting opportunity. • Competitive package and benefits  Beach Energy is an Adelaide based ASX-listed energy company pursuing an exciting growth strategy. We are seeking a tertiary qualified analyst with an interest in energy markets to join the Finance team responsible for Beach’s petroleum sales from existing production assets.  About the Role  Reporting to the Finance Manager (VIC/NZ), the Business Analyst will be responsible for Financial and Joint Venture accounting within the Beach Capital Portfolio, comprising Stay in Business expenditure within the Operations function and Capital expenditure within the Exploration & Subsurface (E&S), and Development functions. This will include the preparation and analysis of accounting statements, reports, and reconciliations for operated and non-operated Joint Ventures.  The role partners with the Senior Business Analysts within the Finance team, and the Project Services team to ensure alignment between project cost control and finance requirements. Additionally, this role encompasses development and stewardship of Capital financial governance, compliance policies and processes, including Asset Recognition and Capitalisation, Prepayments and Project Inventory.  Key Responsibilities will include: • Delivering timely and accurate monthly reporting of operated joint ventures, including review of contribution and other general ledger account reconciliations • Preparing account reconciliations supporting the balance sheet statements, including responding to audit requests. • Preparing and distributing expenditure statements for Joint Ventures and manage queries from JV partners. • Cash calling of external Joint Venture partners, in accordance with JOA requirements, including monitoring financial position of partners as appropriate and following up to ensure funds are received. • Coordinating Joint Venture audits requested by the non-operator Joint Venture partners. • Month end ledger close including the preparation and posting of accounting entries. • Maintaining fixed asset registers including governance of useful lives, depreciation, asset disposals and additions in SAP  About You  The person we are seeking will be an enthusiastic self-starter looking for variety within a role and development through exposure to experienced industry peers. An adept attention to detail, and an ability to work both independently and as part of a team.  You will also need: • Tertiary qualifications in accounting and CA/CPA qualified. • Experience covering joint venture and management accounting. • An ability to build relationships with a variety of stakeholders. • Capability operating under tight timeframes and pressure. • Strong interpersonal and communication skills including clear and concise writing skills. • Proven SAP experience.  About Us  Beach Energy is an ASX listed oil and gas exploration and production company. Founded in 1961, our head office is in Adelaide, and we operate in several locations in Australia and in New Zealand.  Beach’s purpose is to ‘sustainably deliver energy for communities’ and we are committed to producing the energy needed for a sustainable transition – one that supports the needs of societies today, and into the future. See our actions and plans in our Sustainability Report.  How to Apply  Beach is committed to improving gender diversity and Indigenous participation; we encourage all applications.  Please submit your application, cover letter and updated CV by 20 October 2023.  For this opportunity you must be eligible to work in Australia.

job_description.18: About Us  It’s an exciting time for Discovery Parks. Since our inception in 2004 we have experienced extensive growth. We currently own and operate over 65 Holiday and workforce Parks throughout Australia and employ over 1100 people. Discovery Parks has recently acquired Australia’s largest network of parks – Top Parks.  At the heart of Discovery Parks are happy people: happy customers and happy staff. We are building a passionate, adaptable, high performance team that works together to help our customers discover what matters.  The Role  Discovery Holiday Parks is embracing the new normal and is undertaking an historic transformation to build the Park and Digital Experience of the future. Accordingly, significant investment is being made into technology and business processes to develop custom attribution and predictive models focusing on customer behavior across our entire accommodation network. This is an incredibly exciting opportunity to use the latest Microsoft tools and technologies to drive actionable insights to add value to the business.  The Data Scientist will apply the latest data science techniques within the context of our customers and business, to improve customer experience and drive returns.  This role will require you to;  · Lead the team that provides customer insights to the business across the customer journey  · Apply your broad skill-set across data and analytics to understand business problems, create insights and provide practical solutions  · Provide business solutions and optimisation through various statistical and quantitative methods  · Provide statistical models to support predictive analytics and deliver non-technical presentations to all levels of the business as well as technical documentation to the wider team  · Identify and develop the capability to track detailed competitor data and leverage existing internal data to inform smart customer lead decision making  · Conduct investigative analytics reports to inform the customer journey experience  · Liaise closely with a broad range of internal and external stakeholders, you will have a collaborative personal style and be commercial as well as customer focused  Your Experience  A Bachelor’s degree in Mathematics, Statistics, Physics, Finance, Economics along with working knowledge of data science, analytics, or data engineering is essential to the success of this role.  To be successful in this role you will have proficiency and experience in statistical modelling and machine learning techniques combined with a high level of proficiency with programming languages used in data science. You will have excellent verbal and written communication skills which will be utilised when working across cross function teams and external stakeholders.  You will possess a high level of energy, self-motivation, autonomy, initiative, flexibility and attention to detail to be successful in meeting the business demands at Discovery Parks. Your naturally upbeat and open style will fit our cultural values. You will have a highly organised mindset with the ability to assess the urgency of work allocated to you by various stakeholders.  Discovery is a dynamic company with an energetic ‘market disrupter’ reputation. If you are passionate, adventurous, and ready to hit the ground running, we want to hear from you.  Discover more to life - APPLY NOW!  Prior to an offer of employment being made, candidates must provide authority for a Federal Police Clearance to disclose any criminal offences or charges.
job_description.19: About us  Saab Australia is a defence, security and cyber solutions provider, specialising in the development and integration of major defence and security systems. For over 30 years in Australia, we have built a reputation for delivering complex systems integration projects that provide proven and advanced capabilities to keep us ahead of today's challenges.  From combat, communications, security and underwater systems, to mixed reality, cyber security and deployable health solutions, our extensive portfolio of products and services provide high-technology solutions for defence forces and civil industries across the globe.  Apply today to join our crew and deliver solutions with purpose.  The role  As part of our Maritime group, the Business Analyst will be response for developing processes, tools and systems to support EPA (Enterprise Partnership Agreement) and WAMA (Warship Asset Management Agreement) programs in consultation with key stakeholders. This role is directly responsible for implementing, improving and sustaining processes, methodologies, tools and training to others with skills to enhance project and program performance and reporting.  Further, the successful candidate will: • Consult with stakeholders, develop and maintain EPA and WAMA program level cost, schedule and risk reporting regime. • Develop, implement and manage processes, systems and tools support the EPA performance measurement and reporting framework. • Carry out detailed analysis of current processes, systems, tools and data integrity, identify issues and improvement opportunities and influence the uptake of improvements. • Conduct training for business system, processes and tools. • Ensure disparate information sources are validated, cohesively consolidated and aggregated to appropriate levels for management reporting. • Understand the customer, management and project leadership reporting requirements and develop fit-for-purpose management reporting dashboards using multiple system inputs and automated data gathering tools (where appropriate) for reliable and consistent reporting outcomes. • Investigate and assess opportunities to automate processes, developing professional, clear and concise business cases for management review to support improvement initiatives.  Flexible work arrangements such as hybrid work from home / office, 9 day fortnight and part time (0.8 FTE minimum) will be considered for this role.  About you  Your skills and experience will include: • Degree (or Certificate IV minimum) qualified in project management, IT, engineering or business. • Extensive business analysis experience within an engineering & project execution organisation, specifically within the defence or resources industries on complex major capital projects. • Demonstrated understanding and application of best practice business processes, including establishing and maintaining the performance reporting at a program level for the client/customer along with internal management stakeholders. • Strong acumen with Excel PowerPivots, database establishment and management and SharePoint development along with Power BI experience to establish robust and reliable performance reporting to support the program controls functions in reporting planning, scheduling, budget & cost management, risk and opportunity management. • Previous experience working within the Defence network system would be advantageous.  As Defence security clearance is required for this role, applicants must be Australian citizens and eligible to obtain and maintain a NV1 clearance or a minimum of a Baseline clearance.  Culture and benefits  We employ over 700 Australians and are committed to fostering a culture of excellence and enriching the employee experience.  By joining Saab, you'll be a part of a collaborative and supportive organisation, where your professional growth and work-life balance are emphasised. You'll work within an innovative and vibrant workplace, while having the opportunity to develop a long-term, fulfilling career.  For further information about at career at Saab, visit the page adjacent:  Applications  Click 'Apply' to submit your CV and cover letter in support of your application. You may contact our careers team at for a copy of the full position description. Kindly observe that this is an ongoing recruitment process and in exceptional circumstances, the position might be filled before the closing date of the advertisement. We encourage applications as early as possible to avoid disappointment.  Saab Australia is an Equal Opportunity Employer and encourages Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islanders to apply. We also welcome applications from individuals with culturally diverse backgrounds.  Saab Australia is a proud supporter of the Veterans' Employment Program and welcomes the interest of ex-service members, veterans and their families.

job_description.28: Analyst Department : System Design Division : Forecasting  Reference number : 10889  A true forecasting role in the fast-moving energy industry - incredible career opportunitgy with PV & battery focus. This is your opportunity to bring your passion and expertise and contribute to Australia's energy future. Design, run and communicate the model's that everyone's talking about (strong modelling skills in R, Python & SQL a must). Attractive salary and performance incentives. Open to Bris/Syd/Melb/Adel/Perth with hybrid working arrangements.  Who is AEMO?  We are the Australian Energy Market Operator. AEMO's role is to design and operate a sustainable energy system that provides safe, reliable, and affordable electricity and gas today, and to enable the energy transition for the benefit of all Australians. All Australian governments are now committed to a net-zero economy for Australia by 2050, the first step of which is a net-zero energy system.  We are collaborating with industry and other stakeholders to engineer electricity grids that can handle 100 per cent instantaneous renewable generation by 2025, and changes to the gas system and markets to support biomethane and hydrogen. AEMO also plays a significant role in the east coast gas market, which has recently expanded to assessing if there is enough natural gas for customers, including electricity generators. The transition to a renewable energy system is occurring at a world-leading pace. It is an exciting, momentous time to be part of this mission.  About the role  AEMO's forecasting division is responsible for providing long and medium-term forecasts of Australia's energy supply and demand. The team is responsible for delivering critical data that underpins many of our major reports and reliability processes.  At a time when Australia is witnessing a once in a century transformation of the Energy Industry this is an incredible opportunity to be part of a bespoke, supportive, and high performing team. This role is available across multiple office locations, including Brisbane, Sydney, Melbourne, Adelaide & Perth – in addition to offering flexible work from home arrangements.  What you will be doing  Reporting into the Manager, Sector Coupling and working within a team of four, your focus is on how distributed PV and storage develop over timeframes of up to 30 years. You'll be part of robust discussions on consumer needs, market evolution, and technological development.  We're seeking a strategically minded analyst with a strong interest in PV and storage. Your daily role involves diving into PV and battery technology and crafting and refining forecasting models. Solid programming skills, including R and SQL are essential. Attention to detail and collaboration skills are crucial. You'll work within a friendly, supportive team that collaborate to strategise and test internal and external viewpoints. You will also: • Be aware of and contribute to team understanding of industry trends. • Develop, maintain, and document forecasting models for components of the electricity and gas markets. This involves analytical, programming, modelling and data management skills, working with others within and beyond the team. • Interpret, validate, and gain insights from models, simulations, and ad-hoc datasets. • Communicate your results via writing technical reports using clear and concise language that is understandable to a diverse audience. • Have the ability to quickly and accurately complete analytical work within tight timeframes. • Mentor and support graduates and students in the performance of their tasks.  What you will bring to the role • Tertiary qualification in relevant disciplines (engineering, physics, mathematics, econometrics). • At least 3 years' experience in analysis and modelling of energy markets or a related field. • Experience working with Power BI and Excel, alongside R, Python, and SQL. • Experience within Australia's energy systems, particularly Australia's electricity markets, is desirable or a willingness to learn and an interest in energy systems. • Keen interest in data, energy markets, and the art and science of forecasting is well regarded.  Some of our employment benefits • Flexible working: work from home, part time, job share, hybrid options, and additional leave options • Professional development via projects, assignments, industry networks, job rotation, study assistance and formal learning • A full health and wellbeing program, private health discounts and other concessions • Free salary continuance insurance and annual performance bonuses (subject to eligibility) • Up to 4 days volunteering leave per year • A comprehensive and professional Employee Assistance Program (EAP)  We are AEMO  At AEMO, our core values aren't just 'words on a wall' – we are a purpose-based organisation at the centre of our energy future, and we stand for integrity, inclusiveness, empowerment, and excellence.  As we continue to innovate and work on some world-first, ground-breaking projects, we need to attract the brightest people and provide opportunities to contribute, stretch and grow.  We actively encourage you to bring your whole self to work, so that together we can do better, be better, and love our work. For this reason, inviting difference and leading inclusively is a core part of our culture. We challenge ourselves to take bold actions to improve the experience for all our people, with a current focus on gender, flexibility, (dis)ability and our First Nation peoples.  If you would like to know more about working at AEMO, please check out our careers page for more information, or apply now. #joinaemo  For more information on the Australian Energy Market Operator (AEMO) please refer to or visit one of our social media channels below.

For this role we are looking for someone who has worked on consumer facing web applications/products, can create such applications from scratch and also understand the competitive landscape, the market we are operating in and anticipate the market needs before they arise.  Requirements • Australian citizenship required- due to eligibility for NV1 defence clearance requirement for the role • Bachelor degree in Computer Science, Electrical Engineering or other related technical STEM fields • 5+ years experience in Product Management / Technical Business Analysis / Systems Engineering • Experience working on consumer facing, complicated Java web-apps or products • Ability to work with stakeholders to elicit requirements, including clients and other engineering team members • Ability to develop product specifications and meet deadlines • Strong organisation skills, detail orientated, and a collaborative team player with strong communication skills Qualities that make strong candidates: • Experience in technology sector working with defence and government clients • Understanding of analytic challenges in Defence and national security About Fivecast  Fivecast is a world-leading provider of cutting-edge digital intelligence solutions. We enable the world’s most important public and private organizations to explore masses of data and uncover actionable insights, critical to protecting global communities.  As a growing start-up with over 100 people globally, all team members are provided with the opportunity to directly contribute to our success, participate in the development of new and emerging technologies and grow their career in a challenging and dynamic high-tech environment. We are headquartered in Adelaide, Australia with teams in Canberra, Virginia USA, and London UK.  Our Work Environment and Culture  Our Adelaide based headquarters is a purpose-built tech hub centrally based in vibrant Hutt Street. We moved into this brand-new space in early 2023 to allow for continued collaboration, innovation & growth.  Our space has been specifically engineered for brainstorming, idea generation, random encounters across teams and to suit our casual, relaxed culture. This has been achieved through amazing features, including an arcade room, pool table, fully equipped kitchens with fruit and snacks, barista quality coffee machine, end of trip facilities (showers, lockers, bike storage, etc), as well as comfortable breakout spaces.  Fivecast has a connected work culture with team members taking advantage of our social clubs, local cafes, bars, pubs and sporting facilities for team activities. At Fivecast we understand the importance of a good work-life balance and support flexible work arrangements.  Fivecast is an inclusive employer, we value diversity of thought and experience and believe our inclusive culture contributes to our success. We are committed to building a workforce that is representative of the communities in which we live and work.

job_description.36: About Us  Saab Australia is a defence, security and cyber solutions provider, specialising in the development and integration of major defence and security systems. For over 30 years in Australia, we have built a reputation for delivering complex systems integration projects that provide proven and advanced capabilities to keep us ahead of today’s challenges.  From combat, communications, security and underwater systems, to mixed reality, cyber security and deployable health solutions, our extensive portfolio of products and services provide high-technology solutions for defence forces and civil industries across the globe.  Apply today to join our crew and deliver solutions with purpose.  The role  As part of our Maritime group, the Business Analyst will be response for developing processes, tools and systems to support EPA (Enterprise Partnership Agreement) and WAMA (Warship Asset Management Agreement) programs in consultation with key stakeholders. This role is directly responsible for implementing, improving and sustaining processes, methodologies, tools and training to others with skills to enhance project and program performance and reporting.  Further, the successful candidate will: • Consult with stakeholders, develop and maintain EPA and WAMA program level cost, schedule and risk reporting regime. • Develop, implement and manage processes, systems and tools support the EPA performance measurement and reporting framework. • Carry out detailed analysis of current processes, systems, tools and data integrity, identify issues and improvement opportunities and influence the uptake of improvements. • Conduct training for business system, processes and tools. • Ensure disparate information sources are validated, cohesively consolidated and aggregated to appropriate levels for management reporting. • Understand the customer, management and project leadership reporting requirements and develop fit-for-purpose management reporting dashboards using multiple system inputs and automated data gathering tools (where appropriate) for reliable and consistent reporting outcomes. • Investigate and assess opportunities to automate processes, developing professional, clear and concise business cases for management review to support improvement initiatives.  Flexible work arrangements such as hybrid work from home / office, 9 day fortnight and part time (0.8 FTE minimum) will be considered for this role.  About You  Your skills and experience will include: • Degree (or Certificate IV minimum) qualified in project management, IT, engineering or business. • Extensive business analysis experience within an engineering & project execution organisation, specifically within the defence or resources industries on complex major capital projects. • Demonstrated understanding and application of best practice business processes, including establishing and maintaining the performance reporting at a program level for the client/customer along with internal management stakeholders. • Strong acumen with Excel PowerPivots, database establishment and management and SharePoint development along with Power BI experience to establish robust and reliable performance reporting to support the program controls functions in reporting planning, scheduling, budget & cost management, risk and opportunity management. • Previous experience working within the Defence network system would be advantageous.  As Defence security clearance is required for this role, applicants must be Australian citizens and eligible to obtain and maintain a NV1 clearance or a minimum of a Baseline clearance.  Culture And Benefits  We employ over 700 Australians and are committed to fostering a culture of excellence and enriching the employee experience.  By joining Saab, you’ll be a part of a collaborative and supportive organisation, where your professional growth and work-life balance are emphasised. You’ll work within an innovative and vibrant workplace, while having the opportunity to develop a long-term, fulfilling career.  For further information about at career at Saab, visit the page adjacent: https://www.saab.com/markets/australia/careers/saab-life  Applications  Click ‘Apply’ to submit your CV and cover letter in support of your application. You may contact our careers team at careers.mailbox@au.saabgroup.com for a copy of the full position description. Kindly observe that this is an ongoing recruitment process and in exceptional circumstances, the position might be filled before the closing date of the advertisement. We encourage applications as early as possible to avoid disappointment.  Saab Australia is an Equal Opportunity Employer and encourages Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islanders to apply. We also welcome applications from individuals with culturally diverse backgrounds.  Saab Australia is a proud supporter of the Veterans’ Employment Program and welcomes the interest of ex-service members, veterans and their families.
job_description.37: About the ABC  The ABC is the nation's most trusted and independent source of Australian conversations, culture, and stories. With over 4,000 employees from diverse backgrounds across over 50 locations around Australia and overseas, we are proud to create, curate and deliver high-quality content that informs, educates and entertains Australian communities.  Role Purpose  Develop and support the ABC’s digital data capabilities that provide data pipelines, aggregation & processing, data visualisation and data distribution services to ABC digital products and platforms.  Strengthen data engineering foundations within digital product and platform teams, enable experimentation and underpin the success of leveraging data in ABC digital products.  Key Accountabilities • Provide technical development skills within the ABC's Digital Product department, to develop secure and high-performance platforms and services. • Under broad direction, and in collaboration with colleagues, deliver high quality software development and produce best possible results on code quality, efficiency, system sustainability, scalability, and security within agreed time and budget requirements. • Create and maintain accurate and up-to-date documentation, including technical designs, product specifications, architecture details, support & operation guides, testing instructions and thought processes. • Adopt best engineering practices in the industry and share with other team members, to help foster the implementation of best data engineering practices throughout Digital Product teams. • As part of a digital product or platform team, continuously strengthen the architectural foundation of the data platform and drive the architectural improvements and best practices for data products. • Ensure separation of concerns and create layers of abstractions and re-usable data components where appropriate. Adopt service-oriented architecture when designing particularly complex systems and apply industry best practices where appropriate.  About You • Experience in software technologies such as dbt, AWS data services, Datahub, Apache Superset, PowerBI, content management systems, digital media publishing, digital content delivery and integration with APIs & diverse data sources an advantage. • Demonstrated experience in modern data analytics tech stack including real user monitoring, tag management, experiments & A / B testing, product feature pilot measurement, data integration and data anomaly detection. • Experience in developing complex, secure and high-performance data pipelines at scale. • Solid experience in one or more programming languages or frameworks such as Python, Golang, Typescript or Node.js; with ability to write clean, efficient and testable code. • Strong relational thinking and SQL skills. • Excellent planning and tasks prioritisation skills with the ability to work effectively under pressure and meet deadlines.  The following experiences, while not essential , would be advantageous : • Data transformation, storage and query technologies such as Trino, Iceberg, Databricks, Snowplow and Snowflake. • DevOps, Media and web experience • AWS services that support the modern data stack • Database performance optimisation  What’s In It For You?  Come and join the vibrant Digital Product department in the ABC. Our mission is to enable ABC’s digital future, where ABC transitions from a traditional broadcaster to Australia’s most trusted and valued digital media organisation.  Through harnessing our talents in digital, collaborating with our partners and delivering beyond expectations, we ensure the ABC not just remains relevant but thrives.  As a group of product and platform teams, we develop and maintain the ABC's audience facing digital products across mobile, connected TV, desktop, and smart speakers.  Whether it is staying informed of the latest breaking news, bringing some great TV on iview, streaming the Hottest 100 on the triple j app and website, or entertaining the kids with our ABC Kids app - the ABC's Digital Product offerings are some of Australia's most loved and most used platforms.  Your work will be appreciated by millions of audiences across Australia. We are an AWS shop; you will have the opportunity to work on the latest and greatest cloud technology.  You will have the chance to contribute to the solution architecture of our systems. We are an open and cohesive team where your voice will not get lost.  You can get a sneak peek into our product engineering world through our blog : https : / / www.abc.net.au / digital-product  We are committed to career development and invest in our people to grow and become leaders in their fields. Everyone in the Digital Product department has a designated budget for training and development.  We believe in flexible approaches to working and building self-organising and collaborative teams that offer friendly and supportive environments in which all team members can strive and grow.  For further information on this position please contact Jamie Nedved, Digital Talent Acquisition Lead via email nedved.jamie@abc.net.au  We respectfully request that Recruitment Agencies do not submit applications for this position.  In line with our focus on diversity, applications are strongly encouraged from Indigenous Australians, people from a range of cultural and linguistic backgrounds, people with disability and LGBTIQA+ individuals.  The ABC also aims to achieve a gender-balanced workforce.  For more information on inclusive employee networks within the ABC please refer to Life Page on ABC LinkedIn.  For more information on working at the ABC visit abc.net.au / careers
job_description.38: Research Analyst  Job ID  137932  Posted  27-Sep-2023  Service line  Advisory Segment  Role type  Full-time  Areas of Interest  Administrative, Research  Location(s)  Adelaide - South Australia - Australia  Provide key insights for South Australia's commercial real estate markets  Join an experienced Research team & grow your career  Collaborative team culture with a diverse mix of work  Adelaide | Land of the Kaurna people  CBRE Adelaide is seeking a research analyst to join their team. In collaboration with the wider research team you will partner with CBRE business lines and clients by providing an innovative range of research and analysis, serving as a trusted advisor across commercial and residential property markets in Australia and New Zealand.  Here's what you'll achieve: • Collect, review, evaluate, & analyse data, using internal databases, external data and macro-economic, financial and demographic information, ensuring insight and meaning is captured • Assisting in the development and implementation of data management processes and data-based outputs/data visualisation products • Prepare regular research reports and presentations, and other market analysis, including one-off consultancy assignments and more tailored research pieces to drive thought leadership • You'll have the opportunity to collaborate with Head of Research, Directors, Sector Leads and business stakeholders to generate ideas and produce innovative research materials that best meet business & client needs.  About you: • Degree qualified with 1-2 years' working experience in an economic, investment, policy or property research role • Interest in gaining exposure and building a comprehensive knowledge of commercial property markets • Ability to source data, analyse trends, create insights, and present results verbally, graphically and in writing • Strong numerical skills and knowledge of Excel and PowerPoint, with a keen interest in learning and using data analytics tools (Tableau, PowerBI) and sales database systems (especially Salesforce) • Excellent communication skills and enjoy a high degree of integration and collaboration with stakeholders within our business.  What's in it for you?  People are the foundation upon which our success is built. Our company is diverse and so are the opportunities for professional and career development. Our people are free to expand their skills and knowledge to drive their careers and reach their full potential.  We value flexibility and our people work in ways that meet their work/life commitments and support their well-being, learning and performance. Our people benefit from a range of educational, financial, health and well-being benefits and programs, corporate partnerships and discounts, CBRE Cares Foundation, competitive leave offerings and paid volunteer days.  Can we inspire you to join us?  At CBRE, our unwavering commitment to Diversity, Equity & Inclusion begins with you. We are strengthening our inclusive culture, so everyone feels safe, valued, & heard. Because when you belong, we all succeed. We welcome and encourage First Nations Peoples to apply.  If you are successful in progressing, you may be asked to complete a short video interview as part of the recruitment process.  We look forward to hearing from you!
job_description.39: Job Title: Business Analyst  Location: Adelaide, SA  Salary: $70,000 - $110,000 base + super, dependent upon experience  About the Company  Premier Group are currently partnering with a cutting-edge technology company specializing in 3D printing to transform the manufacturing space in a more efficient and sustainable way. With patented processes and tech creating quality product, their unique expertise and footprint have brought on very exciting projects and growth.  About the Role  As a Business Analyst, you will play a crucial role in driving data-driven decision-making processes and supporting the growth and success of the business. You will collaborate with cross-functional teams, gather and analyze data, and provide actionable insights that will inform strategic business decisions.  Key Responsibilities: • Data Analysis: Collect, organize, and analyze data related to projects, market trends, and competitor activities to identify opportunities and challenges • Market Research: Conduct market research to identify emerging trends, customer needs, and growth opportunities in the industry • Financial Analysis: Prepare financial models, forecasts, and cost-benefit analyses to evaluate the economic feasibility of new projects and initiatives • Performance Metrics: Develop and track key performance indicators (KPIs) to measure the success and impact projects • Business Strategy: Collaborate with cross-functional teams to develop and refine business strategies, including product development, pricing, and market entry strategies • Reporting: Create reports and presentations to communicate findings and recommendations to senior management and stakeholders • Continuous Improvement: Identify areas for process improvement and optimization within the company's 3D printing and robotics operations  About You • Bachelor's degree in Business, Finance, Economics, or a related field • Proven experience as a Business Analyst or in a similar analytical role • Strong analytical and quantitative skills with proficiency in data analysis tools • Knowledge of the 3D printing and robotics industry is a plus • Excellent communication and presentation skills • Ability to work collaboratively in a fast-paced, innovative environment  Submit your CV to kickstart your application, otherwise please feel free to reach out to me at ktruong@pgrec.au for a confidential chat!

Would you like to collaborate with a prestigious Management Consulting company in Germany and gain hands-on experience in evaluating business operations? TalentKompass Deutschland is excited to present the perfect opportunity for you!  We are currently offering a beginner-level internship program tailored for individuals passionate about examining business operations and identifying areas for improvement. This internship will equip you with practical experience in business analysis while enhancing your expertise in data analysis, statistical modeling, and more.  As an intern with our client's Management Consulting team, you will work closely with accomplished Business Analysts and consultants to collect and analyze data, discern trends and insights, and formulate recommendations for clients. This remote position allows you to work from the comfort of your own home.  What we're looking for: • A genuine interest in understanding business operations • Robust analytical skills and the ability to extract meaningful insights from complex data sets • Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills, with a knack for collaborating with team members at all levels • Meticulous attention to detail and the ability to work precisely in a fast-paced environment • A commitment to learning and growing in the field of business analysis • Familiarity with Microsoft Excel or other data analysis tools • A basic understanding of statistical analysis and modeling techniques  Responsibilities: • Assist in collecting and analyzing data from various sources • Collaborate with consultants to identify trends and insights • Develop recommendations to address business challenges • Participate in team meetings, contributing ideas and insights • Foster a positive team culture and collaborate to achieve team objectives • Support the creation of project documentation  If you're prepared to embark on your business analysis career and acquire practical experience, we encourage you to apply for our internship program.
