job_description.41: • One of the key requirements for this role is being open to relocating to various locations across Australia for client projects. Don't worry, we're here to help! We provide relocation assistance and support, and we'll also connect you with other friendly FDM Consultants who are based in your new location.*  Are you a recent graduate or End-of-Year Finisher looking to launch your career in tech?  Join our program for the chance to work with Australia’s leading companies including the top 4 banks, consultancies, insurance companies, retailers, and charities. Through our long relationships with FTSE100 client partners, you can add impressive names to your CV!  A career where you are encouraged to meet your potential  Junior Technical Analyst roles often involve high-profile projects in major financial institutions, working on sensitive information and gaining first-hand exposure to business operations. These opportunities are perfect for those who are team players with strong analytical skills and an aptitude for fast learning.  About This Role  If you are eager to take on a challenge and use your logical problem-solving skills to make an impact in the world of technology, then this is the role for you! Our program is designed to equip you with the skills and knowledge you need to start and grow a successful career.  As a Technical Analyst, you will have the opportunity to apply your skills to innovative projects and make a real impact in a variety of sectors. You will be responsible for investigating and developing solutions for applications. It could be robotic process automation, quality assurance and IT infrastructure delivery for global businesses.  What will my time at FDM be like  Your journey will begin with training out of FDM’s award-winning academy. While interviews and assessments are done remotely, you now have the option to undertake training online or at our centrally located, 21st floor Sydney office in Barangaroo.  The 10-week industry specific training covers high-demand skills such as SQL, Unix; Excel/VBA, BA, Python, ITIL, Cloud and OS-Admin with the chance to gain industry recognised qualifications, as well as mentoring and support throughout.  After successfully completing your training, you’ll step into an integral position with one or more of our industry-leading, multinational clients in Australia.  What we offer you: • A full-time employment contract with job security • Opportunities to work across Australia with relocation support where appropriate • Training is provided by industry experts, covering both technical and professional skills to ensure you are job-ready • Ongoing career support throughout your entire FDM journey, including professional development, mentoring, and social networking events with a community of peers • A chance to launch a career in one of the most in-demand tech fields  We ask you have the following: • Educated to a university degree level (bachelor or higher), no STEM degree required • Demonstrable interest and desire to work in technology • Ability to commit to completing our full 2.5-year graduate program • Ability to relocate to Sydney or Melbourne to support our clients. (Relocation package will be provided) • Eligible to work in Australia (Australian citizen or permanent resident)  There has never been a better time to start a career in tech – Apply Now!  About FDM  Our people are our passion. That's why we make your training and career growth our priority. We are a global professional services provider, focusing on IT. We are also one of the Australia's leading graduate employers, recruiting the brightest talent to become the innovators of tomorrow. With centres across Europe, North America, and Asia-Pacific, and over 5,000 consultants placed on client site globally, FDM has shown exponential growth throughout the years, firmly establishing itself as an award-winning FTSE 250 employer.  Diversity, Equity and Inclusion  FDM Group is an Equal Opportunity Employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, colour, religion, sex, sexual orientation, national origin, age, disability, veteran status, or any other status protected by federal, provincial, or local laws.
job_description.42: HomeStart Finance is seeking a Product Analyst to join us on a full-time basis in our Pirie Street office. This role is responsible for the provision of data analysis to support current and future products and fees, maintenance of product rules and delivery via loan calculators. The Product Analyst also helps develop customer-centric product improvement and design processes in order to develop and test product concepts and, in partnership with other teams, implement product change.  This is an exciting opportunity to make a direct impact in creating more opportunities for South Australians to achieve home ownership.  Duties & responsibilities: • Assist the Product Team Leader manage product BAU including analysis and input of multiplier reviews, fees, interest rates and loan pricing recommendations and indexation. • Provide timely and accurate analysis to management on product performance and relevance. • Develop a thorough understanding of customer needs within our target segments to define and iterate product features that overcome barriers to • home ownership within HomeStart’s risk appetite. • Assist the Product Team Leader manage product rules delivered • to customers via loan calculators such as the Calculation Engine including administration, definition, development of test cases and support as required. • Provide support with periodic reviews and risk analysis of builder partners performance. • Provide ongoing analysis of lending pipeline. • Assist in the provision of market analysis.  Essential criteria: • Financial services experience in a comparable role coupled with relevant tertiary qualification. • Some understanding of the legal and compliance environment. • Commitment to the delivery of quality customer service. • Sound understanding and application of research. • Advanced spreadsheet and data analysis skills. • Ability to solve problems with consideration to business needs. • Strong written communication. • Attention to detail and accuracy.  Benefits & Perks: • Annual salary increases • Up to 40% of time working from home • Up to 5 days wellbeing leave in addition to your 4 weeks annual leave • Supportive and diverse team • Centrally located, modern office in Pirie Street • Personal development opportunities & programs • Secure organisation currently undergoing enormous growth in lending volumes  About Us:  HomeStart is a unique South Australian organisation in the financial services sector, providing affordable home ownership solutions to the community. We take a proactive approach to addressing housing financing issues by creating innovative products which assist SA residents to overcome the barriers to entering the housing market, getting more people into home ownership.  With a workforce of over 130 employees situated in the Adelaide CBD with two small offices located in Salisbury and Morphett Vale, HomeStart is a recognised Employer of Choice.  To apply:  Applications for this role close at 5pm Sunday, 8 October 2023 and are only accepted via seek.com.au and are to include a cover letter, current curriculum vitae and include the name and contact details of three current professional referees.  If you wish to discuss this opportunity further, please contact Andrew Grove at andrew.grove@homestart.com.au.  All new employees are required to provide a satisfactory National Criminal History Record (Police Check) prior to commencement.  Please refer to HomeStart's career page at www.homestart.com.au for a copy of the position description and advice to applicants. You will also find testimonials from our employees about how they feel about working at HomeStart. Please note candidate screening and interviews may commence prior to the closing date of the job advert.
job_description.43: • Join an iconic Wesfarmers business, leaders in industrial & safety supplies • Bring your passion & expertise to this role and grow your career with us • Permanent full-time hybrid role offering work/life balance & fantastic employee benefits  OUR STORY  Blackwoods is Australia’s leading supplier of industrial and safety supplies. For over 140 years, we have supported businesses big and small with our range of over 300,000 products from the world’s best brands. From the Sydney Harbour Bridge to the railway and your local mechanic, we supply what our customers need when they need it, along with unparalleled expertise and service from our passionate team.  With a national footprint of over 50 branches and 6 Distribution Centres, our people are at the heart of everything we do. Being a part of the Wesfarmers group, also means that we have endless opportunities to make a difference, so join us, and let’s help more people build a better Australia.  YOUR OPPORTUNITY  Due to exciting growth in the business, we are looking for an enthusiastic National Sales Analyst to join our sales team based in any capital city (such as Macquarie Park NSW, Carole Park QLD, Regency Park SA and Scoresby VIC) to provide an exceptional level of service that supports our growing customer base.  This role is responsible for ensuring customer data alignment and/or key sales data including incentives and territory mapping is correct. This role will ensure data for all customer territory applications is aligned with Blackwoods systems, reducing errors, and facilitating clean order fulfilment.  Your key responsibilities include, but not limited to: • Ensure data alignment is maintained to support key sales hierarchy activity and reporting • Build excel models to support commercial decision making • Create and maintain robust suites of reporting that illustrate performance across multiple stakeholder groups • Drive functional Teams (primarily, Sales) understanding in how to utilise data and make commercial decisions • Engage stakeholders at all levels to ensure process around mapping and alignment can be actioned quickly  To be successful, you will have: • Ability to plan and schedule priorities, manage strict deadlines, work autonomously and adapt to changing situations • Microsoft Word, PowerPoint and Excel skills • Strong written and verbal communication • Understanding and applying new technologies • Collaborative approach with the ability to build effective partnerships within own team and across the organisation  CULTURE & BENEFITS  A career with Blackwoods will offer you rewarding experiences and opportunities for growth and development. We have a diverse, inclusive, and safe workplace where our team members care about each other and enjoy building meaningful connections.  To ensure our employees feel valued, supported, and celebrated, we provide a range of employee benefits including: • Competitive salaries and incentives • Flexible work arrangements • A range of diversity and well-being initiatives • Ability to purchase up to 4 weeks additional annual leave • Team events, celebrations and development opportunities • Team member discounts on Wesfarmers products • Discounted offers from over 300 corporate partners • Generous Wesfarmers annual share plans • Attractive parental leave policy and more  NEXT STEPS  If you meet most of the criteria listed above and would like to be considered for this opportunity, please send your application today. We will be contacting suitable candidates as we receive them.  As part of our recruitment process and commitment to safety, you may be required to undertake background checks (which may include a police check, a pre-employment medical assessment; and/or drug & alcohol testing) as part of your application process.  Blackwoods also promotes diversity and inclusion across our workplaces and encourages applications from all backgrounds, including people from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander communities, the LGBTI+ community and people with disabilities.  Please note: All applications will be reviewed after 3rd October 2023.
job_description.44: • ‘Work where it works’ for you and your clients • Be part of a team where everyone belongs, and individuality is celebrated • Contribute to the financial wellbeing of our 2 million+ clients across Australia  The difference you will make at Insignia Financial In the role of the Salesforce Technical Business Analyst, you will take an active and forward-looking approach to enhance project delivery. This includes providing leadership to analysts and collaborating closely with the Delivery Manager to ensure the successful execution of team activities and deliverables.  You Will Make a Difference By • Conducting in-depth technical analysis, addressing complex business requirements and processes • Serving as a pivotal link between stakeholders and the delivery team, taking charge of complex issues across various applications that involve multiple parties • Evaluating existing processes and systems, offering recommendations for process enhancements • Providing subject matter expertise and conduct business analysis for intricate projects • Developing position statements on complex subject matter inquiries • Assisting in Incident Management during Business as Usual (BAU) operations, identifying the root causes and facilitating defect remediation within stipulated SLAs • Providing comprehensive support throughout the end-to-end delivery process, including technical requirements, testing, and change management for planned releases and maintenance windows as needed  A Little Bit About You • Possess business and/or technology expertise, acquired within the Financial Services sector or other related industries • Extensive experience, with a significant portion dedicated to working with Salesforce • Hold tertiary qualifications or possess equivalent industry experience • Demonstrate prior experience in various business practices, with a particular focus on Financial Services, especially in superannuation and fund management • Expert in systems design, integration, and function/data analysis within specific business functions • Exhibit effective communication and interpersonal skills, crucial for effective stakeholder engagement, including the ability to conduct showcases • Adopt a proactive approach to problem-solving, critical thinking, and the identification of opportunities for improvement • Lead by example by embodying the culture and values that align with the expectations of the team and Insignia Financial  Life at Insignia Financial From people just starting out, to those about to retire – every day we help more Australians secure their future. Helping our clients reach their financial goals sooner is our specialty. Few others can match the range of wealth management products and services we offer.  Insignia Financial is an ASX Top 200 company, and one of one of Australia’s leading wealth managers. We use our scale and expertise to invest in a future that’s better for everyone. We believe success comes from caring about people, consistent performance, and outstanding service. And we recognise and celebrate the value of individual difference: this applies to employees and clients alike.  Diversity and ensuring our people feel they belong is important to us, we take pride in putting our people, as well as our clients, first and value and celebrate diversity within all our teams.  We have a Women in Technology community which exists to bring together female and non-binary people within the tech world at Insignia Financial. With many of us now working from home more than the office, we understand the importance of flexibility. We also offer varied and flexible leave offerings, including 12 weeks paid parental leave and an extra day of leave each year.  We encourage our people to have an impact on the broader community we serve through volunteering leave.  At Insignia Financial, it’s important to us that our people feel secure about their own money. We have an extensive financial wellbeing offering available to our people, including access to financial advice, mortgage, and insurance brokers, Will and estate planning services and more.  Join us and contribute to achieving our ambition of creating financial wellbeing for all Australians through living our Principles: be human, deliver what matters, stronger together, keep it simple and do what’s right, not what’s easy. To apply Please submit your resume with a covering letter by clicking on "Apply Now".  Applicants will be required to provide evidence of their eligibility to work in Australia, and at a minimum be required to undertake police and basic credit checks as a condition of employment.  Please note that applications from agencies will not be considered at this time.  At Insignia Financial, we have a culture of belonging. We are an ‘every person’ organisation that welcomes and appreciates everyone for who they are. If you need assistance or an adjustment during the application process because of your personal circumstances, please reach out and let us know. We recognise and celebrate the value of individual difference.  #AW
job_description.45: Job Description  Job Title: Commercial Analyst - Drakes Supermarkets  Location: Adelaide, SA  Almost 50 years since Roger Drake purchased his first supermarket in 1974, Drakes Supermarkets has now become the largest independent grocery retailer in Australia.  Drakes Supermarkets is a proudly Australian-owned and independent retail chain, committed to providing exceptional service and quality products to our valued customers. With a strong emphasis on community involvement and supporting local suppliers, they have grown to become a trusted name in the retail industry.  The Opportunity  As a Commercial Analyst at Drakes Supermarkets, you will be an integral part of business communicating key data insights around shrinkage, consumer behaviours, sales and profit of the fresh food departments to help the organsiation make data driven decisions that drive the business forward.  Key Responsibilities • Reporting Development, Modelling, Maintenance, and Enhancement: • Develop and maintain a comprehensive monthly reporting suite for Fresh Supervisors and Store Managers. • Understand the specific information needs of the fresh food management team and tailor reports accordingly. • Assist in the development of annual Fresh Food Department budgets for sales, wages, and gross profit. • Actively participate in the month-end close process and review Fresh Food Departments' profitability. • Implement procedures and reporting requirements to improve shrinkage within our fresh areas of operation. • Create insightful dashboards to monitor the performance of key Fresh initiatives such as 'Bakery Model,' 'The Little Kitchen,' and 'Store Concepts.' • Ensure transparent, visual and accurate Fresh P&L reporting. • Commercial Analysis: • Conduct quarterly analysis and benchmarking of Fresh Food Department • Provide analysis and support for new Fresh Food opportunities, job_description.48: Line of Service  Assurance  Industry/Sector  Not Applicable  Specialism  Assurance  Management Level  Senior Associate  Job Description & Summary  Genuine opportunities can be hard to spot. Unless you're someone who's used to finding needles in haystacks made of data. If you're one of those people, you also probably know that opportunities this good don't come along that often.  PwC is one of those places where opportunities create options.  We're a community of people united by the love of solving problems, and every solution we deliver cements trust with our clients. And that trust creates more opportunities to strengthen our relationships and fortify our culture.  More than just a number  Supportive team leaders elevate your success.  We lead differently, empowering our people to harness their human ingenuity, passion and latest technology to create a better tomorrow. We empower our people to use their creativity, authenticity and human differences to be the champions of change.  We know that when people from a variety of backgrounds and with different points of view work together, we create the most value - for our clients, our people and our society. In Data Assurance, we care deeply about our people and the numbers. We celebrate having a culture where innovation meets passion. For us, it's about having an incredible team to solve important problems.  Feel confident in Assurance  What is assurance? A feeling of confidence.  It's what we strive to deliver to our clients as we work side by side to help solve the myriad of issues they face. This assurance, in turn, enables organisations to build and earn trust with their stakeholders.  Data has changed the world. Our clients need trusted advice on how to best gather, use and analyse their information. That's where we come in.  We offer a wide range of services, from data governance and data quality to large scale recalculation, visualisation, data collection and validation platforms, as well as advanced analytics. Our Data Assurance team works alongside clients in a multitude of ways. These may be complex recalculations of business process outcomes, developing bespoke solutions to specific problems.  We help transform external and internal audit approaches by embedding data analytics through the entire audit lifecycle and look to the future as algorithmic decisioning becomes embedded in operational areas.  We also help our clients establish the best controls, processes and structures to ensure that decisions are made on accurate information.  We often assure that information and data provided to regulators and third parties is accurate, complete and can be trusted. About you  You have a background in data analytics. You're skilled in data visualisation, data cleansing and manipulation, and you understand business and risk applications. If you have any previous experience in internal audit analytics, that's a big green flag for us  As a Senior Associate in our Data Assurance team, you'll make an impact through:  Building risk and compliance data analytics outputs using tools like Alteryx, ACL, R, Python, Qlik Sense, Power BI, and SQL Server.  Applying risk and compliance analytics to drive decision making for our clients, helping them to better manage risks, optimise processes and build trust with their stakeholders.  Working across multiple client projects, with a broad range of tasks across the data analytics life cycle, like ETL, data wrangling and cleansing, reporting and dashboarding. Compelling data-driven storytelling to communicate and help clients minimise risk and improve their processes and control framework.  Your New Benefits  Flexible daily working hours, we value work-life balance  Work overseas or interstate, we know how precious time is with your family and friends  Paid study (and leave), we pay all the costs and give you time off to study  No dress code, wear what makes you feel comfortable and dress for your day  Yearly bonuses, because who doesn't love to be rewarded for great performance  Health & fitness perks, like a wellness stipend and discounted memberships  Generous parental leave policy for mums, dads and foster carers  If you're looking for a team that values your work and solves meaningful problems, apply now  We believe the best work is human-led and tech-powered.  If you're keen to apply and need reasonable adjustments or would like to note which pronouns you use at any point in the application or interview process, please let us know. job_description.53: The role You'll be working under the Manager in Health Service Research, Analysis, and Modelling.  In this role, you'll use advanced data tools like Microsoft Azure, Power BI, Posit/R, Python, and SQL to make sure data flows smoothly between users and stakeholders.  Your job is to dig into big datasets, analyse data, and then share your findings in a way that makes sense.  You'll be a key part of making business intelligence products and improving the Planning Portal platform by adding up-to-date data, visuals, and dashboards. This will make it easier for people to access health service planning information.  Additionally, your role will extend to fostering service planning capacity and capability across the Department of Health and Hospital and Health Services.  Your exceptional communication and people skills will enable you to diplomatically consult with a diverse range of stakeholders, fostering open and respectful dialogue while ensuring compliance with contemporary HR principles and practices.  The successful personTo thrive in this role, you need to know about the health system, including key health priorities, challenges, and the unique health needs of different groups of people.  You should also be really good at using Power BI or similar software to create visual representations of important health data. In this job, you'll oversee building applications that show health information for the whole state to make decisions. It's important that you're skilled at getting and handling data from big datasets.  This means you should be great at analysing data and turning it into useful information that you can share with others.  You should also know how to use different tools for handling data, whether it's on a physical server or in the cloud. Some of these tools include Azure, SQL Server, R Studio/Posit Workbench, Power BI, and Qlik.  It's crucial that you can look at numbers critically and turn them into useful insights that can be presented professionally. Your job will also involve managing projects efficiently. This means you should be able to work well on your own and as part of a team.  You'll be responsible for making sure complex projects are completed on time and reach the goals that have been set.  Furthermore, your expertise should extend to utilizing both on-premises and cloud-based data integration tools, including Azure, SQL Server, R Studio/Posit Workbench, Power BI, and Qlik. You should be adept at critically analysing numerical data, transforming it into insightful information, and presenting it professionally.  Additionally, your role will require efficient project management skills, highlighting your ability to work autonomously and collaboratively within a team, ensuring the successful management of complex, time-sensitive projects and meeting specified milestones. About usThe Department of Health is responsible for the overall management of the public health system in Queensland.  We are an organisation that strongly believes in the need to collaborate with people who value the goals of our organisation and who will thrive in our workplace. Working at the Department of Health is about making a difference.  Clinical Planning and Service Strategy (CPSS) is the division responsible for delivering clinical service strategy and planning, workforce strategy, planning, and leadership, mental health strategy and planning and precision medicine and research functions to improve health services available to the Queensland community, optimise health gains, reduce inequalities, and maximise the efficiency and effectiveness of the health system.  The Division collaborates with health system leaders, Hospital and Health Services, clinical networks, key healthcare service providers, research and academic organisations, State and Commonwealth agencies as well as non-government organisations and other divisions. Benefits • A fast-paced, challenging and supportive environment • Competitive salary + generous superannuation and leave loading • Flexible working arrangements • Diverse work culture • Career training and developmentTo apply for this exciting opportunity, please submit your resume and a cover letter (maximum two pages) outlining your skills and experience relevant for this role.

The Opportunity • Join CSIRO - Australia's National Science and Innovation Agency! • Supportive, rewarding, inclusive and truly flexible environment. • Collaborative, flexible, innovative workplace that values you and your career development  CSIRO is the national science agency that undertakes research to make life better for Australia and Australians.  We seek a highly motivated geospatial scientist/programmer to support the delivery of a large complex suite of projects under the National Bushfire Intelligence Capability (NBIC). NBIC is developing a framework to deliver data products and decision support relevant for state, territory and federal bushfire planning and response agencies.  The role requires large data processing, programming, spatial analysis, and cloud computing skills. The role is based within the Bushfire Analytics team in the CSIRO Environment Business Unit. For the successful candidate, opportunities may emerge over time to provide support for other projects in CSIRO’s Environment Business Unit portfolio of projects.  The Bushfire Analytics team is primarily based in Melbourne and Brisbane, and you will interact with other teams who are located in other CSIRO offices throughout Australia. The role provides the opportunity for continual learning and innovation, and you will work with a highly skilled and diverse team in a collaborative and supportive environment.  Your duties will include: • Leveraging statistical, physical and process models to inform fuel and fire behaviour prediction such as species distribution, ecosystem dynamics, vegetation growth and fire behaviour modelling. • Translating science into workflows that utilise technologies such web APIs and remote sensing data archives.  The role will also require: • Innovative design, development and adaptation of experimental methods and systems (some of which may be from beyond traditional bushfire and environmental science disciplines). • An ability to collaborate with staff from other teams and external stake holders to ensure NBIC is meeting their needs and objectives. • Demonstration of a capacity to communicate scientific research results, including collaborating on presentations and written reports for clients and the scientific community, industry or government. • Ability to work to deadlines and accepting responsibility for the scheduling and completion of major project activities, including allocating and directing tasks where appropriate. • Work collaboratively as part of a multi-disciplinary, regionally dispersed research team to perform tasks in support of CSIRO’s scientific objectives. • Adherence to the spirit and practice of CSIRO’s Values, Code of Conduct, Health, Safety and Environment procedures and policy, diversity initiatives and Making Safety Personal goals. • Other duties as directed.  Location: Melbourne, Brisbane or Canberra  Salary: AU$105,806 – AU$114,500 per annum + up to 15.4% superannuation  Tenure: Specified term of 2 years  Reference: 93634  To be considered you will need:  Essential  Under CSIRO policy only those who meet all essential criteria can be appointed. • Postgraduate education and/or equivalent experience in Science, including computer science. • Strong quantitative skills and a demonstrated ability to process, analyse and interpret large and complex spatial datasets. • Experience in the use and role of remote sensing and spatial data in multi-disciplinary projects that report on environmental processes. • Proficiency in computer programming and scripting languages (specifically Python and/or R) for automating workflows and the processing of geospatial data, including an ability to demonstrate skills in software version control. • An ability to use a broad range of computing platforms, including high performance and commercial cloud platforms. • Sound written and oral communication skills, including the production of scientific reports. Desirable: • Established knowledge and understanding of bushfire behaviour modelling, risk analysis and mitigation. • A track record of publication in peer-reviewed journals articles. • Experience developing custom tools using geographic information systems (GIS) such as ESRI ArcGIS and QGIS.  For full details about this role please view the Position Description  Eligibility  Eligibility  Applications for this position are open to all Australian/New Zealand Citizens, Australian Permanent residents or Australian Temporary residents with full work rights without the requirement for sponsorship from CSIRO for the duration of the specified term contract.  Appointment to this role is subject to the provision of a national police check and may be subject to other security/medical/character requirements.  …  How To Apply  Please apply online and provide a cover letter and CV that best demonstrate your motivation and ability to meet the selection criteria and key duties.  Please note that this position was initially advertised a couple of months back and has been re-advertised with enhanced requirements. If you have already applied for this position when it was initially advertised, please feel free to refer to the amended Position Description for the changes in the role, however, you do not need to re-apply, as your application would already be in our database.  Flexible Working Arrangements  We work flexibly at CSIRO, offering a range of options for how, when and where you work.  Diversity and Inclusion  We are working hard to recruit people representing the diversity across our society, and ensure that all our people feel supported to do their best work and feel empowered to let their ideas flourish.  About CSIRO  At CSIRO Australia's national science agency, we solve the greatest challenges through innovative science and technology. We put the safety and wellbeing of our people above all else and earn trust everywhere because we only deal in facts. We collaborate widely and generously and deliver solutions with real impact.  CSIRO is committed to values-based leadership to inspire performance and unlock the potential of our people.  CSIRO is committed to the safety and wellbeing of all children and young people involved in our activities and programs, whether we are undertaking research, engaging with the public or nurturing future scientists in person or online. Source – CSIRO Child Safe policy 2023  Join us and start creating tomorrow today!  How to Apply  Please apply on-line and provide a cover letter and CV that best demonstrate your motivation and ability to meet the requirements of this role.  Applications Close  23rd October 2023, 11:00pm AEST
job_description.70: Full Job Description  Who are you? We are looking for a person with a true desire to learn and the motivation to improve yourself and your skills every day. job_description.76: Children & Youth Justice Systems Reform – Unify  ICT Contractor Position Description  POSITION TITLE:  Senior Data Analyst  LOCATION:  111 George Street, Brisbane  CLOSING DATE:  COB Friday, 4 November 2022  HIRING MANAGER:  Tania Vicary  POSITION CONTACT:  Director  Department overview  The Department of Children, Youth Justice and Multicultural Affairs (CYJMA) recognise Queensland comprises communities of diverse cultural backgrounds who have varying needs and aspirations, and who rely on diverse industries for their livelihoods.  In response to this, the Department works in partnership across government, with local communities, non-government organisations and the private sector to achieve the best outcomes for Queenslanders.  By working with us, you will have the opportunity to work with staff from across the department to resolve complex issues and change life trajectories.  About Unify  CYJMA has commenced a four-year journey to implement a new contemporary and coordinated case management system for vulnerable children, young people and families. The Unify Program has been established to deliver this new system to support current and future child safety and youth justice needs through adaptable technology that can support changes to practice as reform occurs over time.  The program will be comprised of a series of joined up projects to provide new integrated and innovative legislation, practice and performance frameworks and business processes, enabled by technology and underpinned by a human-centered design approach.  The program focuses on three critical capabilities: • It is client-centric: supporting targeted, needs-based responses to children, young people, parents, families, carers and communities while delivering earlier and more effective interventions. • It is integration-enabling: designed around collaboration and information sharing, enabling connected and integrated responses to clients across government agencies and non-government partners. • It is data driven, enabling the effective monitoring of outcomes to improve the experiences of children, young people and families and ensures that future investment is directed to what works.  Purpose of the position  The purpose of this position is to provide high quality data analysis, mapping and modelling to the Unify program for the delivery of Child and Family and Youth Justice Products.  The position will be required to engage and work closely with a range of stakeholders to analyse data needs, gather and document requirements, and develop artefacts. The position will play a critical role in understanding the data required for migration, cleansing, viewing and ultimately reporting. In this role one has to work very closely with transactional systems business analysts to build logical/physical data models for the department’s business processes and manage common data model that satisfies requirements.  The successful applicant will be able to demonstrate the capacity to work within a multi-specialist team and deliver to tight timeframes and deadlines (and rapidly changing priorities).  Key responsibilities • Undertake data mapping against an ICT solution and identify the delivery of data sets to support Product delivery • Understand business needs and processes to identify, analyse and document detailed data requirements • Work with business representatives to determine priorities and validate and justify the requirements • Participate in data extract, transformation and migration activities • Work with development teams and other skilled analysts to validate functionality against the data requirements • Provide timely, strategic and expert advice regarding data requirements, information requirements, business impacts, scope management, and project risks • Manage the delivery of work to a schedule and assist in the setting and managing of expectations • Use high level communication skills to negotiate, establish, and maintain networks and working relationships • Apply standardised templates, methodologies and processes for data analysis activities and related project documentation • Lead and work collaboratively with a wide range of staff at all levels • Contribute to business integration, change management, and testing activities • Actively manage a working environment supporting quality human resource management practices including employment equity, anti-discrimination, occupational health and safety, and ethical behaviour.  Essential requirements  The applicant must demonstrate: • Demonstrated experience in data ingestion, cleansing, manipulation and modelling. • Experience in eliciting, analysing, specifying, documenting and validating the business data needs of stakeholders. • Data/reports development skills and experience relevant to the position • Understanding and experience working with applications that utilise complex relational architecture • Experience working within a large, complex multi-disciplinary organisation • High level of written communication and documentation skills • Proven effective communication and stakeholder engagement skills and experience • Proven ability to manage a large workload whilst maintaining high levels of accuracy  Desirable requirements • Data and ETL experience especially with Microsoft Azure Cloud Data Platform (Azure Data Factory, Azure Synapse, Profisee, Azure Data Verse) • Ability to write complex SQL scripts, queries, and stored procedures to extract and mine data. • Experience in developing complex reports, including consideration of complex business rules and data architecture • Knowledge and understanding of the public sector Information and Communication Technology (ICT) Environment. • See projects through to completion, monitoring project progress and adjusting plans as required. • Take personal responsibility for meeting objectives and progressing work. Demonstrate initiative and proactively steps in and does what is required. Commits energy and drive to see that goals are achieved. • Consults and shares information and ensures others are kept informed of issues. • Experience in agile projects methodology.  Deliverables • Document business data requirements and entity relationship at logical and physical levels and maintenance for business products • Develop a data dictionary, detailed data flow diagrams, specifications, and other project related artefacts and documentation as required by the project/program management leadership team. • Document and implement work package activities • Assist stakeholders with User Acceptance Testing  Acknowledgement  I acknowledge that consideration of employing a public servant for this role was carried out and there was no public servant available to fill the requirements of this position.

job_description.78: • Closing Date: 13 October 2023, 9:00 AM  face2face reference: 591408  Location: Nationwide - Remote  Hours: Full-time  Contract length: 12 Months Contract + 3 x 1 Month (Pending approval)  Entry requirements: Australian Citizen + Ability to obtain Baseline  Pay range: $95.00 – 115.00 p/h inc super  About the role:  The Tertiary Skills and Pathways team is responsible for the unit mapping project, as part of its program of work. Unit mapping uses natural language processing techniques to create a connection between tertiary education learning materials (VET and HE units), and skills taxonomies. Unit mapping helps to identify skills taught in tertiary education, and their potential relationship to occupations and the labour market, to assist in analysis and advice on tertiary education delivery.  The team is working on a demonstration project basis with five key projects to design the end to end process of unit mapping, to continually refine the data science model, and to generate insights on the potential use of mapping outputs. The outputs of models are large, for example one university with approximately 3,000 units can have an output of approximately 30,000 skills mapped. Validation of outputs is a critical part of the mapping process to produce a model and results that are highly accurate.  Duties: • Developing of a comprehensive internal and external validation process for very large data sets, to support improvement of data science models, and the quality of output data sent to partners. This may require an ensemble of approaches, for example statistical sampling, manual and automated approaches to validation. • Managing internal validation processes before outputs are sent to project partners. • Working closely with the data science team to provide feedback for the mapping model development. • Analysing complex model outputs, to derive valuable insights for reporting to project partners, including visualisation techniques. • Providing advice to technical services on interface design for a validation application for project partners.  Required experience/skills: • Demonstrated experience in data analysis and process design, to create replicable data validation processes to improve data output quality. • Excellent analytical skills, with strong attention to detail, and the ability to synthesise and critically analyse large volumes of structured and unstructured data. • Strong skills and experience in data management, in particular how data can be effectively structured, analysed, presented and communicated, to achieve high-quality outcomes. • Excellent communication skills, including the ability to effectively communicate key data insights visually and in written form to a range of diverse stakeholders • Well-developed interpersonal skills, including the ability to work effectively in a multidisciplinary setting.  Desirable experience skills: • Experience in R Shiny, Python, SQL, anduser experience design. • Understanding of, and experience working with tertiary education (HE and/or VET) and/or occupation and labour market data. • Understanding and experience in data science, or related fields. • Experience operating in a policy environment. Join Us  Experience : All levels  Start date : Staggered start dates apply  Location : ANZ  Salary : Remuneration package is negotiable based on experience  Do you have your head in the Cloud? • Combine the best of your ingenuity and Cloud technologies to build a better world and lead clients towards change. • Join us and do extraordinary things.  About you :  As a Data Migration Engineer, you will design and maintain data analytic road maps and data structures that support business and technology ambitions.  Naturally inquisitive and open to exploration of underlying data, finding valuable insights and work with functional areas to drive identified actions, you enjoy supporting a team and contributing and have the confidence to influence and communicate with stakeholders at all levels and comfortable working with ambiguity in complex environments.  Our team :  Accenture’s Modern Data Platforms practice covers the range of Data and AI skills across all domains of data governance & quality, cloud & traditional data engineering and visual insights & next generation user interfaces.  When combined with Accenture’s broader Strategy and Consulting and Technology businesses, we are able to bring together the unique end to end business changes through the application of Data and AI.  You will join our migration capability in the Modern Data Platforms team  About the role :  You will become an integral part of our Cloud First & Applied Intelligence team with the credibility, expertise and insight clients depend on working alongside our industry, functional and technology SMEs with famous brands and household names to tackle some of the most tough problems in industry and the community.  In our team you will : • Work as a hands-on, authentic and committed Data Engineer to support clients across a range of industries. • Take responsibility for all aspects of data engineering from delivery planning, estimating and analysis, through to data architecture and pipeline design, delivery, and production implementation • Design and implement complex data solutions ranging from batch to streaming and data directed architectures, across cloud, on-premises and hybrid client technology landscapes • Provide technical thought to define data migration strategy and solution design using ETL (Extract-Transform-Load) methodology • Carry out root cause analysis of the problem and propose solutions. • Ensure technical expectations of deliverables are met • Drive engineering and architectural practices and standards • Develop end to end analytical solutions which will require transformation of complex data sets from multiple source systems, fix bugs, develop enhancements, address queries and requests from business and assist in data and integration tests.  We are looking for experience in the following : • Using tools and techniques such as Data Lake, SQL, Python / Pyspark (or other programming languages with the capability to learn Python), Git, AWS, ADO DevOps. • Data migration project experience • Strong hands-on experience in building data engineering pipelines. • Worked on delivering Data & Analytics solution on cloud platform, preferably AWS • Used cloud data services, such as S3, RedShift, Glue, Step Functions, Lambda  Desirable • Previous experience with high-scale or distributed RDBMS (Teradata, Netezza, Greenplum, Aster Data, Vertica), including metadata management, SQL development and performance tuning within these database environments. • Experience in addressing and implementing data quality solutions, data reconciliation framework and strong understanding and experience in building data lineage documentation, and Data Catalogues. • Experience with related / complementary open source software platforms and languages (e.g. Java, Linux, Apache, Perl / PHP, Chef)  Apply now to register your interest and have a chat about your current situation and career goals.  Your total rewards  Accenture Flex offers a Total Rewards package which includes compensation recognizing individual contributions and a range of benefits so you can build a coverage package based on your personal needs.  Base pay  We offer a competitive base pay based on your role, career level and skills.  Medical coverage and spending accounts  Employees have a choice of plans (PPO, EPO, HDHP) covering a wide range of medical services and prescription drugs. Dental and vision coverage  Employees can choose a traditional dental plan or a dental maintenance organization plan. A vision care plan is offered which covers an annual routine eye exam as well as frames, lenses, or contacts.  Life Insurance & Long-Term Disability  Accenture Flex provides you with a basic level of life, AD&D and disability insurance, and you have the option of purchasing additional coverage.  Paid Time Off (PTO)  PTO encompasses traditional vacation time along with paid personal time off and sick leave, providing flexibility for how, when and for what purpose time off is taken.  401(k) Savings plan  Employees are immediately eligible to contribute to a standard 401(k), a Roth, or an after-tax account through convenient payroll deductions and are always vested in their own employee contributions.
job_description.90: • Seeking a Data & Insights Analyst for Fundraising & Marketing • Salary: $90K - $100K + Super + Salary packing • Location: Melbourne, Sydney or remote • Opportunities to continually advance your Data Analytics career.  We are seeking candidates with a strong background in proven data and data insights expertise. This role goes beyond merely aggregating data into basic tabular reports; it involves the ability to comprehend and present insights in a compelling manner.  These insights will not only significantly impact the donor experience but also go beyond seeking new financial opportunities. We are looking for individuals who are actively dedicated to enhancing our business offerings.  About the role  In this role, you will be tasked with pioneering innovative approaches to harness consumer behavioural data. Your goal is to derive descriptive and prescriptive insights that will guide optimal decision-making. Additionally, you will be responsible for creating interactive and automated dashboards that empower our fundraising team to make strategic decisions through proactive in-depth analysis and insights.  Key responsibilities • Build and Provide insights for the individual giving team in fundraising. • Develop subject matter expertise in the various channels used by the individual giving team. • Engage with business users to consult and recommend best possible way to answer their business data questions. • Provide rapid answers to business questions using a mix of queries and visualisations. • Support ad hoc data requests from across business areas. • Design and build reporting data models that support user self-serve reporting. • Identify data to integrate with the warehouse to develop actionable insights to drive business decisions. • Build customer segmentation analytics and campaign performance reporting. • Proactively organising training and development activities for business to facilitate adaption. • Design, build, test and present meaningful insights from a complex range of data.  Skills and experience • Bachelor’s degree in computer science, statistics, mathematics, economics, or a related field. • 3-5 years of experience in data analytics, business intelligence, or related field. • 1-2 years’ experience working with fundraising teams • Experience with data visualisation and querying tools such as Power BI and SQL. • Strong analytical and problem-solving skills. • Knowledge of data modelling, data warehousing, and ETL processes. • Strong ability to work in T-SQL and DAX queries. • Ability to communicate complex technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders. • Experience in developing and maintaining reports, dashboards, and visualisations. • Knowledge of fundraising and marketing analytics and metrics. • Ability to work independently and as part of a team in a fast-paced environment. • Strong attention to detail and accuracy.  More about the role  Furthermore, you will play a vital role in supporting the enhancement of consumer engagement strategies and product-specific initiatives. Leveraging technical solutions and advanced analytics, you will be at the forefront of developing ground breaking solutions for consumer profiling and segmentation.  Through your work in extracting insights from diverse data sources, you will drive strategic and operational initiatives. These initiatives will lead to increased revenue, improved efficiency, cost optimisation, and an elevated supporter experience, ultimately contributing to the organisation's success and sustainable growth.  A little about our client  Mission Australia, a renowned national charity with over 160 years of dedicated service, is on a mission to help vulnerable Australians find their path to independence. They are committed to tackling homelessness, supporting struggling families, addressing mental health challenges, and fighting substance dependencies. Mission Australia thrives on the support of everyday Australians, corporate partners, and a passionate team of professionals.  Next step is to APPLY  Ready to embark on an epic journey where your data skills make a real difference?  Send us your application, including a cover letter and resume, send it through Beaumont People now! Join Mission Australia and become a data wizard on a mission to end homelessness and help communities thrive!  Apply now and be part of something truly magical!  Don’t tick all the boxes? That’s okay, we like thinking outside the box. We value skills, passion, and drive. So, if this job resonates with you, we want to hear from you!  If you would like to have a confidential chat, please contact Jack or Dean on 02 9133 9322 or email dean@beaumontpeople.com.au, using the subject line: Data Insights Analyst - Mission Australia enquiry via EthicalJobs.  Beaumont People believe a diverse workplace is a happy workplace, and we love working with organisations that feel the same way. We encourage applications from people of all different backgrounds, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, people from CALD backgrounds and people with disabilities. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, age, disability, marital or parental status. Should you require a reasonable accommodation to be made for your application to be assessed we would be more than happy to discuss how that can be arranged.

job_description.92: • Student Enrichment and Employability Development (SEED) • Exciting and challenging working environment with a great team culture. • Utilise your strong analytical and technical skills to build data sets that support business decisions and product improvements. • Collaborate with cross-functional teams and develop reporting requirements. • Based at our St Lucia campus  About UQ  As part of the UQ community, you’ll have the opportunity to work alongside the brightest minds, who have joined us from all over the world.  Everyone here has a role to play. As a member of our professional staff cohort, you will be actively involved in working towards our vision of a better world. By supporting the academic endeavour across teaching, research, and the student life, you’ll have the opportunity to contribute to activities that have a lasting impact on our community.  Join a community where excellence is at the core of our culture, contributions are valued and a range of benefits and rewards are available, such as: • 26 weeks paid parental leave or 14 weeks paid primary caregiver leave. • 17% superannuation contributions. • 17.5% annual leave loading. • Access to flexible working arrangements including hybrid working options, flexible start/finish times, purchased leave, and a condensed fortnight. • Health and wellness discounts – fitness passport access, free yearly flu vaccinations, discounted health insurance, and access to our Employee Assistance Program for staff and their immediate family. • On campus childcare options. • Cheap parking (from just $5 a day). • Salary packaging options.  About This Opportunity  The Data Analyst is responsible for analysing data sourced by and on behalf of the Student Affairs Division from across the University, in order to respond to the day-to-day needs of various areas of the Division. This position will undertake analysis to identify trends and opportunities for growth to support the student experience and will play a lead role in the development of annual divisional reporting.  Key responsibilities include: • Working in partnership to identify and develop divisional service metrics. • Collecting, collating, and interpreting data from existing data sources and providing support to develop new, and redevelop existing, data sets by contributing to specification design and quality assurance checks. • Undertaking analysis of data sets to provide well-informed briefings and reports, identifying trends and opportunities for service delivery improvements. • Streamlining data reporting ensuring that it meets the needs of Student Affairs and wider University stakeholders. • Maintaining awareness of relevant technology and software improvements that may benefit the collection, integration, presentation, and analysis of data within UQ to support programs and initiatives that enhance the student experience.  This is a full-time, continuing (permanent) position.  At HEW level 7, the full-time equivalent base salary will be in the range $93,254 to $101,680, plus a generous super allowance of up to 17%. The total FTE package will be up to $109,107 to $118,966 annually.  About You • Completion of an undergraduate degree, with experience in a relevant area, or an equivalent combination of relevant experience and/or education/training. • Demonstrated ability to compile and manipulate complex data sets and proven analytical skills with the ability to leverage quantitative/qualitative trend data to draw conclusions related to the student experience provided by the division. • Excellent written and oral communication skills and the ability to design and produce clear, concise, and accurate advice and briefing papers on complex issues. A proven ability to be highly organised and self-managing, including a demonstrated capacity to establish work priorities, meet timelines and achieve project management priorities, work independently and accept responsibility. • Highly developed interpersonal skills, including the ability to develop relationships with key stakeholders and liaise, consult, and negotiate with staff at all levels, both internally and externally. • Awareness of issues related to the student experience, retention, and employability within higher education nationally. • Experience in the use of the Business Objects and/or Tableau data management tool. job_description.93: Brisbane based, permanent position  Hello. We’re Virgin Australia. We’re the airline that’s always done things a little different. Our way. The Virgin way. We’re on a mission to make flying better than ‘nice’. And to do that, it takes a team of talented people who are passionate about customer experience, doing the right thing always, with a focus on safety – in the air, on the ground and in our workplaces. A team who values real diversity and inclusion, in a big brand with big ambitions.  What you’ll be doing  We are looking for an Advanced Analytics Specialist to join our team. This exciting role has a wide variety and breadth of work. It will give you the opportunity to grow and gain great exposure to various parts of the business. The areas span across operations, commercial (airfare pricing and revenue management), econometrics, elasticity, and network optimization.  Key accountabilities • Utilize a variety of statistical and analytic methods to generate data models to help predict and explain commercial and operational trends to senior leadership and other division stakeholders. • Perform ad hoc analysis to support multiple departments by compiling historical data as well as forecasting future trends. • Research and evaluate industry trends, practices, and operational methodologies to continually improve overall company operational philosophy and performance. • Collaborate with stakeholders to validate and improve existing assumptions and processes. • Communicate informed conclusions and recommendations to senior leadership to improve business processes. • Champion a culture of analytics and serve as a centre of excellence for trusted data integrity and analysis needs.  You’ll be great in this role if you… • Minimum of 4 years’ experience in Advanced Analytics • Previous data science and operations research experience. • Ability to take complex mathematical concepts and communicate business relevance to key business stakeholders from front-line operations up to executive level management. • Ability to write database queries for successful data analysis. • Use of machine learning on large data sets to identify drivers and make predictions. • Creation of optimisation models to reduce cost and increase revenue. • Advanced Excel based user including Power Query & PowerPivot. Modelling languages such as PowerBI, DAX, R, Python, and SQL. • Ability to create various predictive and operational models as required. • Simulation models including Monte Carlo and Discrete Event. • Experience with EMSR optimisation and other airline operations research is highly desirable.  We’re committed to looking after you, with some of the best benefits and conditions in the industry – including (but not limited to): • Discounted flights for you and your loved ones (including $1000 worth of travel credits per year) • A flexible, hybrid work style. Work from home or the office, adapt your location to suit your style and needs • One of Brisbane’s most admired head office locations, with South Bank train station, a supermarket, pharmacy, and lunch options downstairs plus a 5-minute walk to the Busway, a rooftop restaurant and onsite gym (with a low membership fee) and South Bank Parklands just across the road • Discounts on travel insurance, lounge membership, car hire, accommodation, and experiences worldwide • Cheaper hospitality, retail, technology, beauty and wellness services • Free counselling and access to a wellbeing app to support your physical, mental, social and financial health • ‘Dress for Your Day’ – enjoy the freedom to wear whatever makes you feel great for the type of work you do and the day you have ahead of you.  When everyone is included, everyone wins  We’re all individuals. And we love that. That’s why we encourage applications from Indigenous Australians, people with disability, those from diverse cultural backgrounds, our friends in the LGBTQI+ community, and anyone else who wants to join our family.  Ready to apply?  We’re ready to hear from you. Apply now.
job_description.94: We are desiring to recruit a proactive Senior Data Engineer - Remote to join our vibrant team at Send in Brisbane.  Growing your career as a Full Time Senior Data Engineer - Remote is an exceptional opportunity to develop necessary skills. If you are strong in attention to detail, presentation and have the right aptitude for the job, then apply for the position of Senior Data Engineer - Remote at Send today  We are Send Payments  Send is an award winning, high growth payments company delivering embedded finance solutions to some of the world's most recognised and valued brands.  Our mission is to build robust, global financial infrastructure supported by world class product and applications which empower and enable our partners to integrate fast, low cost, local and cross-border payments into their business models natively.  We believe in delivering a blend of smart, enabling technology and outstanding customer experience and we bake these values into everything we do, from strategy to execution.  Our vision is to be the payments partner of choice for established brands and we are already disrupting the international payments and fintech space here in Australia and beyond.  Companies like Woolworths, Flight Centre, Pexa and many others are already partnering with Send to expand and monetise their business capabilities and deliver significant experience improvements to their customers.  With global domination firmly in our sights and a strong partnership pipeline to go with it, we are looking to grow our teams and further develop our infrastructure and product offering from here to support these huge growth opportunities. Culture & Values There's a place for everyone at Send. We're a team of ambitious individuals with diverse talents and an entrepreneurial spirit at our core. We're not afraid to challenge ideas or bring different perspectives to the table. We look at problems from all angles and value debate and feedback.  Our values-led culture inspires us to continuously deliver the best experiences for both our team and customers:  Aim Up, Fail Forward: We move fast, experiment, test, verify, and learn then repeat.  Customers At Our Core: It's our aim to delight, add value, and provide an outstanding experience at every touch point.  Think Like an Owner:  Our colleagues put their trust in us to carefully balance risk with reward, and to make decisions for which we're 100% accountable.  Bring Your Best: We pour passion into our work, set high standards and always drive each other forward. Create a Place You Want to Work:We're flexible, compassionate, playful and honest.  Overview As a Senior Data Engineer, you will be responsible for designing, building, and maintaining the data architecture. This role requires expertise in database design, data warehousing, and data modelling. You should be proficient in modern data programming languages as well as familiar with big data technologies. You will also be expected to be proficient in the use of visualisation tools.  We require you to have effective communication skills, as you will often work with cross-functional teams to understand business requirements and translate them into technical solutions.  This role also requires expertise in data security and privacy regulations, and you should be able to lead and mentor junior data team members, as well as collaborate with business stakeholders to drive data-driven decision-making.  You will provide technical leadership and support to analysts, product, quality assurance and operations teams and will be imaginative and creative in exploring a range of application designs, can communicate these effectively to others, and can engage and support others in the team. Main Responsibilities Maintain and develop our ETL/ELT processes, data modelling and data integration into our Snowflake data warehouse and tools such as Matillion Work with data visualisation tools daily such as Tableau, Google Analytics and more.  In our high performing team, you will actively participate in the design, coding, testing, and debugging of our data platform and reports using the latest programming languages and tools.  Bugs bother you, and you are relentless in identifying and resolving defects, performance bottlenecks, and other technical challenges using a creative mindset. Strong Data Analysis skillset used to interpret complex data sets and perform ad-hoc analysis.  Great at Data Modelling, leading the development and implementation of data modelling standards and best practices – achieving things such as high query performance.  You will not be siloed, and you are someone who thrives in cross-functional teams, collaborating closely with talented professionals including product team, business owners and testers. You understand that documentation is important for future reference and effective knowledge transfer and are diligent in your documentation.  In a rapidly fast changing landscape, you are passionate about staying at the forefront of emerging technologies, industry trends, and best practices in data. Did we mention AI?  You understand best practice coding principles and apply your knowledge to participate in code reviews and embrace a culture of quality assurance. You take pride in your work.  Skills and Competencies Demonstrated skills in SQL, Python, and other languages Understanding of business systems such as CRMs & Telephony Strong experience in cloud-based data technology stacks such as AWS, Snowflake, Matillion, Tableau Online and what good data security practices look like Ability to build and maintain technical documentation and version control using tools such as Confluence and CI/CD Confidence in your ability to capture business requirements and transform them into results  Your knowledge of database systems and SQL empowers you to design and optimise data-driven applications / warehouses that are secure and robust. You use your experience gained to peer review, mentor and guide other team members. Natural problem solver, relishing the challenge of analysing and debugging complex software issues with tenacity and resourcefulness. Exceptional communicator and collaborator, excelling in both written and verbal communication to drive effective teamwork and alignment.  You hold a bachelor's degree in computer science, data & analytics, business information systems or a related field (or equivalent experience), demonstrating your commitment to excellence in the field. Experience in financial/payment exchange contexts a big plus A passion for broader business success Joining Send Payments as a Senior Data Engineer, you bring passion, technical expertise, and a drive for innovation. Together, we will shape the future of the payments industry and make a meaningful impact on our customers' lives.  This role reports directly into the Head of Data and Analytics and is a full-time remote position.  Discover the Perks of Joining Us  Reward & Recognition: Earn 'hero dollars' on our HRIS platform for the swag store.  Celebrate Together: Half-yearly parties, town halls, and milestone gifts unite us.  Flexible Workspaces: Choose WeWork in Sydney/Brisbane or our own cozy offices in Sydney/Gold Coast.  Pet-Friendly Office: We understand the joy that pets bring  Wellness Breaks: Enjoy 4 extra wellness days off every year.  Your Voice Matters: We listen, learn, and act based on ENPS surveys.  ESOP for All: Eligibility for our Employee Share Option Plan.  Why Choose Send?  At Send, we thrive on a flat and inclusive team structure where every member plays a pivotal role in our success. We believe in the power of proactive collaboration, recognising the immense value of fresh perspectives. Our team is committed to fostering diversity, adaptability, and a shared determination to push boundaries and achieve extraordinary growth. Regardless of your background or how you identify, we invite you to be a part of our journey. Join us and contribute to something exceptional Benefits of working as a Senior Data Engineer - Remote in Brisbane: • Excellent Benefits Package • Opportunities to grow • Attractive packageCompetitive Pay

Your New Opportunity  We are in search of a skilled Business Intelligence Analyst to join our finance team, with a primary focus on automating existing reporting processes and expanding the internal analytics capability across our professional services firm. job_description.97: Brief Description  About us  At Auto & General (A&G), we provide smarter products and solutions to safeguard our customers in their time of need. Our range of general insurance products protect customers on the road, at home and on holiday with various Car, Motorcycle, Home, Contents, Pet and Travel Insurance products as well as Roadside Assistance.  Our culture of ‘high performance with high integrity’ underpins our values and the way we interact with our customers, the community and each other. We’re excited about the future and we’re always on the lookout for talented, passionate individuals who can help us achieve our goal of being Australia’s best insurer! If this sounds like you, apply today.  If you are seeking a new challenge and would enjoy the opportunity to work in a growing and changing business, click on the APPLY NOW button and submit your application.  The Role  If you're a Reporting Analyst who sees data as a canvas for creativity, we have an opportunity that will truly set your imagination free!  We're on the hunt for a Data Storyteller - Reporting Analyst to join our innovative team. As our resident data artist, you'll be the driving force behind our data-driven narratives, weaving compelling stories that inspire action and ignite change.  Accountabilities  Reporting to the Senior Manager of Service Reporting & Analytics, you will be responsible for: • Crafting data-driven stories that captivate and engage stakeholders, using a blend of analytics, visualizations, and narratives that resonate with diverse audiences. • Collaborating with cross-functional teams to uncover insights, identify trends, and extract meaning from complex data sets. • Pushing the boundaries of traditional reporting by exploring new and creative ways to communicate insights, such as interactive dashboards, infographics, or other innovative formats. • Transforming raw data into stunning visualizations that tell a story, using cutting-edge tools and techniques to create visually appealing and impactful reports. • Be a strategic partner to our senior business leaders, providing actionable insights that inform strategic initiatives and unlock new opportunities. • Continuously innovate and stay ahead of the curve by exploring emerging technologies, data visualization trends, and best practices to elevate our reporting capabilities to new heights.  What Experience You’ll Bring • Bachelor's degree in Mathematics, Actuary, Data Science, or a related field. • Strong proficiency in data analysis, data visualization, and reporting tools such as Tableau, Power BI, or other similar tools. • Proven experience in creating compelling data stories and visualizations that effectively communicate insights and drive action. • Excellent storytelling skills with the ability to simplify complex data concepts into easy-to-understand narratives. • A keen eye for aesthetics and design, with a passion for creating visually appealing reports that inspire and captivate audiences. • Excellent communication and presentation skills, with the ability to convey complex information in a compelling and engaging manner. • Strategic thinking and problem-solving skills, with a creative mindset that pushes the boundaries of traditional reporting. • Ability to work independently and collaboratively in a fast-paced, dynamic environment.  Our perks • Location – Our office is conveniently based in North Lakes - a location with access to retail, restaurants, various parking options and public transport. • Extra leave - Enjoy additional leave days on us! You’ll receive a paid ‘ME’ day and one paid volunteer leave day annually. job_description.98: Are you passionate about outcomes for children and young people across Queensland?  We're committed to providing life-changing healthcare for children and young people for a healthier tomorrow.  About the Queensland Children's Hospital  The Queensland Children's Hospital (QCH), which opened on 29 November 2014, is Australia's largest and most advanced paediatric facility. Located in South Brisbane, the 359-bed hospital features more than 80,000 square meters of facilities spread across 12 levels.  As Queensland's single specialist paediatric facility, Children's Health Queensland's (CHQ) at the QCH is the hub of a dedicated network of paediatric services available at other Brisbane and Queensland hospitals. Expanding on CHQ's state-wide remit, the QCH also supports regional hospitals through telemedicine and outreach services. This means children and young people can access the services they need as close to home as possible.  The hospital precinct includes the Centre for Children's Health Research, the Children's Hospital Foundation, Ronald McDonald House South Brisbane (opened in 2016) and a new Adolescent Drug and Alcohol Withdrawal Service building.  Your Opportunity: • Manage a binational team of data managers and biostatisticians for a binational registry, the “Australia and New Zealand Congenital Outcome Registry for Surgery” designed to evaluate outcomes following paediatric cardiac surgery across Australia and New Zealand • Coordinate data collection, data validation and secure transmission for the dataset across all participating sites. • Manage, extract and prepare data for analysis for annual registry reports and regulatory requirements as well as publications. • Work with collaborators to establish clear data definitions and site-specific processes to ensure quality data is collected and transmitted.  What CHQ HHS can offer  Apart from contributing to the development of Australia's best paediatric health service, you will also benefit from a competitive remuneration package and a working environment which embraces professional development, builds capabilities and supports staff to maximise their health and wellbeing. Additional benefits include: • Up to 12.75% employer superannuation contribution • 17.5% annual leave loading • Salary packaging • Employee Assistance Program • Work/life balance, variety and flexibility  You can find out more about why it's so great to work at CHQ HHS here ( http://www.childrens.health.qld.gov.au/work-for-us/ ).  It is a mandatory condition of employment for this role to be: • vaccinated against, and remain vaccinated against, certain vaccine preventable diseases (VPD) as outlined in the Health Employment Directive NO. 01/16(PDF) ( https://www.health.qld.gov.au/__data/assets/pdf_file/0009/150120/hed-0116.pdf ) • Vaccinated against COVID-19 as outlined in the Health Employment Directive NO. 12/21(PDF) ( https://www.health.qld.gov.au/__data/assets/pdf_file/0022/1108453/hed-1221.pdf ) and the Queensland Health Human Resources Policy B70(PDF) ( https://www.health.qld.gov.au/__data/assets/pdf_file/0024/1108446/qh-pol-486.pdf ).

And it's our expert Technology team who forge ahead every day to make those 'what ifs' a reality.  Suncorp places a strong emphasis on harnessing the potential of its data for business improvement through the Analytics, Data Science & AI Centre of Excellence. This centre pursues a two-fold mission: firstly, by developing and integrating Data Science & AI initiatives into Suncorp's operations at scale, and secondly, by supporting strategic leaders and the broader data science community within the organization.
