These initiatives span from prototypes to scaled data science assets integrated into core business processes.  What you'll do • Contribute to best practices and thought leadership within the Data Science & AI community • Assist with the development of models and algorithms for optimal performance and risk management • Be a part of our evolution of Suncorp's Data Science & AI ecosystem, including platform integration • Work on technically complex AI projects with significant business impact • Prototyping to fully integrated, scaled data science assets in core business processes • Scaling AI initiatives and supporting data science endeavours company-wide  What you'll bring • 2+ years of experience in Data Science, AI, or related fields is required • Ability to discern current and emerging best practices, differentiating hype from efficacy • Ability to use Python or large language models • Bachelor's degree in a technical field (e.g., data science, machine learning, statistics, actuarial, engineering, mathematics) is mandatory • Commitment to team and Suncorp Data Science & AI community success • Pragmatic approach balancing technical excellence with resource constraints • Proficiency in holistic data science solution design, integrating technical expertise with innovative approaches • Skill in solving analytical challenges without prior patterns • Knowledge and practical experience in applying diverse Data Science and AI techniques for financial services solutions • Versatility across various work modes, from rapid innovation to project delivery  What we can offer you • A range of flexible working and leave options, including 20 weeks paid parental leave, 4 weeks paid secondary carer parental leave and unlimited paid emergency response leave • Discounts and offers on a range of retail favourite stores as well as banking and insurance products • Invest in your brighter future with ongoing study support and career development programs • Give back to our communities with payroll giving, donation matching and paid volunteer leave • Prioritise your work/life balance with our robust employee assistance program and dedicated employee council

job_description.102: About the Role  JBS Australia is currently recruiting an experienced HR Data Analyst to join the Group People and Culture team. Based at Riverview (Ipswich) and reporting to the Group Manager – HRIS, this role will be primarily responsible developing and maintaining people analytics utilizing QlikSense. This role is ideal for someone who is keen to be in the driver's seat of design, developing people analytics from the ground up.  Your responsibilities: • Optimizing and streamlining data workflows and data models for People data • Developing and implementing the People Intelligence Dashboard which will include visualization of key people performance indicators and business metrics • Work closely with HR stakeholders to understand/document business requirements and translate them into solutions • Ensuring data quality and accuracy through understanding the HR processes, having structured data validation and testing • Documenting and assisting with developing the People Domain for Master Data Management • Deliver functional training to key stakeholders (as required) • Build new and maintain existing dashboards in QlikSense • Produce reports for audiences ranging from frontline supervisors to C-Suite executives • Work closely with HR leaders to assist with information requests and develop tools to make information more accessible  About You • Bachelor's Degree in a quantitative field (economics, mathematics, finance, etc.) and/or background in Mathematics, Statistics • Experience in programming (Python, SQL) • Drive to develop structure processes and documentation • Experience with data modelling concepts • Experience with QuikSense/PowerBI/Tableau or other equivalent reporting platform • Familiarity with ETL processes and data integration concepts • Strong analytical skills • Excellent problem-solving skills • Strong technical writer • Curious about data and a drive to understand where it comes from • Self-motivated, with the ability to work independently and ask questions as needed • Knowledge of agile and user stories • Knowledge of master data management practices • Strong ability to coordinate and communicate between multiple stakeholders • Documentation skills in developing technical data diagrams, reporting specifications and testing  Why work for JBS Australia? job_description.104: Arq Group changes the way businesses do business. From award winning mobile apps, cloud and analytical insights, to design thinking and digital marketing. job_description.107: At CoreLogic, we are driven by a single mission—to make the property industry faster, smarter, and more people-centric. CoreLogic is the trusted source for property intelligence, with unmatched precision, depth, breadth, and insights across the entire ecosystem.  Our talented team of 5,000 employees globally uses our network, scale, connectivity and technology to drive the largest asset class in the world.  Join us as we work toward our vision of fueling a thriving global property ecosystem and a more resilient society.  CoreLogic is committed to cultivating a diverse and inclusive work culture that inspires innovation and bold thinking; it's a place where you can collaborate, feel valued, develop skills and directly impact the real estate economy. We know our people are our greatest asset. At CoreLogic, you can be yourself, lift people up and make an impact.  By putting clients first and continuously innovating, we're working together to set the pace for unlocking new possibilities that better serve the property industry.  Job Description: Who are you? Across Australia and New Zealand our geospatial capability continues to grow.  We are developers, data analysts, data architects and imagery specialists - and we are looking to add talent to our special team.  Using location intelligence, we provide a deep understanding of what is happening in and around a property to help our customers make better property decisions. What will you be doing? Maintain spatial assets and ensure that the data is fit-for-purpose and maintained to highest standards Work with key stakeholders to develop and maintain datasets for existing and new solutions Define best practice processes for supporting regular and ad-hoc data extracts, reporting and analytical outputs for spatial data Contribute to the development of data engineering solutions using SQL, FME and other geospatial technologies and libraries to enable the effective collection, cleansing, loading, querying and reporting of large spatial datasets Collaborate with SME's to define, research and propose geospatial technology tools, data and methodologies Develop processes to extract, transform, blend and enrich geospatial datasets from various sources Build and maintain FME Workspaces, SQL/Python scripts and procedures as required by the projects Design of solutions that align with the overall data architecture for the business Ensure documentation of all data processes and assets is kept up to date and is coherent Work effectively within an agile team environment to deliver robust, scalable and easily maintainable solutions Deliver solutions that ensure projects are delivered on-time, on-budget and to the quality standards Provide support and expertise as part of a project team to ensure project delivery Undertake analysis, projects or discrete pieces of work as directed Stay abreast of geospatial data and technology developments  What is the role? Collaborate with key stakeholders, product owners and managers and across all business functions to define, understand, prepare and assist as a SME with geospatial data requirements, solution feasibility and development Plan and implement geospatial data engineering/development efforts in accordance with the project scope, including budgeting, scheduling, risk analysis and provide solutions Maintain geospatial databases and processes with focus on automation with FME and other relevant technologies Create geospatial data from scratch or by adapting, transforming and enriching existing datasets Provide maintenance and support for the geospatial datasets to products, solutions and applications Ability to work autonomously while managing multiple tasks simultaneously  Are you the right fit?  You need to have: Excellent ability to make new and useful ideas work Excellent ability to communicate and work with technical and non-technical people Exceptional skills in partnering with clients/ staff and in developing and maintaining long term supportive relationships Ability to assess the effectiveness of processes and procedures, and recommend improvements Assist with the delivery of solutions end to end and ensuring customer outcomes are delivered Ability to work independently and as a contributing, collaborative team member Experience in driving agile ceremonies like sprint planning, retrospectives and backlog grooming across multiple projects 6+ years of relevant experience in geospatial  Job Qualifications:  Core Competencies: Excellent ability to make new and useful ideas work Excellent ability to communicate and work with technical and non-technical people Exceptional skills in partnering with clients/ staff and in developing and maintaining long term supportive relationships Ability to assess the effectiveness of processes and procedures, and recommend improvements Assist with the delivery of solutions end to end and ensuring customer outcomes are delivered Ability to work independently and as a contributing, collaborative team member Experience in driving agile ceremonies like sprint planning, retrospectives and backlog grooming across multiple projects  Required Skills and Experience: Minimum Academic Education Bachelor's degree or equivalent in GIS, Computer Science, Engineering or Scientific Discipline Minimum years of relevant work experience 6 years relevant experience in geospatial data engineering Required skills and competencies Bachelor's degree or equivalent in GIS, Computer Science, Engineering or Scientific Discipline A minimum of 4 years relevant experience in geospatial data engineering Experience in design, building and testing geospatial data solutions that are complex or large-scale working as a GIS Developer/Data Engineer or in a related technical role Advanced knowledge and experience with developing data pipelines using PostGIS, python, FME and other related geospatial tools and platforms Proficiency in data modelling, data integration and relational databases Experience with geospatial analytics Experience in working with geospatial data integration and geospatial problem-solving Experience with the spatial data management, including cloud and hybrid environments Experience working with FME, ESRI and other geospatial technologies for geospatial data processing, management and visualization  Desired additional skills and competencies Experience working in a cloud environment – AWS and GCP  Ability to present outputs using contemporary methods and communicate effectively with a range of audiences to transfer the knowledge gained and present ideas and solutions. Experience using Python or understanding of object-oriented programming concepts. Experience using FME Server for end-to-end automation of geospatial data pipelines and processes. Experience with ESRI platform in building and delivering geospatial data solutions.  What does success look like?  Key Performance Indicators are based on: Completion of commissioned projects on time and within budget Production processes running within expected timelines Focus on quality deliverables, ensuring 99% accuracy for production changes. All processes documented and in confluence. Identify process improvements, reduce wastage, automate where possible. Continuous improvement of processes and systems. Focus on improving customer experience. CoreLogic maintains a Drug-Free Workplace. Please apply on our website for consideration.  By providing your telephone number, you agree to receive automated (SMS) text messages at that number from CoreLogic regarding all matters related to your application and, if you are hired, your employment and company business. Message & data rates may apply. You can opt out at any time by responding STOP or UNSUBSCRIBING and will automatically be opted out company-wide.  Connect with us on social media Click on the quicklinks below to find out more about our company and associates. About Us  CoreLogic is a wholly owned subsidiary of CoreLogic (  NYSE: CLGX), and is the largest data and analytics company in the world.  CoreLogic provides property information, analytics and services across Australia and New Zealand and is currently developing and growing partnerships throughout Asia.  With Australia's most comprehensive property databases, the company's combined data offering is derived from public, contributory and proprietary sources and includes over 500 million decision points spanning over three decades of collection, providing detailed coverage of property and other encumbrances such as tenancy, location, hazard risk and related performance information.  With over 11,000 customers and 120,000 end users, CoreLogic is the leading provider of property data, analytics and related services to consumers, investors, real estate, mortgage, finance, banking, insurance, developers, wealth management and government. CoreLogic delivers value to clients through unique data, analytics, workflow technology, advisory and geo spatial services. Clients rely on CoreLogic to help identify and manage growth opportunities, improve performance and mitigate risk. CoreLogic employs over 700 people at ten locations across Australia and in New Zealand. #J-18808-Ljbffr
job_description.108: Description  About the role  The successful incumbent will lead a team through influencing and consulting with stakeholders to obtain, analyse, communicate and validate technical requirements for changes to business processes, policies, digital systems and applications.  Understand business problems and opportunities in the context of digital user experience and effect solutions that enable the business customer and end user to achieve their goals. • Lead, and influence the discovery and delivery of member-centric solutions supported by clearly identified member benefit both direct and indirect. • Lead the development of technical requirements for opportunity-led initiatives with business areas and product teams across the RACQ. • Leverage technologies such as HTML, JavaScript, .NET, SQL, Xamarin, Sitecore and Web API’s. • Play a key role in the development of functional documentation, facilitating the management of changes, support of testing initiatives and the resolution of problems as they emerge. • Identify and prepare appropriate documentation for new or changed process workflow models in a form easily understood by business units and technical staff. • Provide solution lead role as required including design, costing, co-ordination, and specification activities ensuring that requirement deliverables meet business needs and expectations. • Conduct continuous improvement on Digital initiatives implemented and identify opportunities for further optimisation within the process.  About you • Must have confident, articulate, and professional verbal and written capabilities. • Demonstrated negotiation, mediation and facilitation skills. • Must have Business acumen and industry knowledge with a strong understanding of business processes and products. • Knowledge of digital IT trends. • Knowledge of HTML, JavaScript and .NET. • Experience working with digital platforms. • Experience working with JIRA and Confluence. • Hands-on experience using UML to create sequence diagrams. • Extensive experience working with API’s and Web services. • Knowledge and use of process modeling tools to create BPMN and flow diagrams.  Why join RACQ?  It is an exciting time to be part of RACQ as we continue our transformation towards better, smarter solutions that deliver more security and prosperity for Queenslanders.  We are big enough to make a real difference in our community, yet small enough to nurture your professional and personal development.  By joining RACQ, you’ll be part of new sustainability initiatives, including a commitment to being a carbon neutral organisation by 2030.  We’ve invested in and partnered with sustainable companies, including the introduction home solar and batteries, Green Home and Car Loans, and many other products and initiatives.  We’ll continue to advocate for, research, and offer green solutions.  RACQ is committed to ensuring that every employee has access to flexibility in their role. We encourage all candidates to discuss what flexibility means to you, and how we can help you find your balance.  At RACQ we are passionate about building a diverse and inclusive workplace to create better outcomes for our employees and our members.  We aim for our teams to be a true reflection of our communities and are committed to inclusion particularly people of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander heritage, and those who may experience diversity or disability related barriers in securing employment.  Applicants from these and other diverse backgrounds are encouraged to apply. If you have any support or access requirement, please advise us at the time of applying.  What we offer you :  Our employee benefits are designed to enrich your work life, your home and the community you live in, some of these include : • Financial benefits and discounts on a range of banking, assistance and insurance products • Give back to our communities with paid volunteer leave, payroll giving and volunteering for community events such as MotorFest and EKKA • A range of flexible working and leave options, parental leave of 13 weeks primary carer leave, purchased leave up to 4 weeks per year, cultural observance leave, substitution of public holidays for cultural / religious reasons, personal leave for wellbeing, gender affirmation leave. • Prioritise your wellbeing with our onsite and virtual health hub, discounts on health programs and access to wellbeing initiatives such as yoga, mindfulness, flu vaccinations, free and confidential Employee Assistance Program (EAP). • Invest in your development with in-house development programs and access to 100,000+ online courses.  You can check out all our employee benefits at https : / / www.racq.com.au / about-us / careers / employee-benefits
job_description.109: Salary: $129k+ (9-day) or $168k+ (10-day) + 12.75% super  Energy Queensland (EQL) has two permanent opportunities for two Asset Maintenance Specialists focusing primarily on Data Analytics as part of the Transformer & Reactive Plant and Secondary Plant & Auxiliary Systems department located at either Rockhampton, Townsville, Toowoomba, Brisbane (Newstead). Both EQL and external candidates can apply.  About your new role:  As a data analytics professional at EQL, you will provide systematic advice on network asset performance. Your key responsibilities include monitoring and analysing asset performance and maintenance, planning program performance, and reporting findings and corrective actions to relevant parties.  You will also perform periodic asset performance analysis, maintain documentation, handle asset failure data requests, and ensure regulatory compliance. Identifying developing trends and engineering strategies will be critical to your success.  Why choose to work for us?  It’s an exciting time to join us and to be involved in the energy sector, so consider us for your next career move, where you will experience: • Secure employment backed by a strong collective agreement, with yearly EBA increases. • Strong 12.75% superannuation and the ability to earn more with salary sacrifice co- contributions. • Opportunities for skills and career advancement with access to ongoing training and leadership programs and the capacity to build and grow your skills. • Healthy work life balance with the option to WFH, two days per week and ad hoc as required. • A chance to give back with a paid employee volunteering program allowing our employees to support communities across QLD. • Support and guidance with access to a 24/7 Employee Assistance Program and a mentoring program for professional support and guidance. • A Safety-First culture, the safety of our people, customers & communities is a core priority. • Reward and recognition with an internal reward and recognition program that includes an annual celebration of excellence. • Diversity and Inclusion where all employees can contribute towards multiple diversity and inclusion initiatives across our business. • Grow professionally with full access to LinkedIn Learning. • Need wheels? Options available for novated leases for personal use.  About you:  You have a degree or equivalent experience in data science, business, or mathematics. You have demonstrated experience in line and substation maintenance practices. You have strong communication skills, work well in teams, and prioritise tasks.  You have demonstrated experience using SAP and Ellipse applications. You are highly proficient in programming languages such as Python or R. You are also willing to learn and have excellent problem-solving skills to approach business problems as data science tasks.  The job may require travel and non-standard working hours.  About us:  Even if you haven’t heard of Energy Queensland you might know our operational brands - Energex, Ergon Energy Network, Ergon Energy Retail and Yurika. As a group, we are growing rapidly and as part of the Queensland Energy and Jobs Plan (QEJP), actively helping to advance the energy transition towards net zero.  Energy Queensland is the group of electricity distribution, retail, and energy services businesses 100% owned by the state of Queensland. We deliver electricity across Queensland through our ‘poles and wires’ businesses Energex and Ergon Energy Network. Our retailer, Ergon Energy Retail sells this electricity to customers throughout regional Queensland. And these essential service activities are supported by a range of innovative products and services delivered through our Yurika brand.  How to apply  To shape the future of energy, visit our website and check out the "position description." Then, submit your application before 5.00 pm Monday, 9 October 2023.  If you have any questions or need assistance during the application process, please don't hesitate to contact the Resourcing Advisor, Alisha Benson on 0400 557 913 or alisha.benson@energyq.com.au  We value the differences individuals contribute to our workforce and encourage a diverse range of applicants to apply.  Click to view more information on diversity and inclusion at Energy Queensland, found here: https://www.energyq.com.au/diversity-and-inclusion
job_description.110: Delivering Energy Today, Powering Your Tomorrow.  Elevate your career! Join us in this exciting newly created position as a Forecast Analyst. Reporting to the Retail Analytics Manager this pivotal role, will be the forefront of developing cutting-edge tools to supercharge CSE's demand forecasting services.  Duties include the below, but are not limited to: • Continuously improve existing load forecasting, models, databases and methodology • Maintain and regularly review market data and input assumptions. • Analyse and produce regular reports including assessments of forecasting accuracy and sources of variance • Maintain and regularly review data and assumptions • Develop reports to allow the Retail Business to accurately monitor retail related activities • Contribute to Retail Financial Performance analysis • Assist in documentation of processes, model description, assumptions, and verification to meet requirements as necessary, and ensuring ongoing compliance is demonstrable • Other ad-hoc analysis is a regular requirement of this role  What’s in it for you • An exciting time to join the Energy Industry with numerous new projects underway • Competitive salary and benefits on offer with 12.75 % employer superannuation and an annual incentive payment • Hybrid flexible working environment with brand new offices in Fortitude Valley close to the train station.  About You  To be successful in this role you will have the following skills and experience: • Degree level qualifications in Information Technology, Engineering, Mathematics, Commerce, or Economics • 3-5 years previous energy market experience is desirable • Intermediate or advanced IT skills including use Python, R , Oracle, SQL, Matlab, and other languages • Excellent communication skills – written and verbal • Data collation and analysis • High level of attention to detail  About Us  CS Energy is a proudly Queensland-owned and based company that provides competitively-priced and reliable energy to some of our state’s biggest industries and employers. With power stations and operations around the state we are providing jobs and opportunities for hundreds of Queenslanders. Our staff live in and are part of the communities in which we serve. We are proud to call Biloela, Chinchilla, Dalby and Brisbane our home.  Every voice is important to us  CS Energy is proud to foster an environment that builds respect, promotes inclusiveness, celebrates diversity and embraces the unique skills and qualities of all our employees. Reasonable adjustments to the recruitment process will be supplied to those who require additional support.  As part of the recruitment process, the successful applicant may be required to complete a number of background checks including; reference checks, pre employment medical, national police checks, right to work eligibility, verification of qualifications, and bankruptcy checks.  Job closing date: 20th October 2023  Energy is changing and so are we. Apply today!
job_description.111: Together, we can do great things  We shape leading experiences across office, retail and logistics.  We’re one of Australia’s largest property groups, managing $32 billion worth of assets across the country.  Our sustainable returns from investments come from focusing on what matters most to customers — a great experience and doing good. Every day, our people are driving positive impact for people, place and planet. They’re inquisitive, pioneering industry firsts and pushing new ideas to deliver exceptional outcomes.  This passion and expertise create an employee experience that puts wellbeing, flexibility and opportunity first.  Come join us.  The role  We have an new opportunity for a Business Analyst (6 month fixed term) to join the team supporting the delivery and optimisation of finance technology products.  As Business Analyst, you will work collaboratively with developers and business subject matter experts on the development, management and maintenance of these products, primarily involving Anaplan.  You will also support critical testing work on a project involving financial forecasting alongside the project lead.  This is a rare contract opportunity to gain valuable exposure to working with a top ASX50 property company with strong resourcing, systems and processes.  As a fixed term employee, you will have access to a range of our benefits including reward and recognition, retail discounts and learning and development opportunities.  What you will be doing • Working consultatively with business teams to understand requirements, requests, issues about the system/application • Working with the technical team to design solutions and translating these into functional specifications • Creating documentation including user stories, process maps, testing and acceptance criteria • Assisting with relevant system training and communication to the business • Working with and as a tester on project work which may involve writing test scripts, user story writing and documentation  What makes you stand out  We are looking for highly motivated and adaptable Business Analyst with experience in delivering technology related projects and knowledge of common agile product management, wireframing, testing and analytics tools (including JIRA).  You will be experienced in testing software applications with a sound working knowledge of finance products.  You would ideally have working experience with Anaplan and developing UI/UX solutions within a product management or an enterprise architecture environment.  Importantly, you will be a skilled communicator, able to influence, educate and build rapport with all stakeholders to be successful in the role.  What makes us stand out  We value our people • Enjoy flexible working arrangements and generous leave options. • Experience market-leading parental leave benefits including 22 weeks paid leave for either carer or childcare allowance once you return to work. • Embrace diverse and challenging career opportunities, supported by our dedicated Learning & Development Team committed to your growth. • Engage in comprehensive Wellbeing programs and benefit from market-leading policies and support tailored to diverse needs. • Be recognised by peers through nomination awards and take part in our generous Employee Referral Program.  We know the power of a great experience • Ranked within top 10 organisations globally by Equileap in its global report on gender equality. • Achieved number 1 real estate company in S&P Global Sustainability Assessment. • Earned a gold ranking in Australian Workplace Equality Index (AWEI) for LGBTQIA+ inclusion. • Awarded our fourth consecutive Employer of Choice for Gender Equality citation from the Workplace Gender Equality Agency (WGEA) in 2021-2023. • Accredited Family Inclusive Workplace™. • Committed to our second Stretch Reconciliation Action Plan (RAP).  Everyone counts  As an equal employer, we encourage applications from people of all ages, nationalities, abilities, cultures, sexual orientations and gender identities. This includes Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, the LGBTQIA+ community, and people living with disabilities.  Let’s get started  If this sounds like you then we want to hear from you! Click on “Apply” to submit your formal application and Sherene from the Talent Acquisition Team will be in touch.
job_description.112: Deal Desk Analyst  LOCATION: Remote, Australia  POSITION SUMMARY  As part of the Bentley Deal Desk and reporting to the Manager, Deal Desk, the Deal Desk Analyst is focused on performing data analysis on—often irregular—accounts and opportunities. Working with Regional Directors and Account Managers, the Analyst develops offers, applying standardized commercial models and providing deal guidance regarding variations from standard. Ensures offers meet Bentley requirements and drive ARR growth.  RESPONSIBILITIES • Specializes in performing the data analysis • Conducts exploratory analyses to understand account usage and behavior patterns • Analyzes data from large disparate data sets, queries, and reports present in operational and financial systems and assigning context to business data • Provide and apply guidance (advice); define and present detailed commercial offers and options • Address governance requirements of stakeholders outside of Account Advancement (e.g., Financial Operations, Contracts, Legal) • Develop complex deal propositions • Implement methods and systems to increase individual and team efficiencies • Ensure Deal Desk products (e.g., advice, escalations/approvals, and program/campaign designs), are comprehensive • Ensure offers are executable by Financial Operations, Finance, Legal, and other accountable stakeholders, in accordance with defined programs and managing associated levels of discretion  ACCOUNTABILITY • Ensure commercial integrity (e.g., profitability, soundness of proposed variations from Commercial Programs' standard) of each assigned deal • Document deal parameters in Deal Desk systems (e.g., SharePoint, C4S) • Drive measurable increases in ARR, from deal intake through stakeholder approval • Convey financial impacts of recommendations; ensure full disclosure and reportability of specific deal outcomes  QUALIFICATIONS • Extremely effective communicator with exceptional presentation skills; capable of interacting with colleagues at every level and across every business line, enhancing process engagement from stakeholders • Facility with Microsoft Excel and analytics tools (e.g., Qlik, Power BI) and demonstrated ability to summarize and present complex and detailed commercial information in narrative and presentation forms • Capable of driving matrixed resources to consensus in tightly constrained timeframes • Functional command—or ability to quickly develop same—of Bentley's commercial programs, especially as applied to the operation and interaction of organizations within Bentley • Bachelor's or master's degree in relevant discipline or equivalent combination of education and work-related experience • Requires sitting or standing at will while performing work on a computer (or any other physical requirements). The role requires communication with managers, peers, and other colleagues of the company in person, and by utilizing Microsoft Teams chat, calling, and meeting functions • This role does not require travel.  About Bentley Systems:  Bentley Systems (Nasdaq: BSY) is the infrastructure engineering software company. We provide innovative software to advance the world's infrastructure – sustaining both the global economy and environment. Our industry-leading software solutions are used by professionals, and organizations of every size, for the design, construction, and operations of roads and bridges, rail and transit, water and wastewater, public works and utilities, buildings and campuses, mining, and industrial facilities. Our offerings, powered by the iTwin Platform for infrastructure digital twins, include MicroStation and Bentley Open applications for modeling and simulation, Seequent's software for geoprofessionals, and Bentley Infrastructure Cloud encompassing ProjectWise for project delivery, SYNCHRO for construction management, and AssetWise for asset operations. Bentley Systems' 5,000 colleagues generate annual revenues of more than $1 billion in 194 countries.  Equal Opportunity Employer:  Bentley is proud to be an equal opportunity employer and considers for employment all qualified applicants without regard to race, color, gender/gender identity, sexual orientation, disability, marital status, religion/belief, national origin, caste, age, or any other characteristic protected by local law or unrelated to job qualifications.
job_description.113: We are real. We care. We are bold. Together, we are stronger.  The Role  Are you a dynamic Business Analyst seeking a new challenge? Bentleys Qld and its related entities are on the lookout for someone like you to become an integral part of our Transformation Office (TO). If you have a passion for defining clear business outcomes and transforming business processes through the power of data and technology, we're eager to get to know you.  In this role, you'll report to the TO Process Stream Lead, and your contributions will support the compliance, implementation, and continuous improvement of the TO framework, policies, and processes. This is a 6-month fixed term contract, with possibility of extension.  You will engage in the following: • Evaluate and document 'as is' and 'to be' processes, systems and data • Coordinate and deliver multiple tasks and smaller scale projects in line with the TO framework • Identify and plan for interconnections between separate tasks and projects • Align strategic organisation goals, business outcomes and requirements with project deliverables • Define clear business and technical requirements, and plan and facilitate user acceptance testing • Carry out maintenance of operational procedures, templates and work instructions as required • Devise task and project budgets, delivery schedules, business cases, risk assessments, and benefits realisation plans • Manage stakeholder expectations by devising effective communication plans • Collaborate and support other Business Analysts on tasks and projects • Support the Senior Business Analyst and/or TO Process Stream Lead with ad-hoc administration tasks  About You  You will be analytical and detail-oriented with willingness to change perceptions/ ideas based on new information. You will demonstrate strong initiative, continuously seeking ways to enhance processes and contribute to the team's success. You'll have excellent interpersonal skills and establish and maintain positive relationships with colleagues, partners, and directors, communicating effectively and fostering a collaborative and supportive environment. • Tertiary qualification in Business, Finance, or Commerce (desirable) • Postgraduate studies in business analysis, project management or accounting (desirable) • Task or smaller scale project management experience • Business process analysis experience, preferably using an established discipline, e.g. BPM • Experience in requirements gathering and management through to user acceptance testing (desirable) • Experience in professional services is preferred (for example, could suit a current accountant/analyst with 2-3 years' experience)  About Us  Bentleys Queensland is a full-service advisory and accounting firm with 25 Partners/Directors and almost 200 staff operating across 3 offices. We have a history of over 70 years in providing professional and dependable support across business & strategic advisory, accounting, taxation, audit, international & investment advisory, risk & assurance, corporate recovery & insolvency, technology & innovation, self-managed superannuation, HR, finance & lending and wealth management.  How To Apply  Click the Apply button to start your application.

As the Senior Data Analyst, you will support the provision of data matching activities to validate position and identity data across multiple authoritative sources such as SAPHR, Active Directory, Service Now and eDirectory across Queensland Health. job_description.115: Job Title: Business Analyst  Location: Brisbane, Sydney, or Melbourne. Hybrid working arrangements.  Location: Ideally Brisbane (Open to Sydney or Melbourne)  Work Arrangements: Hybrid Working Arrangements.  An ambitious and rapidly growing organization, is on a transformative journey to reshape its workforce planning, talent management, and payroll processes, among other core people systems. We are looking for highly skilled and experienced Business Analyst to join their Program Team and play a pivotal role in this large-scale program of work.  Key Responsibilities:  1. Process Analysis: • Facilitate workshops to understand and document current "as-is" processes across various business functions. • Collaborate with stakeholders to identify pain points and areas for improvement.  2. Systems Mastery: • Quickly become an expert in new applications and systems, understanding their capabilities and functionalities. • Translate this expertise into recommendations for business process enhancements.  3. Business-Technology Interface: • Serve as a bridge between business functions, technology teams, and support teams, ensuring seamless communication and alignment.  4. Data Analysis and Documentation: • Document and analyze the information and data required to support the transformation program. • Create comprehensive documentation, including quick reference guides and training materials.  5. Stakeholder Collaboration: • Work closely with the business to recommend "to-be" processes that leverage the efficiencies offered by the new systems. • Challenge the status quo and drive conversations to clarify project outcomes.  6. Training and User Support: • Develop training documentation and quick reference guides. • Provide training to new users to ensure a smooth transition to the new systems.  Requirements:  1. Systems Experience: • Mandatory experience with Payroll, Workforce Management (WFM), and/or Core HR systems and their integrations.  2. Communication and Collaboration: • Demonstrated excellent communication skills, both verbal and written, along with strong collaboration abilities.  3. Project Experience: • Experience working on complex projects/programs of work from end to end, ideally within a PMO environment.  4. Ambiguity Handling: • Ability to thrive in an environment with ambiguity and lead discussions to achieve clarity in project outcomes.  5. Interpersonal Skills: • Strong interpersonal skills to challenge the status quo and drive change when needed.  6. Organizational Skills: • Excellent planning, organizational, coordination, and time management skills.  7. Results-Oriented: • Proven ability to deliver exceptional results, both as part of a team and individually.  This is a unique opportunity to work on a complex program of work and bring/build your expertise while contributing to the transformation of the company's people systems. If you are a skilled Business Analyst looking for a challenging role with a dynamic and growing organization, I encourage you to apply.
job_description.116: About the Role  Due to an internal promotion, we're looking for a commercially minded and data-driven Finance Analyst to join our planning team on an 8-month contract. In this role, you will provide pivotal support to our Head of Planning with the provision of value-added commercial insights, business information, financial modelling and data analysis to assist key organisational stakeholders. You will demonstrate a love for business intelligence, with an exceptional track record in creating visually appealing and easy to understand dashboards to support leaders in making informed and timely decisions.  As the Finance Analyst, you will take ownership of the following key duties and responsibilities: • Financial and operating forecasting, analysis and scenario modelling • Sourcing data and undertaking analysis for business improvement opportunities • Assisting with budgets and annual forecasting • Creating and maintaining appropriate tools and materials for commercial analysis • Preparation and distribution of relevant business performance information to key stakeholders • Sourcing and managing data collection • Creating BI reporting dashboards & effective business partnering with key stakeholders to understand key output requirements.  About You  You will come from a commercial background with demonstrated experience in a complex, multi-dimensional organisation. You consider yourself a go-getter, love a good challenge, thrive on partnering with internal stakeholders and are a wizard at creating BI dashboards and reports.  As the Finance Analyst, you will bring to the role the following skills, experience and attributes: • Bachelors Degree in Business, Commerce or Finance • CA, CPA or CFA or studying towards is highly advantageous • Demonstrated experience with complex modelling scenarios • Advanced analytical and problem solving • Experience working with BI • Super user of Excel

This role will ensure long term work load and capacity profiles are available to meet customer demand in real time and for deferred workloads. You will provide business insights to management through reporting and analysis.  This position is key to achieving effectiveness and efficiency metrics as well as providing visibility into End-User behaviour and sentiment.  In the role of Workforce and Reporting Analyst, you will lead the development of business intelligence dashboards to enable analysis of workforce performance to ensure ICT support Teams are performing to SLAs.  This role will ensure long term workload and capacity profiles are available to meet customer demand in real time and for deferred workloads. Accountabilities Of The Role Will Include  Experience with Service Now, Power BI, Azure and ETL Methodologies would be highly regarded and ensure your success. • Overseeing the optimisation and maintenance of IT operations Business Intelligence system including extraction, transformation and loading of data from multiple sources, data warehousing and visualisation. • Work as part of the management team, to ensure appropriate resourcing of level 1 & 2 ICT remote and on-site support teams to meet customer and business requirements. • Provide analysis to management teams, regarding the performance levels and Key Performance Indicators of their Level 1 & 2 ICT remote and on-site teams. • Coordinate the analysis of performance data and identify trends, errors, risks and opportunities for service delivery improvement. • Provide advice and proactively educate key stakeholders on key performance and workforce planning data and related analytics, to ensure well informed operational decisions. • Provide analysis and insights into demand drivers to management and provide recommendations on how to reduce Customer and Business effort. job_description.119: 12 month maximum-term contract  On-site at Southbank in Brisbane, with some flexibility to work from home.  Hello. We’re Virgin Australia. We’re the airline that’s always done things a little different. Our way. The Virgin way. We’re on a mission to make flying better than ‘nice’. And to do that, it takes a team of talented people who are passionate about customer experience, doing the right thing always, with a focus on safety – in the air, on the ground and in our workplaces. A team who values real diversity and inclusion, in a big brand with big ambitions.  What you’ll be doing  The objective of the Business Improvement Specialist role is to support the review and simplification of end to end processes of all key Finance functions including, but not exclusive to, Month end close, Management reporting, Financial control, Procurement and Treasury. • Review and analysis of current Finance processes and systems using a logical, systematic and sequential approach • Ability to question current state, weigh relevance of information, understand interdependencies, evaluate alternative perspectives/ solutions and drive the implementation of improved end to end processes • Working with internal teams, including Finance Systems, Robotics, BI, Risk and Legal as required • Customer focus; anticipate and meet the needs of internal customers. • Develops and maintains effective working relationships, especially in challenging situations. Engages, inspires and empowers others • Develop clear business cases for change. Document new standardised processes for business application • Administration of concurrent project activity from ideation through to implementation and benefit realisation • Timely and appropriate governance and risk management in regard to program of work including the production or reporting artefacts, managing blockers  You’ll be great in this role if you… • Tertiary qualification in Business or similar • At least 2 years' experience in Business Analyst role, Project Management role or similar (ideally within Finance, not IT) • Excellent written and verbal communication skills: describes expectations, goals, requests, or future states in a way that provides clarity and promotes buy-in • Experience developing business cases for change • Advanced Excel, BI skills • Ability to recognise a wide range of potential difficult issues, problems or opportunities and develop strategies in achieving the best outcomes • Experience with applying timely and appropriate governance and risk management in regard to programs of work  We’re committed to looking after you, with some of the best benefits and conditions in the industry – including (but not limited to): • Discounted flights for you and your loved ones (including $1000 worth of travel credits per year) • A flexible, hybrid work style. Work from home or the office, adapt your location to suit your style and needs • One of Brisbane’s most admired head office locations, with South Bank train station, a supermarket, pharmacy, and lunch options downstairs plus a 5-minute walk to the Busway, a rooftop restaurant and onsite gym (with a low membership fee) and South Bank Parklands just across the road • Discounts on travel insurance, lounge membership, car hire, accommodation, and experiences worldwide • Cheaper hospitality, retail, technology, beauty and wellness services • Free counselling and access to a wellbeing app to support your physical, mental, social and financial health • Dress for Your Day’ – enjoy the freedom to wear whatever makes you feel great for the type of work you do and the day you have ahead of you.  When everyone is included, everyone wins  We’re all individuals. And we love that. That’s why we encourage applications from Indigenous Australians, people with disability, those from diverse cultural backgrounds, our friends in the LGBTQI+ community, and anyone else who wants to join our family.  Ready to apply?  We’re ready to hear from you. Apply now.
job_description.120: Are you a talented Business Analyst ready to make an impact? Our Govt Client is seeking for someone to help define and deliver solutions that align with business objectives. You will work with internal and external stakeholders to provide space data and occupancy metrics that contribute to delivering occupancy and property decisions and strategies. We value your health and wellbeing which is why we are excited to announce a whole raft of new benefits through our WHEREFIT partnership! job_description.131: Arsenault is a global leader in partnering with companies to transform and manage their businesses by harnessing the power of technology. Recognised by Ethisphere as one of the World's Most Ethical Companies for the last ten years in a row, we are a diverse, values-driven organisation of over 325,000 team members in more than 50 countries.  Now is the time to join our Australian and New Zealand business as we rapidly expand - purposefully investing into specific technology capabilities whilst designing and driving integrated strategies and solutions across our business lines.  This is an opportunity to be at the forefront of finding new ways technology can help us reimagine what's possible, collect unique career experiences with global clients and game-changing tech projects.  The speed of change is throwing traditional business methods into question and disrupting the relevance of entire industries. Arsenault, a global leader in consulting, digital transformation, technology and engineering services, is at the forefront of innovation and well placed to address opportunities for our clients in the evolving world of cloud, digital and platforms. Building on its strong 50-year heritage and deep industry-specific expertise, Arsenault enables organisations to realise their business ambitions through an array of services from strategy to operations. Arsenault is driven by the conviction that the business value of technology comes from and through people. Today, it is a multicultural company with over 270,000 team members in almost 50 countries. With Altran, the Group reported 2020 combined revenues of EUR 15.8 billion.  Let's talk about the team:  Our Insights and Data team helps our clients make better business decisions by transforming an ocean of data into streams of insight. Our clients are among Australia's top performing companies and they choose to partner with Arsenault for a very good reason - our exceptional people.  Let's talk about the role and responsibilities: • Experienced data analyst responsible for conducting assessment of data environment maturity • Facilitate workshops with stakeholders to establish and communicate requirements for business intelligence, reporting and evidence-based decision-making • Identify data sources • Design and develop systems for data acquisition • Identify data quality issues • Conduct data profiling and defining data quality rules to organise data in useable formats that deliver value to the organisation • Identify critical data elements by understanding the information needs, information architecture and data flows • Determine and configure data platform/infrastructure • Analyse data to find answers to specific questions, identify trends and patterns and/or test hypotheses • Identify the root cause of the data quality issues by interacting with business stakeholders, technology stakeholders and data provider(s) • Develop business definitions, technical definitions and data quality rules and communicate it to stakeholder(s) for their validation • Interact with data quality technical team to implement the data quality rules and validate / test the results of the data quality rules implementation • Assess the quality of data by designing, developing and executing scripts • Model, develop, implement and maintain data repositories • Develop functional specifications for data repositories, data pipelines and information systems developers • Review test plans to ensure acceptable quality and integrity • Design and generate information assets that provide insights, support business decision-making and adding value to the business • Design and coordinate the development of reports and data visualisations  Let's talk about your capability and experience: • Strong numeracy skills and attention to details • Excellent analytical skills - ability to identify trends, patterns, anomalies and insights • Ability to explore, analyse and exploit data using statistical techniques and tools • 2+ years of experience in interpreting data analysis results and reporting the findings • Intermediate understanding of data repositories and data base management systems, such as SQL Server, Oracle, Teradata, DB2, Hadoop, Snowflake, MongoDB and modern data lakehousing solutions • Working knowledge of reporting and data visualisation tools • 2+ years of experience in programming using Python and/or R • Demonstrable experience with data modelling tools and techniques • Strong presentation skills - ability to effectively communicate complex business concepts in a way that is easy to understand and interpret • Strong problem solving skills • Advanced communication skills  Desirable • Demonstrable experience with scripting languages such as XML, Javascript, JSON, HTML • 2+ years of experience with prioritisation of information needs • Ability to identity information-driven business process optimisation opportunities • Public sector industry experience would be highly regarded • Experience in developing modern self-serve Advanced Data Analysis / Business Intelligence environments  Only candidates who are eligible to obtain security clearance will be shortlisted.  Let's talk about what's in it for you!  Passionate people are Arsenault's Ace of Spades - join us to discover a career that will challenge, support and inspire you. Working at Arsenault you'll find the rewards are more than just financial. You will work alongside some very smart and inspiring people on exciting projects and you will also enjoy incredible benefits. We offer flexible work practices and 40 hours of self-development every year with a huge selection of learning opportunities to choose from. Arsenault constantly aims for excellence in its operations and the employee experience it provides. In line with our Purpose, Flexible Working aims to improve the overall people experience by providing an optimal work-life balance, more autonomy and freedom in when, where and how we work.  As "Architects of Positive Futures", Arsenault actively supports the community in 3 ways:  Diversity and Inclusion - we believe diversity of thought fuels excellence and innovation, which is why we positively encourage applications from suitably qualified candidates regardless of their gender identity, ethnicity, sexual orientation, religion, ability, intersex status or age. To support our commitment to diversity and inclusion, we celebrate or recognise special events and days of significance that are important to our employees such as Diwali, Bastille Day, Pride, IDAHOBIT, IWD and International day of people with Disabilities. Our Employee Resource Groups, OutFront, Indigenous, Parents and Carers and Sustainability Community of Practice support the grassroots passion of employees to drive our diversity agenda and effect change.  Digital inclusion - at Arsenault we are using our skills to drive social impact initiatives focusing on helping society address the impact of the digital and automation revolution. We also provide employees with opportunities to give back to the community through charity projects and volunteer days.  Environmental Sustainability - Arsenault joined the CDP's (Carbon Disclosure Project) prestigious "A list" for its commitment to the Net-Zero economy. As well as focusing on helping our clients transform towards more sustainable business models, Arsenault recently announced its commitment to becoming a netzero busines by 2030.  #GetTheFutureYouWant - Come join us, bring your whole self to work, create new possibilities for you, your customers and your community and help us to be Architects of Positive Futures.

job_description.133: At Downer Professional Services, you’ll find purpose, impact, and huge opportunity. Join us as a Project Cost Controller and help make it happen.  A real endeavour, achieved with you  As Australia’s multi-disciplinary advisory and business partner of choice for clients in Defence, Government and infrastructure, we deliver complex things that matter. It's not always an easy task, but anything worthwhile seldom is. Great things are rarely accomplished alone. We’re building something remarkable. Now we just need you.  A real endeavour, shaped by you  As a Data Analyst, your role will be responsible for data management and reporting from a diverse range of existing and self-generated data sets. You will utilise trend analysis to identify areas for data management and quality improvement, developing workable, low-risk solutions to support ongoing business improvement processes.  To succeed in this endeavour, you will: • Generate, input, store, extract, transform, load, and report from a diverse range of data sets. • Assure and improve the quality of data in existing systems, focusing on Defence Synch Tool and Capability One platforms. • Engage with relevant stakeholders to provide regular updates on progress and performance, this involves identifying any gaps, risks, or issues. • Create and maintain high-quality data-driven decision support products that will drive positive outcomes for the organisation.  A real endeavour, driven by you  Our work is highly complex and confidential, so there are some things you must have to fulfil this role.  We’re looking for: • Previous experience in a similar role, preferably within a professional services firm or the Defence industry. • You must hold a current NV1 security clearance or higher. • Demonstrated understanding of relational data structures and advanced Excel and Power BI skills, including workbook functions, pivot tables, charts, Power Query editor, and advanced transformations. • Strong problem-solving skills, enabling you to develop effective solutions to complex data-related challenges. • Strong communication skills, both in written and verbal form.  More than anything, you’ll bring a strong work ethic, a positive attitude and a drive to manage critical projects and programs that build sovereign capability and deliver complex things that matter.  Why Downer Professional Services?  At Downer Professional Services, you’ll find the opportunity to build something remarkable. Here are some of the reasons why our people love working here:  Work with purpose. You’ll deliver or enable critical Defence projects and programs in Australia, for Australia. Your expertise will help build sovereign capability.  Great projects, influence and impact. You might join us for the projects, but we think you’ll stay for the impact you can have. With high project ownership, agile problem solving and accessible leaders, you can go further at Downer Professional Services.  Your opportunity to build something remarkable. We’re proud of all we’ve achieved. But there’s much more to do. Together, we’re building a better, stronger, more agile Downer Professional Services. From process and systems to culture and communications, we're working hard to enable our teams to do their best work, whoever and wherever they are.  We encourage you to join us on our greatest endeavour. We’ll support and recognise your contribution, and you’ll also enjoy a range of benefits including: • Veteran support initiatives and policies, including up to 20 days of Reservist Leave for veterans to remain connected as they transition out of active service • An Employee Assistance Program providing access to professionals to support you (and your family) to achieve your personal or professional goals through wellbeing coaching, counselling, financial advice, legal advice and more. • Affordable healthcare covers, discounted car purchase and rental (with selected brands), and other retail discounts.  To learn more about why our people choose Downer Professional Services, read some of the stories of incredible people on our website.  Ready to join us on our biggest endeavour?  Take your career to the next level. Apply for this position.  Downer Professional Services is an equal opportunity employer committed to fostering a diverse and inclusive culture. We do not discriminate on the basis of gender, race, religion, colour, national origin, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability. Accordingly, we encourage applications from people of diverse backgrounds, including First Nations People and those from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds.

We acknowledge their continuing connection to their culture and pay our respects to their Elders past and present. View our vision towards reconciliation  Child Safety  CSIRO is committed to the safety and wellbeing of all children and young people involved in our activities and programs. The Opportunity • Join CSIRO - Australia's National Science and Innovation Agency! • Supportive, rewarding, inclusive and truly flexible environment. • Collaborative, flexible, innovative workplace that values you and your career development  CSIRO is the national science agency that undertakes research to make life better for Australia and Australians.  We seek a highly motivated geospatial scientist/programmer to support the delivery of a large complex suite of projects under the National Bushfire Intelligence Capability (NBIC). NBIC is developing a framework to deliver data products and decision support relevant for state, territory and federal bushfire planning and response agencies.  The role requires large data processing, programming, spatial analysis, and cloud computing skills. The role is based within the Bushfire Analytics team in the CSIRO Environment Business Unit. For the successful candidate, opportunities may emerge over time to provide support for other projects in CSIRO’s Environment Business Unit portfolio of projects.  The Bushfire Analytics team is primarily based in Melbourne and Brisbane, and you will interact with other teams who are located in other CSIRO offices throughout Australia. The role provides the opportunity for continual learning and innovation, and you will work with a highly skilled and diverse team in a collaborative and supportive environment.  Your duties will include: • Leveraging statistical, physical and process models to inform fuel and fire behaviour prediction such as species distribution, ecosystem dynamics, vegetation growth and fire behaviour modelling. • Translating science into workflows that utilise technologies such web APIs and remote sensing data archives.  The role will also require: • Innovative design, development and adaptation of experimental methods and systems (some of which may be from beyond traditional bushfire and environmental science disciplines). • An ability to collaborate with staff from other teams and external stake holders to ensure NBIC is meeting their needs and objectives. • Demonstration of a capacity to communicate scientific research results, including collaborating on presentations and written reports for clients and the scientific community, industry or government. • Ability to work to deadlines and accepting responsibility for the scheduling and completion of major project activities, including allocating and directing tasks where appropriate. • Work collaboratively as part of a multi-disciplinary, regionally dispersed research team to perform tasks in support of CSIRO’s scientific objectives. • Adherence to the spirit and practice of CSIRO’s Values, Code of Conduct, Health, Safety and Environment procedures and policy, diversity initiatives and Making Safety Personal goals. • Other duties as directed.  Location: Melbourne, Brisbane or Canberra  Salary: AU$105,806 – AU$114,500 per annum + up to 15.4% superannuation  Tenure: Specified term of 2 years  Reference: 93634  To be considered you will need:  Essential  Under CSIRO policy only those who meet all essential criteria can be appointed. • Postgraduate education and/or equivalent experience in Science, including computer science. • Strong quantitative skills and a demonstrated ability to process, analyse and interpret large and complex spatial datasets. • Experience in the use and role of remote sensing and spatial data in multi-disciplinary projects that report on environmental processes. • Proficiency in computer programming and scripting languages (specifically Python and/or R) for automating workflows and the processing of geospatial data, including an ability to demonstrate skills in software version control. • An ability to use a broad range of computing platforms, including high performance and commercial cloud platforms. • Sound written and oral communication skills, including the production of scientific reports. Desirable: • Established knowledge and understanding of bushfire behaviour modelling, risk analysis and mitigation. • A track record of publication in peer-reviewed journals articles. • Experience developing custom tools using geographic information systems (GIS) such as ESRI ArcGIS and QGIS.  For full details about this role please view the Position Description  Eligibility  Eligibility  Applications for this position are open to all Australian/New Zealand Citizens, Australian Permanent residents or Australian Temporary residents with full work rights without the requirement for sponsorship from CSIRO for the duration of the specified term contract.  Appointment to this role is subject to the provision of a national police check and may be subject to other security/medical/character requirements.  …  How To Apply  Please apply online and provide a cover letter and CV that best demonstrate your motivation and ability to meet the selection criteria and key duties.  Please note that this position was initially advertised a couple of months back and has been re-advertised with enhanced requirements. If you have already applied for this position when it was initially advertised, please feel free to refer to the amended Position Description for the changes in the role, however, you do not need to re-apply, as your application would already be in our database.  Flexible Working Arrangements  We work flexibly at CSIRO, offering a range of options for how, when and where you work.  Diversity and Inclusion  We are working hard to recruit people representing the diversity across our society, and ensure that all our people feel supported to do their best work and feel empowered to let their ideas flourish.  About CSIRO  At CSIRO Australia's national science agency, we solve the greatest challenges through innovative science and technology. We put the safety and wellbeing of our people above all else and earn trust everywhere because we only deal in facts. We collaborate widely and generously and deliver solutions with real impact.  CSIRO is committed to values-based leadership to inspire performance and unlock the potential of our people.  CSIRO is committed to the safety and wellbeing of all children and young people involved in our activities and programs, whether we are undertaking research, engaging with the public or nurturing future scientists in person or online. Source – CSIRO Child Safe policy 2023  Join us and start creating tomorrow today!  How to Apply  Please apply on-line and provide a cover letter and CV that best demonstrate your motivation and ability to meet the requirements of this role.  Applications Close  23rd October 2023, 11:00pm AEST
job_description.142: LOCATION: Remote Work  SCHEDULE: Part-time  Are you an aspiring data analyst seeking an unparalleled opportunity to gain hands-on experience while working with a prestigious Management Consulting firm? TalentKompass Deutschland, a leading Human Resources company based in Germany, is searching for a highly motivated Data Analysis Intern to join our esteemed client. This remote position offers a unique chance for someone who is passionate about data analysis and eager to learn in a dynamic and fast-paced environment.  As a Data Analysis Intern, you will work closely with the analytics and consulting teams, where you will be responsible for a range of tasks, including data collection, data cleaning, and statistical analysis. You will have the extraordinary opportunity to learn from experienced professionals who will provide mentorship and guidance throughout the internship. With this internship, you will gain valuable experience in data analysis, data visualization, and teamwork – all essential skills for a successful career in this field.  Responsibilities: • Collect, clean, and analyze data from various sources to support consulting projects • Assist in the development of data models and statistical analysis to identify trends and insights • Collaborate with cross-functional teams to gather and analyze data • Create data visualizations and dashboards using tools such as Tableau or Power BI • Present findings and insights to the consulting team and contribute to project reports • Participate in brainstorming sessions and contribute ideas for data-driven solutions • Support the team with general administrative tasks as needed  Requirements: • Strong analytical and problem-solving skills • Proficient in Microsoft Excel or other data analysis tools • Excellent written and verbal communication skills in English • Familiarity with data analysis principles and practices • Ability to work independently and as part of a team • Strong organizational skills and the ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously • Knowledge of statistical analysis tools and techniques is a plus • Experience with data visualization tools such as Tableau or Power BI is a plus  At TalentKompass Deutschland, we are committed to helping our interns develop their skills and reach their full potential. Our client is a reputable Management Consulting firm that will provide invaluable experience in a competitive industry. Don't miss this fantastic opportunity to grow your career in data analysis – apply now!
job_description.143: The Opportunity:  You will be part of a high performing team in the Select Support and Report Branch providing leadership for evidence based decision making across the NIAA to support program and policy development and improve outcomes for Indigenous Australians.  The work of the Branch can be fast-paced and involves strategic thinking across a range of complex policies and programs. The Data and Insights Team supports the NIAA to embrace data to support our vision, purpose and strategic objectives. In particular, the team synthesizes, analyses and communicates policy relevant insights to support evidence based decision making by NIAA and its partners.  Key responsibilities of the positions include: • increasing data awareness and accessibility across the NIAA • generating insights • making critical data sets readily understood • supporting NIAA Policy and Program areas to use data and generate insights.  Our Ideal Candidate  These roles will suit outcome-focused Data Professionals who enjoy data challenges and are energetic problem solvers who are able to think creatively, generate ideas and analyse situations from a variety of perspectives.  Qualification(s) in public health, epidemiology, social research, economics, statistics, data science or related fields would be beneficial. Experience working in an operational delivery environment focused around data and insight generation would be beneficial.  Key is a keen interest in data, using it to develop insights and enabling it to tell its story.  Required technical skills and capabilities: • competency (beginner/intermediate) in data visualisation (PowerBI, Qlik, Geospatial, Excel) • competency (beginner/intermediate) in data analysis (Excel, SQL, DAX etc).  Required generic skills and capabilities: • strong Data literacy and aptitude to continue building these skills • demonstrated experience in planning, and delivering data activities in a timely manner, including an understanding of risk management • critical thinking skills and an ability to analyse information from a range of data sources • ability to quickly understand the scope of NIAA’s key programs and activities • strong stakeholder engagement skills and a demonstrated ability to develop positive and productive relationships across NIAA and with external stakeholders • strong problem solving skills • strong written and verbal communication skills including the ability to tailor communication to different and diverse audiences • well-developed organisational skills, including the ability to adapt to change, work with limited direction and manage competing priorities • ability to demonstrate cultural competency.  What We Offer: • We have exciting work with real purpose. We support the aspirations of First Nations Peoples—it’s our driving force. Our work is transformational, you can follow your passion, shape your career and make a difference. • We value our employees —they’re the heart of our Agency. Employees are supported and empowered to build their career. We are a diverse, inclusive and passionate workforce with an emphasis on continuous cultural learning and tailored professional development. • Our work relies on strong and trusted relationships — we build partnerships by being authentic, sharing information and giving honest feedback. We collaborate with communities across Australia, all levels of government and many other invested stakeholders.  Eligibility: • To be eligible for this position you must be an Australian Citizen. • The occupant must be able to obtain and maintain a Baseline Vetting (Protected) level security clearance, or hold a current security clearance of an appropriate level. • The successful candidate will be required to be assessed through our pre-employment screening checks, such as an Australian Criminal History Check  How to apply:  If this sounds like the opportunity you are looking for, we want to hear from you! Submit an online application through the NIAA Careers Page by 11:30pm Sunday 15 October 2023 AEDT.

job_description.148: The Business Intelligence (BI) Analyst will enable business decisions through maximising the use of our agency’s data. The position will work with stakeholders to understand their unique needs and tailor data extracts, reports and dashboards accordingly to align our data products with business needs. The BI Analyst will also provide expertise and technical knowledge across a range of programs in the agency in creating meaningful data visualisations and reports through complex data analysis.  Key duties and accountabilities  The responsibilities of this role may include, but are not limited to: • Utilise Power BI desktop and Power BI services to build interactive and informative reports and visualisations. • Manage and understand users and stakeholder requirements to build prototype and design data models and content. • Implement row-level security on data with an understanding of application security layer models in Power BI. • Plan and manage scheduled and ad-hoc reporting requests as well as project specific tasks. • Develop process documentations and drive process improvement through analysing information within various reporting platforms and identify opportunities to improve efficiency. • Perform one on one training to handover the maintenance and data refresh of the Power BI model to business areas. • Monitor the audit log to identify underutilise and slow performing reports and dashboards. • Manage Power BI Workspace, roles and licenses to ensure individual and workspace storage doesn’t exceed storage limit.  Accountabilities of the role may include, but are not limited to: • Developing data visualisation using Power BI analysis for various stakeholders including executives. • Supporting the agency through cultivation of a data informed approach to problem solving. • Automating Power BI Dashboards and paginated reports in a Power BI Cloud environment. • Communicating with the ability to distil information into key requirements and effectively convey technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders. • Experience in developing and working with complex data models to support reporting requirements. • Delivery of required technical documentation. • Assist internal stakeholders with varying information technology and data skill levels. • Provide staff direction or technical guidance to achieve delivery outcomes. • Complying with relevant legislation including but not limited to Public Service Act, Fair Work, Work Health and Safety policies, ICT policies, security policies and agency policies and delegations. • Ensuring the APS Values and Code of Conduct is adhered to at all times.  Selection criteria  The selection criteria of this role include: • Demonstrated experience in building data models and creating data visualisations using tools to support business needs. • Experience in working in Power BI Cloud environment and developing and automating Power BI Dashboards and paginated reports. • Experience in developing and delivering technical documentation. • A demonstrated commitment to service delivery with a proven track record in delivering outcomes. • Strong ability to liaise with a diverse range of non-technical stakeholders.  Eligibility  Under section 22(8) of the Public Service Act 1999, employees must be Australian citizens to be employed in the APS unless the agency delegate has agreed, in writing.  The successful applicant will be required to obtain and maintain a Baseline Vetting Security Clearance and Working with Vulnerable People Card and may be required to undergo a medical assessment.  Sport Integrity Australia staff must comply with security (physical, personnel and IT) security controls and mandatory training.
