job_description.153: About the role  Our Federal government client is working on a demonstration project basis with five key projects to design the end to end process of unit mapping, to continually refine the data science model, and to generate insights on the potential use of mapping outputs. The outputs of models are large, for example one university with approximately 3,000 units can have an output of approximately 30,000 skills mapped. Validation of outputs is a critical part of the mapping process to produce a model and results that are highly accurate.  This role has fully remote working arrangements available.  Key responsibilities • Developing of a comprehensive internal and external validation process for very large data sets, to support improvement of data science models, and the quality of output data sent to partners. This may require an ensemble of approaches, for example statistical sampling, manual and automated approaches to validation. • Managing internal validation processes before outputs are sent to project partners. • Working closely with the data science team to provide feedback for the mapping model development. • Analysing complex model outputs, to derive valuable insights for reporting to project partners, including visualisation techniques. • Providing advice to technical services on interface design for a validation application for project partners.  Skills and experience • Demonstrated experience in data analysis and process design, to create replicable data validation processes to improve data output quality. • Excellent analytical skills, with strong attention to detail, and the ability to synthesise and critically analyse large volumes of structured and unstructured data. • Strong skills and experience in data management, in particular how data can be effectively structured, analysed, presented and communicated, to achieve high-quality outcomes. • Excellent communication skills, including the ability to effectively communicate key data insights visually and in written form to a range of diverse stakeholders. • Well-developed interpersonal skills, including the ability to work effectively in a multidisciplinary setting. • Ability to work in dynamic, highly collaborative environment, and online team setting, using a pro-active, results-oriented approach  Desirable criteria • Experience in R Shiny, Python, SQL, anduser experience design. • Understanding of, and experience working with tertiary education (HE and/or VET) and/or occupation and labour market data. • Understanding and experience in data science, or related fields. • Experience operating in a policy environment.  Contact details  For a confidential chat, please contact Jinal on 0473 567 486 or via email at jinal@exclaim-it.com.au and we would be more than happy to provide you with additional information and assist in the application process.
job_description.154: Vacancy for Senior Data Analyst at National Archives of Australia  Vacancy for Senior Data Analyst at National Archives of Australia  29 September 2021 Full-Time  The Digital Archives Innovation and Research (DAIR) section is leading a transformative program to assist the National Archives achieve its vision of being a world leading archive in the digital age.  This includes maintaining awareness of emerging developments in digital archival practice, engaging with the local and international digital archiving community, developing policies to support long-term preservation of and access to digital material, supporting the implementation of archival management systems and building digital archiving capability within the organisation.  The DAIR is responsible for ensuring the National Archives preserves digital information by researching, designing and implementing contemporary digital archiving techniques. The DAIR section is seeking applications to fill to role of Senior Data Analyst.  The role will research and undertake data analysis and build data visualisations to inform decision making and bring data to life for end users.  The role will also scope and develop regular reports for key business functions and prepare written reports, infographics and presentations detailing the findings and analysis.  The role offers a unique opportunity to develop new insights into the use and management of National Archives' collection spanning 40 million items, including records about military service, immigration, First Australians and much more. #J-18808-Ljbffr

job_description.156: If we inspire you to do the work you love, will you still call it work?  What's in it for you? We are seeking a Data Analyst to join our EY Data and Analytics team ideally in our Melbourne and Sydney offices but can also be based in any of the major Australian cities. Working with a number of high profile clients this role is offered on a flexible, full-time basis.  You will help shape, change, and deliver a data management roadmap to improve and enhance the value and re-usability of data, through modern and evolving data management practices and frameworks.  As a Data Analyst, you will support our clients in defining and implementing a data journey aligned with their strategic objectives, you will work with a diverse range of stakeholders and data teams to uplift the current data quality management capabilities of a number of different high profile client groups.  What we're looking for: Translating business questions to data and analysis requirements; carry out analysis, visualization and presentation. Performing ad-hoc analysis to solve business problems and support decisions. Design and build data products, such as Power BI dashboards, including defining the data models. Surfacing and sharing insights, typically from internal corporate data, using a dashboard. Run human centred design sessions with end-users. Communicating and influencing stakeholders. Coaching non-data experts how to use data.  Skills and attributes for success: Experience in a hands-on role interpreting and telling stories with data. Curious and business outcome focused with an ability to break down a complex problem and work out how to solve it. Evidence of numerical and technical aptitude strong collaboration skills having worked with business stakeholders at different levels of seniority. Comfortable working across a wide range of data sets and systems. Expertise in cleansing, combining and processing data. Have knowledge of SQL, with knowledge of Python an advantage. Familiarity with Power BI and ideally data manipulation tools (e.g. Alteryx and Daraiku).  The preferred applicant will be subject to employment screening by EY or by their external third party provider. Regarding this role, the minimum salary is $90,000 including 11% superannuation.

job_description.158: The Forensic Technology Services Team  Clayton Utz is a leading Australian top tier law firm. Our Forensic & Technology Services (FTS) practice group is one of Australia's fastest growing forensic practices and is an integral and thriving part of the firm. Rapid success and growth enables us to engage individuals who are seeking an opportunity to further drive the FTS practice, and be a part of our market leading projects moving forward.  The role  The Forensic Technology Services (FTS) team is seeking driven Consultants and Senior Consultants to be based in our Sydney or Canberra offices. The role requires the use of data analytics and visualisation technology to deliver bespoke analytical solutions and support forensic investigation and quantification engagements.  Key Responsibilities • Work with Legal and FTS team members on large-scale confidential legal and forensic matters • Consult with multiple stakeholders and develop bespoke data analytics procedures and solutions. • Undertake extensive analytical reviews of client data to produce insights that will assist our clients including but not limited to: • quantification and population identification for class actions, criminal, and civil matters • development of AI-driven solutions for legal issues such as obligations management, wage underpayments, M&A due diligence, and others • use a range of tools including cloud, on-prem, visualisation, analytics, and programming languages • build alongside an industry-leading large eDiscovery practice using globally recognised solutions • Support senior team members in the preparation and presentation of client deliverables in a clear, structured manner. • Work in cross-functional teams with other FTS team members and lawyers from practice groups across the firm. • Proactively manage own workload, meet set KPIs and accurately record time spent on tasks.  Skills & Experience  To be successful in this role, you will have some experience with a broad background ideally within data manipulation and analytics. You will have; • Tertiary qualifications that include relevant components of Information Science, Actuarial, Statistics, Mathematics or equivalent work experience. • Excellent skills querying data using tools including SQL, Python and/or R, and presenting results through visualisation tools such as Tableau or PowerBI. • A demonstrated ability to clearly and concisely present data, conclusions, and recommendations that is easily understandable by a variety of audiences. • Strong focus on accuracy and integrity of data analytics results. • Strong stakeholder management and project delivery disciplines. • Effective written and verbal communication skills and an ability to communicate with impact to both internal and external clients and staff. • A team player with strong time and project management skills. • Experience with legal or regulatory or risk issues is a bonus  In addition to this, we're looking for a resilient, self-starter. Someone who is able to work autonomously and is focused on attention to detail and providing an outstanding service to their clients.  Benefits • Be part of a growing and energetic team that offers genuine career opportunities • Flexible working arrangements including hybrid office and work from home • Access to the right industry standard tool to conduct your work the way you like to work • The opportunity to apply your skills in a legal environment with critical matters and learn new perspectives from our legal teams; • Work with a diverse team skilled in various disciplines • Generous bonus structure and other perks!  How to Apply?  We prefer to work directly with candidates, if you are interested in this role, please click the ‘Apply’ button or contact the consultant, details below, for more information. Clayton Utz is an inclusive employer that supports flexible work arrangements, please feel free to discuss your flexibility needs with the recruiter for this role.  Consultant Contact Details  Carissa Bartels, (02) 9353 4635  Accessibility and Inclusion  We are committed to making reasonable adjustments to provide a positive, barrier-free recruitment process. The Opportunity • Join CSIRO - Australia's National Science Agency! • Are you interested in transforming the abstract into the actual? • Outstanding opportunities to grow & develop your career . • Flexible work arrangements  CSIRO's Information and Technology (IM&T) business unit is continuing an ambitious program of work designed to support the organisation's strategy to 2024. Underpinning the program is a desire for staff to have seamless, secure access to tools, systems and processes that back the delivery of world-class science.  Members of the IMT Data Analytics Team are responsible for developing and supplying Business Intelligence and Analytics capability to staff in all areas of CSIRO. This requires expertise in relevant SAP technologies and a sound understanding of business operations, processes and information requirements.  As an Analytics Business Analyst, you will be passionate about Analytics and Data Storytelling. This opportunity will see you coordinating end-to-end solution delivery including client engagement, solution development, end-user education and service promotion. You will understand the technical capabilities of our platforms and apply these capabilities to solve line of business or research opportunities and problems. As part of an Agile Business Intelligence delivery team, you will also play an active role in quality assurance throughout the solution delivery lifecycle.  You will assist in delivering against our Data Analytics roadmaps and strategy, underpinned by our technical platforms including SAP BW/4HANA 2.0, SAP Business Objects, and SAP Analytics Cloud. Your duties will include: • Engage with business stakeholders, source system SMEs and data custodians to identify opportunities for the application of modern business analytics solutions • Gather business requirements and User Stories using contemporary techniques and approaches • Coordinate end-to-end solution delivery, working with team members, internal and external stakeholders to develop, implement, promote and support Analytics products • Facilitate User Acceptance Testing, data testing, and support business users and subject matter experts • Construct descriptive analysis and contribute to more complex data analysis for reports, analytic applications and ad-hoc requests • Adhere to the spirit and practice of CSIRO’s Values, Code of Conduct, Health, Safety and Environment procedures and policy, Diversity initiatives and Zero Harm goals  Location: Canberra, Melbourne, Sydney, Hobart (other locations considered)  Salary: AU$105,806k - AU$114,500k plus up to 15.4% superannuation  Tenure: Indefinite  Reference: 94160 To be considered you will need: Essential • Relevant tertiary degree or equivalent work experience • Proven experience working with clients to solicit business requirements and translate these into actionable solutions for technical delivery • Demonstrated ability to harness business analysis tools and techniques to deliver multi-disciplinary, complex projects • Experience in the development and delivery of business data management or data analytics products • Excellent written and verbal communication skills with an ability to facilitate client engagement and communicate and translate technical concepts to a diverse audience Desirable: • Experience working with Enterprise Data Warehouse development teams to deliver engaging Business Analytics solutions at scale • Experience using SAP Analytics Cloud, SAP Business Objects or Microsoft PowerBI to develop Data Analytics dashboards and reports.  For full details about this role please review the Position Description Eligibility • Applications for this position are open to Australian Citizens only • Appointment to this role is subject to provision of a national police check and may be subject to other security/medical/character requirements. • The successful candidate will be required to obtain and maintain a security clearance at the NV1 Level. Flexible Working Arrangements  We work flexibly at CSIRO, offering a range of options for how, when and where you work. Diversity and Inclusion  We are working hard to recruit people representing the diversity across our society, and ensure that all our people feel supported to do their best work and feel empowered to let their ideas flourish. About CSIRO  At CSIRO Australia's national science agency, we solve the greatest challenges through innovative science and technology. We put the safety and wellbeing of our people above all else and earn trust everywhere because we only deal in facts. We collaborate widely and generously and deliver solutions with real impact.  CSIRO is committed to values-based leadership to inspire performance and unlock the potential of our people.  CSIRO is committed to the safety and wellbeing of all children and young people involved in our activities and programs, whether we are undertaking research, engaging with the public or nurturing future scientists in person or online. Source – CSIRO Child Safe policy 2023  Join us and start creating tomorrow today! How to Apply  Please apply on-line and provide a cover letter and CV that best demonstrate your motivation and ability to meet the requirements of this role. Applications Close  Sunday 1st of October 11:00pm AEST  Shortlisting for this role may take place as applications are received. We therefore reserve the right to close this vacancy once a suitable candidate has been appointed,  Please consider applying as soon as possible.

job_description.167: About the Australian Transport Safety Bureau (ATSB)  The Australian Transport Safety Bureau (ATSB) is an independent Commonwealth Government statutory agency. The ATSB is governed by a Commission and is entirely separate from transport regulators, policy makers and service providers.  The ATSB's purpose is to improve safety of, and public confidence in, aviation, marine and rail transport through: • independent investigation of transport accidents and other safety occurrences • safety data recording, analysis and research • fostering safety awareness, knowledge and action. The ATSB is established by the Transport Safety Investigation Act 2003 (TSI Act) and conducts its investigations in accordance with the provisions of the Act. Under the TSI Act, it is not a function of the ATSB to apportion blame or provide a means for determining liability. The ATSB does not investigate for the purpose of taking administrative, regulatory or criminal action.  The Bureau's Commission is constituted by a full-time Commissioner/CEO and three part-time Commissioners. The ATSB's staff (approximately 100) includes about 60 aviation, marine and rail safety investigators. While the majority of staff are based in Canberra, we also have regional offices located in Brisbane, Adelaide, Melbourne and Perth.  The key duties of the position include About the role  The Data Recovery Analyst is a member of a small team of transport safety professionals who apply engineering science to the investigation and analysis of transport safety occurrences.  The Data Recovery Analyst provides technical support to the operations teams, in aviation, marine and rail transport modes, by assisting in the recovery, analysis and presentation of data from transport vehicles and supporting infrastructure. Traditionally, this data has been provided by dedicated recording devices (such as cockpit voice recorders, flight data recorders, voyage data recorders), however the increasing implementation and use of technologies such as quick-access recorders, digital engine control systems, embedded GPS devices, alongside personal electronic devices and video and audio recordings has provided a growing range of data sources from which evidence may be obtained. Where devices are damaged, this can include recovering binary data at the chip level, and associated interpretation and validation of binary data to engineering units.  In this role you will be responsible for: • Downloading data from a broad range of electronic devices. Devices may include all types of phones, various GPS devices, iPads/tablets, flight recorders (FDR, CVR), on-train data recorder and/or event recorder, and marine voyage data recorders. If the device has been damaged in the accident it will require dedication to extract the data ready for analysis. • Undertaking detailed analysis of the data recovered, in-line with ATSB processes, a prepare briefs or reports or presentations for the purpose of improving safety within various transport industries. • Working along-side or being mentored by senior ATSB investigators on an accident site or in the ATSB's technical facilities, using own subject matter expertise to contribute to complex safety investigation activities. • Ensuring data recovery and lab equipment (hardware and software) is procured and maintained to a high standard, and procedures are in place for the safe operation of all equipment, and the efficient and accurate recovery of data. • Undertaking project work to advance unique data initiatives for the ATSB, includes working collaboratively with external stakeholders and/or other government agencies. • Actively contributing to, and promoting the ATSB and APS values and culture, and the ATSB's promotion of transport safety awareness.

job_description.169: APS Level 6  Canberra, ACT; Sydney, NSW; Newcastle, NSW; Orange, NSW; Melbourne, VIC; Bendigo, VIC; Brisbane, QLD; Adelaide, SA; Perth, WA; Hobart, TAS; Darwin, NT  $94,332 - $103,731  About the Department of Employment and Workplace Relations  We enable access to quality skills, training and employment services to support Australians find secure work in fair, productive and safe workplaces – supporting individuals and our nation to prosper.  About Jobs and Skills Australia  Jobs and Skills Australia (JSA) engages, advises and assists the Australian Government and other stakeholders on decision-making on current, emerging, and future skills and workforce needs. Our vision is for the full skills potential of our nation to be realised, resulting in improved workforce participation, productivity, wages, and equity. We aim to be a catalyst in activating the potential of Australia’s human capital to meet present and future skills needs.  We have a diverse, inclusive, and professional team of specialists with skills in policy, data, stakeholder engagement, digital solutions, economics, and research, to reach and work with stakeholders.  Our work is enriched through tripartite engagement and collaboration with unions, business, employers, state and territory governments, and education and training providers from across Australia to provide critical advice to improve skills development, employment opportunities and economic growth.  JSA is an independent secondary statutory body situated in the Department of Employment and Workplace Relations (DEWR). The Interim Commissioner is accountable to the Minister for Skills and Training. Our enabling legislation is the Jobs and Skills Australia Act 2022 and the Jobs and Skills Australia Amendment Act 2023.  You can read more about JSA on our website: www.jobsandskills.gov.au  About the Skilled Migration and International Section  The Skilled Migration and International Section, Labour Market and Migration Branch, is a dynamic team, working on some key priorities for the Australian Government.  The Section is responsible for labour market analysis and research on migration. This includes the JSA Migration Labour Market Indicator Model (the JSA Migration Model) that informs advice to the Government on targeting migration to workforce needs, and to ensure that skilled migration supports the productive capacity of the Australian economy, while recognising that Australians have priority for local jobs.  The Section also coordinates JSA interests in and undertakes research on international economic and labour market matters (including monitoring global skill shortages) and analyses the labour market impacts of labour mobility commitments in free trade agreements.  The Roles  Reporting to the Director or the Assistant Director, the Senior Data Analyst / Economist positions in the Skilled Migration and International Section are:  Senior Data Analyst working in the project team responsible for the ongoing development of the JSA Migration Model and related labour market analysis, to support the implementation of temporary and permanent skill migration initiatives in the Migration Strategy.  Senior Economist working on international economic and labour market matters, including for the Australian Labour Market for Migrants and International Labour Market Update publications.  Duties and Responsibilities  Responsibilities at the APS6 level are:  Senior Data Analyst:  Perform research and analysis on more complex labour market issues associated with temporary and permanent migration, using a variety of data sources, methods, and models.  Contribute to the ongoing development of the JSA Migration Model, analyse output from this Model, and manage the relationship and access agreements with data owners.  Senior Economist:  Monitor and analyse reports on the international labour market and economy, initiate and manage internal research projects on these issues.  Analyse data extracted from an international data portal as input to departmental submissions and publications, comparing the Australian and international labour markets.  Manage the JSA subscription to the international data portal, including procurement and payment.  For both positions:  Contribute to the management of longer-term projects with support from senior staff.  Draft briefs, staff blogs, research papers, and fact sheets.  Provide advice on migration and labour market issues to stakeholders as a subject matter expert and represent the team at interdepartmental committees and working groups.  Supervise, mentor and build the capability of junior staff within the section.  Perform other ad-hoc duties assigned by the Director or Assistant Director.  How to Apply  Applicants are required to provide up to a two-page summary (no more than 1000 words) that outlines skills, knowledge, and experience and why you should be considered for this vacancy. You should take into consideration the position overview (including any detailed position specific requirements) when drafting your response. Where possible include specific relevant examples of your work.  The APS work level standards accommodate the diversity of roles across the APS and are structured to clearly differentiate between the work expected (i.e. responsibilities and duties) at each classification level.  In the eRecruit (the department’s online recruitment system) you will also need to:  upload a Curriculum Vitae  provide contact details for 2 Referees.  Eligibility  Citizenship - to be eligible for employment with the Department, you must be an Australian Citizen or, in limited circumstances, in the process of obtaining it.  Security Clearance - our successful candidate is required to hold, or have the ability to obtain, and maintain a Baseline security clearance.  Please refer to the Job Information Pack for more information about the role. job_description.178: Closing date: 15/10/2023  Data Analyst • APS Level 5 • Ongoing • $80,328 - $84,688  Working within the Mint’s Sales Development Team, the Data Analyst plays a critical role by leveraging data to inform decision making, drive insights and support the achievement of the Mint’s organisational objectives. Reporting to the Sales Product and Project Manager, the Data Analyst works under limited supervision to provide market analysis and deliver evidence based advice. Through collecting, analysing, cleaning and interpreting data, the Data Analyst produces reports, forecasts and recommendations, contributing to how product sales are managed across the Mint. The Data Analyst undertakes risk assessments, using data to inform sales and production activities.  The Data Analyst manages key data related projects for the Mint, in particular developing and delivering the annual sales budget to inform key stakeholders of the planned revenue position of the Mint. They respond to ad hoc requests from senior managers and are responsible for gathering and analysing data at limited notice, requiring a high level of attention to detail. The Data Analyst leads a small team, including setting priorities, identifying opportunities for growth and managing individual and section performance. They regularly find ways to continuously improve processes and procedures to achieve strategic objectives.  The duties of this position include:  1. Undertaking collection and analysis of sales, production and competitor data, including:  a. cleaning, validating and interpreting data from a variety of sources;  b. conducting quantitative and qualitative data analysis to identify trends, patterns and anomalies;  c. developing, implementing and maintaining budgets, databases and data extracts; and  d. using statistical and data visualisation techniques to present findings.  2. Developing high level, comprehensive reports, forecasts and dashboards to present data-driven insights and translate complex data into actionable advice or recommendations for the Mint.  3. Developing, implementing and tracking the annual sales budget to inform the planned revenue position of the Mint for key stakeholders including the Chief Financial Officer, Chief Executive Officer and the Treasury.  4. Responding to ad hoc reporting requests from senior management, government officials or other stakeholders, including quickly gathering and analysing data to address urgent information needs.  5. Collaborating and negotiating with internal and external stakeholders relating to complex operational and administrative matters, including sale and production of Mint products, costs, revenue and associated recommendations.  6. Providing tailored advice and guidance to the Customer Experience and Sales Managers relating to sales and production statistics, and managing stock allocation.  7. Undertaking risk assessments of sales and budget related data, identifying and reporting on risks as they arise and making relevant recommendations.  8. Supervising a small team including setting priorities, providing feedback, identifying development opportunities and managing performance.  9. Identifying opportunities for process improvement including defining new data collection and analysis processes, developing work instructions and creating efficiencies.  10. Representing the Mint at various internal and external forums.  11. Ensuring compliance with regulatory, departmental and Treasury reporting requirements.  Security clearance  This position requires a Baseline security clearance. The successful applicant will be required to obtain and maintain a clearance at this level.  Qualification  A bachelor’s degree or higher in Data Science, Statistics, Economics, Computer Science or a relevant field.  How to apply  The successful applicant for this position may be granted flexible office arrangements to allow them to work off-site. If these arrangements are put in place, the successful applicant may at times be required to travel from their location to the Mint’s premises in Deakin, ACT to undertake work onsite at their own expense.  Please submit your application by 11:30pm on Sunday, 15 October 2023. You will need to upload: • A current resume • A 500 word pitch that describes how your skills meet the requirements of the role as detailed in the position description.  Information on applying for a job in the Australian Public Service is available at the Employment page of our website.  Should you have any questions regarding the role, please contact Elisa Rodriguez on (02) 6202 6830.

job_description.185: Line of Service  Assurance  Industry/Sector  G and PS - Other  Specialism  Data, Analytics & AI  Management Level  Senior Manager  Job Description & Summary  About Us  The challenges facing business and society are complex and need new angles and fresh thinking. Your human ingenuity, passion and experience, combined with the latest technology, make these problems easier to tackle.  Together, we are a passionate community of solvers coming together in unexpected ways, creating new solutions for a new day. We're in the business of transformation.  To transform the future, we're building a diverse, ambitious team that champions imaginative ways to solve our clients' most important challenges.  A career in our Analytics Data Assurance practice, will provide you with the opportunity to assist clients in developing analytics and technology solutions that help them detect, monitor, and predict risk.  Using advanced technology, we're able to focus on establishing the right controls, processes and structures for our clients to ensure that decisions are based on accurate information and assure that information provided to third parties is accurate, complete, and can be trusted. How and where work gets done is being reimagined. It all adds up to The New Equation.  About the Opportunity  At PwC Canberra, we combine local and global expertise, public sector experience and people-focused purpose to help the federal government make life better for our communities.  As Senior Manager in our Canberra Assurance team you'll work as part of a team of problem solvers, helping to solve complex business issues from strategy to execution.  Your impact will be seen by: Delivering crucial business insights to clients through data analytics and data visualisation  Providing business confidence through innovative use of data analysis and visualisation techniques to improve efficiency and quality of assurance processes  Helping businesses make sense of complex data sets and familiar with widely used analytics tools  Partnering with clients to enable them to understand the value in their data through analytics and visualisation  Assuring that information and data provided to regulators and third parties is accurate, complete and can be trusted  Supervising and coaching a team, to foster an environment of continued growth and development within the team.  Leading client projects, to help businesses make sense of complex data sets and given them the confidence they are doing things right  About you  You have 5+ years experience with demonstrated strengths in Data Science / Advanced Analytics, Data Management, Data Governance, Data Engineering, Data Modeling, Computing Engineering / Sciences, Applied Statistics / Mathematics, DevOps and/or Cloud Computing, underpinned by related degree-level or higher qualifications or other fields such as Business Informatics, Econometrics, Finance, Accounting, Commerce, Information Technology, Science or Engineering.  You are a confident senior data analyst and/or engineer with working knowledge of ETL, quality control and testing processes and/or robust data infrastructure design, implementation, test, integration, management and optimisation, as well as expertise in automation, visualisation and / or advanced analytics process automation, reporting digitisation / visualisation, advanced analytics data governance / transformation and/or data accessibility for real-time analytics . You are able to use widely used analytics tools i.e. Power BI, Tableau, Qlik, Python, R, Alteryx, SAS, Power Automate, Power Apps, SQL and/or Azure. Experience in Assurance, Consulting and / or the public sector is highly desirable.  Passionate about being at the forefront of change, you're ready to help our Data Analytics team solve complex business issues, improve how systems work and provide confidence on the bigger decisions. You're collaborative and enjoy working in an innovative environment.  You're a problem solver by nature and want to join a firm that values the kind of people who reimagine the possible for their clients and stakeholders. Most importantly, you act with integrity and show care for the people you work with.  Please note this role is based in Canberra.  Due to the nature of the work, you must be an Australian citizen, eligible to obtain and maintain an Australian Government issued security clearance. To solve important problems we need to aim for the inclusion of our diverse talent. We empower our people to use their creativity, authenticity and human differences to be the champions of change.  We know that when people from diverse backgrounds and with different points of view work together, we create the most value - for our clients, our people and our society. If you don't think you quite meet all of the qualifications, we'd still love to hear from you. job_description.188: About the company:  Seeing Machines is the world leader in the field of Safety-AI and prides itself on developing technologies that save lives, for real!  Around the globe and at any time of the day, there are almost 1 million cars on the roads that are using state-of-the-art operator monitoring technology developed by Seeing Machines which provides real-time protection from distraction and drowsy-related driving events. Seeing Machines works with the world’s leading brands (eg. General Motors, Mercedes Benz, Qantas, Caterpillar, Toll) across multiple transport sectors of automotive, commercial road transport (Fleet), and aviation to enhance safety.  As a Business Analyst in our team, you will play a pivotal part in the discovery, design and collaborative problem solving for new features and the continuous improvement of our products alongside a dynamic and progressive Product Management team. This key role acts as a bridge to ensure feature discovery, design and implementation, meet the desired outcomes for customers and the business.  Key Responsibilities: • Contribute to feature discovery and design with product management, including leading on aspects of activities such: • Mapping current and future state user journey / service flows • Running co-design sessions • Liaising with development on technical constraints / systems process mapping • Input to concept prototyping with designs to test solutions • Documenting user insights and lessons learn in presentations and confluence • Lead on documentation of user stories during design and handover to development, including follow through end-to-end to release. • Document final user stories in JIRA as design flows are approved • Support handover from design to development • Lead as the point of contact for specific feature for delivery, quality and development.  Knowledge, Skills and Experience: • Relevant tertiary degree in computer science, product design or similar, or equivalent practical experience. • Excellent problem solving skills, using design thinking approaches to solve problems collaboratively, in a small multi-disciplinary team. • Ability to lead and facilitate workshops, co-design and ideation sessions, and customer and stakeholder interviews. • Ability to provide concise presentations on both quantitative and qualitative insights. • Technical understanding to work effectively with architects and development team to understand feasibility constraints and assess merits of different proposed solutions. • Ability to map both customer current and future state journey’s and system processes to ensure the feature roadmap is comprehensive and documentation enables effective delivery. • Demonstrated experience managing the delivery of digital product features from discovery to release, in a fast-paced, agile environment.  About you:  With demonstrated experience in a previous similar role, you will be a collaborative team member with a mindset that encourages different perspectives to solve problems. Your ability to adapt to changing circumstances will compliment your approach to taking ownership from start to finish to achieve outcomes. Lastly, you will have a growth mindset while being energised by the opportunity to learn and support others in your project team to do the same.  Why Seeing Machines: • We are inventive, innovative and collaborative and are making a real difference to safety on roads, all around the world • Work flexibly – we encourage our people to manage their work and personal lives to achieve a balanced outcome • We are global, Seeing Machines serves a growing market in the UK, Europe, Africa, North America, Latin America, and Asia Pacific • We are focused on employee support and understand the importance of our collective wellbeing. You will have access to our Employee Assistance Program any time you require it • We reward and recognise achievement. You will have access to our global benefits and reward platform.  For more information, visit: http://www.seeingmachines.com  Seeing Machines acknowledges Traditional Owners of Country throughout Australia and recognises the continuing connection to lands, waters and communities. We pay our respect to Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander cultures; and to Elders past, present and emerging.
job_description.189: We are looking to connect with Business Analysts in the ACT who are interested in working as an embedded team member with our Government clients in both contract and ongoing roles. Contribute to a wide range of projects that aim to achieve strategic objectives, modernise business processes and provide reliable information to help decision-makers. • Do you adopt a human-centred approach to your work as a Business Analyst? • Do you have a keen eye for asking the right questions to uncover key requirements? • Can you cultivate stakeholder relationships, bridging business, technology, strategy and creative? • Are you happiest when working with large, agile teams delivering digital products and services, navigating through ambiguity?  We'd love to hear from you!  Who are Local Peoples?  Local Peoples is a strategic research and design studio based in Melbourne and Canberra.  Our mission is to design healthy, resilient and resourceful communities. We are proud to be a certified B-Corporation with a strong focus on our social, environmental and economic impact.  We work across brand and digital design, place and experience design,, content and community engagement. Our key partners include state and local government, social enterprises, universities and large commercial organisations. All are experiencing complex challenges right now and we believe that design research, thinking and delivery can help to solve these challenges and make positive change for people and the planet.  We produce www.mattersjournal.com , a publication and community of 100K+, which focuses on design-led social innovation and impact.  Benefits Of Working With Local Peoples • We are experts in team design and augmentation - supporting with the right skills and experience at the right time. • We are leaders in the human centred design space with diverse design skills across brand design, service design, User interface (UI) and User experience (UX) design, design research, communications and place design. • We are a certified B-Corporation and prioritise the social, environmental and economic impact of our work. • We are top tier talent who are experienced and incredibly passionate about supporting the impact of your agency and the public sector. • Our people always have the full support of the studio to call upon for design thinking, tools and tips, so you are not just getting access to one bright mind, but a collective of many with diverse and deep experiences.  Required Skills And Experience.  General • Business Analyst with 5+ years of experience working within Agile frameworks, particularly Scrum and SAFe • Experience managing discoveries, co-design activities (workshops, interviews etc), process modelling, journey mapping, user stories, management of requirements within a product backlog.  Business Requirement • Identifying business needs and making sure they are fully captured by planning, defining, and managing user stories, acceptance criteria, and functional and technical requirements. • Conducting business discovery and co-design workshops, interviews, and meetings with internal and external stakeholders/working groups. • Recommend effective business and ICT changes  Analysis and reporting • Extensive experience and highly developed skills in performing analysis of systems and business processes, process mapping, user stories, use cases, data migration source-to-target mapping, specifications, and wireframes. • A strong eye for detail and excellent data presentation skills. • An ability to describe the business impacts of current and proposed solutions, including risks and benefits. • Analysis and reporting on the results of new solutions implemented in business and IT processes.  Stakeholder management • Ability to build relationships and work collaboratively with stakeholders, including the ability to act as the team's representative in meetings with business units. • Experience facilitating workshops, stakeholder interviews, presentations, product backlog management and user acceptance testing.  Documentation • The ability to design, manage, and refine business processes, user journeys, and other supporting documents as necessary. • Developing artifacts to support requirements definition, such as process models, operational concepts, prototypes, and insights derived from data. • Assisting in the development of training materials, user guides and standardisation documents in connection with the deployment of new systems.  Residency and Clearance • Hold a current ASGVA Baseline clearance or be able to obtain one. • Australian Citizen  This role is open to Canberra based applicants.
job_description.190: The key duties of the position include The Role APS 6 Data Analyst This role will leverage your understanding of statistics, Geographical Information Systems (GIS) and programming. You will work as part of a team to develop and implement new tools and methodologies that use AGO's data and GIS more effectively and efficiently. You will work with a range of stakeholders, including AGO's intelligence analysts, data scientists and capability managers, ensuring your analytics meet user requirements, are rigorous and consistent with AGO's system environment.  APS 6 Data Scientist This role will leverage your experience in Machine Learning/Artificial Intelligence (AI/ML), data analysis and automation, to assist AGO to derive deeper insights from larger volumes of data, and at a pace that enables decision advantage. You will liaise with a range of stakeholders to evaluate and implement AI/ML technologies that drive innovation and modernise AGO's analytic practices.  The additional payment is a Building Defence Capability Payment (BDCP) which enables Defence to provide a premium, in addition to the rate of salary otherwise payable under the Enterprise Agreement (EA) to some or all of the jobs within a critical occupation(s) or discipline within a workplace.  Applicants engaged into a BDCP position must consider the following. BDCPs provide remuneration in addition to the Defence Enterprise Agreement (EA). This arrangement is subject to meeting eligibility criteria and is subject to annual review. Should your performance fall beyond requirements or the eligibility criteria not be met, your eligibility for the BDCP may be reviewed and ceased. It may also be ceased should you change positions or the requirement for the BDCP is no longer necessary, as determined by Defence. Should the BDCP be ceased you will be advised and your BDCP additional payment will cease.  About our Team The Australian Geospatial-Intelligence Organisation (AGO) makes a critical contribution to protect the lives and safety of Australians at home and overseas by providing accurate and timely geospatial-intelligence to support decision makers at all levels.  The Data Innovation and Analytics Directorate (DIAD) is a team of highly motivated data specialists who provide analytical support to AGO's intelligence and production areas. Our vision is to transform analytic workflows, increasing automation and augmentation through the application of data science and machine analytics. We work closely with a range of stakeholders to understand their analytic requirements, and deliver new tools and methodologies that enable them to achieve more efficient and innovative outcomes.  We foster a data-driven culture that supports analysts to gain deeper insights from larger volumes of data. We provide opportunities for continuous learning and development, including funding for tertiary qualifications in machine analytics, and the opportunity to engage with industry and academia.  Our Ideal Candidate Successful candidates will be highly motivated, have strong oral and communication skills, with broad knowledge of geospatial data applications and analytical techniques. In addition, they will be able to work both individually and as part of a team, build and maintain productive working relationships with diverse stakeholders, and proactively address skill/knowledge gaps. They will be resilient problem solvers, willing to engage with ambiguity and are able to harness collective knowledge to optimise outcomes.  They will also possess some of the following: • Strong data analysis/science skills, including the ability to use, manage, manipulate and analyse data to produce evidence-based conclusions. • Intermediate to advanced python programming experience. • Intermediate to advanced GIS experience. • Strong communication skills, including the ability to communicate complex technical concepts simply and clearly. • Experience developing/delivering data-centric training. • Knowledge of machine-learning techniques and data processing frameworks. • Knowledge of cloud computing platforms, such as AWS and Kubernetes.

job_description.194: • Establish data-driven decision-making to optimize the online learning experience at the University • UC Level 7, Salary Range $94,134 pa - $101,979 pa + 17% Super • Full time, 3 years Fixed Term Opportunity     UC has curiosity, ambition and inclusiveness at its core. We challenge the status quo through the pursuit of excellence in teaching, learning and research. Our place-based commitment ensures that we visibly serve Canberra’s community and the surrounding region with impact on the nation. The University of Canberra is ranked in the top five universities globally for reducing inequalities (THE Impact Rankings, 2023).   The University of Canberra is undergoing an exciting time of transformation, growth and change. It is embarking on a transformational program to enhance student learning and increase student enrolments through the development of new capabilities and capacities. We will generate new online courses and develop a more flexible approach to delivering existing courses, both at our Bruce campus, our campus in the cloud and with our partners. The University is also undertaking a realignment in its support for learning and teaching, its curriculum development and its policy suite. This role gives you the opportunity to bring your skills and experience to influence and impact these important changes at the University.  We are currently seeking an Online Learning Analytics Specialist to join the University in support of a major strategic program to grow student numbers, the Education Transformation and Growth Program. Operating under broad direction and reporting to the Manager, Insights & Data Storytelling, the Online Learning Analytics Specialist will lead the development of a new capability focused on improving the experience and effectiveness of our online course offerings.  The Online Learning Analytics Specialist is a dynamic role within the Insights & Data Storytelling team at the University of Canberra, established to drive data-driven decision-making and optimize the online learning experience. This newly created position focuses on harnessing the power of learning analytics to enhance the quality of online education, improve student engagement, and inform instructional design strategies. The specialist will collaborate closely with cross-functional teams to gather, analyse, and interpret online learning data, contributing to the university's commitment to delivering innovative and effective online education.  To be successful in this role, the preferred candidates will have experience as an analyst or a learning designer with exposure to data analytics. Existing knowledge of Canvas, Power BI, web and/or product analytics will be highly regarded. As a new capability in the team, the successful applicant will need to have initiative to drive, mould and design the framework to maximise the e-learning experience for our student with support from the Manager, Insights & Data Storytelling.     The University offers excellent conditions and benefits such as flexible, family-friendly policies, on site gym, on site medical services, a supermarket and childcare facilities.   Connected - A Decadal Strategy 2023-2032 sets a goal to be the national sector leader in equity, diversity, inclusion and access, and the ambitious goals of our Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Strategic Plan are designed to ensure that our Indigenous students and staff flourish in a welcoming and culturally safe environment. UC encourages applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, people with disabilities and people from culturally diverse groups.   To be considered for this role all we want is your CV, no other documentation are required.   Please ensure you take the time to align you CV with the Position Description requirements. We want to understand how your skills and experience relate to the position you are applying for.  To download the position description please copy and paste the below URL into your web browser which will redirect you to the University of Canberra website - https://uctalent.canberra.edu.au/cw/en/listing/  If you are initially shortlisted, you may be asked to complete an online one-way video interview. There will be a list of pre-set questions that will need to be answered within a stipulated time.   Working Rights: Applicants who wish to apply for this position should have valid working rights or eligibility to obtain a work visa for Australia.   For job specific information: Please contact Simon Hopkins - Manager, Insights & Data Storytelling - Simon.Hopkins@canberra.edu.au - 0423267173. job_description.197: • Closing Date: 13 October 2023, 9:00 AM  face2face reference: 591408  Location: Nationwide - Remote  Hours: Full-time  Contract length: 12 Months Contract + 3 x 1 Month (Pending approval)  Entry requirements: Australian Citizen + Ability to obtain Baseline  Pay range: $95.00 – 115.00 p/h inc super  About the role:  The Tertiary Skills and Pathways team is responsible for the unit mapping project, as part of its program of work. Unit mapping uses natural language processing techniques to create a connection between tertiary education learning materials (VET and HE units), and skills taxonomies. Unit mapping helps to identify skills taught in tertiary education, and their potential relationship to occupations and the labour market, to assist in analysis and advice on tertiary education delivery.  The team is working on a demonstration project basis with five key projects to design the end to end process of unit mapping, to continually refine the data science model, and to generate insights on the potential use of mapping outputs. The outputs of models are large, for example one university with approximately 3,000 units can have an output of approximately 30,000 skills mapped. Validation of outputs is a critical part of the mapping process to produce a model and results that are highly accurate.  Duties: • Developing of a comprehensive internal and external validation process for very large data sets, to support improvement of data science models, and the quality of output data sent to partners. This may require an ensemble of approaches, for example statistical sampling, manual and automated approaches to validation. • Managing internal validation processes before outputs are sent to project partners. • Working closely with the data science team to provide feedback for the mapping model development. • Analysing complex model outputs, to derive valuable insights for reporting to project partners, including visualisation techniques. • Providing advice to technical services on interface design for a validation application for project partners.  Required experience/skills: • Demonstrated experience in data analysis and process design, to create replicable data validation processes to improve data output quality. • Excellent analytical skills, with strong attention to detail, and the ability to synthesise and critically analyse large volumes of structured and unstructured data. • Strong skills and experience in data management, in particular how data can be effectively structured, analysed, presented and communicated, to achieve high-quality outcomes. • Excellent communication skills, including the ability to effectively communicate key data insights visually and in written form to a range of diverse stakeholders • Well-developed interpersonal skills, including the ability to work effectively in a multidisciplinary setting.  Desirable experience skills: • Experience in R Shiny, Python, SQL, anduser experience design. • Understanding of, and experience working with tertiary education (HE and/or VET) and/or occupation and labour market data. • Understanding and experience in data science, or related fields. • Experience operating in a policy environment. job_description.205: About Alooba  Hello! We are Alooba - a skills assessment platform for analytics, data science & data literacy. Our customers use us to better understand their people and their job candidates. We are like the ‘Moneyball’ of hiring, helping businesses focus on the things that matter and removing those that don’t. The result? A fairer, cheaper, faster and more accurate hiring process that focuses on the skills needed for the job. Our vision is to create a world where everyone can get the job they deserve. Can you help us achieve that?  Our culture is very important to us. We value no-nonsense people who use common sense to get sh!t done and make it happen. You’ll put our users first, and focus on improving our product and yourself every day. You’ll be able to straddle the need to work very fast and push stuff live, while maintaining a high standard and taking care of the details. You really must care, and this can’t just be ‘a job’ for you. And when work time is over, it’s party time!  Our hiring process always starts with a fair, skills-based quiz on our platform, customised for the role. This will help us both understand your skills, ensure everyone is treated fairly and you’ll get a chance to see what you’ll be building. If you ace the quiz, you’re guaranteed an interview. No matter what happens, you’ll see your score at the end of the quiz.  We are, genuinely, an equal opportunity employer. We also don’t care about things that traditionally appear on job ads like ‘years of experience’, university qualifications etc.  The Role  We currently have a small team of remote developers, however we’re looking to set up our core development office in Sydney at Fishburners. We’re looking for a set of strong senior software engineers to help bring our product to the next level, with a major overhaul of the system architecture, using a service oriented approach and expanding our feature set.  You should have experience building well structured systems and are keen to work in the fast paced startup environment with a drive to do whatever it takes to make it happen. As we are still a small company, you will have a direct impact on the success of the business. You will be the driving force behind the implementation of the features and functionalities you’ll be working on.  You will work directly with the CTO, founder and a small team of developers to build out our assessment platform to be an enterprise grade web application to serve our small but growing user-base spread across the world.  Our application is built with PHP (Laravel/Lumen), PostgreSQL, and React.js and is running on AWS. We are looking for capable people that can help expand our product and build it to scale with our users. You will be responsible for designing, developing, testing and maintaining the application and supporting services.  Responsibilities • Take ownership of features and functionality and see it through from conceptualisation to productionisation • Design and develop highly scalable, and maintainable code • Design and develop system database schemas and RESTful API interfaces • Thoroughly test new functionalities and existing systems • Manage infrastructure as code and utilize CI/CD pipelines  Benefits • Unlimited opportunities to grow your skill set in a fast-paced startup environment. • No corporate bureaucracy, red tape, endless meetings and other big company nonsense - work directly with the CTO and founder on a daily basis. • 5 days paid learning leave per year. • Competitive salary and share options. • The chance to get in early on the next big thing, and leave your legacy.  Must Have Requirements • A can do attitude • Attention to detail • Ability to understand and interpret user needs • Good problem solving skills • Solid understanding of Object-Oriented Programming principles and patterns • Solid understanding of Relational Databases and SQL • Strong communication skills  Nice to Have Requirements • Experience working at a start-up • Working knowledge of PHP • Working knowledge of PostgreSQL • A good understanding of internet security best practises • Experience building RESTful APIs and integrating with 3rd party APIs • Experience with Docker and CI/CD pipelines • Experience managing AWS services • Frontend web development experience using HTML, JavaScript, CSS, and React.js  Job Types: Permanent, Full-time  Salary: $90,000.00 – $140,000.00 per year  Work Remotely: • Temporarily due to COVID-19  COVID-19 Precaution(s): • Remote interview process
job_description.206: • Data curious with a technical mind, including the ability to engage with all levels of our business • Advance excel skills and programming experience developing business intelligence tools, including Microsoft Excel, Python, R, SQL and Power BI. • Strong analytical, problem solving and reporting skills  Salary range from $109,612 plus super  At Hydro Tasmania, we’re leaders in renewable energy, powering Australia with clean hydropower. We really care about making a difference for better, but it’s a big job and we can’t do it alone. Which is right where you come in.  We are passionate about diversity and inclusion and welcome applications from qualified candidates of all ages, cultural backgrounds, abilities and genders. There’s a place for you amongst us to belong, and we welcome you to speak to us about any special requirements you may have to give you the best opportunity for success.  About You  The Data Analyst will be someone who seeks continuous improvement and innovation. You operate with a view to progress the business by acting reasonably and efficiently when dealing with decision making. It's imperative that alongside developed technical ability you also possess a strong ability to communicate effectively to reports, peers and colleagues. You will be able to engage stakeholders at all levels and demonstrated a strong collaborative approach.  A flexible, proactive and self-starter attitude will be essential, along with the ability to work to deadlines you will have a passion for driving best practice and enjoy streamlining processes. Your flair for presenting data in a convincing and easy to understand format assists you in comfortably communicating your work with a broad range of stakeholders. Agile and resilient, you can quickly adapt to shifting priorities. You will ideally hold a degree in a relevant discipline, coupled with several years experience working in a similar role and advance experience with data analysis and exposure to various software programs.  About The Role  You will support the business by providing technical and analytical support to our forecasting activities, delivery of information and data services supporting the business’s financial and operational activities. You’ll work collaboratively with a broad range of stakeholders across our business, establishing and maintaining stakeholder relationships. As the Data Analyst you will be responsible for; • Constructing PowerBI reports and dashboards connected to enterprise data systems to effectively distil data into actionable insights • Utilise data analytics and models to held change ways of working and reduce business waste • Work with Commercial Finance to manage data integrity and add value to financial trading analytics • Constructing PowerBI reports to replace and automate existing excel models • Excellent analysis and problem solving skills • Can do attitude with a willingness to learn • Great communication & attention to detail • Ability to work autonomously and eager to learn from others • Ability to build sound relationships with stakeholders and business partnering experience based on trust  Further information can be found on the attached Position Description: PD - FIN - Data Analyst - HT4 - September 2023.pptx  What You’ll Get Back  This is an opportunity to grow your career and redefine your role in tomorrow’s industry landscape. We offer truly flexible work that suits you, a competitive remuneration package, and the rare opportunity to play a role in Australia’s renewable energy transformation while enjoying the – lifestyle Tasmania has to offer.  If you want to make a difference for better  Please attach your resume and a cover letter outlining what skills and experience you will bring as soon as possible. We will be running an agile recruitment process and will engage with suitable candidates as soon we have reviewed their applications.
job_description.207: Hydro Tasmania has been at the forefront of clean energy innovation for over one hundred years. We are Australia’s largest producer of clean energy – generating hydro and wind power – and the largest water manager in the country. Hydro Tasmania has 55 major dams, operates 30 hydropower stations and has built some of Australia’s largest wind farms. We also sell energy in the National Electricity Market through our retail business Momentum Energy, and deliver our expertise internationally through our consulting business Entura. Hydro Tasmania at a glance * Hydro Tasmania is Australia’s leading renewable energy business. We generate hydropower in Tasmania and trade electricity and energy-related environmental products (such as Renewable Energy Certificates) in the Australian market. * Hydro Tasmania is the largest water manager in Australia. * We own and operate King Island’s Huxley Hill wind farm and two diesel power stations on Bass Strait islands. They’re good examples of innovative use of combined renewable technologies. * We’re owned by the Government of Tasmania and currently employ over 800 people. We have assets worth around $4.8 billion.

job_description.209: • Closing Date: 13 October 2023, 9:00 AM  face2face reference: 591408  Location: Nationwide - Remote  Hours: Full-time  Contract length: 12 Months Contract + 3 x 1 Month (Pending approval)  Entry requirements: Australian Citizen + Ability to obtain Baseline  Pay range: $95.00 – 115.00 p/h inc super  About the role:  The Tertiary Skills and Pathways team is responsible for the unit mapping project, as part of its program of work. Unit mapping uses natural language processing techniques to create a connection between tertiary education learning materials (VET and HE units), and skills taxonomies. Unit mapping helps to identify skills taught in tertiary education, and their potential relationship to occupations and the labour market, to assist in analysis and advice on tertiary education delivery.  The team is working on a demonstration project basis with five key projects to design the end to end process of unit mapping, to continually refine the data science model, and to generate insights on the potential use of mapping outputs. The outputs of models are large, for example one university with approximately 3,000 units can have an output of approximately 30,000 skills mapped. Validation of outputs is a critical part of the mapping process to produce a model and results that are highly accurate.  Duties: • Developing of a comprehensive internal and external validation process for very large data sets, to support improvement of data science models, and the quality of output data sent to partners. This may require an ensemble of approaches, for example statistical sampling, manual and automated approaches to validation. • Managing internal validation processes before outputs are sent to project partners. • Working closely with the data science team to provide feedback for the mapping model development. • Analysing complex model outputs, to derive valuable insights for reporting to project partners, including visualisation techniques. • Providing advice to technical services on interface design for a validation application for project partners.  Required experience/skills: • Demonstrated experience in data analysis and process design, to create replicable data validation processes to improve data output quality. • Excellent analytical skills, with strong attention to detail, and the ability to synthesise and critically analyse large volumes of structured and unstructured data. • Strong skills and experience in data management, in particular how data can be effectively structured, analysed, presented and communicated, to achieve high-quality outcomes. • Excellent communication skills, including the ability to effectively communicate key data insights visually and in written form to a range of diverse stakeholders • Well-developed interpersonal skills, including the ability to work effectively in a multidisciplinary setting.  Desirable experience skills: • Experience in R Shiny, Python, SQL, anduser experience design. • Understanding of, and experience working with tertiary education (HE and/or VET) and/or occupation and labour market data. • Understanding and experience in data science, or related fields. • Experience operating in a policy environment. job_description.215: About The Role  In this role, you will become a trusted and relied upon financial analyst whose primary objective is to elevate the team's expertise in regulatory financial modelling. By aiming to foster a deeper understanding of financial regulations and their impact on the organisation's operations and overall financial position. This capability empowers the team to offer invaluable insights into the commercial and financial dimensions of regulatory compliance, ultimately enhancing the quality of regulatory reporting and decision-making processes.  Concurrently, there is a focus on enhancing the team's corporate and financial modelling, a pivotal component in supporting TasNetworks strategic decision-making. Financial models serve as indispensable tools for forecasting, conducting scenario analyses, and evaluating the financial ramifications of strategic objectives. Additionally, the role provides support for vital team-managed processes, encompassing treasury and debt management, and extending assistance to the Investment Governance Committee, which oversees the businesses major investment decisions. This also includes creating, reviewing and refining models using a DCF approach for potential new deals for the business.  Furthermore, data gathering and validation are central to the role's responsibilities and are essential for providing meaningful and insightful analysis.  Lastly, the role encompasses the development and upkeep of a comprehensive long-term financial model, which serves as a strategic compass for long-term financial planning and decision-making.  About Us  At TasNetworks, we are proud to be the leading provider of electricity transmission and distribution services in Tasmania. With our unwavering commitment to safety, reliability, and customer satisfaction, we deliver a superior electricity supply to over 285,000 residential, commercial, and industrial customers. Our core values and forward-thinking approach make us the trusted brand for all your energy needs.  By joining TasNetworks, you will experience the difference of a company that puts customers first, values safety above all, unifies in the face of challenges, and embraces diversity and forward thinking. Together, we are powering a bright future for Tasmania.  About You  To be successful in this role, it is imperative to embody TasNetworks' Core Capabilities, which form the cornerstone of all positions within the organisation.  Having a solid foundation in business, commerce, accounting, or a related professional field, coupled with a demonstrated period of relevant experience, is essential.  Proficiency in Excel, including the ability to construct intricate financial models, is crucial. Moreover, a deep understanding of valuation techniques pertaining to the evaluation of future investment opportunities, including mergers and acquisitions, is highly valuable.  Success in this role hinges on possessing robust analytical, problem-solving, and critical thinking skills, allowing for the transformation of data and complex analysis into comprehensible insights that facilitate informed decision-making processes. This also includes the ability to summarise data efficiently in order to present to various stakeholders across the business, including executives and board members.  What's on offer  This is a full time permanent opportunity based at our Lenah Valley Office in the South of the state. At TasNetworks we want to power a bright future for our people, our community and our customers. We offer a supportive work environment where safety is at the heart of everything we do. We offer our team excellent benefits including • Great professional development opportunities • Flexible work arrangements • Paid volunteer days • Free onsite parking • Onsite gyms (or gym rebate if unavailable) • All the equipment you'll need to be successful  We are proud to be work180 accredited, check us out  How to apply  If this role and working at TasNetworks is of interest we look forward to hearing from you. TasNetworks is an Equal Opportunity employer and is committed to responding to every applicant. We encourage applications from all members of the community, including people of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander descent, culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds and mature aged people. Please ensure you attach a cover letter outlining how your skills and experience are aligned with this role, and an up to date resume. For more information about this opportunity and to acquire a position description, please click  Applications close 11:59pm Sunday 15th October 2023  For further information about the role, please contact  To be eligible for this position, you are required to have Australian citizenship, permanent residence or a current valid visa that allows you to fulfil the requirements of this role.
