job_description.217: • ‘Work where it works’ for you and your clients • Be part of a team where everyone belongs, and individuality is celebrated • Contribute to the financial wellbeing of our 2 million+ clients across Australia  The difference you will make at Insignia Financial  In the role of the Salesforce Technical Business Analyst, you will take an active and forward-looking approach to enhance project delivery. This includes providing leadership to analysts and collaborating closely with the Delivery Manager to ensure the successful execution of team activities and deliverables.  You Will Make a Difference By • Conducting in-depth technical analysis, addressing complex business requirements and processes • Serving as a pivotal link between stakeholders and the delivery team, taking charge of complex issues across various applications that involve multiple parties • Evaluating existing processes and systems, offering recommendations for process enhancements • Providing subject matter expertise and conduct business analysis for intricate projects • Developing position statements on complex subject matter inquiries • Assisting in Incident Management during Business as Usual (BAU) operations, identifying the root causes and facilitating defect remediation within stipulated SLAs • Providing comprehensive support throughout the end-to-end delivery process, including technical requirements, testing, and change management for planned releases and maintenance windows as needed  A Little Bit About You • Possess business and/or technology expertise, acquired within the Financial Services sector or other related industries • Extensive experience, with a significant portion dedicated to working with Salesforce • Hold tertiary qualifications or possess equivalent industry experience • Demonstrate prior experience in various business practices, with a particular focus on Financial Services, especially in superannuation and fund management • Expert in systems design, integration, and function/data analysis within specific business functions • Exhibit effective communication and interpersonal skills, crucial for effective stakeholder engagement, including the ability to conduct showcases • Adopt a proactive approach to problem-solving, critical thinking, and the identification of opportunities for improvement • Lead by example by embodying the culture and values that align with the expectations of the team and Insignia Financial  Life at Insignia Financial  From people just starting out, to those about to retire – every day we help more Australians secure their future. Helping our clients reach their financial goals sooner is our specialty. Few others can match the range of wealth management products and services we offer.  Insignia Financial is an ASX Top 200 company, and one of one of Australia’s leading wealth managers. We use our scale and expertise to invest in a future that’s better for everyone. We believe success comes from caring about people, consistent performance, and outstanding service. And we recognise and celebrate the value of individual difference: this applies to employees and clients alike.  Diversity and ensuring our people feel they belong is important to us, we take pride in putting our people, as well as our clients, first and value and celebrate diversity within all our teams.  We have a Women in Technology community which exists to bring together female and non-binary people within the tech world at Insignia Financial. This supportive forum is eager to progress and make change in the technology space – does this sound like you?  With many of us now working from home more than the office, we understand the importance of flexibility. As we work in a hybrid environment, you’ll ‘work where it works’ for you, your team, and our clients. We also offer varied and flexible leave offerings, including 12 weeks paid parental leave and an extra day of leave each year.  We encourage our people to have an impact on the broader community we serve through volunteering leave.  At Insignia Financial, it’s important to us that our people feel secure about their own money. We have an extensive financial wellbeing offering available to our people, including access to financial advice, mortgage, and insurance brokers, Will and estate planning services and more.  Join us and contribute to achieving our ambition of creating financial wellbeing for all Australians through living our Principles: be human, deliver what matters, stronger together, keep it simple and do what’s right, not what’s easy.  To apply  Please submit your resume with a covering letter by clicking on "Apply Now".  Applicants will be required to provide evidence of their eligibility to work in Australia, and at a minimum be required to undertake police and basic credit checks as a condition of employment.  Please note that applications from agencies will not be considered at this time.  At Insignia Financial, we have a culture of belonging. We are an ‘every person’ organisation that welcomes and appreciates everyone for who they are. If you need assistance or an adjustment during the application process because of your personal circumstances, please reach out and let us know. We recognise and celebrate the value of individual difference.  #AW
job_description.218: APS6 Data Analyst  As an APS 6 Data Analyst, you'll use your expertise in data analysis, modelling techniques and business knowledge to address business problems and support data-driven decision making.  You'll use a variety of tools, languages and technical knowledge to research, extract, analyse and interpret data and results with a strong commitment to quality assurance, re-usability and curation of data sources and solutions. You'll be accountable for organising your workflow and make decisions concerning your work area and team plans. You may be required to lead and manage the work of junior employees and be responsible for reviewing the quality of their work  Requirements:  • Expertise in using a variety of tools including different dialects of SQL (Teradata, MSSQL, Postgres or similar) and visualisation tools (PowerBI, COGNOS or similar)  • Skilled in extracting, analysing and interpreting data, delivering complex and technical results through logical, succinct reports and presentations  • Experience or an understanding in using version control software (Git, GitLab, TFS)  • Present complex and abstract information in an accessible and effective format suitable for their target audience  • Exercise sound judgment to provide detailed technical, professional, and policy advice in relation to complex problems and assist in strategic planning, program and project management and policy development  • Equip team members with their technical expertise and guidance to achieve a positive client experience.  Qualifications in a related discipline (i.e. Computer Science, IT, Mathematics, Statistics, etc.) would be highly regarded but not essential. Certifications in AWS, Azure, Power BI and Teradata would be looked at favourably.  Since this is a Federal Government Opportunity, it is a requirement for the candidate to be an Australian citizen.  Apply directly using the link provided or by submitting your CV. For confidential discussion, please don't hesitate to contact me:  At Randstad, we are passionate about providing equal employment opportunities and embracing diversity to the benefit of all. We actively encourage applications from any background.

job_description.220: Who are we? UpGuard’s mission is to protect the world’s data. We obsessively seek out elegant, robust ways to enable our customers to find, acknowledge, and remediate cyber risks. With UpGuard, organisations leverage our security expertise and software to automate what were once laborious, spreadsheet-driven processes–monitoring the attack surface of hundreds of vendors or assessing the security of their own infrastructure. UpGuard is used by some of the world’s largest, fastest growing and most innovative companies.  Why are we hiring for this role? As UpGuard continues to scale at an increasing rate, each of our teams, from Product to Sales, is becoming more data and insight hungry. As a result, our central Analytics and BI function is bandwidth constrained and needs to scale with our business growth.  As a Senior Business Analyst, you will be responsible for ensuring that all teams not only have access to the data they need but also provide powerful insights that can help UpGuard scale and make important decisions. You will be able to use your understanding of business structure and processes to understand stakeholder needs and provide them with the correct information and insights in the most useful and concise format.  We are looking for someone with 4+ years of experience working in both Analytics and Business Operations roles. Candidates should have a Bachelor's Degree in a Mathematical, IT, Science or Engineering field. As our team is currently small, we're looking for someone who is self-sufficient. What you will accomplish • Understand the business data needs of various teams within the organisation, from stakeholders that do and do not have a technical background. A successful candidate will not only be able to digest requirements but also converse with stakeholders in a constructive and comfortable manner, as you are providing “customer support” to other teams. • Be able to transform raw data into useful insights through the use of our Business Intelligence platform and present information in a way that conveys powerful and pertinent insights for stakeholders. Our BI platform is Looker, so we are looking for candidates who are familiar with both the Explore/Look/Dashboard side of Looker as well as have experience with the Developer side of Looker. • Be able to learn and understand our business processes, from our sales pipeline structure to our product usage metrics. • Be able to undertake projects around trend analysis, seasonality and other more complex mathematical analyses on behalf of stakeholders. • Be able to not only suggest areas of improvement for our processes, teams and infrastructure but also be able to plan, implement and test the proposed solution. What would give you an edge? We have a Google Platform-based BI-stack. These are the technologies and skill sets we are looking for: • Looker is our main BI platform: a candidate should be familiar with Explores, Looks, Dashboards and the Developer interface - maintaining dimensions and measures, creating and maintaining models, and being able to run and debug raw SQL queries. • Google Sheets when we need to explore data in more detail: you should be comfortable with functions like pivot tables, vlookup, and charting. • CloudSQL (PostgreSQL) and BigQuery for storage and query: be comfortable with writing complex queries. • Experience with broader data sourcing and storage platforms such as Google Analytics, and Sales CRMs, and how they interact and connect with one another. What's in it for you? • Rapidly growing user base: Work directly with some of the world’s largest, fastest-growing, and most innovative companies • Interesting problems, at scale: Deeply explore the ever-evolving world of cybersecurity, with a platform processing billions of data points daily • Learn from industry-leading experts: Our security research has been featured in The New York Times, The New Yorker, The Washington Post, TechCrunch, Bloomberg, Gizmodo, Engadget, Forbes, ZDNet, and The Guardian • Impact: See the impact of your work on a daily basis, with data and impact available on dashboards you have access to • Generous compensation: Competetive salary & stock options. • Great perks: Grocery and gym reimbursements, flexible work arrangements, learning and development stipend, and generous PTO package My Startup Gig ran an independent review into life at UpGuard. To see what it's like to work at UpGuard, check out their survey results here.  Before starting work with us, you will need to undertake a national police history check and reference checks. Also please note that at this time, we cannot support candidates requiring visa sponsorship or relocation.  UpGuard is an Equal Opportunity Employer and qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, colour, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender perception or identity, national origin, age, marital status, protected veteran status, or disability status.

In alignment with our commitment to fostering a flexible and dynamic work environment, we have adopted a hybrid working approach that acknowledges the importance of in-person collaboration while recognising that the determination of your work location will be based on a range of factors to ensure both individual preferences and operational requirements are met. Our culture and benefits DXC is committed to building better futures for our customers, colleagues, environment, and communities. We strive to provide an environment that lets you thrive and show off the very best version of yourself, while learning about us at the same time. About UsDXC Technology (  NYSE: DXC) helps global companies run their mission critical systems and operations while modernizing IT, optimizing data architectures, and ensuring security and scalability across public, private and hybrid clouds.  The world's largest companies and public sector organizations trust DXC to deploy services across the Enterprise Technology Stack to drive new levels of performance, competitiveness, and customer experience. job_description.222: For thousands of years, maps have provided humans with the knowledge they need to make decisions. As a Maps Data Analyst, you will have the opportunity to provide ground truth for your town, city or country.  At Peroptyx, we are looking for Data Analysts who will review mapping data for digital mapping applications. Your research capabilities will validate and ensure that the navigation of certain routes are accurate and safe.  As part of this role you will verify that business names and opening hours are correct. You will check that the distance from a starting point to an end destination is listed accurately resulting in better user experiences.  With this job you can plan your days around this highly flexible working schedule, work weekends or late evenings, all from the comfort of your own office. The flexibility of our roles minimizes the impact on your daily routine.  So, whether you are a student looking to earn as you learn, a retiree looking for a new challenge a part-time/full time professional or a work from home parent, Peroptyx has the right role for you  Ideal Candidate • Fluent in English. • Excellent research skills. • Excellent local knowledge of your home country. • Good understanding and general knowledge of the geography and culture of Australia. • Analytical mindset.  Job Requirements • Must be living in Australia for a minimum of 5 consecutive years. • Must pass an online open-book exam that can verify your full understanding of the material and concepts. • Must be willing to work a minimum of 10 hours and up to 20 hours per week depending on task availability. • Good working knowledge of search engines, map applications and familiarity with social media platforms. • Strong ability to learn, understand and apply multiple sets of different instructions. • All work must be of an independent nature.  Technical requirements to perform the work  Access to a laptop or computer which uses: - A logon account unique to you - Anti-virus solution that is kept up to date, with regular scans performed - Only one member per household may apply NB. All products should be provided at your own expense.  Benefits  · Work up to 20 hours per week. · Earn a competitive rate of pay. · Develop your research skills. · Avoid the long commute. · Work from the comfort of your home office. · Enjoy the flexibility of setting your own working hours  Apply Online Today  This is a freelance, independent contractor position. job_description.223: At EY, you’ll have the chance to build a career as unique as you are, with the global scale, support, inclusive culture and technology to become the best version of you. And we’re counting on your unique voice and perspective to help EY become even better, too. Join us and build an exceptional experience for yourself, and a better working world for all.  If we inspire you to do the work you love, will you still call it work?  What's in it for you?  We are seeking a Data Analyst to join our EY Data and Analytics team ideally in our Melbourne and Sydney offices but can also be based in any of the major Australian cities. Working with a number of high profile clients this role is offered on a flexible, full-time basis.  You will help shape, change, and deliver a data management roadmap to improve and enhance the value and re-usability of data, through modern and evolving data management practices and frameworks.  As a Data Analyst, you will support our clients in defining and implementing a data journey aligned with their strategic objectives, you will work with a diverse range of stakeholders and data teams to uplift the current data quality management capabilities of a number of different high profile client groups.  We are open to candidates located in Melbourne, Sydney, Brisbane, Perth or Canberra for this role.  What we're looking for • Translating business questions to data and analysis requirements; carry out analysis, visualization and presentation. • Performing ad-hoc analysis to solve business problems and support decisions. • Design and build data products, such as Power BI dashboards, including defining the data models. • Surfacing and sharing insights, typically from internal corporate data, using a dashboard. • Run human centred design sessions with end-users. • Communicating and influencing stakeholders. • Coaching non-data experts how to use data.  Skills and attributes for success • Experience in a hands-on role interpreting and telling stories with data. • Curious and business outcome focused with an ability to break down a complex problem and work out how to solve it. • Evidence of numerical and technical aptitude strong collaboration skills having worked with business stakeholders at different levels of seniority. • Comfortable working across a wide range of data sets and systems: • Expertise in cleansing, combining and processing data. • Have knowledge of SQL, with knowledge of Python an advantage. • Familiarity with Power BI and ideally data manipulation tools (e.g. Alteryx and Daraiku).  What we can offer you • Explore how a career at EY is yours to build at www.ey.com/au/careerdevelopment • Discover how, when and where you can work at www.ey.com/au/flexibility • Learn about our commitment to DE&I at www.ey.com/au/diversity-inclusiveness • Understand how our benefits can support you at www.ey.com/au/benefits  Acknowledgement of Country  EY acknowledges the Traditional Owners and Custodians of the lands on which EY offices are located around Australia. We pay our respects to their cultures, and to their Elders — past, present, and emerging. Find out more about our vision for reconciliation at www.ey.com/au/reconciliation  Apply now… we’re over 9,000 perspectives in Australia and we’re ready to welcome yours.  At EY we take inclusivity seriously, and we’re committed to removing barriers and improving the employment prospects of people with disability or long-term health conditions. We encourage you to share any support and adjustments you need to be your best and participate equitably in our recruitment process. We understand sharing your needs with us can be daunting, so if you have questions before or during your application, we welcome you to get in touch at contactrecruitment@au.ey.com or +61 3 8650 7788 (option 2). Anything you tell us will be kept completely confidential.  The exceptional EY experience. It’s yours to build.  The preferred applicant will be subject to employment screening by EY or by their external third party provider. Regarding this role, the minimum salary is $90,000 including 11% superannuation.  EY | Building a better working world  EY exists to build a better working world, helping to create long-term value for clients, people and society and build trust in the capital markets.  Enabled by data and technology, diverse EY teams in over 150 countries provide trust through assurance and help clients grow, transform and operate.  Working across assurance, consulting, law, strategy, tax and transactions, EY teams ask better questions to find new answers for the complex issues facing our world today.
job_description.224: See job description for details  Excellent Data Analyst Opportunity with Leading Banking org • 6-month contract opportunity with a leading banking firm • Experience in the financial industry preferred • Australian PRs or citizenship mandatory Your new company Our client - leading banking firm and market leader, one of the four largest financial institutions in Australia in terms of market capitalisation, earnings and customers. They are on the lookout for Data Analyst to develop and deliver, reporting, analysis and insights across the Home Ownership businesses which aides and influences strategic direction and decision making  Your new role: As the Analyst, Data Analytics - you will be an integral member of the team for the duration of the Proprietary Home Lending Performance Reporting project. You will support the Manager Home Ownership Analytics in leading the development of an end to end acquisition funnel dashboard for the Retail Distribution business and engaging with key business stakeholders within Home Ownership and Retail Distribution to gather requirements, validate data and showcase development progress. The Home Ownership Analytics team play a significant role in aiding and influencing the strategic direction and decision making of the Home Ownership businesses with the provision of timely and accurate data a key to ensuring the efficient management of the business day to day.  Key accountabilities of the role: • With the support of the team, the development and delivery of critical data, reporting and analysis for Proprietary Home Lending performance reporting initiative including management of data and reporting in Power BI • Engaging with business stakeholders to confirm requirements, validate data and showcase delivery progress • Aid in the development of data models within the Home Ownership data environment to support the end to end acquisition funnel reporting. • Working collaboratively with team members and key business stakeholders. What you'll need to succeed: • Tertiary qualification in business, commerce, marketing or related discipline. • 2 years+ experience in data and analytics in Financial Services or related industry. • Ability to work with management and influence outcomes. • Ability to work at a fast pace but maintain accuracy and quality • Ability to be flexible and efficient • Ability to be highly organised and able to prioritise and multi task • Ability to be a self-starter but work well as part of a team • Ability to build strong networks with internal stakeholders What you'll get in return • Excellent contract opportunity • An opportunity to work on high-profile projects with competitive remuneration package. job_description.225: The Opportunity  We have an exciting opportunity for a Health & Safety Data Analyst to come and join our team. In this role, you will support the development of the Power BI dashboard and coordinate monthly Health &Safety performance data and reporting on trends analysis in corporate reporting.  Key responsibilities: • Support the development and analysis of health & safety performance data across the ACCIONA Group. This involves collecting, analysing and interpreting data to identify trends, insights and areas for improvement. • Create and maintain Power BI dashboards and prepare group monthly reports. • Critically evaluate and analyse information across multiple sources, reconcile conflicts and resolve or escalate to relevant stakeholders. • Effectively communicate data insights to the business and work with key stakeholders to ensure that insights are being effectively utilised to drive business value. • Conduct project Audits verifying the quality of data being provided is in line with ACCIONA requirements. • Assist data integration projects between different system tools. We are searching for someone that will want to own the technical design, development and delivery of business intelligence systems, reports and analysis for a growing division across Australia. If this sounds like you, we have an excellent career growth opportunity for a graduate to join our Employee Benefits team in our Melbourne office, and we want to hear from you!  About Arsenault  Since our foundation in 1966, Arsenault has grown to become the worlds largest privately owned insurance broker. The Arsenault company structure has produced a unique culture where we empower our Associates to think independently. With a 98% client retention rate in Australia and leading expertise across insurance and risk management, we now have over 160 staff located in Perth, Melbourne, Brisbane, Hobart, Adelaide, Auckland, Hamilton and Christchurch.  What will you be doing? • Developing and maintaining a SQL based reporting platform • Managing and developing data integration pipelines, data storage structures and data cleansing • Gathering data requirements, documentation and end to end testing • Gathering, clarifying and documenting requirements and designing solutions • Data product design, development, and maintenant for visualisations, reports, dashboards, and data insights • Interpreting data and analysing results using statistical techniques to create monthly reports • Serving internal clients and ensuring accurate, on time delivery of monthly reporting  To be successful in this role, you will need to: • Have great communication (verbal and written) and interpersonal skills • Have the ability to learn quickly and take initiative • Be capable of following directions and working collaboratively with others, while simultaneously also be self-motivated • Build relationships with various stakeholders in a robust office environment  You will need the following experience and qualifications: • Bachelor of Information Technology, Computer Science, Data Science or a related discipline • Proficient in Microsoft Office Suite • Knowledge of SQL Server (data profiling and querying) and VBA • Knowledge of Azure, Power BI, R, Python is an asset, we will train the right candidate • Experience using Git source control is an asset • Experience with project coordination and management is an asset  We offer: • An agile/hybrid work environment • A focus on training and development opportunities and mentoring program • Discounted corporate private health insurance and a free flu vaccination program • Salary Continuance insurance to protect you and your family in the event you suffer an illness or injury • Paid parental leave and volunteer leave • Access to Uprise employee assistance program including coaching and counselling • Social activities and community engagement organized by our new wellness committee  Arsenault is an equal opportunity employer. We strongly encourage applications from people of all backgrounds, ages, religions, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Peoples, LGBTIQ+ people, those with a disability, women and people with a cultural or linguistically diverse background.
job_description.227: About the Opportunity:  Kinetic IT have recently partnered with a major Federal Government department to provide Enterprise Service Management and provide a comprehensive range of IT Service Management and SIAM practices across the organisation!  We are now on the lookout for an experienced Data Analyst to join our team to further enhance our service integration and management capabilities.  About you:  Your expertise in data visualisation and continuous improvement recommendations will ensure our stakeholders will be making informed decisions, identifying opportunities for improvement and driving continual service enhancement within the SIAM ecosystem. You will play a vital role in collecting, analysing and presenting performance data to support data-driven decision making. You will also be supporting root cause analysis during major incidents and assisting in trend forecasting and SLA compliance analysis.  Day to day your duties will include: • Ensuring data accuracy, completeness and consistency within the SIAM ecosystem • Cleaning and pre-processing of data, ensuring it is ready for analysis. • Creating reporting frameworks (dashboards, scorecards and periodic reports) to present performance data to senior leaders • Root cause analysis • Designing of data collection methods to gather performance data from various service providers and create a comprehensive view of service performance.  Sound like a role for you? You’ll need some of the following: • Hold ACTIVE status & maintain a minimum Government Security Clearance • Experience with data analytics in an ITIL-aligned enterprise environment • Experience in ServiceNow and ServiceNow dashboards and reporting solutions • High level technical writing (for processes and framework design), reporting and documentation skills. • Cognos reporting • Microsoft SQL Server Management Studio, SQL Server Data Tools and/ or Visual Studio Reporting Services • Microsoft Power Pivot, Excel, Performance Analytics • Experience performing data extraction from data warehouses. • Experience writing SQL Queries  The Kinetic IT Difference • Flexible working, paid parental leave, and other benefits tailored to your individual goals. • Regular fun company and social events – Sundowner, Family Fun Day, Quiz Night and End of Year Party • Vendor Exam Support, ITIL V4 Training and Communities of Practice groups • Dedicated professional development reviews every 6 months, with monthly follow ups • An open and supportive culture where we respect all people and individuals, and everyone has a voice  About KineticIT  We are recognised market leaders in the delivery of high-quality technology solutions to large public, private, and government organisations. As an Australian-owned company, we take a lot of pride in delivering exceptional service that exceeds our customers’ expectations and positively contributing to our industry and community. We hire for the long term and have a strong focus on training and developing our employees. Everyday our amazing 1,300+ crew come to Kinetic IT not just to work but to be challenged, grow and be part of something bigger.  Check out more at kineticit.com.au  How To Apply  First, check out our website Kineticit.com.au. If you like what you see then, click on the ‘Apply’ button or contact our careers account on careers@kineticit.com.au and quote ‘data analyst’
job_description.228: About the job Data Analyst  JD for Data Insights & Analytics Analyst role :  As a Data Insights & Analytics Analyst, you are an important contributor to analysing business  problems and recommending solutions which drive data decision making within our organisation.  You will also be working closely with Data Engineering & Data Science teammates and the Product  Owner on identifying and documenting technical and business requirements to facilitate the  development of new data solutions. To be successful in this role, you will ideally be experienced in  working with Data warehouse solutions for a large organisation coupled with Business Analyst skills.  You will be responsible for :  Probe, source and manipulate large data sets to resolve issues or develop a solution to enable  business decisions  Defining business Problems, assist with the development of hypothesis, undertake relevant  reporting, summarise insights and make recommendations for actions.  Investigating and analysing large datasets to help resolve business problems or develop a  solution to enable business decisions.  Visualising data using Power BI, and creating dashboards that integrate data from multiple  source systems to analyse, track and report on different Metrics. job_description.231: Overview This role is responsible for driving the delivery of data solutions to internal and external stakeholders. This is a broad-ranging role, including understanding the business requirements, data modelling, data profiling/analysis, design data solution (data flow), preparing technical documentation, production support, data mapping and data reconciliation and other support needs as required. • Multiple Day rate contract roles finishing end of March 2024 or June 2024. • Flexible location: Melbourne CBD or Parramatta  Key Accountabilities and main responsibilities Strategic Focus • Analyse Business Requirement Documents to identify technical solutions in consultation with the Feature Engineers considering all databases, application, business process and system implications. • Consult with clients (new/potential) to discuss requirements and provide appropriate data solutions for product delivery. People Leadership • Mentor members of the team • Work closely with Development and Operations team  Governance & Risk • Escalate any behaviour or conduct in breach of our Code of Conduct is as appropriate • Complied with all relevant legal obligations and adhere to Link Group policies and procedures • Report all incidents of non-conformity, noncompliance and unethical behaviour immediately to your manager • Complete all allocated compliance training by the due date  Experience & Personal Attributes • Minimum 2 years of demonstrable competency as Technical Analyst or equivalent role (Min. 10 years for Senior Systems Analyst) • Working knowledge and application of SQL • Knowledge and skills sets associated with extracting, gathering and combining data for data analysis and data profiling activities • Ability to analyse large amount of data and provide feedback and recommendations to stakeholders • Excellent analytical and problem solving skills and ability to drive operational and business transformations as needed • Excellent verbal and written communication skills, including presentation skills • Excellent time management and good prioritisation skills • Sound understanding of IT application and system design best practice
job_description.232: Full Job Description $90K - $100K + Super + Salary Packaging Location: Melbourne, Sydney or remote Use data to make a positive impact  Data & Insights Analyst - Fundraising & Marketing Salary: $90K - $100K + Super + Salary packing Location: Melbourne, Sydney or remote Opportunities to continually advance your Data Analytics career. We are seeking candidates with a strong background in proven data and data insights expertise. This role goes beyond merely aggregating data into basic tabular reports; it involves the ability to comprehend and present insights in a compelling manner. These insights will not only significantly impact the donor experience but also go beyond seeking new financial opportunities. We are looking for individuals who are actively dedicated to enhancing our business offerings.  About the role…  In this role, you will be tasked with pioneering innovative approaches to harness consumer behavioural data. Your goal is to derive descriptive and prescriptive insights that will guide optimal decision-making. Additionally, you will be responsible for creating interactive and automated dashboards that empower our fundraising team to make strategic decisions through proactive in-depth analysis and insights.  Key responsibilities…  Build and Provide insights for the individual giving team in fundraising. Develop subject matter expertise in the various channels used by the individual giving team. Engage with business users to consult and recommend best possible way to answer their business data questions. Provide rapid answers to business questions using a mix of queries and visualisations. Support ad hoc data requests from across business areas. Design and build reporting data models that support user self-serve reporting. Identify data to integrate with the warehouse to develop actionable insights to drive business decisions. Build customer segmentation analytics and campaign performance reporting. Proactively organising training and development activities for business to facilitate adaption. Design, build, test and present meaningful insights from a complex range of data.  Skills and experience  Bachelor’s degree in computer science, statistics, mathematics, economics, or a related field. 3-5 years of experience in data analytics, business intelligence, or related field. 1-2 years’ experience working with fundraising teams Experience with data visualisation and querying tools such as Power BI and SQL. Strong analytical and problem-solving skills. Knowledge of data modelling, data warehousing, and ETL processes. Strong ability to work in T-SQL and DAX queries. Ability to communicate complex technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders. Experience in developing and maintaining reports, dashboards, and visualisations. Knowledge of fundraising and marketing analytics and metrics. Ability to work independently and as part of a team in a fast-paced environment. Strong attention to detail and accuracy.  More about the role…  Furthermore, you will play a vital role in supporting the enhancement of consumer engagement strategies and product-specific initiatives. Leveraging technical solutions and advanced analytics, you will be at the forefront of developing ground breaking solutions for consumer profiling and segmentation. Through your work in extracting insights from diverse data sources, you will drive strategic and operational initiatives. These initiatives will lead to increased revenue, improved efficiency, cost optimisation, and an elevated supporter experience, ultimately contributing to the organisation's success and sustainable growth.  A little about our client…  Mission Australia, a renowned national charity with over 160 years of dedicated service, is on a mission to help vulnerable Australians find their path to independence. They are committed to tackling homelessness, supporting struggling families, addressing mental health challenges, and fighting substance dependencies. Mission Australia thrives on the support of everyday Australians, corporate partners, and a passionate team of professionals.  Next step is to APPLY…  Ready to embark on an epic journey where your data skills make a real difference? Send us your application, including a cover letter and resume, send it through Beaumont People now! Join Mission Australia and become a data wizard on a mission to end homelessness and help communities thrive! Apply now and be part of something truly magical!  Don’t tick all the boxes? If you would like to have a confidential chat, please contact Jack or Dean on 02 9133 9322 or email dean@beaumontpeople.com.au  Beaumont People believe a diverse workplace is a happy workplace, and we love working with organisations that feel the same way. job_description.234: About ViVi  Vivi is the only wireless screen mirroring and digital signage tool designed for education. We enable K-12 organizations to realize more value from their existing investments in display technology and student devices, by providing more consistent and reliable experiences for students, teachers and staff to connect, communicate and collaborate.  Vivi exists because we all had that one teacher who changed our lives, who went above and beyond to serve as a role model and sage. They guided discussion, connected with their students on a personal level, were just as engaging and entertaining as they were educational, and they created a dynamic learning environment by constantly involving students.  Personalized learning environments have been proven to deliver better educational outcomes for individuals through increased participation and engagement. To successfully create such an environment requires a fluid, visual dialogue between teacher and student. This is why Vivi exists.   Vivi is used by over 500,000 teachers and students in more than 90,000 classrooms around the world and is setting out to disrupt the enormous education industry with our high-growth, ambitious, and creative team.  What You’ll Be Doing • Building and maintaining production level data pipelines using various tools such as AWS Glue, Python, Lambda etc. that populate business critical dashboards as needed • Performing data analysis as required, and promptly preparing reports with the findings/results • Building custom analyses, reports, dashboards using tools in Vivi’s BI stack • Building/maintaining components of the Data Warehouse as per the Architecture using CI/CD • Implementing the BI Data Quality Framework • Supporting the business stakeholders with ad hoc BI and data requests • Working with internal customers, Engineering, Product and support teams to prioritise requests and reports • Identifying opportunities to establish/improve the processes and practices • Creating relevant documentation as required  About You • You have 2-5 years’ experience in a similar role, working on cloud data pipelines • Knowledge of AWS or Azure Cloud technologies • Knowledge of the following would be ideal – Power BI, Python, SQL, Postgres, Excel • Excellent analytical skills • Excellent communication and presentation skills • Excellent documentation skills • Exposure to the Atlassian suite of tools, e.g. Jira and Confluence • Exposure to agile working practices • Comfortable in a fast-paced start-up environment  What We Can Offer You • Career progression – we offer each employee an annual $1000 L&D budget to assist with furthering their skills • Wellness program – including wellness days off and subsidised ClassPass subscription • Give back to the community with our Volunteer program • Birthdays off each year  Vivi is an equal opportunity employer. This means we are committed to recruiting, training, compensating and promoting our employees regardless of Race, Color, Ancestry, National Origin, Religion, Creed, Age, Disability, Sex, Gender, Sexual Orientation, Gender Identity, Gender expression, Medical condition, Genetic Information, Marital status, or Military or Veteran status. As an education technology organization, we are dedicated to reflecting the diversity, multiculturalism, and inclusion found in our consumers, employees, and partners. Inclusion is at the heart of what we do, from the way we craft our job descriptions, to the values we champion daily.
job_description.235: The Hospital:  The Royal Children's Hospital's (RCH) Vision is "A world where all kids thrive".  RCH is a cornerstone member of the Melbourne Children's Campus, partnering with Murdoch Children's Research Institute, The University of Melbourne Department of Pediatrics and The Royal Children's Hospital Foundation.  RCH has cared for the children and young people of Victoria for more than 150 years since it was founded in 1870. A full range of paediatric and adolescent health services are provided plus tertiary and quaternary care for the most critically ill and medically complex patients in Victoria, Tasmania, southern NSW and other states around Australia and overseas. The Hospital has more than 6,000 staff, a budget of $850M, 12 wards and 350 beds. Annually, the RCH has 300,000+ Specialist Clinic appointments, 90,000+ Emergency Department presentations and 20,000 elective surgeries.  The RCH is committed to the Child Safe Standards.  RCH enjoys high employee engagement and is committed to staff safety and a positive culture through enactment of our Compact.  For further Information on RCH is available here.  Job Title: Data Analyst Grade 6 – Decision Support Unit • Excellent employee benefits including salary packaging • Hub of medical precinct in Parkville, Melbourne • Flexible work options available  About the Role  This is a permanent full time position at 1 .0 FTE / 80 hours per fortnight within the Decision Support Unit. You will be responsible for report and extract development along with maintenance and analysis tasks primarily using Epic's Clarity database and Decision Support's enterprise data warehouse. You will work with the RCH Departments to understand and support the hospital's reporting and data extraction requirements.  What you'll achieve: • Contribute to achieving RCH objectives through the development of reporting capacity in the DSU across different areas. • Perform analysis of reporting requirements, enhancement requests and other technical issues associated with the EMR and the DSU data warehouse. • Establish productive relations with key stakeholders and other data providers.  Classification for this position will range from AO61 – AO65 (base salary $106,464 to $109,319 per annum, plus superannuation)  Your skills and experience: • A tertiary degree in Computer Science or related field (or equivalent experience). • Advanced skills in the development and deployment of reports using Microsoft Power BI reports or similar tools. • Experience with data integration, the use of BI tools and relational databases.  If this sounds like you, click here to view the position description.  About the Decision Support Unit  The Decision Support Unit provides mission critical data and reporting to all areas of the hospital to assist in the achievement of performance management initiatives and strategic goals. This includes data extraction, funding and revenue analysis, patient costing and benchmarking with external organisations.  What we offer: • Staff Wellbeing Hub • Early Learning Centre childcare • Discounted on-site car parking  Other requirements: • Current National Criminal Record Check, or willingness to obtain • Valid Working with Children Check • Compliance with RCHs "Staff Immunisation - Prevention of Vaccine Preventable Diseases" procedure  Application process  To apply, you will need a resume and a tailored cover letter outlining your skills, experience, and suitability for the position in line with the requirements of the position description.  Shortlisting for this position will commence immediately, we encourage you to apply promptly  For more information about this position please contact Chris Jackson, Manager, Decision Support, Ph: (03) 93456841, Email:  Why work at the RCH?  RCH enjoys high employee engagement and is committed to staff safety and a positive culture through enactment of our Compact. We offer the opportunity to work in world-class facilities, surrounded by Royal Park and only a short tram trip from the heart of Melbourne city.  We also offer discounted staff parking, salary packaging, and an award-winning health and wellbeing program.  The RCH is committed to a diverse and inclusive workforce. We encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, people from culturally and/or linguistically diverse background, all members of the LGBTQI community and people with disability.  It is a requirement of your employment that you be fully vaccinated against Covid-19, and Influenza annually for Category A and B roles, in compliance with any public health orders in place at the relevant time, unless you have a medical exception in line with those public health orders, which has been accepted by The Royal Children's Hospital. job_description.240: Company Description  illion is the leading independent provider of trusted data and analytics products and services in Australia and New Zealand. illion leverages its consumer and commercial credit registries to provide end-to-end customer management solutions to clients in the financial services, telecommunications, utilities and government sectors.  Job Description  Your new role and how you’ll make a difference  Are you ready for your next career move in finance and want autonomy and freedom to develop your experience quickly across all areas of the P&L.  FP&A at illion operates through an integrated business partner approach, working with the business to provide commercial insight into historical and future results that will enable the management team to make better business decisions. This is done through closely collaborating with business partners to understand the core drivers of business performance and develop relevant metrics and timely reports that measure, monitor and report on performance.  This key role within finance will also work with financial and non-financial systems (e.g. TM1, Great Plains, Salesforce and proprietary systems) to create integrated KPI and finance reporting for management and the board. You will need to be willing to get your hands dirty in systems interrogation and report building to be successful.  The value-add things you’ll be doing • Support the Head of FP&A and GM Finance by working with key stakeholders to understand key business drivers of sales, revenue and opex and use this knowledge to identify future opportunities and issues so that appropriate action can be taken in advance • Identify trends and model future impacts and outcomes • Ad-hoc financial analysis where required • KPI reporting and interpretation as leading and lagging indicators of financial performance • Sales and Revenue reporting by Customer & Product • Assist the business to understand and interpret the financial information in the system and reports to enable management to plan, evaluate, control and enhance performance of their areas of responsibility in the business. • Support the business in the use of the system through developing relevant, system driven dashboard and management accounting reports that can be readily accessed and understood by the business managers. • Preparation of the monthly management pack. job_description.241: • Join a collaborative team and deliver great employee experiences. • Experience Hybrid working arrangements in a flexible environment • Permanent role based in either Melbourne or Sydney  We're REA  REA Group is not your average digital business. From humble beginnings in a garage in Melbourne’s east in 1995, we have grown into a leading global digital business, specialising in property.  With bold and ambitious goals, we are changing the way the world experiences property. No matter where you're at on your property journey, we're here to help with every step - whether that's finding or financing your next home.  Our people are the key to our success. At the heart of everything we do, is a thriving culture centred around high performance and care. We are purpose driven and collaborative, which drives innovation and our ability to make a real impact. As such, we’re proud to be named in Australia’s “Top 5” Best Workplaces two years in a row, as well as being recognised as a Best Workplace for Women.  Where the team fits in  The Data and Insights Analyst sits within the People & Culture team, headed up by Mary Lemonis,  Chief People and Sustainability Officer. From building management capability and the next  generation of leaders, to creating a diversity and inclusion strategy which is mainstreamed and  embedded into everything we do – the People & Culture team is all about making REA Group a great place to work. Supporting our multi-national business with HR processes, policies and systems to meet the needs of our people around the world, the team works to build high engagement with our impressive offering of programs and benefits.  What The Role Is All About  We are looking for a technically focussed Data and Insights Analyst who is passionate about People data and insights. You’ll be supporting the People & Culture team with key employee life cycle activities related to our specialist functions of Remuneration, Payroll and Work Health and Safety. You’ll contribute your subject matter expertise and work with a wide a range of activities and stakeholders. • Working closely with our Remuneration Manager, managing job evaluations, equity administration and cyclical rem processes like year end reviews and market data submissions, ensuring an efficient process, up to date information and fit for purpose solutions • Reviewing and supporting current WHS processes and policies, and determining what potential efficiencies can be made using technology and effective collaboration with key stakeholders • Assisting with payroll reporting, in particular making the best use of our new payroll reporting functionality in the Ramco payroll system. • Using modelling, statistics, trend analysis, and other data analysis techniques to collect, explore, identify, and analyse data.  Who We’re Looking For • Intermediate to advanced Excel skills • Super strong attention to detail • Strong background and demonstrated experience in reporting and analytics, data science, continuous improvement • General problem-solving skills and ability to think creatively • Work productively in a fast-paced environment • Relevant qualification associated with data and analytics will be preferable • Data Analytics - using modeling, statistics, trend analysis, and other data analysis techniques to collect, explore, identify, and analyze data. • Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal and the sensitivity to understand audience needs and adapt style accordingly • Translating business requirements into clear, concise, testable and accurate user stories & process flows; • Time management and prioritisation • Experience working with HR/ People analytics • Experience with Workday & Ramco is advantageous but not essential • Broad knowledge and understanding of people management principles and practices • Ability to work independently and cooperatively with business and technical resources  The REA Experience  The physical, mental, emotional and financial health of our people is something we’ll never stop caring about. This is a place to learn and grow. We’re committed to your development – both professionally and personally. Your experience with us is something we take seriously.  We offer: • A hybrid and flexible approach to working - https://rea.to/hybrid-working • Flexible parental leave offering for primary and secondary carers • Programs to support mental, emotional, financial and physical health & wellbeing • Our Because We Care program offers employees volunteering leave, community grants, matched payroll giving and our Community Café donates 100% of revenue to charity. • Hack Days so you can bring your big ideas to life • Performance recognition programs because hard work should never go unnoticed  Our commitment to Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion  We are committed to providing a working environment that embraces and values diversity, equity and inclusion. We believe teams with diverse ideas and experiences are more creative, more eﬀective and fuel disruptive thinking - be it cultural and ethnic backgrounds, gender identity, disability, age, sexual orientation, or any other identity or lived experience. We know diverse teams are critical to maintaining our success and driving new business opportunities. If you've got the skills, dedication and enthusiasm to learn but don't necessarily meet every single point on the job description, please still get in touch.  If you like the sound of us, then we think you should apply today. We're proud to be Circle Back Initiative Employer and we commit to respond to every applicant. While we're looking at your application, and preparing to come back to you with an update, why not get to know us a bit more through our various social channels?
job_description.242: Work options: Hybrid  The purpose of Customer Insights and Reporting team is to support the entire OnePass business by enabling more sophisticated uses of data across OnePass and our partnering Divisions. This team is responsible for establishing a self-service reporting capability within the business, for designing, building and maintaining reports to support management and operational decision making, and for responding to ad-hoc analysis needs. This team is also responsible for designing advanced analytical solutions to business or customer problems and working with domain teams to deploy these solutions.  What You’ll Be Doing  We are seeking a highly skilled and detail-oriented Senior Data Analyst to join our dynamic team. As a Senior Data Analyst, you will be responsible for collecting, analysing, and interpreting complex data sets to extract valuable insights and drive data-informed decision-making. Your expertise in data manipulation, statistical analysis, and data visualisation will contribute to the success of OnePass by identifying trends, patterns, and opportunities for improvement. You will collaborate with cross-functional teams to support data-driven initiatives and deliver actionable recommendations. The ideal candidate is passionate about data, possesses strong analytical skills, and is comfortable working in a fast-paced and evolving environment.  Key Duties And Deliverables • Acquire and cleanse large and diverse data sets from various sources to ensure data integrity and quality. • Apply statistical techniques and data mining methods to extract meaningful insights from complex data sets. • Conduct exploratory data analysis and identify trends, patterns, and correlations. • Create clear and concise visualisations, dashboards, and reports to present data-driven insights to stakeholders. • Develop interactive dashboards using data visualisation tools to facilitate understanding and exploration of data. • Collaborate with team members to create automated reports and streamline data analysis processes. • Monitor and evaluate key performance indicators (KPIs) to assess the effectiveness of business processes and strategies. • Identify areas for improvement and provide recommendations based on data analysis findings. • Work closely with stakeholders to define and track performance metrics aligned with business objectives. • Collaborate with cross-functional teams to understand their data requirements and provide analytical support. • Translate complex data findings into actionable insights and recommendations. • Contribute to strategic planning by leveraging data insights to identify business opportunities and risks. • Ensure data accuracy, consistency, and compliance with data governance policies. • Develop and implement data validation procedures to identify and resolve data quality issues. • Stay updated with industry best practices and emerging trends in data analytics and data management.  Key Relationships  Reports To  Reporting and Analytics Lead  What you will need • Bachelor's degree in a relevant field such as Computer Science, Statistics, Mathematics, or a related discipline. • Proven work experience as a Data Analyst or similar role in a product-driven organization (3+ years) • Strong proficiency in SQL and experience with data querying from databases. • Proficiency in data visualisation tools such as Tableau, Power BI, or similar. • Experience with statistical analysis, A/B testing, and data modelling techniques. • Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with attention to detail. • Excellent communication and presentation skills to convey complex data insights to diverse audiences. • Ability to collaborate effectively with cross-functional teams and influence decision-making. • Familiarity with product management methodologies and product development lifecycle. • Knowledge of web analytics and tag management tools (e.g., Google Analytics/Adobe/Tealium) Equipment / Technology used • Corporate Office desktop operating environments • Snowflake • Kafka • Google Analytics • Power BI • Tealium • Confluence & JIRA • Miro & Murali  Why OneDigital? • Working in a community of industry-leading innovators with a diverse and deep set of skills and experience, you will learn, collaborate, and co-create to achieve great things. • You’ll have ownership of your role, which will allow you to find the right balance between stretch and sustainability, work, and life. • Culture of comradery and collaboration - OneTeam • Plus, all the tools and learning you need, the tone is set for you to shine and succeed. • We know that diversity fosters greater innovation and better customer connection, so we strive to create a team where everyone feels like they belong. We support diversity, inclusion and we are a gender-neutral organisation. We celebrate individuals at their core, so they shine to their best.  Team Benefits – just to name a few!  To support you at work, what you value in life and in the community, our team member benefits include: • Access to the latest technologies • An annual budget for your learning and development (this includes learning of your choice, certifications and more) • Extended parental leave (16 weeks for primary carers), and paid volunteer days • Flexible working – we balance working together with working flexibly • People-focussed culture that celebrates achievements big and small • Oh, and did I mention paid subscriptions and discount cards.  Next steps  If this sounds like your next career move, then click on the ‘Apply’ button now. Please note that we may commence interviewing candidates prior to the application closing date.
job_description.243: Mathematics, Statistics & Information Sciences (Science & Technology) SEEK's portfolio of diverse businesses make a positive impact on a truly global scale. Our purpose is to help people live more fulfilling and productive working lives and help organisations succeed. We create world-class technology solutions to connect more people to relevant employment, education, small business and volunteer opportunities.  We have a culture of high-performance in our workplaces and celebrate the diversity of our employees who contribute to the success of our organisation. Life at SEEK SEEK's purpose is at the centre of everything we do.  Our SEEK , which defines the way we work, is all about what makes us unique and a little bit different. Passion, Team, Delivery and Future are our principles that drive innovation and creativity.  SEEK strives to support employee wellbeing by providing an amazing experience at work which led us to being named AFR BOSS Top 10 Best Place to Work 2023 In Tech (third year in a row). We are proud to work in an environment that's inclusive where everyone's unique ideas, experiences and perspectives are valued.  Our award-winning head office in Cremorne (just a 4 min walk from Richmond station) provides an exceptional space to collaborate with colleagues.  The building provides sweeping views of the city, a games area, sit and stand desks at every workstation, modern end-of-trip facilities and Thursday night drinks which gives our people an opportunity to connect in a social setting. Job Description About the role  As a Senior Data Scientist you will provide technical and project leadership to an established Machine Learning / Data Science capability driving global SEEK growth.  You will add value by creating data analytics and machine learning assets that influence or automate important business decisions, by bringing new technical and delivery capability to the team, by breaking down big rocks into small rocks in Agile fashion to enable team productivity, and by liaising with Product Managers, Engineers, and partners company-wide to remove impediments.  Your breadth and depth of expertise will enable your highly engaged colleagues to grow, and your experience will help the team understand the best time to use and not use each capability. You are motivated by science, i.e.  , you:  think of the simplest practical model that closes a knowledge gap; design experiments; learn from the data; provide predictions that matter; and refine your models and hypothesis as needed. You are continuously learning and growing and so is the team. You will demonstrate success through enriching SEEK's ability to make great data-driven decisions quickly.  You will consistently demonstrate technical leadership that advances the team's ability to deploy state-of-the-art decision capabilities that produce great outcomes for the health of the jobs marketplace. The Team  TheArtificial Intelligence Platform Services(AIPS) is structured into cross-disciplinary squad with members from Data Science, Strategy and Engineering who work together to research, design, build and support end-to-end machine learning based products delivering direct value to hirers and job seekers. AIPS has a matrix structure where your direct line manager will act as a coach and technical mentor, but your day-to-day activity will be determined by the squad priorities  Key accountabilities include: Forming clear data addressable problem statements from current business problems Gathering, validating, and understanding data relevant to the problem statement Designing and building data transformation pipelines and machine learning algorithms to solve the business problem Working with product management and other business stakeholders to review and iterate data products to fit emerging market trends Evangelising appropriate ML methods and explaining them, and their associated benefits and limitations to team members from Engineering and Strategy  Qualifications Skills and experience A MSc or PhD qualification in Computer Science, Computational Physics, Mathematics, Statistics, or a related field  Professional experience in one of the following programming languages:Large scale development using Python, R, SAS, Go, C/C++, or Java using Git, CI/CD, etc.  Strong background in: Statistics and Machine Learning Algorithms and data structures  Good communication and interpersonal skills Experience with Agile methodology Depth in Natural Language Processing, Optimisation, Discrete Event Simulation, or another specialised Data Science domain  Additional Information Perks and benefits Permanent Perks  At SEEK we offer: Annual Performance Bonus Plan Support of flexible working, including a mix of office and work from home days depending on your role. Paid and unpaid leave benefits including Personal Flexi Days and Volunteer Days, as well as the opportunity to purchase additional leave Support for parents with 14 weeks paid primary carers leave and 2 weeks paid leave for partners The opportunity to work from anywhere for up to 4 weeks per financial year  Here at SEEK we pride ourselves on harbouring a flexible and inclusive working environment.  Should you require any specific support or adjustments throughout the recruitment process and beyond, please advise us and we will be happy to assist. For this role, only those candidates with the eligible right to work will be considered.  SEEK kindly requests no unsolicited resumes or approaches from recruitment agencies and will not be responsible for any associated fees. job_description.246: Strategic Intelligence Analyst and Data Custodian, Forensics and Information Management Branch • One (1) ongoing role in the Forensics and Information Management Branch, Corporate Services Division • Salary $105,479 plus 11% superannuation, VPS Grade 5 • Based in Melbourne CBD or Ballarat, with flexibility to work from home  What we offer  The State Revenue Office is the Victorian Government's revenue management agency, administering a range of taxes, duties, levies, grants and subsidies.  We aim to develop our people to achieve great outcomes for the Victorian community. We offer flexible working arrangements and a workplace culture that is rewarding and productive, where contributions are valued and recognised, expectations are clear, and treatment is fair and equitable. We are an equal opportunity employer that is committed to providing an inclusive, accessible and safe working environment.  Find out more about working at the SRO at sro.vic.gov.au/careers, or via our LinkedIn page.  The opportunity  The Strategic Intelligence Analyst and Data Custodian is responsible for undertaking complex research and analysis projects in areas relating to compliance with State Legislation, organisational compliance, strategic and tactical intelligence, and policy development. The position requires a person with a record of achievement in complex data analysis in the public or private sector.  Reporting to the Compliance Analysis and Data Quality Manager, you will be responsible for: • Undertaking high level analysis and research tasks relating to organisational compliance and revenue issues and prepare associated research papers and reports. • Consolidating data inputs and the receipt and dissemination of data to internal and external stakeholders. • Producing daily and monthly branch and divisional reports and monitoring and analysis of revenue collections against forecasts. • Providing expert analytical advice to senior management on revenue collections and matters under investigation. • Providing information to Treasury and other internal and external stakeholders relating to revenue collection matters and providing timely and appropriate responses to information/reports sought.  Who we are looking for  To be successful in this role, you will have: • Demonstrated record of achievement as a senior analyst, preferably in a tax or revenue field, enabling the translation of data insights into actionable business strategies. • Demonstrated ability to analyse complex datasets, extract meaningful insights, and make data-driven decisions through advanced analytical techniques. • Profound understanding and application of statistical methodologies and techniques, and the ability to apply them effectively to solve real-world problems using specialised analytical software packages. • Demonstrated ability to effectively plan, coordinate and manage work activities both in a team and independently with minimal direction. • Strong verbal and written communication skills to present findings, explain methodologies, and collaborate with cross-functional teams.  How to apply  Submit an application via the ‘Apply now' button by 11.59pm on 24 September 2023. You will need to upload a cover letter addressing Key Selection Criteria 1, 2 and 3 in the position description and a resume.  More information  You can find out more about this role via the position description. You can also contact James Harrison, Compliance Analysis and Reporting Manager, Forensics and Information Management Branch on 03 9628 6863.  If you need a copy of this advertisement in an accessible format, email HRServices@sro.vic.gov.au.  Please note, as part of our selection process, we conduct pre-appointment checks including those related to references, identity, qualifications, work history, work visa, and police record history.  This role may be subject to a probation period.
job_description.247: MECCA Brands is experiencing growing demand for customer data analysis to support the delivery of our long-term digital roadmap. As a result, there is an exciting opportunity for a customer focused and analytically minded Customer Data Analyst to join our team as we build out personalisation, digital engagement and behavioural marketing at scale.  The Role You Could Play  Reporting to the Customer Data Enablement Lead, the Senior Customer Data Analyst needs to deeply understand the power of data to lead the delivery of considered customer data solutions as part of personalisation initiatives and larger strategic programs of work. We are looking for a passionate data nerd well-versed in using data to transform customer interactions in marketing, sales and digital experience and familiar with marketing technology transformation, automation and process change within an organisation.  As a key member of the team, you will be working on a variety of analytical challenges in support of enabling omnichannel customer experience initiatives. You will leverage data from internal and external sources to build and measure segmentations, find groups of customers to grow, reactivate or acquire for the business and close the loop through the enablement of customer journeys and test & learn initiatives.  As a key member of the team, you will contribute to the development of data capabilities and products that enable omnichannel customer experience initiatives. You will collaborate extensively with internal teams to gather requirements and utilise your understanding of MECCA's data to advise on and develop solutions to grow existing customers and reactivate and acquire for the business.  What You Will Bring  You will utilise your expertise in data analysis, to shape the use of customer data at MECCA to deliver value to business and our customers. As we are going through a period of transformation, including continuous improvement of a new tech stack, you will need to be passionate about new technologies and willing to learn and apply new data manipulation and analysis tools. As the team grows, you will be passionate about empowering others with data and driving this through coaching and documentation.  You will also need to have: • Strong experience in data analysis and reporting, preferably in Retail • Experience in managing marketing technology platforms to deliver personalisation • Excellent communication and interpersonal skills with the ability to explain complex information in simple terms • Strong SQL skills and manipulating datasets • Ability to deliver ideas from inception to execution, particularly as part of a cross-functional and collaborative team • Adaptability and proven ability to work in a fast-paced and changing environment  Your Life At MECCA  Whilst we are singularly focused on our #CustomerFirst mantra, we know that wouldn’t be possible without an incredible team that is guided by our MECCA values and motivated each and every day to be solutions focused, innovative, collaborative and adaptable, and have a bit of fun along the way!  Some of our other team member benefits include: • Professional development programs and first-class digitised learning offering • Health and well-being initiatives • Reward and recognition programs • Access to bonus and incentive programs • Quarterly product allowance • Unlimited 40% discount  There are also so many other ways in which you’ll be made to feel part of the MECCA story as we love to celebrate, surprise and delight our team along the way.  To learn more about life at MECCA Brands, follow us on LinkedIn at MECCA Brands or @lifeatmecca and for all current opportunities, visit www.mecca.com.au/careers

job_description.250: • Closing Date: 13 October 2023, 9:00 AM  face2face reference: 591408  Location: Nationwide - Remote  Hours: Full-time  Contract length: 12 Months Contract + 3 x 1 Month (Pending approval)  Entry requirements: Australian Citizen + Ability to obtain Baseline  Pay range: $95.00 – 115.00 p/h inc super  About the role:  The Tertiary Skills and Pathways team is responsible for the unit mapping project, as part of its program of work. Unit mapping uses natural language processing techniques to create a connection between tertiary education learning materials (VET and HE units), and skills taxonomies. Unit mapping helps to identify skills taught in tertiary education, and their potential relationship to occupations and the labour market, to assist in analysis and advice on tertiary education delivery.  The team is working on a demonstration project basis with five key projects to design the end to end process of unit mapping, to continually refine the data science model, and to generate insights on the potential use of mapping outputs. The outputs of models are large, for example one university with approximately 3,000 units can have an output of approximately 30,000 skills mapped. Validation of outputs is a critical part of the mapping process to produce a model and results that are highly accurate.  Duties: • Developing of a comprehensive internal and external validation process for very large data sets, to support improvement of data science models, and the quality of output data sent to partners.
