job_description.256: The Opportunity  Due to an exciting growth phase, Centric is seeking a Junior Research Analyst to join our Investment Platform. This is a full-time, permanent opportunity, flexible on location for the right person.  The Investment team is a dynamic part of the Centric Group. The team is responsible for multiple investment components that are delivered to dealer groups and other external partners including trustee and administrative. A key area of the teams responsibilities is model portfolios / managed accounts where we provide asset allocation and investment blending targeting specific investment objectives.  The successful candidate will learn how an investment is likely to perform and how sustainable it is. You will participate in our sound portfolio-management strategy by providing the necessary data for our decision-making process.  What does a typical week look like? • Performance reporting for portfolios, sectors and individual funds, • Quantitative analysis on respective listed and unlisted investments, • Adviser and client materials, • Preparation of recommendations for Investment Committee purposes, • Investment administration as required (compliance/risk checks etc), • Liaise with external investment and fund managers.  The natural progression of this role is into an analyst role, where you would be involved in fund manager research, macroeconomic research, and portfolio construction amongst other things.  Let's Talk About You  The successful person will possess the following skills, experience and attributes: • Relevant Tertiary degree in Finance/Business/Economics/Investments, • CFA or relevant industry qualification (highly regarded), • Relevant working experience within financial planning, investments, etc. • Solid understanding of financial set-up, procedures, statistics and economics • Excellent quantitative and qualitative analytical skills • Demonstrated background in working with others to achieve common outcomes and/or goals, • Stay focused and use time effectively to achieve goals by ensuring outcomes are the primary focus of actions, • Ability to display original thinking and creativity  The Perks • Dynamic working environment – work from home and/or office, great flexibility to work around your family, lifestyle or personal commitments • Work with a collaborative, fun team • Beautiful office facilities with quality, ergonomic equipment • Access to Employee Assistance Program and online learning, supporting a healthy work-life balance • Career development opportunities based on your preferences as the business is rapidly growing  Why Centric?  Centric is a comprehensive online wealth management platform providing advisers and investors the ability to manage their wealth easily and efficiently. Through the platform, clients have a full view of their assets and liabilities in one place, even if they're held outside Centric.  Offering access to competitive investment products including Centric Super, Centric is a dynamic way to design and manage portfolios for investors at all life stages, also enabling reporting and access for aligned professionals such as accountants.  With over $3 billion in FUM and backed by FNZ, Centric offers a flat administration fee and full pricing transparency, together with healthy cash rates and a low cost to trade. Designed for advisers through extensive consultation with advisers, the Centric team is passionate about delivering a quality platform and experience, enabling advisers and their clients to thrive.  Next Steps?  Apply now – we can't wait to hear from you Please note, you will be directed to our careers page to apply.  Please note:  Only candidates with valid work rights within Australia in which this position is based will be considered.  This role is being managed by Findex Talent Acquisition and we will not accept unsolicited resumes/applications from Recruitment Agencies.

job_description.261: About the Role Your work will complement the established research and education strengths of the school which range from the applied to the theoretical. You will also have a strong commitment to teaching and the supervision of research students. Teaching will occur within the School of Mathematics and Statistics undergraduate and postgraduate programs and the applicant will have the opportunity to teach mathematics and its applications to a variety of audiences.  Your responsibilities will include: • The conduct of research and contribution to knowledge through scholarship, refereed publications and presentations. • Active application and success in obtaining external research grant income to support that research • Proactive development of subject materials and delivery, including the use of modern technology and online resources as appropriate • Development of curriculum in mathematics and/or statistics in both undergraduate and postgraduate levels  Who We Are Looking For We seek an individual who possesses the potential for research excellence in mathematics or statistics, with the ability to engage in research collaborations, secure research funding, and effectively teach both undergraduate and graduate-level mathematics or statistics courses.  You will also have: • A PhD or equivalent research higher degree in mathematics, statistics or a closely related discipline • The ability to interact well with other academic staff and to contribute to the administration of a large school • Clear potential in graduate student supervision • Demonstrated ability to develop, administer and see through to completion appropriately designed research projects with limited supervision  For further information regarding responsibilities and requirements, please refer to the attached PD.  This position requires the incumbent to hold a current and valid Working with Children Check to ensure the University provides a safe environment for everyone.  Your New Team – School of Mathematics and Statistics The University of Melbourne's School of Mathematics and Statistics is one of Australia's leading mathematics and statistics schools. It has achieved this status through the high quality of its research and teaching programs. The School offers a wide range of subjects to undergraduate and postgraduate students and is involved in aspects of community life that impact on the interests of the School and the discipline.  The School of Mathematics and Statistics has a total of 90 continuing teaching and/or research staff; 37 research only staff and consultants; 19 academic specialists and 16 support staff. In 2023, there were 143 Research Higher Degree and 189 Coursework Master of Science students and over 13,000 undergraduate students. Seven members of the School staff and one Emeritus Professor are members of the Academy of Science. The school currently hosts one ARC Centre of Excellence and one ARC Industrial Transformation Training Centre, and has hosted four ARC Laureate Fellows, thirteen ARC Future Fellows and twenty-four DECRA Fellows.  What We Offer You In addition, we offer the opportunity to be part of a vibrant community and enjoy a range of benefits, including generous leave provisions, salary packaging, health and well-being services and discounts on graduate courses. For more information, check out our benefits page  About the University of Melbourne We're tightly connected with the community, both at home and abroad. We take pride in our people, who all contribute to our mission to benefit society through the transformative impact of education and research. Discover more via our website and stay connected with our stories and people on LinkedIn.  We are dedicated to ensuring barrier free and inclusive practices to recruit the most talented candidates. If you require any reasonable adjustments with the recruitment process, please contact the email address listed at the bottom of the page. You will implement advanced analytics solutions that improve business outcomes, such as digital engagement and student conversion, better customer experience, marketing campaign optimisation and to improve Data Engineering practices across IDP.  This is a full-time permanent opportunity. We invite applications from Talent with full working rights in Australia to apply for this role based out of our head office in Melbourne.  Responsibilities Include  Pipeline • Develop accurate and production-ready models that enable IDP to focus effort on the right opportunities • Suggest changes to process and core systems to improve accuracy of predictions • Suggest changes regarding interventions to improve conversions • Continuously iterate and innovate existing products to stay relevant and ahead of the competition • Work with global marketing and call centre teams to run experiments and identify new revenue generation and cost reduction opportunities  Engineering • Collaborate with engineers at offshore teams on existing IDP architecture patterns • Develop appropriate incremental engineering patterns specific to Data Science applications  Essential  What we're looking for • Minimum two years experience in a similar role with a proven track record of delivering business value using advanced analytics • Knowledge of marketing analytics, including customer segmentation, propensity scoring, and campaign optimisation • Ownership of goals - ability to focus on the goal of a piece of work and find a way to make it possible • Strong SQL skills – ability to write advanced SQL from problem statements worded in business language by collaborating with various SMEs, building their own knowledge as they go. • Python (or any other programming language) – 1-2 years coding experience • Strong communication skills – ability to question, probe and demonstrate understanding a problem, and to propose/check a possible solution to that problem • Curiosity – keen to understand how IDP works and how this shows in the data– how students, clients and counsellors feel and behave.  Desirable • Experience with AWS • Post graduate qualification in statistics, data science, computer science or mathematics. • Accountability for the full scope of Management Accounting functions in a Technology context including Budget, Forecasting and Actuals analysis.  About Us  An ASX100 business with a 50-year heritage, IDP is a pioneer in international education services. Our core business lines include student placement to Australia, US, UK, Canada, Ireland and New Zealand institutions, English-language testing and training.  We are on a mission to build the world's leading platform and connected community to guide students along their journey to achieve their lifelong learning and career aspirations.  As a co-owner of IELTS, we deliver the English test that is trusted by more governments, universities and organisations than any other. We also operate English language teaching schools in Southeast Asia.  We are innovators, driven by the needs of our customers and deep data insights. Our 5,000 team members based around the world understand that our services change lives – not only of our customers, but their wider communities.  As the global leader in international education, we have focused on building trusted human relationships for more than 50 years.  In recent years, our investment in digital technology and customer research has enhanced these personal connections, enabling us to deliver global success to more students, test-takers and our partners.  Proudly customer-first, our expert people are powered by global technology. Together, we offer unmatched services, helping local dreams become realities, all over the world.  And best yet, at 50, we are just getting started.  More About Us  We are evolving rapidly. This is an exciting time to join us as we transform the way people access global education and opportunities, through leveraging innovative technology and a creating a connected world.  With our core business in student placement, digital marketing, English-language testing, and training across a global network, we are a global leader in the international education sector. We strive to provide workplaces that are truly diverse and representative of the communities that we work in, so our people feel empowered to bring their best and authentic selves to work. job_description.269: Want to be part of a MedTech startup working on cutting edge technology? Want to contribute to a groundbreaking, live product with real world impact? Let me tell you about Cyban…  About Cyban  Cyban is advancing the way brain injuries are detected and managed through the creation of their patented, non-invasive medical device which monitors brain oxygen and pressure levels. Their Brain Pulse Monitor delivers accurate results quickly to enable confident clinical care at every stage of the patient journey and helps hospitals to save costs and free up valuable resources.  Cyban’s first product for use in patients with Acute Brain Injuries is close to launching after significant clinical trials in patients with some of the world’s most well-known and regarded institutions and a successful round of funding. This is the perfect time to join the team and be part of something meaningful!  About the role  Cyban is looking for a passionate and highly skilled Data Scientist to join their team. Working closely with their team of data scientists, research scientists, and engineers, you will play a pivotal role in developing innovative algorithms to extract valuable insights from complex biological waveforms. Your work will directly impact the development of production ready advanced medical technologies, improving patient care and outcomes.  What will you be doing?  Algorithm and Model Development for Clinical Outcomes • Leverage your expertise in Machine Learning (ML) and data analysis to design, develop, and optimise statistical models and algorithms for biological waveform data and clinical outcomes. • Utilise advanced techniques such as deep learning, ensemble models, and time-series analysis to improve data accuracy and interpretability. • Extract relevant features, identify trends, anomalies, and predictive biomarkers, while regularly evaluating and fine-tuning model performance to enhance algorithmic efficiency.  Data Exploration and Visualisation • Conduct in-depth exploratory data analysis to identify patterns and relationships within biological waveform datasets. • Visualise findings in a meaningful and interpretable manner, enabling stakeholders to gain insights and make informed decisions.  Research Advancements • Stay up-to-date with the latest developments in signal processing and ML algorithms, methodologies, and tools. • Continuously explore and evaluate emerging technologies and techniques that could enhance the effectiveness and efficiency of data analysis.  Documentation and Reporting • Maintain comprehensive documentation of data processing steps, model development processes, and experimental results. • Prepare reports and present findings to internal and external stakeholders, communicating complex concepts in a clear and concise manner.  What skills and qualifications are we looking for? • Bachelor’s or post-graduate qualifications in a related field e.g Statistics, Data Science, Applied Mathematics, Computer Science, Physics or Neuroscience. • You have a minimum 3 years commercial or industry work experience in Data Science or a related field, alongside your academic studies or research. • Proficient in Python and have experience in other languages e.g R or MATLAB. • Skilled in statistical analysis and ML frameworks, with a solid understanding of time-series analysis, signal processing techniques, and feature extraction methods. • Experience or strong interest in health or medical-related technology, with an understanding of relevant physiological and clinical concepts. • Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, able to dissect and understand complex datasets and extract meaningful insights. Proficient in statistical analysis and hypothesis testing to validate findings and ensure the robustness of models. • Excellent verbal and written communication skills, with the ability to effectively articulate and present technical concepts to diverse teams and medical professionals.  Plus, bonus points for: • Experience in getting ML models into production • Familiarity with biological waveforms and experience working with processed physiological time series data from medical devices (e.g., PPG, ECG, or EEG sensors) • Familiarity with languages like C++ and C, cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, GCP)  This is a hybrid role within a dynamic start-up environment, where priorities and requirements may evolve rapidly. At Cyban, they believe that success comes through recognising the value of their people and fostering an environment of respect and openness. They work with a sense of urgency and purpose and continuously endeavour to understand the perspectives and needs of those who will use their products.  Sounds exciting? Want to know more?  Apply now or reach out to Cass at affix: cass.galliott@affix.com.au

Capture business requirements and identify underlying business needs. • Carry out analysis of present approaches and identify opportunities to enhance processes current and target state. • Collaborate with stakeholders to ensure appropriate stakeholders are included in the development of business requirements. • Translate subject-matter expert and stakeholder discussion into process flows, procedures and business requirements. • Identify and document instances where existing business processes may be streamlined or improved or do not meet current or potential future business needs. • Develop, maintain and validate business requirements with stakeholders. • Input to the design and implementation of solutions that support the business processes and deliver business insight. • Liaise with management to coordinate process improvement project activities. • Workshop facilitation with business stakeholders to map out processes and elicit business requirements. • Practical Agile Delivery framework experience, developing Initiatives, Epics, User Stories and other documentation. • Ability to work with the business to identify business process issues, improvement opportunities and potential solutions. • Ability to gather, analyse and translate business data to meaningful insights.  Every application requires to address selection criteria as part of application submission.  Essential Criteria  1. Able to translate discussion into process flows, requirements and documentation.  2. Able to understand and capture business requirements relating to use / application of data to business problems.  3. Have experience in as is and to be process mapping.  4. Hands on experience with agile product development process for data products as well as developing detailed User Stories and UAC.  5. Intermediate skills with JIRA and Confluence, Visio, Excel, Powerpoint, Word.  6. Showcase good analytical and evaluating skills.  Desirable Criteria  1. Experience as a scrum master.  2. Experience creating wireframes.  3. Data analysis skills.  4. Experience working in data businesses.
job_description.279: An exciting opportunity is available for a dynamic and energetic CRM and Data Specialist to join Melbourne’s leader in prestige Real Estate. The successful candidate will drive CRM & Data innovation, strategy and execution across Marshall White’s digital platforms, serving as a crucial conduit across the business while enabling insightful and targeted success.  About Us  Marshall White is a prestige real estate agency servicing Bayside, Boroondara, Manningham, Port Phillip, Stonnington & the Mornington Peninsula. We pride ourselves on our values and providing expertise and an exceptional experience to get the best outcomes for our clients while growing your successful career in the process.  About You  The role calls for an individual who thrives in a fast-paced, dynamic, and at times high-pressure environment. Rewarded for balancing speed and accuracy, this position will deliver excellent growth opportunities for some seeking to springboard their career. The successful candidate will need to be able to work both independently and within a team environment. This varied output will see the successful candidate coordinating Marshall White’s business needs and priorities including and assisting with development, implementation, continued optimisation and operational CRM/Data training and most importantly our regular reporting.  Reporting to the Head of Marketing and Chief Commercial Officer, the position will sit within the Marketing Department and support internal stakeholders to achieve a range of growth and retention metrics. The role has one direct report, our highly skilled, long-term CRM & Data Analyst.  We have a People first approach so let’s lead with our Values:  #Teamwork  Working together toward common goals in a collaborative and inclusive manner.  #Accountability  Working with urgency and a commitment to be successful from an individual perspective and a company perspective.  #Integrity  Being open and honest in all our dealings and always maintaining the highest integrity. Inspiring trust from others in the way we behave.  #Learning  A commitment for continuous improvement in how we work, to take risks outside our comfort zones and gain knowledge when we make mistakes.  #Support  To be supportive of each other and demonstrate respect for differences in opinion, always fostering open communication.  Your day-to-day activities will include • Manage and execute the business’s end-to-end CRM and data analysis campaigns • Continually audit processes and improve business efficiency and strategic results across multiple channels (Website, Direct Mail, Email, SMS etc.) • Identify and deliver innovation in the CRM and data analysis output • Champion and enhance the use of Marshall White’s CRM and data platforms • Manage the prioritisation of workflow for the CRM team, incl. management of one direct report; CRM & Data Analyst • Conduct weekly stakeholder updates and sprints, supporting quarterly sprints and reviews • Create and distribute clear, regular reporting to internal stakeholders with action-focused insights • Build business dashboards and reporting tools used for generating actionable insights • Enable targeting identification to assist Marketing in addressing customers with relevant and personalised offers leveraging analytics and big data solutions. • Support the Commercial, Sales and Marketing/Digital teams to be change agents within the business through the execution of ideas • Maintain healthy relationships with internal stakeholders and software suppliers • Support sales agents with CRM, Learning & Development and data-related inductions • Provide system support to all business units on CRM and associated industry software and tools • Complete daily data admin tasks and software management  To be successful in this role, your experience and skills ideally will include: • 5+ years’ experience translating CRM & Data into insights • Understanding of software, applications, data, and integration is essential • Google Analytics, Google Tag • Ability to learn and champion the following basic CRM software -Box+Dice, Campaign Track , Yellowfin • Proficient in interpreting data analysis • High level of verbal communication and presentation skills • Excellent English writing ability to translate data to laymen’s terms • Energetic and ability to self-manage priorities and problem-solving • Ability to learn new topics quickly and think creatively • Implementing technology and digital strategies  Benefits of Joining our team • Enjoying working within a dynamic and rewarding environment • Competitive salary, fun social events, and an inclusive work environment • Learning and development including internal and external training programs to build your career skills • An inclusive and diverse workplace centred on health, wellbeing and growth  Please note: only short-listed candidates meeting the required criteria will be contacted.  A Note to Recruiters: We have this role in hand; there is no need to approach us.

Employment and advancement decisions at DiDi are always made based on the needs of the position and the qualifications of the candidate. We do not discriminate against any employee or applicant based on their gender, age, sexual orientation, nationality, marital status, pregnancy/maternity, disability, race, religion and beliefs, or any other status protected by applicable laws wherever we operate.  We are committed to building inclusive and diverse teams, and a workplace that is free from discrimination and harassment, because that’s how we create better products and services, make better decisions and better serve the communities we’re a part of.  Didi Chuxing (“DiDi”) is the world’s leading mobile transportation and convenience platform. The company offers a full range of app-based transportation and life services for over 550 million users across Asia, Latin America, Australia, and Russia, including Taxi, Express, Premier, Luxe, Bus, Designated Driving, Enterprise Solutions, Bike Sharing, E-bike Sharing, Automobile Solutions, Food Delivery, and Payment. Tens of millions of drivers who find flexible work opportunities on the DiDi platform provide over 10 billion passenger trips a year.  DiDi is committed to collaborating with policymakers, the taxi industry, the automobile industry, and communities to solve the world’s transportation, and environmental, and employment challenges with localized smart transportation innovations by leveraging its AI capabilities. By continuously improving user experience and creating social value, DiDi strives to build a safe, inclusive, and sustainable mobile transportation and convenience ecosystem for cities of the future.  DiDi uses technology to improve mobility in our world. As such, we always look for people from every background who want to support our vision, through equal opportunity and nondiscriminatory, fair and impartial treatment, completely free of prejudice related to race, nationality, religion, gender, ethnicity, age, political affiliation, sexual preference, marital status, disabilities or family responsibilities.  For more information, please visit: www.didiglobal.com/news  About The Team/role  We are seeking a BI to play a crucial role in our business for future growth. In this role, you will report directly to the ANZ Operations Director, leveraging your expertise to transform our data analysis in the Australia & New Zealand Region into business insights. You will also be dedicated to making direct business impact with internal stakeholders like operations, product, tech, with daily data monitoring, and special project analysis.  In this role, you'll be...  Responsibilities: • Perform data analysis tasks, which will include operation and marketing campaign performance design and review, and will cover mechanical, programming, database disciplines. • Writing and maintaining Hive and Python script to generate business dashboard and automatic email report. • Writing and maintaining Hive and Python script to collect driver information automatically and validate this information through government’s public API. • Writing and maintaining Hive and Python script to collect driver information from different sources and format it into one consistent format, forward the info to the related party with detailed history records, which finally form a coherent reporting system. • Reviewing, writing and revising program code to meet operation and business requirement, diagnosing and correcting errors in existing database and product logic. • Manage and analyze large volumes of complex data through advanced digital analytics information systems that require SQL, Python etc. • Understand the BAU projects that ANZ BI team managing, which include various reporting system based on Tableau, Excel, DataE, Insight. • Use SQL, Excel, and other tools to help prepare supporting data as backup of other team’s output when there is a need. • Use SQL, Apollo, Tag-system to provide insight from data perspective for cross functional teams on initiating the business action plan for city launch, which assist whole ANZ business. • Use Excel, Python, DataE, Tableau to address ad-hoc analysis of business issues to better support Operating team in guiding the driver and rider on boarding process. • Make judgments in all of the department he attends. The line manager will review and approve all judgments  Requirement: • Bachelor's degree in a relevant field such as Business Analytics, Data Science, or Computer Science. Master's degree is preferred. Minimum of 2 years of relevant work experience in data analysis. • Proficiency in using common analysis and modeling tools such as strong proficiency in data analysis and visualization tools such as Excel, SQL, R/Python, and familiarity with experimental design and evaluation methods. • Experience in statistical analysis, predictive modeling, and machine learning techniques is highly desirable. • Ability to work independently and thrive in a fast-paced, dynamic environment with multiple priorities. job_description.282: “Otic” means smart people doing smart work, together.  We are a wholly owned Australian company committed to helping our clients design and build intelligent software solutions that unlock value in their business.  Otic Group was formed to provide talented technology professionals an opportunity to work with not only some of the most prominent companies in Australia, but work with incredibly talented peers in an exciting, dynamic young environment.  We provide highly skilled expertise in Data & Analytics, Cloud Strategy, Application Modernisation, and Cybersecurity.  The key technical skills we’re looking for in this role are: • Advanced skills with Azure and data tools (Data Factory, Databricks), • Strong Microsoft BI / SSRS, SSAS, SSIS, Power BI and SQL skills, • Significant professional experience in Business Intelligence (BI) and Analytics.  Over and above having these technical skills, you will also have a strong passion and flair for creating professional prototypes and dashboards. job_description.283: About the role  Job Title: Data Analyst - ANZ Plus  Location: Melbourne preferred  Blended Working Model • Work in an agile way to innovate and deliver quality outcomes at pace • Be a part of our Australian Business Transformation, and work with people who are passionate about redefining banking for the future • Join a progressive organisation with the people and policies you want  At ANZ our purpose is to shape a world where people and communities thrive and to achieve this, we need a talented Data Analyst to join our Data Enablement chapter within our Australian Business Transformation. Your mission is to derive compelling insights and identify opportunities to shape the direction of our customer experience. You will be working within a cross functional team and driving end to end delivery of insights.  Your key accountabilities will include: • Work with agile teams on identifying analytical opportunities • Curating and modelling data to ascertain customer and business value • Visualising outcome and presenting compelling opportunities to stakeholders  What will your day look like • Embedding within Agile teams you will be individually accountable to ensure that quantitative analysis is performed across a number of customer and business driven use cases • You will be working with key product owners to formulate details hypotheses to work on which will fundamentally change the direction of the squad • Working with data will be a key part of the role including the need to discover, identify, curate and model the data appropriately to drive insights • All insights will need to be presented back to key stakeholder and will require the development of interactive reports and dashboards  What will you bring?  We know not everyone will bring all of the skills and experience, and at ANZ we are focused on people bringing a growth mindset to their approach to work. Some of the skills we are looking for are below, but don’t worry if you don’t have all of these as learning on the job is the way we work.  But back to some of the skills – • Strong BI expertise, Visualization, Tableau highly advantageous • Data Discovery against business objectives • Definition of Metrics and Translation to data Model • Data Modelling, able to design data model /concept and understand the solution architecture in Cloud infrastructure • Requirements Gathering / Gap Analysis: Business consulting interaction, Documentation • Data manipulation: translation, prototyping, problem solving • Technical data expertise: strong SQL – Big Query/Cloud highly advantageous  You’re not expected to have 100% of these skills. At ANZ a growth mindset is at the heart of our culture, so if you have most of these things in your toolbox, we’d love to hear from you.  So, why join us?  There’s something special about being part of ANZ. From the moment you join us, you’re part of a team working towards a common goal: improving the financial wellbeing and sustainability of our millions of customers.  But it’s not just our customers who’ll feel your impact. You’ll feel it too. Because at ANZ, you’ll have the resources and community you need to take the next big step in your career, towards even bigger things in the future.  We offer a range of benefits tailored to the countries in which we operate including Health and Wellbeing programs and flexible working arrangements.  You’ll also enjoy working in a diverse and inclusive workplace where the different backgrounds, perspectives and life experiences of our people are celebrated. We encourage you to talk to us about any adjustments you may require to our recruitment process or the role itself. If you are a candidate with a disability, let us know how we can provide you with additional support.  To find out more about working at ANZ or to view other opportunities visit www.careers.anz.com. You may apply for this role by visiting ANZ Careers and searching for reference number 43011  Job Posting End Date  October 19, 11.59pm, (Melbourne Australia)
job_description.284: Company Description  Visa is a world leader in digital payments, facilitating more than 215 billion payments transactions between consumers, merchants, financial institutions and government entities across more than 200 countries and territories each year. Our mission is to connect the world through the most innovative, convenient, reliable and secure payments network, enabling individuals, businesses and economies to thrive.  When you join Visa, you join a culture of purpose and belonging – where your growth is priority, your identity is embraced, and the work you do matters. We believe that economies that include everyone everywhere, uplift everyone everywhere. Your work will have a direct impact on billions of people around the world – helping unlock financial access to enable the future of money movement.  Join Visa: A Network Working for Everyone.  Job Description  Sr Data Analyst, Managed Services - 1 year fixed-term  Melbourne (Australia)  About the role:  Do you want to be a part of Visa’s fastest growing team in Australia and New Zealand? Do you enjoy delivering and getting things done? Do you want to make positive impacts for customers and accelerate the pace of innovation in the payments industry? If so, Visa Managed Services (VMS) is the team for you.  The VMS team is all about delivery, implementation, and execution. We create squads of delivery consultants to embed within our clients’ organizations to help them deliver better results, faster.’  If you're a Data Analyst who loves data, create insights, solve challenging business problems and want to use your skills for the greater good… then we have the perfect role for you!  Why join us: • This role will support a key strategic client in Australia helping them deliver on their bank-wide, large-scale simplification agenda. • Visa Managed Services is our fastest growing team in Australia and New Zealand – we’ve grown 10x in less than 2 years – and always have fun projects on the horizon to sink our teeth into • We get to work with incredible people every day. We’re a team of intrapreneurs who work hard, have fun, and get stuff done. • We are a people business where the people are our product. As a result, all our people leaders are 100% dedicated to ensuring a positive employee experience. We attract top talent and are manically focused on developing and retaining that talent at Visa. • We are committed to building a diverse team with an inclusive culture that reflects the communities we work in • We’re a global company and VMS is a global focus area for Visa. Once established in our Australia team, you’ll have the opportunity to explore roles focused on scaling our VMS business around the world. • We support flexible working options and industry leading compensation & benefits.  Join us and make a difference today.  What you will be doing:  Ideally based in Melbourne but with hybrid work options, you will develop and maintain dashboards to understand the performance of various portfolio optimisation initiatives. Your responsibilities will include transforming data for use in creation, maintenance, and automation of the dashboards. You will work closely with the Data Delivery Lead, Product Consultant and Client Portfolio lead to build dashboards, generate insights, solve business problems using customer and transactional data.  In this role you will: • Explore our clients’ data infrastructure and systems, analyse various datasets, perform data analysis, finding patterns and generating valuable insights to support critical business initiatives and present them back to the business teams. • Build dashboards to visualize insights and understand behaviour of customers or understand performance of various portfolio optimisation initiatives. • Perform ad-hoc analysis to solve business problems and support decisions. • Producing written communication, visualizations and presentations for leadership and other key stakeholders.  What you will bring:  Key competencies: • Solution-mindset – Applying creative problem-solving techniques and championing a client-first approach to customer insights when opportunities and challenges arise to meet specific business objectives. • Active Contributor to Team Success – Strong team orientation with a collaborative, diplomatic, and flexible style. Able to work effectively in a matrixed organization. • Tenacity – Self-motivated, results-oriented individual with the ability to progress multiple priorities concurrently. • Building Strategic Work Relationships - Excellent client engagement and relationship management skills with a collaborative approach to stakeholder management • Driving Execution – Motivated by delivery and with a high attention to detail.  What you will need to be successful: • Proficient in SQL as an intermediate to advanced level. • Experience of working on data platforms like Teradata or GCP is highly preferred. • Experience in data visualisation is required, Tableau or QlikSense is highly preferred. • Experience in analytics programming languages (e.g., Python) is highly preferred. • Advanced skills in Excel and PowerPoint and the ability to effectively communicate a story through data (visualisations, storytelling) • Experience with GitHub and Confluence is highly preferred. • Adept at data crunching, and passionate about unearthing significant patterns and meaningful insights. • An eye for accuracy, the ability to self-manage multiple data sets and data requests, and flexibility to respond quickly.  You’re not expected to have 100% of these skills. At Visa a growth mindset is at the heart of our culture, so if you have most of these things in your toolbox, we’d love to hear from you.  What will also help: • High performance delivery focus with a high attention to detail • Strong communication skills to make complex concepts accessible for business stakeholders. • Ability to influence and collaborate at all levels without relying on hierarchy. • Strong team orientation with a collaborative, diplomatic, flexible style and able to work effectively across multiple teams. • Strong analytical skills with the ability to collect, organize, analyse, and disseminate significant amounts of information with attention to detail and accuracy. • Outcome orientated, persistence to challenge the status quo and deliver customer results. • A Growth mindset, constantly striving to learn and develop. • Excellent client engagement and relationship management skills with a collaborative approach to stakeholder management • Innovation minded with high problem-solving skills, with demonstrated intellectual and analytical rigor. • Self-motivated, results-oriented individual with the ability to progress multiple priorities concurrently.  Why Work with us: • We are known for offering industry-leading compensation. • We have state of the art offices in Melbourne, Sydney, and Auckland • We provide world class benefits including: • Mental health and wellbeing resources to all employees • Generous annual leave plus carers leave, parental leave, baby bonding leave, and pregnancy loss leave, among others • Paid volunteering leave & employee referral program cash awards. • Ability to work from another location for up to 1 month each year. • Global company with global opportunities. We can share endless stories of how we’ve supported our employees to accelerate their career progression and pursue opportunities in other geographies around the world.  This is a hybrid position. Hybrid employees can alternate time between both remote and office. Employees in hybrid roles are expected to work from the office 2-3 set days a week (determined by leadership/site), with a general guidepost of being in the office 50% or more of the time based on business needs.  Qualifications  • Proficient in SQL as an intermediate to advanced level.  • Experience of working on data platforms like Teradata or GCP is highly preferred.  • Experience in data visualisation is required, Tableau or QlikSense is highly preferred.  • Experience in analytics programming languages (e.g., Python) is highly preferred.  • Advanced skills in Excel and PowerPoint and the ability to effectively communicate a story through data (visualisations, storytelling)  • Experience with GitHub and Confluence is highly preferred.  • Adept at data crunching, and passionate about unearthing significant patterns and meaningful insights.  • An eye for accuracy, the ability to self-manage multiple data sets and data requests, and flexibility to respond quickly.  Additional Information  Visa is an EEO Employer. Qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity, disability or protected veteran status. Visa will also consider for employment qualified applicants with criminal histories in a manner consistent with EEOC guidelines and applicable local law.
job_description.285: Company Overview : Beyond Zero Technologies is a leading technology solutions provider, committed to driving innovation and transforming businesses with data-centric solutions.  Our mission is to empower businesses with actionable insights, enabling them to make informed decisions and achieve extraordinary growth.  We take pride in our collaborative and forward-thinking culture, where every team member is valued for their unique contributions and expertise.  Position Overview : We are seeking a talented and motivated Data Analyst to join our dynamic team. Analyse large datasets using statistical methods and data analysis techniques to identify trends, patterns, and correlations.  Develop and maintain interactive dashboards, reports, and data visualisations to present findings effectively. Conduct ad-hoc data analysis to support specific business inquiries and provide actionable recommendations.  Work closely with the data engineering team to optimise data pipelines and ensure data quality. Stay up-to-date with industry best practices and emerging trends in data analysis and technology. Proficiency in data manipulation and analysis using SQL and Python or R. Familiarity with data visualisation tools such as Tableau, Power BI, or similar.  Strong understanding of statistical concepts and data modelling techniques. Solid problem-solving skills and an ability to think critically about complex data sets.  Detail-oriented with excellent organisational and time-management abilities. Effective communication skills to present findings to non-technical stakeholders. Application Process :

job_description.288: You shall find the IDA team very self-motivated, high standard and forward thinking focused, and highly hands-on.  Responsibilities • Collaborate with team leader and senior data scientists, as well as clients and internal stakeholders to understand and document their business requirements, problems and objectives. • Understand data structures and business and extract and integrate required data sources for analysis according to business requirements. • Develop and evaluate data analytics models, algorithms, systems and solutions, including undertaking data extraction, pre-processing, modeling, evaluation, deployment, and maintenance. • Collaborate with senior data scientists and team leader and clients to productise and pilot analytical models for production and insight per clients required. • Undertake cost-benefit, forecasting and impact analysis by effective presentations of data-driven findings to clients and stakeholders. • Document and communicate all relevant work and work outcomes.  Qualifications • Solid background, knowledge and capabilities in statistics, mathematics, computer science, informatics, computing, or closely relevant scientific field. • Experienced in data-driven analytics hands-on experience with deep know-how of predictive modeling, machine learning and data mining, and relevant modeling approaches and algorithms. • Demonstrated capabilities to develop and evaluate statistical analysis and modeling algorithms and apply these algorithms for data-driven solutions to problems in new domains. • Demonstrated knowledge of SQL (data extraction and manipulation), expertise in SAS programming, and software development skills in one to several scripting languages (Python/R). • Demonstrated capabilities to communicate and engage with a range of stakeholder groups and technical project teams. • Demonstrated capabilities to work effectively as a member of a data science project team. • Demonstrated experience for independent problem-solving and self-motivated innovation, education and services. Our goal is to make every interaction with the VSBA a positive one for our customers, colleagues and key partners regardless of our individual role or team. The Principal Data Analyst role is responsible for leading data analysis and management work to support the implementation of the Government's Pre-Prep Reform. As well, this role will be critical in supporting the continued successful roll out of Three-Year Old Kindergarten.The role sits within the Early Childhood Infrastructure Planning - State Projects Branch and will be part of the leadership team of the Branch. This role will also work closely with the Early Childhood Infrastructure and Planning - Sector Partnerships Branch. This role will be responsible for working with teams across the Branches, VSBA and Department to support critical functions needed to develop and embed data systems and processes to deliver the infrastructure needed for Pre- Prep and Three-Year-Old Kindergarten. This role will have a high degree of autonomy and will be self-motivated and driven to produce results through collaboration. Key components of this role include program and project planning, data analysis and management, and reporting. Some policy development will be required. An ability to develop and deliver key data systems and process will be key. In addition, the candidate will have excellent stakeholder engagement skills, which will be required to build and maintain strong relationships. Candidates will have proven data analysis, program/project management and implementation experience, preferably relating to supporting delivery of complex projects and programs. Early Candidates will also be able to demonstrate their ability to lead, and work confidently and constructively with stakeholders to ensure the successfully delivery of the Reform. Candidates will have significant experience with a range of data/information management tools, systems and processes, such as Excel, Power BI, Microsoft Access, etc, proven leadership experience, preferably relating to complex government programs in a government setting. Candidates will also be able to demonstrate their ability to work confidently and constructively with stakeholders. The executive team in Early Childhood Infrastructure Planning - State Projects Branch in the VSBA are committed to growing our staff, and the successful candidate will have the support they need to deliver and expand on their current skill set. job_description.290: Reporting & Data Analyst - ERP Implementation  Join one of our clients in the State Government. They are looking for an experienced Data & Reporting Analyst with experience implementing ERP systems! This is a 3 month contract with the potential opportunity to extend. This role is paying up to $700/day + Superannuation. You will be working on a Oracle Cloud Implementation where you will lead the budgeting and forecasting requirements.  Some key responsibilities: • Facilitate the requirements gathering and high-level solution design workshops with SME’s and business stakeholders for the following topics: • Budgeting & Forecasting • Reporting & Analytics • Assess the suitability of Oracle Enterprise Performance Management and its key components. • Lead development of high-level Reporting & Analytics Strategy, including how the upgrade to Oracle Fusion could address the different types of reporting in the context of the broader Enterprise Data Strategy, including: • Executive reporting • Management reporting • Statutory and regulatory reporting • Operational/transactional reporting • Work with business stakeholders to identify possible business benefits to justify and agree which solution components of EPM and which reporting solutions should be included as part of the upgrade scope. • Work with the project team to analyse possible solutions, presenting options back to business stakeholders and facilitating agreement on the cost/benefit analysis of each option. • Document the scope and requirements for EPM and reporting tools for inclusion in the RFT.  To succeed in this position you will have: • 5+ years Data Analytics/Reporting Analyst with ERP implementation experience • Proven knowledge of EPM and its components including: Planning and Budgeting Cloud Services, Accounts Reconciliation Cloud Services, Enterprise Data Management Cloud Services, Project Financial Planning. • Strong relationship-building skills and able to establish credibility with senior stakeholders  As a Randstad Contractor there are benefits to the position: • Flexible work arrangements and CBD Location • Access to Udemy courses • Weekly Pay • Resilience and Wellbeing initiatives • Employee Referral Program and much more.  At Randstad, we are passionate about providing equal employment opportunities and embracing diversity to the benefit of all. We actively encourage applications from any background.  skills  Oracle, ERP, Oracle BA, Business Analyst, Data Analyst, Reporting Analyst  qualifications • Bachelor's degree in IT • Data or Similar  education  Bachelor Degree
job_description.291: • Data Analyst role within Swinburne University • Full time, ongoing position at our Hawthorn campus • Attractive and competitive total remuneration package  About The Role  The Information Technology team at Swinburne University of Technology are looking for a Data Analyst to join their team!  The Data Analyst will play a crucial role in analysing and interpreting data to support decision-making processes, optimize operational efficiency, and create valuable data products within the university.  The purpose of this position is to support the collection of data from business applications, perform the verification, curations and structuring of the data to align to an enterprise perspective, and subsequently enabling self-service business analytical capabilities and the support of more detailed, scientific, and statistical data analysis. Ultimately the position will enable key business decision making to optimise, grow and transform the overall capabilities of the university.  The successful candidate will be able to demonstrate experience with data warehousing, dimensional modelling, ERD model knowledge, SWL, and cloud experience.  About You  To be suitable for this role you will need to have experience in the below key accountabilities: • Proven experience as a Data Analyst or similar role, preferably in an educational or research environment • Experience with and knowledge of modern lakehouse architectures • Experience in distributed cloud-based data platforms such as Snowflake or Databricks • Strong knowledge of data analysis and data modelling. • Proficiency in SQL for data manipulation • Experience with any ETL tool such as Matillion, Fivetran, Trifacta, etc.  Qualifications • Bachelor’s degree in computer science, Information Systems, Statistics, or a related field with at least 4 years subsequent experience; or an equivalent combination of relevant experience and/or education and training • Relevant data platform certifications (e.g. Snowflake Certification)  About Swinburne University Of Technology  Swinburne Horizon 2025 draws upon our understanding of future challenges. With this new strategic plan, we choose to build Swinburne as the prototype of a new and different university – one that is truly of Technology, of Innovation and of Entrepreneurship, and proud of it. We are committed to a differentiated university proposition in education and research, so that: • Every Swinburne learner gets a work experience • Every Swinburne graduate gets a job • Every Swinburne partner gets a tech solution • Swinburne is the prototype of global best practice  The achievement of our 2025 moon shots depends on our capacity to work collectively, always, as One Swinburne.  To Apply  Please submit your CV and cover letter addressing your suitability for this position.  To review the Position Description and to apply, please scroll down to the bottom of the page.  If you are viewing this advert from an external site, please click ‘apply’ and you will be redirected to Swinburne’s Jobs website to access the Position Description at the bottom of the page.  Please Note: Appointment to this position is subject to passing a Working with Children Check.  If you are experiencing technical difficulties with your application, please contact the Swinburne Talent Acquisition Team on staffrecruitment@swin.edu.au.  Applications Close: Tuesday 17th October 2023, 5pm  Swinburne offers flexible working options, leave and parenting/carer policies to support work life balance.  Equity and Diversity  Swinburne is a large and culturally diverse organisation and we are proud of our commitment to equity, diversity and inclusion through key initiatives. For further information on all our initiatives visit our  Equity & Diversity  website.  We welcome and encourage applicants from diverse backgrounds to apply.  We are committed to making the recruitment process fair and equitable for all our candidates. If you have specific accessibility or support requirements please contact  inclusion@swin.edu.au  Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Applicants  We welcome and strongly encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people.  For any support please contact  DeadlyCareers@swin.edu.au  or for more information on our Indigenous strategies please follow the link to our RAP  Reconciliation Action Plan  We are a 2023 Circle Back Initiative Employer – we commit to respond to every applicant

job_description.293: We are seeking a confident Workforce Data Analyst to join our knowledgeable team at University of Melbourne in Melbourne.  Growing your career as a Full Time Workforce Data Analyst is an unparalleled opportunity to develop excellent skills. If you are strong in planning, strategic planning and have the right drive for the job, then apply for the position of Workforce Data Analyst at University of Melbourne today! Workforce Data Analyst Job no : 0059331 & 0059315 Location : Parkville Role type : Full-time;  Continuing Department : Human Resources - Office of the Provost Salary : UOM 7- $102,338- $110,780 p.a. plus 17% super Provide insights and analytics for the University's workforce Fantastic opportunity to join a highly motivated, supportive and inclusive team 17% super, generous leave benefits, 25% discount on courses for you and your family, and a flexible hybrid work environment! About the Role Make a positive impact on the heart of the University of Melbourne's workforce in an opportunity rich environment by maintaining and improving datasets and workforce information throughout the University.  Join the quest to shape our culture and practices by being a part of a "community of practice" of reporting colleagues across the university in central functions, such as IT, Finance and Student Services.  Workforce Data Analyst responsibilities include : Sources and pragmatically stages data from HR systems to support a range of business reporting requirements Reviews staged data on a regular basis to ensure its continued and ongoing relevance to end user processes Maintains contemporaneous documentation around data supporting key reporting processes and artifacts including necessary definitions, transformation rules and purpose Engages with the WorkDay ERP Program to support cut-over of data and reporting processes Workforce Reporting Officer responsibilities include : Delivers regular and ad hoc reporting to University stakeholders Reviews and regularly updates standard reporting artifacts for University stakeholders Co-ordinates the delivery of regular Workforce reporting for external stakeholders (eg.  WGEA Reporting) Supports HR stakeholders in their understanding of, and ability to interpret workforce and service reporting and metrics Who we are looking for Are you skilled at juggling tasks, working with integrity and implementing order and consistency?  We are looking for someone who is great with data and great with people, who can communicate with a diverse range of stakeholders Essential Skills include : Tertiary qualification / s in a relevant discipline, and / or demonstrated equivalent professional experience Demonstrated experience in developing and delivering reporting and / or pragmatic data solutions, ideally related to HR and / or workforce information Experience working in the higher education sector or a similar regulatory environment will be highly regarded Experience working with confidential HR, OHS and organisational data with respect for information privacy.  Demonstrated experience with a range of reporting tools and solutions. Ideally MS Office Applications (including Excel and Power BI) Ability to create and maintain documentation regarding technical processes at a level that can be understood and referenced by non-technical users Workforce Data Analystwill also have : Experience with native reporting capabilities of modern and legacy HRIS.  Superior Excel skills are essential. Familiarity with Oracle / PeopleSoft and WorkDay systems highly regarded Workforce Reporting Officerwill also have : Experience with cloud-based HRIS reporting such as WorkDay would be highly regarded For further information regarding responsibilities and requirements please refer to the attached PD.  To ensure the University continues to provide a safe environment for everyone, this position requires the incumbent to hold a current and valid Working with Children Check.  This role requires current valid work rights for Australia. Your new team - "Human Resources" This function is responsible for developing the people strategy to support the University's strategic plan and is accountable for the performance and delivery of the Human Resources function across the University.  It provides policy, industrial relations, governance and other critical advice and guidance ensuring that the University is compliant and cohesive whilst creating a culture that attracts and retains talent.  The function is also responsible for creating and maintaining a safe workplace where people can thrive and do their best work.  What we offer you! In addition to working in an opportunity rich environment, you will be part of a vibrant community and a enjoy a range of benefits including generous leave provisions, salary packaging, health and well-being services and discounts on graduate courses.  For more information check out our benefits page! The University of Melbourne We're tightly connected with community, both at home and abroad. Through our agile structure, we enable our employees to drive their own work – with a lot of autonomy, and have fun along the way!  The role  As a Data Analyst in our Supply Chain Logistics chapter, you will utilise your Power BI experience to create high quality reports, and provide insights to drive continuous improvement of our complex supply chain solution. • Create Power BI reports • Facilitate the connection of data sources • Recommend best practice report building and inform tools to generate insights • Drive cultural change on the value of quality reporting • Provide insights and analytics to optimise supply chain solutions • Drive a continuous improvement culture  What’s in your toolkit? • Experience working with Power BI and sound analytical sk • End to end supply chain knowledge, including an understanding of supply planning, logistics operations and inventory control • Ability to build positive relationships with internal & external stakeholders • Strong communicatio skills and abaility to deliver complex messages and reporting insights • Experience in a complex retail environment would be adventageous  Don’t worry if you don’t tick all the box’s for this role, we encourage you to still apply. job_description.296: Join a collaborative team and deliver great employee experiences.  Experience Hybrid working arrangements in a flexible environment  Permanent role based in either Melbourne or Sydney  We're REA  REA Group is not your average digital business. From humble beginnings in a garage in Melbourne’s east in 1995, we have grown into a leading global digital business, specialising in property.  With bold and ambitious goals, we are changing the way the world experiences property. No matter where you're at on your property journey, we're here to help with every step - whether that's finding or financing your next home.  Our people are the key to our success. At the heart of everything we do, is a thriving culture centred around high performance and care. We are purpose driven and collaborative, which drives innovation and our ability to make a real impact. As such, we’re proud to be named in Australia’s “Top 5” Best Workplaces two years in a row, as well as being recognised as a Best Workplace for Women.  Where the team fits in  The Data and Insights Analyst sits within the People & Culture team, headed up by Mary Lemonis,  Chief People and Sustainability Officer. From building management capability and the next  generation of leaders, to creating a diversity and inclusion strategy which is mainstreamed and  embedded into everything we do – the People & Culture team is all about making REA Group a great place to work. Supporting our multi-national business with HR processes, policies and systems to meet the needs of our people around the world, the team works to build high engagement with our impressive offering of programs and benefits.  What the role is all about  We are looking for a technically focussed Data and Insights Analyst who is passionate about People data and insights. You’ll be supporting the People & Culture team with key employee life cycle activities related to our specialist functions of Remuneration, Payroll and Work Health and Safety. You’ll contribute your subject matter expertise and work with a wide a range of activities and stakeholders.  Working closely with our Remuneration Manager, managing job evaluations, equity administration and cyclical rem processes like year end reviews and market data submissions, ensuring an efficient process, up to date information and fit for purpose solutions  Reviewing and supporting current WHS processes and policies, and determining what potential efficiencies can be made using technology and effective collaboration with key stakeholders  Assisting with payroll reporting, in particular making the best use of our new payroll reporting functionality in the Ramco payroll system.  Using modelling, statistics, trend analysis, and other data analysis techniques to collect, explore, identify, and analyse data.  Who we’re looking for  Intermediate to advanced Excel skills  Super strong attention to detail  Strong background and demonstrated experience in reporting and analytics, data science, continuous improvement  General problem-solving skills and ability to think creatively  Work productively in a fast-paced environment  Relevant qualification associated with data and analytics will be preferable  Data Analytics - using modeling, statistics, trend analysis, and other data analysis techniques to collect, explore, identify, and analyze data.  Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal and the sensitivity to understand audience needs and adapt style accordingly  Translating business requirements into clear, concise, testable and accurate user stories & process flows;  Time management and prioritisation  Experience working with HR/ People analytics  Experience with Workday & Ramco is advantageous but not essential  Broad knowledge and understanding of people management principles and practices  Ability to work independently and cooperatively with business and technical resources  The REA experience  The physical, mental, emotional and financial health of our people is something we’ll never stop caring about. This is a place to learn and grow. We’re committed to your development – both professionally and personally. Your experience with us is something we take seriously.  We offer:  A hybrid and flexible approach to working - https://rea.to/hybrid-working  Flexible parental leave offering for primary and secondary carers  Programs to support mental, emotional, financial and physical health & wellbeing  Our Because We Care program offers employees volunteering leave, community grants, matched payroll giving and our Community Café donates 100% of revenue to charity.  Hack Days so you can bring your big ideas to life  Performance recognition programs because hard work should never go unnoticed  Our commitment to Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion  We are committed to providing a working environment that embraces and values diversity, equity and inclusion. We believe teams with diverse ideas and experiences are more creative, more eﬀective and fuel disruptive thinking - be it cultural and ethnic backgrounds, gender identity, disability, age, sexual orientation, or any other identity or lived experience. We know diverse teams are critical to maintaining our success and driving new business opportunities. If you've got the skills, dedication and enthusiasm to learn but don't necessarily meet every single point on the job description, please still get in touch.  If you like the sound of us, then we think you should apply today. We're proud to be Circle Back Initiative Employer and we commit to respond to every applicant. While we're looking at your application, and preparing to come back to you with an update, why not get to know us a bit more through our various social channels?
job_description.297: About the Role  An exciting opportunity to join BOQ as a Senior Data Management Analyst during our transformation journey. By joining the digital bank of the future, you will be able to make a difference with integrity and empathy, overseeing the successful and effective analysis of the data quality capability adding significant value to our organisation.  As a Senior Data Management Analyst, you will be working closely with the Group Technology Team that consists of Business Analysts, Developers and Testers. Reporting to the Manager of Data Management, you will be responsible for supporting the execution of data initiatives that enable our bankers to have access to trusted, governed and easily available data which supports their needs.  In this role you will ensure data management practices are conducted in line with statutory, regulatory, audit and risk expectations. Furthermore, you will support operations of the Data Management Framework which includes data principles, policy, standards, and guidelines ensuring their pragmatic and beneficial application to data platforms and the wider data ecosystem. You will also be involved in conducting awareness and training initiatives to create a measurable uplift in data literacy and data handling skills across the bank.  About you  As an experienced data management and analytics professional, you will be a collaborative outcome and people focussed individual who thrives on working in a fast-paced environment. You will have 6+ years of experience working in enterprise data platforms (Data Warehousing, Data Analytics Data Governance or BI) with an ability to manipulate and analyse large amounts of data using SQL queries and map data from source to target.  Alongside your experience working with third party vendors and developing lasting relationships to ensure success, you will have a strong understanding and practical experience in data quality, data management/governance frameworks and methodologies.  About Us  BOQ is one of Australia’s leading regional banks and provides a genuine alternative for Australian financial services customers and employees. Our purpose is to create prosperity for our customers, shareholders and people through empathy, integrity and by making a difference. Our ambition is to be known as the bold challenger bank; with multi-brands that are digitally enabled with a personal touch.  BOQ is passionate about providing opportunities for you to develop your career as we continuously adapt and deliver in a transformational and collaborative environment with a strong focus on community.  BOQ’s Inclusion vision is to foster a workspace that values and leverages difference and creates new possibilities, a place where our people feel confident to bring their best selves to work every day. We embrace difference and believe that our workforce should reflect the customers and communities that we serve.  Since BOQ Group is recognised as an Employer of Choice for Gender Equality by the Workplace Gender Equality Agency (WGEA).  Our Benefits Flexible working arrangements Discounted financial products Salary sacrificing options Paid parental leave with no minimum Paid volunteer days Purchase annual leave Discounted private health insurance plan Employee Assistance Program (EAP) 5 employee diversity network groups focusing on: First Nations Reconciliation Council, Proudly ME (LGBTIQA+), Multicultural, Gender and Early Career BOQ Group is a member of Pride in Diversity and a participating organisation in the Australian Workplace Equality Index
job_description.298: **If you love:** - Identifying, communicating and working cross-functionally, to resolve data gaps impacting the team’s reporting and analytical requirements - Working collaboratively to automate manual data processes to drive operational efficiency wherever possible - Support the development of Risk’s new data platform in the MS Azure environment - Responsible for data requests from both internal and external stakeholders - Assist with ongoing data quality improvement initiatives across the risk landscape - Work to upskill and mentor junior Analysts within the team and wider business • *Then this just might be…** • *Your dream job:** - Accountable for end-to-end data analytics solutions, including documentation and quality assurance - Support data governance through the documentation of data sources and data lineage - Adopting best practice, take responsibility for the migration of existing reporting and the build out of new reporting in Power BI on the new data platform - Support the testing of front-line system changes that impact data integration across the risk data platform
job_description.299: Description  We are currently seeking a motivated and experienced Data Analyst on a permanent, full-time basis to review data to identify key insights, and solve problems and be able to communicate this information to various stakeholders across the organisation.  The Data Analyst will turn data into information, information into insight and insight into business decisions. The Data Analyst will be responsible for conducting full lifecycle analysis to include requirements, activities and design. The Data Analyst will develop analysis and reporting capabilities. They will also monitor performance and quality control plans to identify improvements.  Key duties of the role include: • Interpret data, analyse results using statistical techniques and provide ongoing reports. • Develop and implement databases, data collection systems, data analytics and other strategies that optimise statistical efficiency and quality. • Acquire data from primary or secondary data sources and maintain databases/data systems. • Identify, analyse, and interpret trends or patterns in complex data sets. • Filter and "clean" data by reviewing computer reports, printouts, and performance indicators to locate and correct code problems. • Work with management to prioritise business and information needs. • Locate and define new process improvement opportunities.  Requirements  What you can bring to the role:  Essential: • Tertiary level qualification/s in Mathematics, Economics, Computer Science, Information Management or Statistics. • At least three years of experience in a Data Analyst role. • Proven analytical skills, including mining, evaluation, analysis, and visualization. • Strong SQL, SSRS and Power BI skills with the ability to learn other analytic tools. • Current National Police Certificate (or ability to acquire). • Applicant must be based in Australia.  Desirable: • Prior experience with database and model design and segmentation techniques. • Strong programming experience with frameworks including XML, Javascript, and ETL. • Practical experience in statistical analysis through the use of statistical packages including Excel, SPSS, and SAS. • Proven success in a collaborative, team-oriented environment.  Benefits  What We Offer: In return for your dedication and expertise, we offer: • * Competitive remuneration and benefits • Attractive pay incentives, along with not-for-profit salary packaging. • The chance to engage in purposeful work within a values-driven organisation. • Long-term job security in an industry resistant to economic fluctuations. • A thriving, positive organisational culture that prioritizes well-being. • Abundant prospects for personal and professional growth through learning and development initiatives. • Discounted health insurance.
job_description.300: Job Description  Location: Melbourne | CBD  Job type: Full time / 6 months  Organisation: Victorian Building Authority  Salary: $105,479 - $127,621  Occupation: IT and Telecommunications  Reference: VG/6274T  The VBA has an exciting 6 month fixed term opportunity to join the State Building Surveyor department in the role of Data Analyst Position overview Reporting to the Manager Technical Capability and Capability the primary responsibility of the Data Analyst is to continue to build, expand and maintain the existing data analytics platform. The Data Analyst will work with structured and unstructured data and has experience working with and integrating data from a variety of sources, including Google Analytics, Survey Monkey, YouTube, Channel Management System (CXOne) and other internal systems, to generate accurate and insightful data analysis and visualisation reports using PowerBI, advanced Excel or Power Apps. Working with internal data owners to primarily source data, develop and maintain reports that inform the development of education resources and measure the effectiveness of those education resources. In addition, the Data Analyst will provide insights into Channel Management System data to develop and implement efficiencies in the Building and Plumbing Technical and Regulatory Team and perform other data analysis functions to inform the implementation of new regulatory tools. Who we are looking for  experience in delivering insightful analysis & Power BI reporting solutions on the Azure platform proven excellence in analytical thinking and the translation of complex unstructured and structured data into informative visuals, reports and actionable insights. demonstrated ability to be pro-active, professional, customer-focused, organised, and self-managed to deliver a consistently high level of output and service in a deadline and fast-paced environment.  VBA Commitment We value diversity and inclusion in all forms - gender, religion, ethnicity, LGBTIQ+, disability and neurodiversity. We encourage you to discuss flexible work options with the hiring manager during the recruitment process.
