job_description.302: Our technology, our people, our product... At PointsBet, we’re built different.  Launching in Australia in 2017, PointsBet are dedicated to providing our customers with the ultimate betting experience. We're on a mission to make racing and sports betting easier to understand, fun to use and faster. After some recent business changes, PointsBet Australia is about to head into a exciting stage of it's journey and as we continue to grow, we're looking for an experienced BI Reporting Analyst to join us.  The BI Developer will be responsible for delivering insight and actionable reports across the organisation and focus on becoming a subject matter expert in the company’s data. This role will need to provide support to the Data Analytics team in defining and prioritising requirements as well as testing data before releasing reports to the business. The Senior BI Developer will also be involved in reporting and providing analytical support to the Operations, Trading, Marketing, Compliance, Finance and Product team.  What you’ll own:  • Develop engaging and focused analytical reports & visualizations • Extract, interpret, and present data and insights using MS SQL and Power BI • Follow processes and methodologies around implementing and supporting BI systems • Assist stakeholders to define, clarify, and document reporting and analytical requirements • Strong stakeholder interaction skills and the ability to communicate insights in a manner that aids and informs decision making • Establish effective working relationships with internal stakeholders, same department teams, senior management, and external parties • Ensure the accuracy of reported information and work with data stewards in a cycle of continuous improvement of data quality • Establish automation and QA processes necessary to ensure quality provided to the business • Build and maintain a strong documentation repository • Become an expert in digital wagering data and information • Assist users to define, clarity, and document reporting and analytical requirements  The skills we seek:  • 3-5+ years of experience in querying data using T-SQL or similar • Experience with reporting & visualization tools such as Power BI, Tableau, SSRS • Experience with data modelling and data warehouse processes • History in data analysis and presenting insights visually • Experience in using JIRA and Confluence would be beneficial • Proficiency in data visualization techniques and dashboard creation in Power BI • Ability to construct complex queries and manage large data sets. • The ability to think creatively and problem solve is critical • Strong attention to detail • Strong commercial acumen • Wagering Experience highly regarded  The PB Perks!  • PointsBet Flex Program – Filled with Hybrid Working, Work from Anywhere weeks, Sabbatical Leave to name a few. • PointsBet Day – Get your PointsBet anniversary off. • Annual Bonus Scheme – We reward great work, earn even more on top of our competitive salary packages. • Parental Leave – 18 weeks for Primary Carers and 4 weeks for Secondary Carers. • Daily breakfasts, sporting event tickets, a range of wellness programs.  So you don’t tick every requirement on the job description but are still interested? Please apply anyway! We are built different at PointsBet, because we think different. We promote diversity of thought and would love to hear from a wide range of applicants as we believe that any unique skillset adds value to the team. Once you're in the door, your talents will be fostered, with 42 Australian promotions in 2022 alone, we are truly committed to growing talent at PointsBet!
job_description.303: Company Description  illion is the leading independent provider of trusted data and analytics products and services in Australia and New Zealand. illion is headquartered in Melbourne with offices in all major metropolitan cities across Australia and New Zealand. Our team work with leading brands in our region to bring data & analytics to life!  Job Description  Your new role and how you’ll make a difference  Our Data and Insights Analysts are charged with the fulfilment of Data Services requests within our Service Level Agreement, as well as maintaining systems and information that provide our customers with the most optimum data specific to their needs!  The value-add things you’ll be doing • Fulfilment of S&MS Marketing and data lists within Service Level Agreement or as negotiated depending on the complexity of the work requested. • Scope customer requirements and work with and provide advice to the internal RMS and S&MS sales function to ensure best possible customer solution. • Maintaining and servicing of existing databases to perpetuate quality output. • Identify data integrity issues and proactively identify solutions to improve processes and data accuracy. • Create, maintain and perform analytics and statistical reports required to assist all internal teams including Marketing, Trade, RMS and S&MS using R and/or Python. • Act as pivot point between IT and trade team to achieve all KPIs set by the business.  Qualifications  The experience and qualifications you’ll need to be successful • Customer service focus, high standards and ethical values. • A desire to contribute to the long-term strategy of service quality within illion. • Experience with Python or R Languages • SAS experience, SQL experience • 1-3 years of experience in a related field and Tertiary qualification, i.e. Business / Mathematics / Science / Engineering / IT tertiary degree. • Experience with Python or R Language  Additional Information  Some of our perks • Flexibility and Remote Working Options • Gifted Leave, Purchased Leave, Public Holiday Swap and Paid Volunteer Leave • Paid Parental Leave • Novated Leasing and Corporate Discounts (ie. Health Insurance) • Education Assistance and dedicated time for professional development as part of your role • Free Employee Assistance Programme, Free Flu Shots and Subsidised Gym Memberships.  illion’s values  Wonder what if  We wonder on many levels. About ideas. And about how others see them. We listen with curiosity. Obsess the numbers. And embrace new ways to make data, make a difference  We’re good eggs  Everything we do is built on integrity. We hold ourselves to high standards. And higher principles. We act with good intentions. Taking every opportunity to be that little bit better.  Human. Kind  People are the hart of our products, processes and culture. Our relationships are a gift. We’re inclusive. Measuring the impact of our actions on other’s first. Kindness and humanity prevail.  We all add up  We work wonders when we work together. Our diverse perspectives and backgrounds make us greater than the sum of our parts. We’re one team, where every single one of us counts.  How to Apply  To apply, please click “Apply Now” button and we will be in touch shortly.  Due to the sensitive data that illion works with, employment at illion is subject to employees having full working rights for Australia and/or New Zealand and successful completion of a Criminal Record Check.  Here at illion, we value diversity and inclusion and believe that we are able to grow and learn better together with a diverse team of employees. By joining illion you'll be part of an inclusive culture that celebrates a diversity of cultures, skill sets, educations and opinions. People from all culturally diverse backgrounds including Aboriginal & Torres Strait Islander Peoples are encouraged to apply.
job_description.304: See job description for details  Operations Data Analyst within Banking domain • Long term contract with great pay rates (12 months) • Experience in Financial industry preferred • Operations knowledge and experience with data analytics Your new company Our client - leading banking firm and market leader, one of the four largest financial institutions in Australia in terms of market capitalisation, earnings and customers. They are on the lookout for Operations Analyst to perform a range of analytical activities efficiently and effectively  Your new role: This is an Operations role responsible for gathering, analysing and maintaining various operational processes and performance information, reports and data for Private Wealth Operations. The role will be required to restructure the information and data and provide scheduled and ad-hoc reports to stakeholders of private wealth business.  Key accountabilities of the role: • Analyse Operation's performance data, where required, establish performance measures, and provide scheduled and ad-hoc reports • Establish operating rhythm in building and sharing Operational reports e.g Performance, Risk Events, Change initiatives etc • Maintain Change Initiatives register for Productivity and Efficiency Program • Create communication to engage wider business stakeholders to keep them abreast of Operations changes, performance and SLA compliance • Support Operations impacting projects change management activities • Escalate risks and issues in a timely manner • Help PWO teams in establishing activity processing times and SOP documentation What you'll need to succeed: • Operations knowledge and experience with data analytics and written and oral communication • Create performance dashboards and Visual Management Board • Ability to multitask and deliver Operations insights and reports on time • Experience and ability to engage stakeholders, create formal communication - inter team and intra team • Process analysis and procedure (SOP) development • Experience working in Banking, Wealth, Advice or Broking business • Basic understanding of project life cycle • Intermediate to Expert level of MS Excel skills - Pivot tables, Graphs and formulas What you'll get in return • 12 months contract role with a leading bank. • An opportunity to work on high-profile projects with competitive remuneration package. What you need to do now If you're interested in this role, click 'apply now' to forward an up-to-date copy of your CV to Kanika.Behl@hays.com.au #2810030
job_description.305: IQ Group  IQ Group has supported Superannuation and Wealth Management clients through unprecedented change for more than 15 years in Australia. From our offices in Melbourne, Sydney and Brisbane, over 90 specialist consultants assist clients improve their operations and use of technology. Our clients benefit from IQ Group's domain experience and commitment to project delivery. IQ Group is part of a global company with other offices in South Africa.  The Opportunity  IQ Group is undergoing an exciting period of growth, and have been engaged as the partner of choice to deliver a number of strategic programs on behalf of our customers.  In order to be a successful candidate for this position, we do require an experienced Data Analyst. You will ideally have solid experience setting up SQL queries across a number of data sources to automatically detect and manage data quality exceptions in the Financial Services Industry  Skills required (non negotiable): • Min 3-5 yrs proven experience as a Data Analyst • Advanced SQL Scripting • SQL Server - For Extract, Transform & Load • Advanced Excel for building reports • Superannuation & or Financial Services experience Why IQ Group? Our purpose is to nurture and support a team who share our passion for delivering solutions that accelerate change and improve our clients' business results. As an IQ Group Consultant, you will have the chance to make an impact in the development of complex solutions for a wide range of organizations whilst working alongside and learning from other knowledgeable and experienced consultants. You may also have the opportunity to travel interstate and collaborate with your interstate colleagues.  If you're keen to join a dynamic and progressive organisation on the forefront of the financial services sector please apply now.
job_description.306: About Agoda  Agoda is an online travel booking platform for accommodations, flights, and more. We build and deploy cutting-edge technology that connects travelers with more than 3.6 million accommodations globally. Based in Asia and part of Booking Holdings, our 6,000+ employees representing 90+ nationalities foster a work environment rich in diversity, creativity, and collaboration. We innovate through a culture of experimentation and ownership, enhancing the ability for our customers to experience the world.  Get to Know our Team:  The Supply Equity Platform (SEP) team sits within the Product Supply team at Agoda Bangkok. We work closely with the sales department (Partner Services) to identify and optimize growth opportunities on accommodations supply for the company and to set up experiments to measure and implement changes. The projects SEP team works on directly impact Agoda’s bottom line and have long lasting structural impact to the business. We cover a range of topics including resource and product optimization. We collaborate with multiple departments and produce high quality results backed up by experimentation and data. Utilizing powerful tools and possessing an end-to-end view of how Agoda works, the SEP offers a team of learning and experience that will push you (and Agoda) into new territory.  In this Role, you’ll get to:  • Manage complex analytics processes and algorithms to ensure their continued smooth operation, identifying root causes and debugging them where needed. • Use and analyze data from multiple large-scale data warehouses and understand data flows across the entire organization. • Identify, support, and lead projects aimed at improving the operations of our automated systems (e.g. root cause detection, anomaly detection, performance analysis). • Develop automated infrastructure supporting business intelligence at a global level as well as the analytics processes supporting them. • Drive new analytical initiatives and projects aimed at improving resource and product optimization.  What you’ll Need to Succeed: • A hacker’s mindset – the ability to build simple but clever and elegant solutions to new problems within significant resource, operational and time constraints through deep understanding of the business, creative problem solving, and a wide range of expertise in data, analytics, automation, programming, and prototyping. • Either Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science or Bachelor’s degree in a quantitative discipline with extensive programming experience. • Experience in big data cleaning and wrangling as well as simple analytical processing (SQL is a must). • Have working experience in Python for data analysis. • A basic understanding of statistics and data, and the ability to implement this understanding in complex business situations. • The ability to visualize and understand complex data flows, pipelines, and processes.  It’s Great if you have: • Experience with complex analytics and statistical/machine learning techniques using R/Python/Spark. • Experience building automated analytical processes and functionality.  #sanfrancisco #newyork #seattle #boston #washdc #sydney #melbourne #perth #paris #london #tokyo #dhaka #vienna #edinburgh #manchester #amsterdam #munich #berlin #toronto #vancouver #moscow #dublin #seoul #hcmc #singapore #ENG #IT  Equal Opportunity Employer  At Agoda, we pride ourselves on being a company represented by people of all different backgrounds and orientations. We prioritize attracting diverse talent and cultivating an inclusive environment that encourages collaboration and innovation. Employment at Agoda is based solely on a person’s merit and qualifications. We are committed to providing equal employment opportunity regardless of sex, age, race, color, national origin, religion, marital status, pregnancy, sexual orientation, gender identity, disability, citizenship, veteran or military status, and other legally protected characteristics.  We will keep your application on file so that we can consider you for future vacancies and you can always ask to have your details removed from the file. For more details please read our privacy policy .  To all recruitment agencies: Agoda does not accept third party resumes. Please do not send resumes to our jobs alias, Agoda employees or any other organization location. Agoda is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes.
job_description.307: Position overview Reporting to the Manager Technical Capability and Capability the primary responsibility of the Data Analyst is to continue to build, expand and maintain the existing data analytics platform. The Data Analyst will work with structured and unstructured data and has experience working with and integrating data from a variety of sources, including Google Analytics, Survey Monkey, YouTube, Channel Management System (CXOne) and other internal systems, to generate accurate and insightful data analysis and visualisation reports using PowerBI, advanced Excel or Power Apps. Working with internal data owners to primarily source data, develop and maintain reports that inform the development of education resources and measure the effectiveness of those education resources. In addition, the Data Analyst will provide insights into Channel Management System data to develop and implement efficiencies in the Building and Plumbing Technical and Regulatory Team and perform other data analysis functions to inform the implementation of new regulatory tools. Who we are looking for • experience in delivering insightful analysis & Power BI reporting solutions on the Azure platform • proven excellence in analytical thinking and the translation of complex unstructured and structured data into informative visuals, reports and actionable insights. • demonstrated ability to be pro-active, professional, customer-focused, organised, and self-managed to deliver a consistently high level of output and service in a deadline and fast-paced environment.  VBA Commitment We value diversity and inclusion in all forms - gender, religion, ethnicity, LGBTIQ+, disability and neurodiversity. Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander candidates are strongly encouraged to apply. We're hoping to find a broad range of experiences, and people from all backgrounds and communities to join us at the VBA. We invite you to talk to us about any preferences or adjustments you may need to either our recruitment process or the role itself. If you identify as a person with disability, please let us know how we can provide additional support to your application. If this is you, please don't hesitate to get in touch via recruit@vba.vic.gov.au. We value and encourage flexibility for all, and so we support all our roles to be worked flexibly in some way, including part-time, to support a diverse, adaptive, and high-performing workforce. We encourage you to discuss flexible work options with the hiring manager during the recruitment process. Working at the VBA - what you can expect • A hybrid working model • Challenging work and a continuous learning environment • Flexible work options including part-time, compressed work schedules, flexible start and finish times, and purchased leave options. • A competitive salary, 11% superannuation  How to Apply We require you to upload: • A detailed copy of your resume • A cover letter outlining your relevant experience and how you feel it aligns to the role.  Applications Close: Midnight 18th October 2023  Important information • Only electronic applications submitted via careers.vic.gov.au will be accepted. • Candidates deemed suitable from a selection process may be considered for identical or similar vacancies within 6 months.
job_description.308: Apply Job no: 8MGGX Luxury Escapes is one of the world's fastest growing travel businesses, reaching up to 6 million subscribers each month with exclusive limited time offers at 'insider' prices. Here at Luxury Escapes, our mission is to delight our customers with incredible deals for the world's best holidays. We are a collective of forward-thinking people, driven to challenge the travel industry and ourselves to bring ever better travel experiences to our customer community. Our award winning employee experience is king here having been recognised as "One of the Best Places to Work' by the AFR in both 2021 and 2023, with weekly events, monthly recognition programs and significant professional development opportunities we do what we can to make you look forward to waking up every day! We are now seeking a highly skilled and analytical Senior Data Analyst who will be support our marketing activities. Playing a crucial role in driving data-driven decision-making, measuring marketing campaign effectiveness, and optimizing marketing strategies; your expertise in data analysis and reporting will be instrumental in supporting our performance marketing initiatives, enabling Luxury Escapes to maximize ROI and achieve business goals. Please note, it is essential that you have extensive commercial SQL experience to be successful in this role. You will be responsible for: Become the SME for Luxury Escapes' customers and performance marketing channels including conversion data, customer journeys, funnel analysis, and attribution as well as the modern data and analytics technology stack with emphasis on Google Analytics, AppsFlyer, Snowplow, Tableau and Looker (Data Studio). Collect, clean, and analyse marketing data to extract valuable insights and identify trends. Develop and maintain dashboards and reports to track key performance indicators (KPIs) for marketing campaigns. Provide regular performance reports to stakeholders, highlighting key findings and actionable recommendations. Conduct A/B testing and multivariate analysis to optimize ad creatives, targeting, and bidding strategies. Analyse user behaviour across marketing channels to identify opportunities for conversion rate optimization. Track and report on funnel performance metrics, including acquisition, activation, retention, and revenue. Collaborate with cross-functional teams to implement strategies for improving funnel efficiency. Ensure data accuracy and integrity by implementing data governance processes and performing regular data audits. Generate actionable insights and recommendations based on data analysis to support strategic decision-making. What we are looking for: Bachelor's degree in Mathematics, Statistics, Economics, Computer Science, or a related field. A postgrad degree would be highly regarded . Commercial experience as a Data Analyst or similar role within the performance marketing domain. Strong analytical skills with expertise in data manipulation, analysis, and visualization using tools such as SQL, Python, R, or Excel. Proficiency in data visualization tools: Tableau, Google Looker (Data Studio). Experience with performance marketing platforms, such as Google Ads, Facebook Ads Manager, or Adobe Analytics. Strong attention to detail and a commitment to data accuracy. Excellent communication and presentation skills, with the ability to effectively convey complex information to both technical and non-technical stakeholders. Please note we use SQL extensively, so require excellent SQL skills What's in it for you? Competitive remuneration package First class health and well-being program including annual vaccinations, yoga, meditation, gym discounts a, daily breakfasts and lunches provided 4 days a week. Fun working environment: Friday afternoon onsite gatherings (wine included!) and monthly celebration & recognition programs Discounted travel, birthday leave and a whole lot more! If this sounds like you and you feel you have the skills and experience to meet the requirements of the role, please apply online today! At Luxury Escapes we embrace diversity in our people and make hiring decisions based on experiences and skills. We do not discriminate based on gender identity, religion, race, national origin, sexual orientation, age, marital status, or disability status. You'll find a collaborative, inclusive, and respectful workplace here at Luxury Escapes, and we are proud to celebrate who you are. Please let us know if you require any reasonable adjustments during the interview process. We are a 2023 Circle Back Initiative Employer - we commit to respond to every applicant. job_description.309: Good call. We’re an exciting new digital enterprise with big ideas, supporting some of Australia’s most trusted and iconic brands focussed on making lives better for people all around Australia. We’re well on our way towards bringing the best of digital and data possibilities together to create more personalised shopping experiences for customers across our retail brands. Why? Because we want to make life more effortless for all Australians.  We’re continuing to bring the best talent and skills under one roof, working together and across disciplines to build amazing experiences for our customers. We continuously feed off each other’s insights, talents and capabilities, because we are a business that thrives on open collaboration and a shared vision of positive, fun and rewarding experiences.  In this role, you'll get to • Identify the key actionable insights through the analysis of data and translate this into clear business relevant recommendations and presentations. • Showcase, benchmark and quantify the value and outcomes of analytics-based decision making. • Apply appropriate analytical methods and techniques in an agile, pragmatic way that reflects the needs, constraints and KPIs of the business (e.g. time, cost, quality, data availability). • Serve as a trusted advisor by cultivating relationships with stakeholders and across various Leadership teams to deliver ad-hoc insights and by building repeatable reports and so the value from becoming a data driven organisation. • Contribute to the direction, development and implementation of the data and analytics strategy, roadmap and knowledge base within OneDigital and broader analytics teams within Wesfarmers divisions.  Relationship & KPIs • Collaborate with stakeholders in Analytics, Digital / Ecommerce, Marketing, Commercial, Technology, Data Engineering and Data Science teams to deliver valuable solutions to key business problems. • Serve as a trusted advisor by cultivating relationships with stakeholders to improve their understanding and knowledge of analytical techniques and outcomes. • Effective communication with key stakeholders around the delivery of key projects.  Delivery • Design and implement new analytics solutions, to meet business needs.  Innovation • Source, develop and apply new and existing analytical methods and techniques.  To shine on day one, what you need to have: • Analytics professional with a proven track record (1-2 years) in the development and business use of digital analytics technology and working with large & complex data sets. • Track record in designing and delivering data driven and/or analytics solutions that are actionable. • Proficiency in SQL and digital analytics (e.g. Google BigQuery, Tealium). • Ability to engage and influence business users in the opportunity and benefit from data driven decisions.  It's a bonus, but not required, if you have: • Experience with BI visualisation tools (e.g. PowerBI, Tableau). • Experience with Python. • Experience in big data analytics and technology. • Proficiency in DAX and Power Query. • Familiarity with web architecture including tag management, data layers, analytics tracking, and corresponding data flows.  Why OneDigital? • Working in a community of industry-leading innovators with a diverse and deep set of skills and experience, you will learn, collaborate, and co-create to achieve great things. • You’ll have ownership of your role, which will allow you to find the right balance between stretch and sustainability, work, and life. • Culture of comradery and collaboration - OneTeam • Plus, all the tools and learning you need, the tone is set for you to shine and succeed. • We know that diversity fosters greater innovation and better customer connection, so we strive to create a team where everyone feels like they belong. We support diversity, inclusion and we are a gender-neutral organisation. We celebrate individuals at their core, so they shine to their best.  Team Benefits – just to name a few!  To support you at work, what you value in life and in the community, our team member benefits include: • Access to the latest technologies. • An annual budget for your learning and development (this includes learning of your choice, certifications and more). • Extended parental leave (16 weeks for primary carers), and paid volunteer days. • Flexible working – we balance working together with working flexibly • People-focussed culture that celebrates achievements big and small • Oh, and did I mention paid subscriptions and discount cards.  Next steps  If this sounds like your next career move, then click on the ‘Apply’ button now. Please note that we may commence interviewing candidates prior to the application closing date. For brief enquiries please contact our Talent Acquisition Partner at sprasad@wesdigital.com.au
job_description.310: Full Job Description Join part of a centralised team for Data analytics | Be mentored and learn from Origin SME's You will have the ability to work on cutting edge technology stack capabilities Permanent, Hybrid Opportunity | Melbourne based  Delivering good energy starts from within  It’s an exciting time to join Origin. Creating a great place to work means together we’re powering a cleaner, smarter energy future. We’re always looking for better ways to deliver for our customers - and for our people.  The role An exciting opportunity for a passionate and motivated individual, who is eager to learn and develop, is now available. We are hiring for a ‘Data Analyst’ to support the Origin data and analytics platform by contributing to the design and development of our data model and associated data processes. The role will work with a wide range of business areas, implementing data-driven strategies and leading to improvement in performance and efficiency. Working with data from various source systems. Responsible for the development and coordination of ETL, reporting and analytical solutions within our central, cloud-based data and analytics environment.  Key responsibilities: Work with stakeholders to understand business requirements and translate these into technical specifications.  Contribute to the design and implementation of our data model by following best practices.  Prepare and maintain documentation, including design documents for data pipelines and models.  Build and maintain a large suite of visual reports.  Provide insight from reports, data and queries, leading to better business decisions and outcomes  Is this you?  To be successful in this role, you will have a learning mindset, and be keen to roll up your sleeves and get involved. You will be inquisitive and ability to work autonomously but also within a team. You will also be able to demonstrate:  Tertiary qualification in an IT related discipline  Strong SQL skills, ideally in PostgreSQL  Good understanding of relational database design principles and query optimisation  Experience documenting data models, including entity relationship diagrams  Strong analytical and interpretive skills  Experience orchestrating ETL jobs and a good understanding of ETL frameworks  Cloud experience will be highly regarded, in particular, experience with AWS and Redshift (Desirable)  SAP CRM/ISU experience highly regarded (Desirable)  What we can offer  A great team as well as interesting, rewarding, and engaging work! job_description.314: Data Scientist/Data Analyst H/F - Melbourne  CDI  Melbourne, Australia  Conseil  Publiée le 21/08/2023  Annonces similaires  Data analytics in the energy and climate space is growing at an incredible rate. Blunomy is growing the team to support the energy industry through its digitisation, decentralisation and decarbonisation transition and to support operability and planning in Australia and around the world.  We are looking for someone passionate about energy and data analytics to do-well-and-do-good by delivering data science products to better the energy market. As an analyst, you will work on projects under the supervision of project managers. In this setting, you will be exposed to the diversity of current energy challenges, leveraging your data and analytical skills to address them.  Example projects  We are always growing the products we deliver but over the last 12 months we have delivered: • Load forecasting: model and predict the evolution of the load on the electrical network. Use machine learning, data analytics and a fair amount of software development to forecast long-term energy consumption, daily energy profiles and Distributed Energy Resources (Electric Vehicles, Battery, Solar PV). • PV connections approval tool: dynamically model the energy network bringing together power flow modelling and machine learning to determine the PV hosting capacity of the local area. Used in production to approve hundreds of PV connection requests a day. • Vegetation management using LiDAR: collect three‑dimensional images of the local network gathered by drone or helicopter. Use machine learning and geometric models to detect and manage vegetation near powerlines. • Bushfire risk modelling: model and compute the network‑related bushfire risk based on fault ignition likelihood. Calculate the consequences of bushfires such as property damage or agricultural loss. • Low-Voltage network mapping: identify errors within the current mapping of the low-voltage network, especially targeting customers whom connection to the network has not been properly recorded. This was performed using outlier detection with out-of-bag predictors.  Depending on the objectives, projects will entail tasks of varying nature. Your first focus will be on projects requiring data analytics capabilities.  Why work for Blunomy?  You will be joining a passionate group of professionals, aligned in our mission to move towards a decarbonised, circular and inclusive economy. As we are currently in a stage of significant growth, you will be much more than a ‘cog in the machine’, with the ability to make a real and lasting impact across the business. We are focused on finding the right people to journey with us, and to those who do, we offer: • Attractive salary packages • Ability to participate in the company bonus scheme • Hybrid working environment, based in either Melbourne or Sydney • Ability to be part of a global team • Ongoing learning and development opportunities • Weekly team lunch/breakfast • Access to our health and wellbeing platform, Moka Care  Profil recherché  About you  We are looking for a motivated and talented person. The right person will have some of the following and a willingness and ability to learn the rest: • You are passionate about the energy transition and climate change, with a strong interest for energy, environment and/or sustainable development • An undergraduate degree or a postgraduate in a relevant discipline such Computing Science, Statistics, Maths or Engineering • 1-3 years experience in data science or software development will be highly regarded. • Knowledge of statistical and machine learning concepts and algorithms • Experience with the data science tool kit: • Python or R • Source control (such as Git) • software engineering and app development skills • Knowledge of cloud computing (such as Azure, GCP, AWS) • parallel computing (such as Spark or Dask) is a plus • Consultant tool kit: • good oral and written communication • client engagement skills • an ability to work to project timelines • Languages: Fluency in English is mandatory. • To be eligible to apply for this position, candidates must be either an Australian citizen or have working rights in Australia.  Location: Melbourne CBD  Salary: Depending on experience  Work type: Full Time, starting ASAP  Annonces similaires  Recevez chaque jour les nouvelles annonces qui correspondent exactement à votre recherche.

All while staying committed to our member first ethos as a proud Industry Fund.  About the role  The (Senior) Data Governance Analyst role sits within the Data Governance team and is responsible for collaborating with a range of internal & external stakeholders to understand their information needs and ensure Cbus’ data assets meet and/or exceed those needs within an acceptable level of cost and risk.  The Data Governance team has developed a framework to ensure Cbus’ data assets are well managed in accordance with policies, practices & techniques and meet the availability, quality, & security needs of all stakeholders. The (Senior) Data Governance Analyst plays a key role in helping the team bring the framework to life, embed it into the organisation’s change management & business-as-usual processes, and drive a strong data-centric culture.  In your role you will work with internal & external (business & technical) stakeholders to identify critical data, profile data, investigate data quality anomalies and issues and provide input into improving data quality.  You will also be responsible to work with the data governance team & projects to define, implement, & maintain metadata and reference data, and support users of the data catalog. You will have demonstrated experience working with data governance tools & technologies such as Alation, Bigeye, etc and possess strong SQL skills. Knowledge of / demonstrated experience using modern data management solutions such as Amazon S3, Amazon Redshift, DataGrip, Tableau, Microsoft Power BI, will also help you succeed. job_description.321: About CPBJH JV  CPBJH JV brings together two of Australia's leading construction partners, CPB Contractors and John Holland, with unparalleled expertise in large-scale and complex project management, civil construction, traffic management and tunnelling.  The West Gate Tunnel is a partnership between the Victorian Government and Transurban. The Joint Venture has been chosen as the contractor for construction, which began in early 2018 following planning assessment.  About the Project  The West Gate Tunnel Project is a city-shaping project that will deliver a vital alternative to the West Gate Bridge, provide quicker and safer journeys, and remove thousands of trucks off residential streets. The project will include: • Widening the West Gate Freeway from eight lanes to 12 between the M80 Ring Road and Williamstown Road; • Building a 2.8km eastbound tunnel and a 4km westbound tunnel under Yarraville; • Constructing a bridge over the Maribyrnong River providing an alternative to the West Gate Bridge; • Constructing an elevated road along Footscray Road to the Port of Melbourne; • Major new cycling and pedestrian paths.  Gender Diversity  We aim to maximise the potential of all our people. This means having an inclusive culture that values and sustains diversity and a work-life balance. To achieve this, we are focused on: • Embedding flexible work practices • Providing development opportunities for our women • Leaders championing and supporting our females to succeed • Actively looking to attract and promote women into non- traditional roles and putting support structures in place to help them succeed.  Your Opportunity  We are currently seeking applications for an experienced Safety Strategy, Systems and Innovation Coordinator to support the Health and Safety team.  Your key responsibilities will include: • Develop, improve and maintain Power Bi data management software • Develop new dashboards using advanced Power Bi system knowledge • By using existing database systems and Power Bi, define new ways to extract and present project data • Assist with the analysis of safety, health and project data. • Help shape and lead strategic initiatives to improve safety by analysing trends and identifying risks to project delivery. • Assist in developing, implementing, and managing an innovative safety system to enhance workplace health and safety. • Conduct in-depth quarterly analyses of project data to identify trends and focus areas, providing comprehensive reports and recommendations to senior management. • Schedule, monitor, and report on project safety activities and other Health, Safety, and Environment (HSE) deliverables. • Collaborate with project clients and business units to share health and safety initiatives and insights. • Coordinate and facilitate the One HSE Culture Survey Program, analyzing trends to develop and implement cultural initiatives. • Maintain a safety dashboard to monitor project performance. • Coordinate and ensure the completion of external assurance activities, such as CPB Global Actions. • Provide support in other safety, health, and environmental areas requiring compliance and governance considerations. • Ensure consistent application of project health and safety systems through site reviews and support for safety and operational personnel. • Assist the Health and Safety Administrator during work overflow periods.  Desired Skills: • Advanced system knowledge of Power Bi including back end dashboard development (essential) • Proven application skills using data management systems (ie; Power Bi, SharePoint) • Advanced Microsoft Excel skills • Stakeholder Relationships: Build and maintain effective relationships with key stakeholders, fostering collaboration. • Data Analysis: Possess highly developed analytical and quantitative skills to evaluate complex data and offer recommendations. • Communication: Strong written and oral communication skills to engage with individuals on various issues. • Data Proficiency: Proficient in data analysis and reporting. • Versatility: Experience in working with individuals at different organizational levels. • Adaptability: Ability to work under pressure and meet deadlines while remaining flexible.  In return, we offer rewarding careers, genuine opportunities to develop and grow, and a workplace culture that values and recognises effort and contribution. job_description.322: Acknowledgement of Country  CSIRO acknowledges the Traditional Owners of the land, sea and waters, of the area that we live and work on across Australia. We acknowledge their continuing connection to their culture and pay our respects to their Elders past and present. View our vision towards reconciliation  Child Safety  CSIRO is committed to the safety and wellbeing of all children and young people involved in our activities and programs. View our Child Safe Policy .  The Opportunity • Join CSIRO - Australia's National Science and Innovation Agency! • Supportive, rewarding, inclusive and truly flexible environment. • Collaborative, flexible, innovative workplace that values you and your career development  CSIRO is the national science agency that undertakes research to make life better for Australia and Australians.  We seek a highly motivated geospatial scientist/programmer to support the delivery of a large complex suite of projects under the National Bushfire Intelligence Capability (NBIC). NBIC is developing a framework to deliver data products and decision support relevant for state, territory and federal bushfire planning and response agencies.  The role requires large data processing, programming, spatial analysis, and cloud computing skills. The role is based within the Bushfire Analytics team in the CSIRO Environment Business Unit. For the successful candidate, opportunities may emerge over time to provide support for other projects in CSIRO’s Environment Business Unit portfolio of projects.  The Bushfire Analytics team is primarily based in Melbourne and Brisbane, and you will interact with other teams who are located in other CSIRO offices throughout Australia. The role provides the opportunity for continual learning and innovation, and you will work with a highly skilled and diverse team in a collaborative and supportive environment.  Your duties will include: • Leveraging statistical, physical and process models to inform fuel and fire behaviour prediction such as species distribution, ecosystem dynamics, vegetation growth and fire behaviour modelling. • Translating science into workflows that utilise technologies such web APIs and remote sensing data archives.  The role will also require: • Innovative design, development and adaptation of experimental methods and systems (some of which may be from beyond traditional bushfire and environmental science disciplines). • An ability to collaborate with staff from other teams and external stake holders to ensure NBIC is meeting their needs and objectives. • Demonstration of a capacity to communicate scientific research results, including collaborating on presentations and written reports for clients and the scientific community, industry or government. • Ability to work to deadlines and accepting responsibility for the scheduling and completion of major project activities, including allocating and directing tasks where appropriate. • Work collaboratively as part of a multi-disciplinary, regionally dispersed research team to perform tasks in support of CSIRO’s scientific objectives. • Adherence to the spirit and practice of CSIRO’s Values, Code of Conduct, Health, Safety and Environment procedures and policy, diversity initiatives and Making Safety Personal goals. • Other duties as directed.  Location: Melbourne, Brisbane or Canberra  Salary: AU$105,806 – AU$114,500 per annum + up to 15.4% superannuation  Tenure: Specified term of 2 years  Reference: 93634  To be considered you will need:  Essential  Under CSIRO policy only those who meet all essential criteria can be appointed. • Postgraduate education and/or equivalent experience in Science, including computer science. • Strong quantitative skills and a demonstrated ability to process, analyse and interpret large and complex spatial datasets. • Experience in the use and role of remote sensing and spatial data in multi-disciplinary projects that report on environmental processes. • Proficiency in computer programming and scripting languages (specifically Python and/or R) for automating workflows and the processing of geospatial data, including an ability to demonstrate skills in software version control. • An ability to use a broad range of computing platforms, including high performance and commercial cloud platforms. • Sound written and oral communication skills, including the production of scientific reports. Desirable: • Established knowledge and understanding of bushfire behaviour modelling, risk analysis and mitigation. • A track record of publication in peer-reviewed journals articles. • Experience developing custom tools using geographic information systems (GIS) such as ESRI ArcGIS and QGIS. job_description.326: About Tabcorp  Tabcorp is Australia's leading gambling entertainment company, renowned for our world-class brands including TAB, Sky Racing, and MAX. It’s an exciting moment in our history – a new era of Tabcorp. We’re bringing industry-leading products and services to our customers, leading with integrity, and creating value for our shareholders and industry partners by breaking into new horizons.  What You'll Do  As a Senior Digital Analyst you’ll join our Data & Analytics Centre of Excellence which is a game-changing hub of innovation and insights that is tasked with developing cutting-edge data and analytics solutions that tackle complex business challenges head-on.  Your role will be to partner with our Digital and Product teams to champion digital data analytics, support major digital initiatives and deliver insights that improve performance and create leading products and services. Therefore, you will: • develop digital insights leading to new and improved app and website features; • partner with developers on Adobe and Google Analytics initiatives; • drive digital engagement and growth through personalisation and tagging strategies; • analyze data to identify trends, understand user journeys, improve conversion funnels, and identify drop-off / pain points for customers; and • lead A/B Testing to evaluate effectiveness of digital marketing, web/app changes and conversion rate tests.  What you’ll bring  As a Senior Digital Analyst, you’ll have demonstrated experience in digital analytics role where you have developed a range of skills and experiences including: • strong experience developing strategies to drive digital engagement and growth across websites and apps; • experience in data analytics and exposure to website and mobile app development processes; • strong experience with Adobe Analytics or equivalent software (such as Google Analytics); • experience partnering with a range of stakeholders including product teams and software developers; and • ability to write and develop specifications for web and app tracking implementation.  Beyond technical expertise, you’ll be a passionate and attentive self-starter with a proven ability to deliver results. Operating in our fast-paced, flexible, and team-oriented environment, you'll need excellent communication and relationship management skills to effectively engage with both technical and non-technical audiences.  What You'll Get:  By joining our dynamic team, you will not only be part of redefining the future of our industry but will also enjoy a range of rewards and benefits, including: • Hybrid working environment, offering flexibility and work-life balance. • Comprehensive leave types, including cultural leave, volunteer leave, and 18 weeks of parental leave for all new parents. • Access to The Arena, a comprehensive health and well-being app that supports you and your family's mental and physical health. Here at Luxury Escapes, our mission is to delight our customers with incredible deals for the world's best holidays.  We are a collective of forward-thinking people, driven to challenge the travel industry and ourselves to bring ever better travel experiences to our customer community.  Our award winning employee experience is king here having been recognised as "One of the Best Places to Work' by the AFR in both 2021 and 2023, with weekly events, monthly recognition programs and significant professional development opportunities we do what we can to make you look forward to waking up every day  We are now seeking a highly skilled and analytical Senior Data Analyst who will be support our marketing activities.  Playing a crucial role in driving data-driven decision-making, measuring marketing campaign effectiveness, and optimizing marketing strategies; your expertise in data analysis and reporting will be instrumental in supporting our performance marketing initiatives, enabling Luxury Escapes to maximize ROI and achieve business goals.  Please note, it is essential that you have extensive commercial SQL experience to be successful in this role.  You will be responsible for: • Become the SME for Luxury Escapes' customers and performance marketing channels including conversion data, customer journeys, funnel analysis, and attribution as well as the modern data and analytics technology stack with emphasis on Google Analytics, AppsFlyer, Snowplow, Tableau and Looker (Data Studio). • Collect, clean, and analyse marketing data to extract valuable insights and identify trends. • Develop and maintain dashboards and reports to track key performance indicators (KPIs) for marketing campaigns. • Provide regular performance reports to stakeholders, highlighting key findings and actionable recommendations. • Conduct A/B testing and multivariate analysis to optimize ad creatives, targeting, and bidding strategies. • Analyse user behaviour across marketing channels to identify opportunities for conversion rate optimization. • Track and report on funnel performance metrics, including acquisition, activation, retention, and revenue. • Collaborate with cross-functional teams to implement strategies for improving funnel efficiency. • Ensure data accuracy and integrity by implementing data governance processes and performing regular data audits. • Generate actionable insights and recommendations based on data analysis to support strategic decision-making.  What we are looking for: • Bachelor's degree in Mathematics, Statistics, Economics, Computer Science, or a related field. A postgrad degree would be highly regarded . • Commercial experience as a Data Analyst or similar role within the performance marketing domain. • Strong analytical skills with expertise in data manipulation, analysis, and visualization using tools such as SQL, Python, R, or Excel. • Proficiency in data visualization tools: Tableau, Google Looker (Data Studio). • Experience with performance marketing platforms, such as Google Ads, Facebook Ads Manager, or Adobe Analytics. • Strong attention to detail and a commitment to data accuracy. • Excellent communication and presentation skills, with the ability to effectively convey complex information to both technical and non-technical stakeholders. • Please note we use SQL extensively, so require excellent SQL skills  What's in it for you? • Competitive remuneration package • First class health and well-being program including annual vaccinations, yoga, meditation, gym discounts a, daily breakfasts and lunches provided 4 days a week. • Fun working environment: Friday afternoon onsite gatherings (wine included) and monthly celebration & recognition programs • Discounted travel, birthday leave and a whole lot more  If this sounds like you and you feel you have the skills and experience to meet the requirements of the role, please apply online today  At Luxury Escapes we embrace diversity in our people and make hiring decisions based on experiences and skills. We do not discriminate based on gender identity, religion, race, national origin, sexual orientation, age, marital status, or disability status. We currently have an exciting opportunity for a Master Data Analyst to join our IT team. You will have: • A demonstrated understanding of data analysis and validation techniques in SAP environment • Attention to detail and accuracy in managing data in the system • Ability to create supporting documentation including (Master Data process documents, Data Standard Documents, Data flow diagrams etc.) • Ability to work effectively in a dynamic environment and use team work to resolve problems and issues within and outside of our direct accountabilities • Strong attention to detail, analytical and problem-solving skills • Strong communication skills (written, verbal & interpersonal) • Strong stakeholder management skills • Intermediate to advanced Excel skills • FMCG and dairy industry experience would also be highly regarded. Based in Asia and part of Booking Holdings, our 6,000+ employees representing 90+ nationalities foster a work environment rich in diversity, creativity, and collaboration. We design tailored business and product solutions with our partners and help them generate measurable value. Members of our team are empowered and supported to grow their market(s) or accounts. We develop win-win relationships and leverage Agoda’s unique accommodations portfolio and tech solutions to bring our partners the advantages they seek. Utilizing our strong brand and resources, we build new channels to increase the visibility of Agoda, introduce more travelers to our great products and service and deliver significant revenues to the overall business.  The Opportunity:  The role sits within the Supply Analytics team under Supply department, where new business ideas, and partnership types are incubated and scaled. We are looking for a BI Analyst whose main focus areas are providing visibility and insights for people-related issues through Business Intelligence tools like Tableau and SQL, managing data warehouses, building ETL processes, and helping build other tools to optimize the business. This role will be involved in strategic projects and work closely with commercial owners and business stakeholders, using data to identify and translate business needs and opportunities into actionable initiatives. You will report directly into the Manager, Senior Manager, or Associate Director of Supply Analytics.  In this Role, you’ll get to: • Translate internal briefs into analytical projects (to include refining the initial brief and asking the ‘right questions’, working through potential hypotheses and storyboarding the output) • Use and analyze data from multiple large-scale data warehouses and present statistically strong analysis to a wide range of business stakeholders • Proactively identify opportunities for growth within supply and the wider business • Drive new analytical initiatives and projects aimed at improving organizational efficiency and shaping Agoda supply • Identify, support, and lead projects aimed at scaling up the way the Supply organization leverages on data, insights, and intelligence • Automate manual operational processes and present back on time savings gained through modernization of business operations  What you’ll Need to Succeed: • 5+ years of experience as a BI Analyst in analytics/insights/strategy • Bachelor’s degree ideally in a business or quantitative subject (e.g. computer science, mathematics, engineering, science, economics or finance) • Hands-on experience with BI & analytics tools (SQL, Tableau, Metabase or PowerBI) • Experience in conducting A/B testing experimentation (a plus) • Good stakeholder management experience. Comfortable presenting to senior leadership and C-suite • Strong experience in finding data insights and provide business recommendation to the business • A good understanding of statistical modelling knowledge or any machine learning technique knowledge is a plus (regression, logistic regression, random forest, etc.) • Excellent skills in presenting and storytelling. • A hacker’s mindset – the ability to build simple but clever and elegant solutions to new problems within significant resource, operational and time constraints through deep understanding of the business, creative problem solving, and a wide range of expertise in data, analytics, automation, programming, and prototyping • Excellent communicator with superior written, verbal, presentation and interpersonal communication skills • Data driven in both decision making and performance measurement • Extreme comfort in ambiguous, fast-paced environment • Ability to multi-task, prioritize and coordinate resources  It’s Great if you Have: • Travel industry / e-commerce / tech / consulting experience  #Singapore #Berlin #Dublin #London #Jakarta #Hongkong #paris #sanfranciso #newyork #austin #seattle #tokyo #shanghai #seoul #sydney #brisbane #melbourne #toronto #moscow #saintpetersburg #kyiv  Equal Opportunity Employer  At Agoda, we pride ourselves on being a company represented by people of all different backgrounds and orientations. job_description.357: Hi! And thanks for stopping by!  We’re MYOB, a business management platform designed to unleash the potential of businesses across Australia and New Zealand! As the #originalstartup, our roots are in finance and accounting software, but today we are so much more. We help our Aussie and Kiwi customers unleash their full potential, giving them the tools to Start, Survive and Succeed: all in the one place.  We’re always on the hunt for those who bring a different perspective, diversity of thought and the drive to make our culture even better. Take your career to a new dimension at MYOB.  About the Team  Our Unified marketing team is here to drive un-believe-able results for the business. They create demand in market for MYOB and engage AU & NZ businesses when it matters most to either acquire or retain them. They’re dedicated to delivering value for our customers by understanding their business pain points, and needs and ensuring we deliver them value at every stage of their journey.  Are you passionate about utilising data to drive strategic marketing decisions? Do you have a curiosity for extracting insights from complex datasets and turning them into practical recommendations? If so, we have an exciting opportunity for you to join our marketing team as a Marketing Performance Analyst.  About the Role  As a Marketing Performance Analyst, you will play a crucial role in supporting our marketing team by analysing data, tracking program performance, and providing strategic insights. Your focus will be on optimising channel effectiveness, enhancing marketing program outcomes, and contributing to the overall success of our marketing efforts. Reporting to the Marketing Analytics and Performance Manager, you will collaborate with various team members across the organisation, including marketing leaders, cross-functional teams, and external partners.  Key Responsibilities  - Conduct in-depth tactical data analysis across marketing channels, identifying areas for process improvement and implementing metrics from engagement to conversion across segments.  - Mine and analyse data from multiple sources to track the performance of marketing programs against key performance indicators, offering insights to drive optimisation.  - Monitor and analyse performance throughout the marketing and sales funnel, pinpointing opportunities for enhancement.  - Collaborate with marketing, sales, revenue operations, and finance teams to contribute to quarterly and annual forecasts and performance modelling.  - Develop and implement regular reporting and data visualisations to communicate insights to senior leaders, enhancing self-serve analytics across the marketing function.  - Stay up-to-date with the latest web analytics tools and technologies, making recommendations for new tools that can improve web performance monitoring.  About You  - Deep understanding of data analytics across multiple channels.  - Strong operational experience in systems, processes, and technologies.  - Profound understanding of B2B marketing and sales strategies.  - Proven experience in website analytics, preferably in e-commerce or digital marketing environments, with expertise in Google Analytics, including configuration and reporting.  - Proven experience with various data platforms and tools, including Google Analytics, Microsoft Power BI, CRM systems (e.g., Salesforce or HubSpot), Microsoft Excel, and SQL for data analysis.  - Ability to extract insights from extensive data volumes to inform customer acquisition and retention strategies.  - Prior experience in creating dashboards and reports to convey findings to diverse audiences.  - Familiarity with business databases and data warehouses (e.g., Snowflake) is desirable.  Skills and Competencies  - Commercial savvy and business insight.  - Proficiency in data analysis and insights generation.  - Effective communication and collaboration skills.  - Passion for getting results through data-driven decisions.  - Ability to work successfully in a cross-functional team environment.  Our Culture & Benefits  Our values have stood the test of time. If you want to work and collaborate where opinions are valued, and your ideas can make a difference, come to a place where Your Work Matters.     See what it's like to work at MYOB and what we're all about.     Do your best work in a flexible work environment, right down to financial assistance to set up your home office…it’s called Flexperience, and it’s designed by you and your team!     Our partnership with Smiling Mind helps support the wellbeing of our team members and customers     Drive your own learning via conferences, in-house training, LinkedIn Learning, study assistance and a strong focus on leaders creating a learning environment     A multitude of leave options including up to an additional four weeks of purchased leave, generous parental leave, domestic violence leave, transgender leave, volunteer leave, study leave, plus more!     Communities built around ‘Wellness’, ‘Belonging’ and the ‘Planet’ where you can make a meaningful contribution     Access to best-in-class discounts and vouchers from leading retailers, and a lot more.  We are proud to be a Circle Back Initiative Employer and we commit to responding to every applicant.  MYOB are an equal opportunity employer and we champion diversity. Don’t meet every single requirement of this role? Still apply! Research tells us that that women and underrepresented groups are less likely to apply unless they meet every single requirement. At MYOB we believe that the right hire is someone who makes an addition to our culture, rather than someone who fits in and conforms to our status quo. Moving to ‘Culture Add’ means adding team members who not only value MYOBs standards and workplace culture, but also bring an aspect of diversity that positively contributes to MYOB. So, if you’re excited about this role, or about MYOB, we’d still love to hear from you!
job_description.358: About Future Fund  The Future Fund is Australia's Sovereign Wealth Fund. Our purpose is clear: we invest for the benefit of future generations of Australians.  Decision making is our commercial competitive advantage. Our organisation is home to ambitious, high-performing people who are driven to do meaningful work, grow professionally, support their peers and colleagues, and contribute to the future success of our organisation.  Our ‘One team, One purpose’ philosophy underpins our unique culture and the way we work together. This philosophy extends into all aspects of our organisation and guides how and why we do what we do.  The Opportunity  An exciting opportunity awaits an experienced Senior Analyst to join the IDM Data Operations team. This role is aimed at supporting the Overlays investment team, for whom you will manage upstream investment data management activities. Your in-depth understanding of data analysis, management, tools, models, and the data lifecycle, coupled with your expertise in derivative products (including their valuation and trade life cycles) along with proficiency with the Aladdin platform, will be invaluable in managing investment data for this specialised domain.  Your primary focus will be on daily delivery of data into the Aladdin OMS and ensuring that trading data is both timely and accurate for our Overlays investment team. Key stakeholders to this role are the Overlays team and Investment Operations teams, your ability to drive meaningful and successful relationships with stakeholders is key to success. Your innovative and proactive approach, along with strong statistical skills, will drive data-driven solutions to enhance their experience with the data.  If you are an ambitious professional with a proven background in data analysis and possess expertise in derivative products and lifecycles, along with proficiency in the Aladdin platform, we invite you to apply.  Key Responsibilities  Data Management and Technical Support: Investigate and resolve technical issues related to trades, monitor trading activities, and provide technical expertise on the Aladdin derivatives system. Collaborate with investment teams and technology to ensure accurate processing of trades and settlements. Enhance processes through Aladdin platform improvements.  Operational Service Delivery: Oversee outsourced partners, ensuring high-quality service delivery to downstream consumers. Monitor data delivery, certification, and exception management. Implement market data requirements, drive data quality improvements, and proactively develop solutions to enhance operational efficiency.  Partner and Provider Management: Support oversight of partner delivery, prioritize and manage data service requests. Monitor partner services/products in line with solution parameters. Assist in project and product management of data-related initiatives, fostering effective partner relationships.  About You  1. Technical Proficiency: A strong grasp of the Blackrock Aladdin system, coupled with expertise in derivative securities, trade lifecycles, and market conventions. 2. Analytical Acumen: Proficiency in quantitative analysis and problem-solving, enabling the development of data-driven solutions and insights. 3. Effective Communication: Outstanding interpersonal and communication skills, with the ability to engage stakeholders, convey information, and influence decisions. 4. Professional Attributes: A commitment to professionalism, accuracy, and quality in tasks, along with a proactive, innovative, and adaptable mindset to navigate a dynamic environment.  Life at Future Fund  Our approach to building an inclusive culture is aimed at facilitating impactful, effective and objective decision making. We continue to deepen our understanding of the lived experience of underrepresented groups within our industry.  To continue to expand our knowledge, we actively encourage you to apply to this role and contribute to our collective Purpose. We are better for our differences and support our people in bringing their authentic selves to work. It not only benefits our teams, it means you can focus on what matters most, being you. job_description.360: Bonfire isn’t just another digital marketing agency. We deliver results for our valued customers – businesses whom we see as partners, that have a real-world impact on their bottom line.  Our focus and passion for data-driven outcomes have cemented our position as one of Australia’s leading digital performance agencies. Return on investment (ROI) is the foundation of everything we do.  We work with REIWA, Water Corporation, Furniture Bazaar, CurtainWorld, and many more iconic brands.  We have a fantastic opportunity for a Data Analyst to join our Operations team. This is a hands-on technical role that will suit a self-motivated analytical mind with experience and passion for solving complex multi-faceted problems using data.  Reporting to the General Manager – Business Operations, you will be responsible for working with internal stakeholders to translate complex business questions into abstract analytical models which you will then implement, explore, interpret, and visualise using our best-practise modern data stack.  Most days your role will involve: • Meeting with members of our leadership team to translate their business intelligence problems into actionable reporting solutions • Building elegant, modular, extensible data models with Data Build Tool (dbt) using SQL • Querying our Snowflake data warehouse using SQL to answer ad hoc questions • Building beautiful dashboards and reports to power insight analysis across all of our internal functions (Operations, Customer Service, Finance etc) using Power BI and ThoughtSpot • Deep diving into our Snowflake data warehouse to uncover unheralded insights into the performance of our clients digital marketing  Occasionally your role will involve: • Working directly with clients to resolve interesting questions they might have about their digital marketing data • Supporting in the development and implementation of data pipeline and automation projects • Helping educate all Bonfire employees on data-driven analysis and methodologies  You’re likely to have the following qualities: • You’ve got experience working in similar hands-on analytical roles • You’ve got formalised training, probably a university degree, in a field relevant to the role at hand, or can make a strong argument why you don’t need one • You can write complex SQL statements in your sleep • You may not have had direct experience using Data Built Tool (dbt) but you’ve always wanted to learn • Data is a hobby and a passion as well as a profession, you’re always using data in your personal life and building personal projects using data • You can confidently explain what a Google Analytics session is and how marketing attribution works • You might have worked with Snowflake as a data warehouse, or if not, you’ve definitely worked with similar column-orientated storage like Google BigQuery • You’re a veracious learner, and revel at the opportunity to learn a new skill or platform • You celebrate wins, and analyse the opportunities that come from misses • Though you’re highly analytical, you’re also an excellent communicator and enjoy distilling complex concepts in the clearest, most concise fashion possible  What we can provide you:  We have an excellent office environment located in the heart of Subiaco, and an unparalleled agency culture.  While our way of working is like a well-oiled machine, we have a strong innovation orientation. You will have access to the latest software and programs to hone your craft, and the benefits that come with a collective mindset geared towards continual improvement.  We have strong values (we created them together as a group), we have a talented team with a genuine focus on high performance – and a growing, profitable business with all the benefits that come along with it.  What else can you expect at Bonfire? • Excellent work-life balance, with a strict ‘no agency hours’ approach, flexible start and finish times and work from home options • Ongoing training and professional development • Wellbeing program including an Employee Assistance Program • Great café-style coffee, cold pressed juices, kombucha, snacks and fresh fruit • Regular opportunities to socialise and celebrate our success  To get to know us better visit: https://www.bonfire.com.au/work-at-bonfire/.  Interested? Apply via the link with your resume and cover letter. Please note you will be redirected to an external site.
job_description.361: Data Analyst  Are you a Data Analyst who is keen to bridge your technical skills with a passion for Sport? Are you interested in developing your technical skills whilst enabling the next generation of Western Australian Olympians and Paralympians to achieve their goals?  About WAIS  The Western Australian Institute of Sport (WAIS) is the peak high-performance sporting organisation in Western Australia. WAIS has a proud history of Olympic, Paralympic and World Champions who have accomplished amazing achievements within sport and in life. WAIS enables and supports WA athletes to achieve success on a national and international level. Our culture of Striving for Excellence is lived through the behaviours of athletes and staff that demonstrate Passion, Integrity, Quality and Teamwork.  WAIS is proudly supported by the State Government and is a member of the National Institute Network who collectively support National and State Sporting Organisations to deliver the National High Performance Sport Strategy.  About the role  The Data Analyst supports the delivery of the sports intelligence strategy with skills in scripting, querying and analytics to deliver timely and accurate insight to stakeholders.  The Data Analyst will be part of the Performance Systems and Analytics (PSA) team which is a newly formed team in the Western Australian Institute of Sport (WAIS). WAIS supports Western Australian athletes perform at the highest levels through providing coaching, training environment and support services (including medical, sports science, coaches, and other service providers. The role of data analyst is key to support the Performance Systems and Analytics team deliver the WAIS sports intelligence strategy.  This position entails a multifaceted scope, affording you the opportunity to acquire and cultivate skills through practical experience. Core duties will include the following:  · Organisation Intelligence: Build and maintain reports, dashboards and intelligence solutions for stakeholders  · Data management: Maintain current and future processes and standards on the data platform  · Data ingestion: Build and maintain sustainable ingestion solutions for new external data sources  · Organisational Data Literacy: Assist in creating organisational data literacy, culture and trust in data solutions  · Communication with stakeholders  The role is based out of the WAIS High Performance Service Centre in the Mt Claremont Sporting Precinct and may require domestic travel.  About you  We are looking for an enthusiastic Data Analyst with proven technical abilities to support the work of the Performance Systems and Analytics Team.  Experience and qualification requirements:  · Experience with SQL, Python and dashboarding tools (Power BI, Tableau etc.)  · Database management  · Ability to translate stakeholder requirements then design and implement relevant solutions  · Data visualisation, reporting and communication  · Familiarity with sports analytics frameworks  · Ability to work with a multidisciplinary team  · Passion for sport and sports performance  Desirable:  · Experience with Fusion/Smartabase  · Experience with Azure  · Data engineering experience  · Power BI experience  Next steps  To apply, you must create an account via our career’s portal and apply https://wais.elmotalent.com.au/careers/default/jobs  Please submit a one-page cover letter along with your resume and experience against the Position Description found on our careers portal.  Applications will close on 4th September 2023, at 5pm AWST.  Please note, shortlisting of candidates will commence prior to this date and applicants are encouraged to apply at your earliest opportunity.  This is a full-time, maximum term contract. The anticipated salary is from $80,570 - $86,797 + superannuation and will be negotiated with the successful candidate.  Please note, only successful applicants will be contacted for an interview.  For further information  For role related queries please contact Kawther Sidhoum, HR Advisor, via email ksidhoum@wais.org.au  Building System Capability  At WAIS, we offer career opportunities for people who share our ambition and passion for high performance sport. From graduates to expert professionals, we are committed to offering fulfilling careers and the chance to grow as we grow. We would love you to be part of our journey.  Apply today.
job_description.362: We are looking for a creative Data Analyst to join our diverse team at Ventia in Perth. If you are strong in decision-making, teamwork and have the right initiative for the job, then apply for the position of Data Analyst at Ventia today  About the role  Ventia's Defence Base Services (DBS) team are seeking an experiencedData Analystto join their Finance team based in Perth WA. As a Data Analyst you are responsible for managing the master data, developing reports and troubleshooting data issues. You are adept in translating project requirements into custom-formatted data reports.  The ideal candidate for this position can complete life cycle data generation and outline critical information for each program of work. SQL experience advantageous but not essential to this role In depth understanding of relational database management systems Strong problem solving and diagnostic skills Strong business and commercial acumen An ability to successfully engaging stakeholders from various levels of the business High level of detail  Other special conditions  The incumbent to this position must be eligible to obtain and maintain a Defence Security Clearance up to a level of negative vetting 1 (secret). As a result of this requirement the incumbent is preferred to be an Australian Citizen. This position requires a National Criminal History check and a valid Australian driver's licence. This role comes with the added security of being offered as a permanent position with consideration of future flexible working requirements.
