job_description.363: About Us  Fortescue is both a proud West Australian company and a global green solutions business. We are recognised for our culture, innovation and industry-leading development of infrastructure, mining assets and green energy initiatives.  Our Opportunity  Work Location: Fortescue Centre & Bennett St • Fortescue’s Perth office is located on the traditional lands of the Whadjuk Noongar people.  Roster: Monday to Friday  The Data Scientist is a critical role within the Data Analytics for Health and Safety team at Fortescue, responsible for leveraging data-driven insights to enhance health and safety initiatives. This role requires expertise in Python, machine learning, deployment in AWS using SageMaker, as well as proficiency in Snowflake and SQL for data access and analysis. Additionally, this role includes components of the Analytics Engineer role, such as automation using SQL/Snowflake and reporting using Power BI and Streamlit.  Key Responsibilities • Utilize SQL and Snowflake to access, query, and analyze operational and safety data. • Explore and clean data to identify trends and patterns relevant to health and safety objectives. • Develop and implement machine learning and deep learning models to predict safety-related outcomes and support decision-making. • Utilize Python libraries and frameworks for machine learning and deep learning tasks. • Deploy machine learning models into production using AWS SageMaker, ensuring scalability and reliability. • Monitor and maintain deployed models for optimal performance. • Implement data automation solutions using SQL/Snowflake, including the development of stored procedures and tasks to streamline data workflows. • Create data visualizations and reports using Power BI and Streamlit to communicate insights effectively to stakeholders. • Collaborate with the Visualization Engineer to enhance data storytelling. • Collaborate with health and safety stakeholders to understand their data needs and align data science solutions with organizational objectives. • Document data science methodologies, model development, and deployment processes. • Share knowledge and best practices within the team.  Qualifications And Experience • Master's or Ph.D. in Data Science, Computer Science, or a related field. • Strong proficiency in Python for data analysis, machine learning, and deep learning. • Experience with machine learning model development and evaluation. • Proficiency in SQL and experience working with Snowflake for data access, analysis, and automation. • Strong problem-solving skills and the ability to derive actionable insights from complex data. • (Beneficial) Deep learning expertise, including working with neural networks and frameworks (e.g., TensorFlow, PyTorch). • (Beneficial) Demonstrated experience with model deployment in AWS using SageMaker or in a cloud environment. • Excellent communication skills and the ability to convey technical findings to non-technical stakeholders. • A collaborative mindset and the ability to work effectively in cross-functional teams.  Our Commitment  Fortescue is deeply committed to providing a safe culture that builds respect, fosters inclusiveness, and values diversity. We celebrate individual strengths and team members from all backgrounds are encouraged to bring their whole selves to work. Our global workforce drives and promotes an inclusive culture, both within our organisation and throughout the communities we interact with across the world. Diverse backgrounds include First Nations Peoples, people with differing abilities, LGBTIQ+ community, gender, neurodiverse, cultural diversity, all age groups, and those with an intersectional or multiple diverse characteristics. We encourage candidates from all backgrounds to apply.  https://fortescue.com/careers  Internal Candidates / Current Contractors please apply via Success Factors Careers Portal. For further information on how to apply please visit the Fortescue Hub.  Fortescue reserves the right to close applications early should a suitable pool of candidates be identified. Fortescue will never contact you to ask for payment of any kind, whether directly or through a third party.

job_description.365: About Our Client  Our client is a data consulting firm with offices in Australia, London and the USA, who work with a range of clients across utilities, resources, government and finance-sector clients.  You will be embedded with one of their utilities clients, working in parallel to a couple of other consultants in there (but also quite independently), as a key contributor to their data and analytics function.  You'll be supported with on-the-job training and have access to salary increases against your performance, as well as opportunity to move through formal training and certifications, in support of your success.  Job Description  You will be responsible for: • Analysing business processes, collecting business requirements, assisting with specification of solutions. • Sourcing, restructuring, manipulating, and modelling data to support decisions around clients' commercial issues. • Supporting client understanding of analytical insight through creative presentation of data visualisations. • Documenting implemented solutions and processes, providing guides and trainings for users. • Ensuring all data management and processing is undertaken in adherence with internal policies. • Building relationships within the business, working towards common objectives.  The Successful Applicant  To be considered for and successful in this role you will: • Arrive with 2+ year's experience in a similar role, and be ready to expand your level of responsibility and autonomy • Be able to demonstrate your commercial acumen, in delivering insights (not just analysis), to drive decision making within an organisation • Ideally offer some programming experience in R or Python • Be competent to build meaningful dashboards and reports that meet business requirements • Offer good foundational skills in Excel, SQL, Power BI (including DAX)  What's on Offer  In return you will: • Align with a data specific consulting firm, who will support your success in this role, and your ongoing development within the organisation more broadly • Develop your skills in basic data engineering • Pick up some experience in cloud technologies including Snowflake • Get to access formal professional development opportunities • Work in an autonomous role with a reasonable degree of responsibility / the ability to make your own decisions
job_description.366: The Data Analyst is an integral role within the SPS Division specializing in the analysis of contractual obligations, KPIs and monthly reporting.  Our Company  Pacific Energy is one of Australia’s leading producers of sustainable distributed energy. We’ve been servicing remote townships, utilities and the mining industry for more than 40 years, delivering customised systems that integrate solar, wind, gas, diesel and battery storage systems.  Our dedicated team of experts and complete in-house capabilities mean we can deliver world-class projects from beginning to end, safely and on time.  We’re proud to be Australia’s largest remote power station builder and operator, with 48 sites nationally and more than 40% of our energy portfolio now powered by renewable and hybrid systems.  At Pacific Energy, we know the importance of a clean energy future. That’s why our organisation is driven by some of the industry’s finest engineers, electrical contractors, production specialists and project managers. Join us and help pave the way to a cleaner, brighter future.  Our Role  Our office in Perth is currently looking for a Data Analyst to work within the Service, Products and Stand-alone Power Systems Division, specializing in the analysis of contractual obligations, key performance indicators (KPIs), and monthly reporting on operational Renewable Energy assets and power stations.  This role will work closely with the Contract Manager and other internal stakeholders to provide actionable insights derived from financial, CRM, CMMS, and ERP systems data.  The Data Analyst will utilize tools such as Power BI, Power Query, and Excel to Export, Transform & Load (ETL) data into meaningful models and reports that drive business decisions for clients, managers, and teams.  Key Responsibilities  Position’s Duties Include But Are Not Limited To • Contractual Analysis: Review and analyse contractual obligations and KPIs defined by the Contract Manager related to operational Renewable Energy assets and power stations. • Monthly Reporting: Generate monthly reports focusing on the performance and status of energy systems designed, constructed, and/or owned by the Group. • Data Integration: Assist in the analysis, reporting, and forecasting of data from financial, CRM, CMMS, and ERP systems. • ETL Processes: Collaborate with internal subject matter experts to Export, Transform & Load data into useful data models and reports. • Data Visualization: Utilize Power BI and Power Query to create compelling visualizations that communicate complex data in a straightforward manner. • Stakeholder Communication: Present findings and insights to the Contract Manager, clients, and internal teams to inform and drive business decisions. • Quality Assurance: Ensure the accuracy and consistency of data by implementing and following best practices in data management. • Continuous Learning: Stay abreast of industry trends and advancements in data analytics tools and techniques. • Responsible for compliance with OHS policies, ensuring workplace compliance, and reporting hazards and near misses. • Foster a workforce culture of excellence, innovation, honesty and teamwork. Selection Criteria: • Bachelor’s degree in Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science, Business, or related field. • 1-2 years of experience in data analysis, preferably within the Renewable Energy sector. • Proficiency in Power BI, Power Query, and MS Excel. • Additional skills in Python, SQL, VBA, R, or similar languages would be advantageous. • Strong analytical skills with the ability to collect, organize, analyse, and disseminate significant amounts of information with attention to detail and accuracy. • Excellent interpersonal and communications skills • Excellent communication and time management skills, conflict resolution abilities and confidence dealing with a wide range of people, from tradespeople to customers/stakeholders and supervisors. • Understanding of OHSE requirements. Additional benefits include: • 9 Day fortnight (optional) • Salary continuance insurance • Employee Assistance Program (EAP), accessible to all employees and their families • Retention bonus scheme • Additional paid days off exceeding annual leave • Employee referral program We are an Equal Opportunity Employer  At Pacific Energy, we celebrate the richness and depth that diversity brings. We know that it’s good for our people, our customers and the solutions that we bring to the table. That’s why we strongly encourage people from all backgrounds, ages, cultures, abilities, sexual orientations and gender identities to apply. We’re always learning, so please let us know what adjustments we can make to our recruiting processes to better support you.  For more information visit www.pacificenergy.com.au/ or follow Pacific Energy on LinkedIn at www.linkedin.com/company/pacific-energy-pty-ltd

job_description.369: About Agoda  Agoda is an online travel booking platform for accommodations, flights, and more. We build and deploy cutting-edge technology that connects travelers with more than 3.6 million accommodations globally. Based in Asia and part of Booking Holdings, our 6,000+ employees representing 90+ nationalities foster a work environment rich in diversity, creativity, and collaboration. We innovate through a culture of experimentation and ownership, enhancing the ability for our customers to experience the world.  Get to Know our Team:  The Supply Equity Platform (SEP) team sits within the Product Supply team at Agoda Bangkok. We work closely with the sales department (Partner Services) to identify and optimize growth opportunities on accommodations supply for the company and to set up experiments to measure and implement changes. The projects SEP team works on directly impact Agoda’s bottom line and have long lasting structural impact to the business. We cover a range of topics including resource and product optimization. We collaborate with multiple departments and produce high quality results backed up by experimentation and data. Utilizing powerful tools and possessing an end-to-end view of how Agoda works, the SEP offers a team of learning and experience that will push you (and Agoda) into new territory.  In this Role, you’ll get to:  • Manage complex analytics processes and algorithms to ensure their continued smooth operation, identifying root causes and debugging them where needed. • Use and analyze data from multiple large-scale data warehouses and understand data flows across the entire organization. • Identify, support, and lead projects aimed at improving the operations of our automated systems (e.g. root cause detection, anomaly detection, performance analysis). • Develop automated infrastructure supporting business intelligence at a global level as well as the analytics processes supporting them. • Drive new analytical initiatives and projects aimed at improving resource and product optimization.  What you’ll Need to Succeed: • A hacker’s mindset – the ability to build simple but clever and elegant solutions to new problems within significant resource, operational and time constraints through deep understanding of the business, creative problem solving, and a wide range of expertise in data, analytics, automation, programming, and prototyping. • Either Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science or Bachelor’s degree in a quantitative discipline with extensive programming experience. • Experience in big data cleaning and wrangling as well as simple analytical processing (SQL is a must). • Have working experience in Python for data analysis. • A basic understanding of statistics and data, and the ability to implement this understanding in complex business situations. • The ability to visualize and understand complex data flows, pipelines, and processes.  It’s Great if you have: • Experience with complex analytics and statistical/machine learning techniques using R/Python/Spark. • Experience building automated analytical processes and functionality.  #sanfrancisco #newyork #seattle #boston #washdc #sydney #melbourne #perth #paris #london #tokyo #dhaka #vienna #edinburgh #manchester #amsterdam #munich #berlin #toronto #vancouver #moscow #dublin #seoul #hcmc #singapore #ENG #IT  Equal Opportunity Employer  At Agoda, we pride ourselves on being a company represented by people of all different backgrounds and orientations. job_description.372: If we inspire you to do the work you love, will you still call it work?  What's in it for you? job_description.379: Western Australia Police Force  Data Analytics and Reporting Manager  Position Number: 223655  Level/Salary: Level 7, $128,077 - $136,891 p.a. (PSCSAA 2022)  Work Type: Permanent - Full Time  Branch: Data Science and Analytics  Location: Perth  Closing Date: 2023-10-17 4:00 PM  You don't have to wear a uniform to make a difference in the Western Australia Police Force!  The WA Police Force Data Science and Analytics Division supports operational and tactical policing and assists investigators with solving crime faster and keeping the WA community safe.  We are looking for an enthusiastic and talented Manager to join the WA Police Force in their data journey by leading the Data Analytics and Reporting unit within the Data Science and Analytics Division. If you have a passion for solving problems and want to lead a team that is working with exciting and diverse data sources in the latest cloud and cutting-edge technologies then apply now!  About the role  The Data Analytics and Reporting Manager is an outcomes focused leader who will grow and develop the team and drive innovation that will provide exceptional data analytics and services for the WA Police Force and the WA community. You will join a dynamic group of individuals who are leading the way in enabling WA Police Force to not only use data to facilitate informed decision making in all aspects of the business but also to solve crime faster and keep the community safe.  In this role you will lead the Data Analytics and Reporting unit to deliver data centric products and tools that positively contribute to delivering data driven insights in a policing environment.  Key Responsibilities will include, but are not limited to: • Leads and provides subject matter expertise in relation to the development, review and implementation of new data-centric products to meet corporate reporting, statistical and analytical needs • Drive change and set strategic priorities for the Data Analytics and Reporting unit • Ensures thorough governance processes, that the design, analysis, and implementation of data analysis practices are fit for purpose to enable the efficient and effective use of data resources to meet the Agency's need for information products for corporate business intelligence, statistics, performance management and operational needs • Establish and maintain strong relationships with internal and external stakeholders • Work collaboratively with data engineers and data scientists, project managers to deliver high quality solutions • Ensures there is a collegiate culture focused on delivery, excellence and mutual support • Lead the exploration of new approaches for data analytics and reporting  The successful applicant will be required to work 75 hours per fortnight.  SPECIALIST PRE-REQUISITE  It is a requirement that the position holder is successful in obtaining and maintaining a NEGATIVE VETTING LEVEL 2 security clearance for the duration of their appointment in the position. Only Australian Citizens are eligible to hold and maintain the NEGATIVE VETTING LEVEL 2 security clearance. Any applicants who are currently not an Australian Citizen must be aware that this is an essential requirement to fulfil this position (please refer to the attached position description). Whilst there is nothing to preclude applicants from applying for the position if they have not yet been granted Australian Citizenship, applicants who are successful should be aware that they cannot be appointed unless they are in the process of applying for Australian Citizenship and are eligible to receive a waiver.  APPLICATION PROCESS  Please ensure you complete, sign and scan the Integrity Check Consent Form (refer attached) and submit it along with your application (the Integrity Check Consent Form is not required for current WA Police Force employees).  Applicants are asked to provide a cover letter outlining why you are suited to the role in no more than three (3) pages.  Applicants are also required to submit a comprehensive Curriculum Vitae (CV). Your CV should provide enough detail (dot points are sufficient) to allow the selection panel to assess your skills, experience and qualifications relevant to the Key Accountabilities of attached Position Description Form.  Whilst applicants are not required to address the Essential Work Related Requirements of this position as a separate document, it is important that applicants are able to satisfy the 'context' requirement in relation to Technical Leadership and Capability and Leadership and Management within the CV and cover letter. These are integral requirements to the role(s) and will hold considerable weighting when determining whether an applicant is competitive.  The CV must also include the names and contact details of two (2) referees who can comment on the applicant's ability to satisfy all of the Essential Work Related Requirements. Applicants should nominate at least one immediate (most contemporary) supervisor/manager unless exceptional circumstances exist.  Please note: For applicants deemed suitable, all Essential Work Related Requirements listed in the Position Description Form will be assessed at some stage during the selection process.  OTHER CONDITIONS  Whilst this selection process will initially be used to fill the above vacancy, it may also be used to fill other similar vacancies throughout the metropolitan area. In addition to this, should the successful applicant decline or vacate the advertised position, then the panel may select another suitable applicant from this selection process. Both of these options remain valid for a period of twelve (12) months from the initial date of the appointment.  Integrity and criminal checks will be conducted if the recommended applicant for a position is not a current WA Police Force employee. Any relocation costs associated with appointment to these positions may be the responsibility of the successful applicants.  SUBSTANTIVE EQUALITY & WORK HEALTH & SAFETY (WHS) STATEMENT  The WA Police Force is an Equal Opportunity Employer and encourages Aboriginal Australians, young people, people of diverse sexualities and genders, people with disability, people from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds and women to apply for positions within our agency. The Department also promotes flexible family friendly work practices.  Throughout the recruitment process we provide reasonable adjustments to allow people with a disability to participate effectively. Reasonable adjustments can also be made available to assist you in the job, if you are successful in gaining employment.  WHS is a vital component within the WA Police Force. Safety is a partnership between the employer and their employees and it relies on all of us working together to ensure that everyone is safe in their working environment, which enables them to go home safely. We incorporate safety in every part of our business and it is an integral part of the decision-making process.  The WA Police Force has a duty of care to ensure employees are not adversely affected by alcohol or drugs in the workplace. The effect of alcohol or drugs can impact on the health and/or safety of the individual or others, and this behaviour is not aligned with the WA Police Force Code of Conduct. As a result, a testing regime has been established as an important way of providing assurance to the community that the expectations they hold for all members of the WA Police Force are being met. Regular testing of all employees for alcohol and drugs aims to ensure the health, welfare and safety of all personnel and promote community confidence in the WA Police Force.  FOR FURTHER JOB RELATED INFORMATION  Please contact Janelle Baily on telephone number (08) 9223 3231.  SUBMITTING YOUR APPLICATION  Applicants are requested to apply online. Desirable • Experience in participating in managing change activities. • Ability to translate concepts into outputs and prototypes and captures user feedback to improve designs. • Capability in dealing with problems and issues, managing resolutions, corrective actions, lessons learned and the collection and dissemination of relevant information. • Participation in study groups and/or courses to gain understanding of BABOK®, Agile, Design Thinking, Business Data Analytics and Product Ownership Analysis  Certifications • Professional recognition of your Business Analysis competency via certification (not training course), e.g. IIBA Certification of Capability in Business Analysis™ (CCBA®), ACS Certified Technologist, BCS International Diploma in Business Analysis, or equivalent. job_description.388: • Closing Date: 13 October 2023, 9:00 AM  face2face reference: 591408  Location: Nationwide - Remote  Hours: Full-time  Contract length: 12 Months Contract + 3 x 1 Month (Pending approval)  Entry requirements: Australian Citizen + Ability to obtain Baseline  Pay range: $95.00 – 115.00 p/h inc super  About the role:  The Tertiary Skills and Pathways team is responsible for the unit mapping project, as part of its program of work. Unit mapping uses natural language processing techniques to create a connection between tertiary education learning materials (VET and HE units), and skills taxonomies. Unit mapping helps to identify skills taught in tertiary education, and their potential relationship to occupations and the labour market, to assist in analysis and advice on tertiary education delivery.  The team is working on a demonstration project basis with five key projects to design the end to end process of unit mapping, to continually refine the data science model, and to generate insights on the potential use of mapping outputs. The outputs of models are large, for example one university with approximately 3,000 units can have an output of approximately 30,000 skills mapped. Validation of outputs is a critical part of the mapping process to produce a model and results that are highly accurate.  Duties: • Developing of a comprehensive internal and external validation process for very large data sets, to support improvement of data science models, and the quality of output data sent to partners. This may require an ensemble of approaches, for example statistical sampling, manual and automated approaches to validation. • Managing internal validation processes before outputs are sent to project partners. • Working closely with the data science team to provide feedback for the mapping model development. • Analysing complex model outputs, to derive valuable insights for reporting to project partners, including visualisation techniques. • Providing advice to technical services on interface design for a validation application for project partners.  Required experience/skills: • Demonstrated experience in data analysis and process design, to create replicable data validation processes to improve data output quality. • Excellent analytical skills, with strong attention to detail, and the ability to synthesise and critically analyse large volumes of structured and unstructured data. • Strong skills and experience in data management, in particular how data can be effectively structured, analysed, presented and communicated, to achieve high-quality outcomes. • Excellent communication skills, including the ability to effectively communicate key data insights visually and in written form to a range of diverse stakeholders • Well-developed interpersonal skills, including the ability to work effectively in a multidisciplinary setting.  Desirable experience skills: • Experience in R Shiny, Python, SQL, anduser experience design. • Understanding of, and experience working with tertiary education (HE and/or VET) and/or occupation and labour market data. • Understanding and experience in data science, or related fields. • Experience operating in a policy environment. job_description.392: At EY, you’ll have the chance to build a career as unique as you are, with the global scale, support, inclusive culture and technology to become the best version of you. What if your most rewarding experiences couldn’t be captured by a resume?  At EY we believe that whoever you are, your uniqueness helps us stand apart. When you join us, we will invest in your career and your development, to ensure you achieve your goals, now and into the future. That is the IGO difference. We currently have three underground nickel mining operations, a 170-person corporate office and a large exploration team working across Australia. We also have a significant indirect interest in the Greenbushes lithium mine through a joint venture.  We are in an exciting period of growth and are building capability within our teams and are currently seeking a Data Analyst to be an integral part of our future success by making meaningful use of the information and data we capture with a specific focus on our people and their safety.  The purpose of this role will be to gather and analyse quality data driven HR analytics and HR metrics to support leadership decision making in people and safety strategies.  Reporting to the Chief People Officer some of your key accountabilities will include:  Collect and analyse HR and safety related data from various sources such as Success Factors, Page Up, Qlik Sense, INX etc.; Perform data analysis using statistical methods and visualisation tools to identify trends in workplace safety and people processes; Generate meaningful insights from HR and safety data such as employee turnover, accident reports and workforce planning; Provide data driven recommendations to streamline recruitment, onboarding, performance management and employee development processes; Create interactive dashboards to communicate key HR and safety metrics to stakeholders in a clear and understandable manner; Assist in audits and compliance reporting; Collaborate with HR and safety teams to identify areas of improvement based on data analysis and develop and implement data driven strategies to meet these improvements; Act as a subject matter expert in data science and provide guidance to non-technical stakeholders.  YOUR EXPERIENCE  We are proud to offer a unique workplace culture, a welcoming and friendly team coupled with diverse and challenging work. The ideal candidate will have a strong commitment to workplace safety and bring strong data analysis and problem-solving skills. To be considered for this role you must possess:  Bachelor’s degree in Data Science, Statistics, or related field; Proven experience as a Data Analyst in a similar role with exposure to people and safety data; Proficient in data analysis tools and software; Knowledge of HR and safety software systems; Excellent communication skills to convey complex data to non-technical stakeholders; Strong problem solving and critical thinking abilities; The ability to work independently and collaboratively with cross functional teams; and National Police Clearance obtained within the last two months.  To be considered for this opportunity, please click “Apply Now” and submit an up-to-date resume along with a cover letter.  ‘We are a Circle Back Initiative Employer - we commit to respond to every applicant’  We believe in a world where people power makes amazing things happen. Where technology opens up new horizons and clean energy makes the planet a better place for every generation to come. We have big aspirations to explore, develop, produce and partner to achieve our strategy to become a globally relevant, premium producer of energy storage and distribution minerals.
job_description.395: VCID 852826  Hello! Are you… A data specialist? A team player? A programming guru? Interested in transforming data to make informed decisions? Interested in contributing to the health of Western Australia?  This is an exciting time for the Healthcare Quality Intelligence Unit as we are looking for adaptable, resilient and enthusiastic people to join our growing team.  About The Healthcare Quality Intelligence Unit  The Clinical Excellence Division is the focal point for clinical policy development, engagement with the clinical workforce and health research.  As a unit in the Clinical Excellence Division, the Healthcare Quality Intelligence Unit (HQIU) provides analysis to support front line clinical staff to improve the quality of patient care. Our team delivers value to patients and clinicians by using data to provide information about quality of patient care. It is critical that this information is built from a solid data platform.  Your new role  We are seeking enthusiastic and suitably experienced individuals for the roles of Principal Data Scientist and Senior Data Scientist.  As a Principal/Senior Data Scientist, you will be responsible for developing data engineering pipelines, applying machine learning, implementing data science models and constructing data visualization products to support Healthcare Quality Intelligence Unit projects. As part of a technical team, you will utilize services and tools such as Snowflake, SQL, Databricks, Python, R and Power BI.  Our team is involved in the full data lifecycle to extract, transform, organize, analyse and visualise data to deliver solutions to our stakeholders. This involves a passion for learning new technologies, and our team has flexibility in the technological stack and languages used. We are looking for someone with experience working on large linked datasets, cloud services, has a passion for data and can apply their technical skills to the role.  For further details, please view the Job Description Form (JDF) found above which provides a full statement of duties for this role.  If you would like further information about this role and the amazing team you are working with, we encourage you to please contact Peter Li, Lead Quality Analyst on 08 6373 2282.  Job Category  These are Fixed-Term Full-Time appointments with the possibility of extension(s).  If you are successful in a place in the pool, you will be eligible for direct appointment for opportunities equivalent to the skillset and specified level until 31/12/2024.  Why should you join our team? • Being part of a team that is working with data to improve patient care • Being part of a team that delivers on innovative solutions • We encourage continuous professional development and upskilling • Being part of a team culture that thrives in collaborating with other teams to achieve shared goals • Working within a multifaceted team to learn of different approaches to the same problem  In the Healthcare Quality Intelligence Unit, we believe the best services come from a workplace where varied perspectives and experiences are welcomed and encouraged. We are committed to eliminating all forms of discrimination in the provision of our service and embrace diversity, encouraging applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, people from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds, people with disabilities and members of our LGBTQIA+ community.  Benefits Of Working With Us  In addition to a competitive salary, we offer you a range of benefits, which may include (in line with operational requirements): • 11% employer contributed superannuation into a fund of your choice. For further information click here. • Professional development opportunities and Study/Leave assistance • Flexible working (including working from home) and leave arrangements • Discounts with corporate partners • Salary Packaging Benefits  Are you ready to join our team?  To be eligible to apply for this role, you are required to: • Undertake a criminal record screening, a pre-employment health assessment and integrity check, as part of the appointment process. We may ask referees to comment on your integrity and past demonstration of ethical behaviour.  How To Apply  To apply for this position, please apply online at www.jobs.health.wa.gov.au  In Your Application You Should Provide The Following • A Curriculum Vitae (CV) that clearly shows your experience relevant to the role • Statement demonstrating your knowledge, skills and experience relevant to the responsibilities of the role, addressing all selection criteria as outlined in the JDF (no more than three [3] pages) – please note there are templates attached to this advert we encourage you to use • The name and contact details of two professional referees with one referee preferably being your current line manager  Please indicate in your application the classification level or levels that you would like to be considered for. If you are applying for both levels, please direct your response to the higher level. You are not required to submit two applications.  Please ensure you have saved your documents in one of the following formats .doc, .xls, .pdf, .rtf or .ppt. Please be aware that .docx or .xlsx files are not accepted formats.  Please ensure you give yourself adequate time to submit your application and upload your attachments.  If you experience difficulties while applying online, please contact Employee Services on 13 44 77 for immediate assistance during business hours.  You must have a current, valid email address to apply and will be used to communicate with you.  WA Health is committed to growing the Aboriginal workforce as a part of WA Health’s Aboriginal Workforce Policy. As a measure to achieve equality, Section 51 of the Equal Opportunity Act 1984 applies to this position. Aboriginal people are encouraged to apply.  Thank you for taking the time to apply for the role in our team and we hope to see you at the next stage.

The successful candidate will be responsible for developing and managing the data warehouse, creating data visualizations, and engaging with stakeholders to ensure that our data-driven insights are accurate and actionable. They will also create Power BI dashboards and reports to provide insights into our business operations. Additionally, they will work closely with stakeholders to ensure that the data visualizations accurately reflect their needs.  Requirements • Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science or a related field • At least 3 years of experience in Business Intelligence/Data Analytics • Expertise in Power BI, SQL, DAX, and other analytics tools • Excellent communication skills with the ability to engage stakeholders effectively • Strong problem-solving skills with an analytical mindset • Ability to work independently as well as part of a team  Offer  Our client has ensured market rate for this opportunity. job_description.404: Could the skills you build here unlock doors anywhere?  At EY we believe that whoever you are, your uniqueness helps us stand apart.  We bring together extraordinary people, like you, to build a better working world.  The opportunity  Due to continued success and growth, an exciting opportunity exists for a Data Analytics Senior Consultant or Manager to join our highly regarded People Advisory Services team.  Our team works as a well-integrated national team, where you’ll have the opportunity to work with Australian-based and multinational clients across the country, therefore offering you the ability to work with large corporates, and a diverse range of industries. In this role, you will have access to training, coaching and support that’s available to help grow your career even further!  This role is open to various locations - Melbourne, Sydney, Brisbane, Adelaide, and Perth.  What’s in it for you?  As our Data Analytics Senior Consultant or Manager - your responsibilities will include: • Modelling of various Industrial Instrument (including Enterprise Bargaining Agreements, Industry Awards etc.) for wage compliance projects; • Modelling of superannuation and Pay-As-You-Go Withholding data modelling projects (including the preparation of superannuation guarantee charge statements and voluntary disclosure letters); • Liaise directly with clients and other regulatory authorities (e.g. Australian Taxation Office, Fair Work Australia etc.) in the delivery of data projects; • Work with different parts of the business in driving growth in the global mobility data analytics practice; • Preparing & presenting training seminars to both clients and team members.  What We’re Looking For  Here’s our ‘wish list’ but don’t worry if you don’t tick all the boxes. We’re interested in your strengths, what you want to learn, and how far you want to go. • Degree in Data Analytics/Commerce, or similar; • Between 1-5 years’ experience in a data analytics discipline (focused towards wage compliance and employment taxes remediation); • Experience with Alteryx at the intermediate or advanced level; • Experience with data visualisation software such as Power BI and Tableau; • Experience with SQL, Python, and other database/coding languages [preferred]; • Ability to lead and mentor junior members of our team; • Commitment to excellence in client service, with the ability to work both autonomously and as part of a team.  What We Can Offer You • Explore how a career at EY is yours to build at www.ey.com/au/careerdevelopment • Discover how, when and where you can work at www.ey.com/au/flexibility • Learn about our commitment to DE&I at www.ey.com/au/diversity-inclusiveness • Understand how our benefits can support you at www.ey.com/au/benefits  Acknowledgement of Country  EY acknowledges the Traditional Owners and Custodians of the lands on which EY offices are located around Australia. We pay our respects to their cultures, and to their Elders — past, present, and emerging. Find out more about our vision for reconciliation at www.ey.com/au/reconciliation  Apply now… we’re over 9,000 perspectives in Australia and we’re ready to welcome yours. job_description.405: Working at Access Analytic  Access Analytic is a world-famous consulting and training company that specialises in providing amazing Power BI, Excel and complimentary solutions in areas such as financial modelling, reporting, dashboards, data analytics and training for medium and large companies.  We have a client base that is the envy of our competitors covering most of Perth’s top companies.  Come and do something you love where you will be treated like part of the family!  What we offer  We are a nimble, low “red-tape”, highly professional but fun organisation. We pride ourselves on our expertise and being the type of people that want to help clients solve their problems.  Our Senior Business Analyst remuneration packages includes a great bonus scheme, additional holidays based on length of service, high spec laptop, phone allowances, plus free access to an on-site pool & gym.  Our bonus scheme means that the best analysts and consultants could earn significant amounts in addition to their base salary, which makes for an incredibly competitive package.  For the right candidate this could be a path to becoming your own boss with an ownership stake in the business.  Applications  To apply, please send your CV, covering letter (and samples of your work) to info@accessanalytic.com.au  For further enquiries, call Jeff Robson on +61 8 6210 8500.  Only those who are eligible to work in Australia already should apply (we cannot sponsor you, unfortunately). Applications from recruitment agents are not generally considered – your fees are too high!  Senior Business Analyst – Power BI  The Role  Are you passionate about Power BI, Excel, and the Power Platform? Come and make the most of your skills with a wide variety of projects using the technology you love all day, every day!  We are looking for highly professional, highly skilled and motivated individuals who would relish the challenge of providing reporting, data analytics, & reporting to a variety of world-class companies.  Reporting to the Directors, you will be involved directly in working on client consulting assignments, with responsibility for ensuring these are delivered on time, on budget, and in accordance with best practices.  You will have a lot of independence, flexibility, and autonomy. We do not micro-manage at Access Analytic.  Mandatory  A Power BI enthusiast.  Excellent understanding of Power Query (writing M), DAX, Power BI, data modelling, analytics, dashboard presentation.  Solid understanding of the Power BI service architecture – Workspaces, Apps, security.  5+ years’ practical experience (at least 2 years using Power BI) in reporting to internal stakeholders at all levels in the organisation, or experience in another related consultancy.  Bear in mind that this is a client-facing consulting role so we’re looking for more than just technical skills – you need to be comfortable talking to clients, calling them, attending client functions, and always dealing professionally with clients of all levels.  Confidence in providing the highest quality professional service to a wide client base. This role involves extensive client contact so highly-developed written and verbal English communication skills are essential. You also need to be comfortable with the idea of contacting clients, visiting them on your own, and managing your own time.  A friendly personality with the natural ability to form strong relationships with clients. We’re looking for people our clients will naturally love to work with time and time again!  A desire to develop yourself, learn and grow, plus the ability to handle multiple projects with conflicting demands at once.  Highly Desirable  Professional Accounting / Management Reporting background  Microsoft Power BI Data Analyst Exam PL-300  An extensive network of Perth business contacts  Advanced Excel skills  Power Apps and Power Automate experience  A working knowledge of Azure SQL Databases
job_description.406: DHL Global Forwarding (Australia) Pty Ltd is a global leader in the Freight Forwarding industry. We currently have a vacancy for a Senior Project Operations Specialist in our Industrial Projects Team based in our Perth office, WA.  About Us  Connecting People. Improving Lives.  DHL is the leading global brand in the logistics industry. Our DHL divisions offer an unrivalled portfolio of logistics services ranging from national and international parcel delivery, e-commerce shipping and fulfillment solutions, international express, road, air, and ocean transport to industrial supply chain management. With about 380,000 employees in more than 220 countries and territories worldwide, DHL connects people and businesses securely and reliably, enabling global sustainable trade flows. With specialized solutions for growth markets and industries including technology, life sciences and healthcare, engineering, manufacturing & energy, auto-mobility, and retail, DHL is decisively positioned as “The logistics company for the world”.  DHL is part of Deutsche Post DHL Group. The Group generated revenues of more than 81 billion euros in 2021. With sustainable business practices and a commitment to society and the environment, the Group makes a positive contribution to the world. Deutsche Post DHL Group aims to achieve net-zero emissions logistics by 2050.  Overall Role Purpose • Provide customised freight forwarding solutions to meet or exceed customer requirements. • Manage and support the execution of complex project shipments maintaining safety throughout. • Maintenance and update of freight movement records on the Tracking System and with shipment record files. • Liaise with carriers, sub-contractors and project clients in the coordination of freight movements. • Strictly control the record keeping of cargo deliveries to the client at relevant handover points. • Positively contribute in promoting safe and best practices with regards to HSE compliance within DGF Group, its Clients, Subcontractors and affiliates. • Minimise risk exposure through careful planning of work activities, adherence to all internal and external procedures, and identification and reporting of hazards. • Help the Project meet strict KPI deadlines without compromising safety standards. • Work very closely with Project Manager and other key project team members to ensure project priorities are completed in a timely manner. • Supervise all cargo handling requirements for the project. May be implanted in client’s depots and/or project site pending project requirement. • Ensure cargo handling procedures are compliant with internal HSE processes, Operational procedures and industry best practice. • Preparation of quotations for freight movements. • Support and participate in Project Implementations in line company and client requirements. • Support and participate in Project Tenders and RFQ’s • Project invoicing and File Profitability Management – including financial reporting and invoice preparation and submission in line with company and client requirements.  Skills / Qualifications • Tertiary qualified or an equivalent qualification • At least (5) five years working experience in Project Operations, Logistics, Logistics Systems, or industry-related fields. • Minimum three (3) to five (5) years of previous experience/knowledge of International Project Operations / Freight Forwarding / Account Management • COR Certifications • Wide ranging knowledge of Industrial Projects and/or the freight forwarding business, its  characteristics, competitors and likely future evolution. • Experience handling Heavy Lift and Over Dimensional cargoes. • Experience supervising sub-contractors. • Strong Knowledge of Road Transport and Freight Forwarding procedures and regulations. • Strong knowledge of cargo handling procedures and requirements. • Strong knowledge of project over-dimensional and heavy lift cargo handling procedures. • Strong operational management, risk management and business process skills. • Strong HSE disciplines and adherence to DHL and Client compliance requirements. • Strong problem-solving abilities. • Strong consulting, persuasion, influencing and negotiation skills. • The ability to make safe and responsible decisions yet meet project KPI’s and project deadlines. • Organizational skills with the ability to prioritize and deliver time pressure and limited information/resources • Sound administrative skills • Results-driven and attention to details • Able to work independently and coordinate account management requirements i.e. client visits • A high degree of reliability and attention to detail • Be a team player with a positive can-do attitude • Be results driven and be able to demonstrate strong communication and administration skills • Possess a high degree of attention to detail and a professional work ethic.  Why DHL Global Forwarding?  In a global business like ours, the opportunities are endless. So join us. Work with us. Grow with us. Stay with us. Discover the positive impact you can make and build an amazing DHL career.  We're one big team: Our culture, our values, and the way we work together as a team, ensure that everyone feels valued and rewarded for the contribution they bring.  We grow together: We've worked hard to create an environment where every individual can keep learning, keep growing, and enjoy a rewarding long-term career.  We do the right thing: We understand the importance of contributing to society, reducing our environmental impact, and making a positive difference in the world.  Excellence. Simply Delivered. job_description.407: • Do you like building visual representations of data? • Do you enjoy exploring what value can be extracted from data? • Do you like to innovate and problem solve? • Do you have a curious analytical mind?  If your answer is “YES” to these questions, we are interested to talk to you!  What We Are Looking For  We are seeking a person who has a passion for all things data to join our team as a Data Analyst. In this position you will be responsible for assisting with the analysis, development and timely provision of Workforce related reports, data extracts and performance information for the North Metropolitan Health Service (NMHS).  Our team wants to transform data into insights that enable people to make decisions that have positive impacts on our people and patients. This role reports to the Principal Workforce Information Analyst.  This vacancy is for Permanent Full-Time and Permanent Part-Time appointment at various hours.  About Us  North Metropolitan Health Service covers almost 1000 square kilometres, with a population of almost 740,000, representing about 28 per cent of Western Australia’s total, and is projected to grow to more than 0.9 million by 2031. NMHS healthcare providers are fully accredited and offer a range of highly specialised, multidisciplinary, state-wide services from several hospital and outpatient/ambulatory care settings, as well as services specifically aimed at the north metropolitan catchment.  North Metropolitan Health Service (NMHS) fosters an environment of equity and inclusion and strives to ensure everyone experiences a sense of belonging. We celebrate the rich diversity of our community and are committed to recruiting a team that is reflective of those we care for. We encourage anyone who aligns with our values of respect, integrity, teamwork, innovation and care to apply for this role.  NMHS is committed to growing the Aboriginal workforce as a part of our Aboriginal Health and Wellbeing Strategy. As a measure to achieve equality, Section 51 of the Equal Opportunity Act 1984 applies to this position.  NMHS upholds the social model of disability. If you have any access needs or require adjustments to participate in the recruitment process, please contact Justin Lenhoff on 0402 670 645 or email justin.lenhoff@health.wa.gov.au .  While your qualifications and experience tell us part of your story, your values and attitude speak louder still. At NMHS, we aim to ensure our behaviours reflect our core values: Care, Respect, Innovation, Teamwork & Integrity. During the selection process you will be assessed on your ability to fulfil the responsibilities of this position while upholding our values.  What We Offer  In addition to the great salary our employees enjoy an amazing range of benefits • Generous salary packaging • Diverse and inclusive culture • A smoke free environment • Flexible leave arrangements • Professional development opportunities • Paid study leave • Flexible working arrangements • Continuous learning • Professional and location-based allowances  NMHS supports flexible working practices and consideration will be given to flexible work options, where operationally appropriate.  Want to know more about this role?  We encourage you to contact Justin Lenhoff on 0402 670 645.  We think you’ll like it here  Our employees like working here, and we think you will too. Watch this video to find out what they have to say.  Ready to join our team?  Applicants are required to apply online so allow enough time to complete the online application process and attach your documentation. If you experience difficulties, please contact Employee Services on 13 44 77 for immediate assistance during business hours.  Your Application Should Include • A statement in no more than 3 pages addressing the selection criteria as outlined in the attached JDF. • A comprehensive CV that clearly shows your experience relevant to this role; and • The names and contact details of two (2) professional referees. It is preferable for one of your referees to be your current supervisor or manager.  Eligibility to Apply: Australian citizenship or permanent residency is an essential requirement for applicants to be considered for permanent positions in the public sector. To be eligible for a fixed term appointment you must have documentary evidence of your entitlement to live and work in Australia for the period of the contract.  Whilst this selection process will initially be used to fill the above vacancy, it may also be used to fill other "similar" vacancies throughout the health service. In addition to this, should the successful applicant decline or vacate the advertised vacancy, then the next most suitable applicant may also be selected from this process. Both of these options remain valid for a period of twelve (12) months from when the authorised delegate endorses the recruitment decision.  Lodgement is system generated. Any submissions after or on, 4:00pm on the closing date will not be accepted.  We look forward to receiving your application.
job_description.408: Full Job Description 3 months contract working on Spatial Analytics for a well-known Utilities entity in WA  Your new company  You will be working for a well-known utilities entity in WA within their Data & Analytics team which provides geospatial information and solutions to various business needs.  Your new role  Responsible for developing and delivering geographical information systems (GIS) mapping and visualisation data products and solutions at all levels of the business. Provide technical support and services in mapping and visualisation in a spatial environment to achieve required business outcomes. Collaborate with the business to understand customer requirements and apply GIS best practice standards and tools.  What you’ll need to succeed  A degree level qualification in Geographical Information Science, Geography, Environmental Science or related discipline, and considerable experience in and knowledge of geospatial information analysis techniques and applications (e.g., ESRI ArcGIS, GE Smallworld, FME, CAD, ERDAS Imagine, FME, python). Knowledge of geographic information systems and geospatial data management, as well as relevant knowledge of static and web mapping, cartography and 3D visualisation within a GIS platform. Have well-developed interpersonal, verbal, and written communication skills, good analytical and problem-solving skills, and the ability to work in a team environment.  What you’ll get in return  Opportunity to work on exciting and challenging projects that involve geospatial data analysis and visualisation. Work with a supportive and collaborative team that values your contribution and expertise. Enjoy competitive rates, as well as opportunities for professional development and career growth.  What you need to do now  If you're interested in this role, click 'apply now' to forward an up-to-date copy of your CV to Lakita.Tarachandani@hays.com.au, or for more information and a confidential discussion, please call us on 08 9254 4551.  #2817519
job_description.409: VGW is a fast-growing technology company and creator of market-leading online social games. With offices across Australia, USA, Canada, Malta and the Philippines we are on a mission to be the biggest gaming company in the world!  We have a brand new role for a BI Analyst to join our Business Intelligence team.  As the BI Analyst you will support the BI team's ability to be proactive by leading the creation of data assets to be used as building blocks for our newly developed framework and promoting the BI team's policies and procedures across the organisation.  Note: This is a hybrid role to based in either our Sydney or Perth office location.  Key responsibilities will include: • Support the creation of the new target state framework and governance for end-to-end reporting, tooling integration and self-service BI products • Maintain VGW reporting taxonomy by updating and classifying terms and metrics • Create new reports and retrofit existing reports as part of the rollout strategy of BI-related products to the new state • Follow and promote the adoption of the governance framework for VGW’s Data Catalog to ensure policies, standards and definitions are followed with peer Analysts across the organisation • Create supporting documentation that support the rollout and adoption of the new BI framework across VGW • Deliver dashboard/ reporting solutions that meet user expectations and follow the new state framework and governance • Work closely with business users to understand their data and reporting needs • Work under the direction of senior team members and escalates issues encountered after attempting to solve • Collaborate with other data team members to resolve any questions that arise in relation to VGW’s Data Catalog and BI’s new processes and procedures  What you will bring to the role: • A Degree in Computer Science, Mathematics, Statistics, Data Engineering, Data Science or Artificial Intelligence. • 2+ years of experience in data analysis, business intelligence or data insights • Experience using statistical computer languages (R, Python, SLQ, etc.) to create and review queries. • Business acumen • Experience working with BI analysts, data analysts, and/or cross-functional teams. • Problem-solving skills to identify pain points and recurring concerns. • Excellent written and verbal communication skills. • A drive to learn and master new technologies and techniques  About VGW  VGW has been disrupting the online gaming world since 2010 and we're only getting started. We've assembled an incredibly talented global team who bring their passion, energy and expertise to build games that people love.  At VGW, we have a modern approach to getting work done and a focus on creating an environment where amazing people can do amazing work. That means giving you the flexibility you need, providing spaces that will keep you comfortable and finding opportunities for you to keep learning and growing.  Find out more at www.vgw.co  If you want to join a team that does things differently apply today and we look forward to seeing what you can bring to our team.  Why VGW?  We are on a huge mission to become the biggest gaming company in the world. As we grow to meet this goal, we need talented people rich in diversity to propel us forward. We truly believe the right mix of diversity and authenticity will be our winning hand.  We are committed to creating a diverse, engaging and inclusive culture for our people to shine, with a workplace that honours your experiences, perspectives, unique identity and passions. For those reasons, we encourage you to browse our employment opportunities and apply today. Please let us know of any accommodations you may need during the application process.  Privacy Policy

Our program is designed to equip you with the skills and knowledge you need to start and grow a successful career.  As a Technical Analyst, you will have the opportunity to apply your skills to innovative projects and make a real impact in a variety of sectors. You will be responsible for investigating and developing solutions for applications. It could be robotic process automation, quality assurance and IT infrastructure delivery for global businesses.  What will my time at FDM be like  Your journey will begin with training out of FDM’s award-winning academy. While interviews and assessments are done remotely, you now have the option to undertake training online or at our centrally located, 21st floor Sydney office in Barangaroo.  The 10-week industry specific training covers high-demand skills such as SQL, Unix; Excel/VBA, BA, Python, ITIL, Cloud and OS-Admin with the chance to gain industry recognised qualifications, as well as mentoring and support throughout.  After successfully completing your training, you’ll step into an integral position with one or more of our industry-leading, multinational clients in Australia. (Relocation package will be provided) • Eligible to work in Australia (Australian citizen or permanent resident)  There has never been a better time to start a career in tech – Apply Now! And we’re counting on your unique voice and perspective to help EY become even better, too. Join us and build an exceptional experience for yourself, and a better working world for all.  What if we didn’t focus on who you are now, but who you could become?  At EY we believe that whoever you are, your uniqueness helps us stand apart. EY DnA is the data and advanced analytics capability within EY Asia-Pacific, with over 500 specialist employees working across multiple industry sectors. From building management capability and the next generation of leaders, to creating a diversity and inclusion strategy which is mainstreamed and embedded into everything we do – the People & Culture team is all about making REA Group a great place to work. Supporting our multi-national business with HR processes, policies and systems to meet the needs of our people around the world, the team works to build high engagement with our impressive offering of programs and benefits. Cookies settings  Award Obtained BNPP has won Top employer Europe award in a 10th consecutive year Position Purpose • The role of the Data Analyst sits within the Data Governance team whom are part of the Business Change Management (BCM) division of BNP Paribas. The Data Analyst’s primary objective is providing the business with data analytics and solutions in a cost-effective way by determining the requirements of a project or program and communicating them clearly to stakeholders, facilitators and partners. • The Data Analyst will report directly to the Head of Data Governance and work within a matrix structure, delivering into projects that are managed across all platforms. They communicate with internal and external stakeholders including business stakeholders in operations, product and coverage, Paris and London branches for global projects, standards, vendors and consultants.  Key Responsibilities  Business & Data Requirements • Engage stakeholders to establish a common understanding of the business and data needs • Identify and correctly translate business needs into business requirements and data solution requirements • Clarify and elicit business requirements, proactively identifying additional requirements not explicitly provided, obtaining missing information and resolving conflicting information among the needs and requirements • Ensure data requirements are consistent with the business requirements. Where possible relate deliverables and their acceptance criteria to the requirements • Validate data requirements with stakeholders to ensure they are based on an understanding of the stakeholder needs, expectations, constraints, and interfaces  Data Solution Design • Gain a firm understanding of the impacts of the solution on People, Process and Technology. • Engage stakeholders to ensure a common understanding of (and commitment to) all aspects of the project including objectives, scope, risks, benefits and any element they may be providing Gather all the necessary inputs and review to fully understand the requirements, specifications, applicable standards etc. • Document the current (as-is) business process design if this does not already exist • Document the to-be business process design and identify how the implementation of the data solution will benefit the business  Data Quality and Integrity • Liaise with the business to identify data inconsistencies and provide the capability to identify these items in advance • Lead and/or undertake data quality activities and initiatives where required. Ensure appropriate tools and techniques are used for data analysis tasks and deliverables. • Encourage peer reviews and feedback sessions within the community. • Personally review a selection of the deliverables generated by the community.  Engage and contribute to a Data analysis community of practice, which includes: • Establishing regular community meetings with all data analysts to provide group mentoring, discuss concerns and issues, and implement actions for continuous improvement. • Perform reviews of deliverables produced by the community’s business analysts and provide feedback and constructive critiques. • Formalise standards and consistency around business analysis deliverables and encourage the community’s adherence to these standards.  Alteryx Designer/Gallery/Power BI Implementation: • Using the analysis, requirements gathering and stakeholder workshops mentioned above, create Alteryx workflows or Power BI Dashboards that align with the correct business outcomes and optimise business process and introduce operational efficiencies • Ensure that developed workflows meet the standards of Data Governance and Analytics teams and can be scaled to run on the Alteryx Gallery • Create consistency amongst existing workflows and ensure that the user experience is maintained across the data governance and analytics gallery and standards are set for future developments  Competencies (Technical / Behavioural)  Technical • 3+ years analysis experience • Experience in an Information Technology & Change capacity in the Financial Services Industry • 3+ years of Alteryx Designer/Gallery or Power BI experience is essential • Experience in custody or back-office administration for the funds management industry • Familiarity with analytical capabilities such as Power BI, Tableau, Alteryx • Thorough knowledge of Investment administration platforms such as HiPort • Excellent working knowledge of relational databases, be able to confidently write SQL • Experience in dealing with large data sets and knowledge of HiPortfolio and Data Warehouse’s. • Strong analytical ability to analyse, summarise and explain large data sets through verbal, written and visual forms. • Identifying efficiency opportunities, writing business cases and creating POC’s that will add business value through the implementation of Alteryx • Assist in developing the governance and framework to ensure operational readiness of new business technologies • Excellent analytical skills, able to manage multiple projects under strict timelines, work well in a demanding and dynamic environment to meet overall objectives. • Project management skills; experience with Agile, scheduling and resource management. • Ability to motivate cross-functional, interdisciplinary teams to achieve tactical and strategic goals.  Behavioral • Accountable: Want someone who is accountable for their actions. The Business analyst must be accountable for their estimates and for tracking their actions against the relevant plans as well as outlining issues as they arise • Attention to detail: Ensures accuracy and implements processes to ensure quality of output. Ensures high personal standards in all areas of work. • Problem solving: gathers and analyses information and uses it to develop effective solutions to difficult problems or situations • Client Focus: Complete commitment to provide professional, intelligent and timely responses to internal and external clients’ needs and to changes in the market. • Communication: Write, speak and present information effectively, relevantly and in a timely fashion • Negotiation & conflict resolution: Negotiates or mediates sound agreements in situations where there is disagreement or differences in interests • Innovation: Develop and implement original ideas, approaches and solutions to typical, unusual or difficult situations or problems • Collaboration and team work: Develops and maintains a good working relationship with others. Provide support to other team members and seeks the same from others. • Strategic thinking: Understands the business, and anticipates business needs, reflecting this in the approach to current solutions • Pro Active: Must be someone who can see a need and be willing to assist in meeting that need even if it falls outside the word specific area of their job description. Want a team player who realizes the importance of delivering the business solution and is willing to assist with this  Specific Qualifications Required • Degree qualified in IT, Business, or related discipline; and / or relevant work experience in a similar role.
job_description.439: Maven Partners Sydney NSW Corporate Finance & Investment Banking (Banking & Financial Services) The Opportunity - Data Analyst - Manager (Corporate Finance)  Are you currently in audit analytics and interested in a move to the corporate finance industry? If so, Maven Partners are working exclusively with a global financial advisory firm to recruit for a number talented Data Analysts into their Sydney-based corporate finance practice.  This is the perfect opportunity for those looking to leverage their analytical experience to move into the deals sector, with a business that will offer you exposure to some of the largest transactions taking place in the Australian market. Responsibilities  To work closely with the wider corporate finance practice and with the companies' clients and to maximise the financial efficiency of each engagement. Gathering large amounts of data and extracting tangible insights from that data, to help inform client's investment decisions. Develop combinations of scripts, workflows and functions to manipulate data in a way that enables in-depth analysis.  To aid in the growth of the business' Deal Analytics team through the coaching and mentoring of junior staff, while also managing their workflow. Drive the wider adoption of data analytics in deals to improve the firms' offering.  Requirements  At least three years' exposure to analytics within a Big Four professional services firm, ideally within audit or corporate finance. Experienced in the use of Tableau, Alteryx, Python, PowerBI and other data analysis tools. A commercial mindset, with the ability to build strong, lasting relationships with clients.  The Benefits  On top of the basic remuneration offered on this position, the company also operate using a model that offers financial incentives based on work completed.  Bonuses are transparent and calculated as a sum of the engagements you have been a part of; they are uncapped. Maven Partners Maven Partners is a specialist financial advisory, accounting and taxation recruitment services business.  The partners have a wealth of experience in executive search and interim management, servicing clients in the UK, Europe, Middle East and Asia Pacific markets from our offices in London, Jersey, Dubai, Melbourne and Sydney. At Maven Partners, we are holders and seekers of knowledge. In our case this refers to knowledge gained through experience, dedication, and perseverance. Knowledge is Maven's central value. job_description.440: Bluefin Resources has partnered with a renowned and prestigious university to seek a Senior Business Data Analyst for an initial 12-month contract. This role is pivotal as it involves contributing to a substantial ERP transformation project.  Position Purpose  The Senior Business Data Analyst will work on the Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) Program as part of the Information Technology Unit (ITU) and Operations Division. The successful candidate will ideally have end-to-end ERP delivery experience (including ERP System Integrator evaluation and selection experience) as a Senior Business Data Analyst or equivalent.  The Senior Business Data Analyst will work closely with internal and external senior stakeholders to drive the scoping, planning and execution of data initiatives (including but not limited to data quality assessments, data cleansing and mastering, and data extraction / transformation / loading / validation). As it is anticipated that a Systems Integrator (SI) will be appointed to deliver the new ERP platform, this role will work in conjunction with SI leaders and project teams to provide input, detailed review, and validation of deliverables produced by the SI.  The ERP program aims to deliver an integrated and standardised suite of business applications across the university, with significant change improvements and impacts to People (HR) and Finance business processes across the People and Finance Units within the Operations Division, as well as all Faculty, Research and Academic business areas.  Selection Criteria • Advanced SQL, data quality assessment and data migration experience (Min 5 years) • Extensive ERP implementation (Oracle or Workday) functional (finance and people) working experience (Min 8 years) • Experience in business analysis, process mapping, designing, and recommendations for process re-design using tools (Min 2 years) • Experience producing high quality documentation of business analysis and data discovery (Min 5 years) • Experience with Power BI including DAX (Min 2 years) • (Preferred) - Basic python data analysis skills (Min 2 years)  What's Available:  This opportunity commences as a 12 month contract, with a strong likelihood of extensions. The role is based in Ultimo, Sydney but offers the flexibility to work from home (WFH).  You'll collaborate with a team of dedicated individuals and contribute to a meaningful and fulfilling project where your impact will truly matter.  If you wish to be considered for this position, please submit your application online along with your most up-to-date resume. Alternatively, you can reach out to Lee Bartlett at 0410 744 438 for a more in-depth discussion. About the Role  The Global Senior Data Reporting Analyst provides expertise in data reporting and analytics to support decision making within OneSchool Global (OSG). This role will work closely with key leaders to develop understanding of OneSchool Global’s organisational data and produce meaningful data analytics to enable decision making. About you • Demonstrated a track record of working as a Senior Data Analyst. • Experience in the Education system highly desirable. • Proficiency in SQL for data extraction and manipulation. • Strong analytical skills and experience using statistical analysis tools (e.g., PowerBI). • Experience with data visualisation tools (e.g., Power BI). • Experience with data warehousing and data modelling. • Ability to work with large datasets and perform data cleansing and validation. • Excellent problem-solving skills and attention to detail. • Strong communication and interpersonal skills for effective collaboration.  The OneSchool Global Culture is based on strong values, and we have a supportive and dynamic team of educators and professional staff across the globe.  OneSchool Global is an Equal Opportunity Employer.
