job_description.444: Avant is Australia’s leading medical defence organisation with a proud heritage of protecting Australian medical professionals for over 130 years.  Avant now represents 82,000 health practitioners and medical students across every state and territory, delivering market leading products and services to meet their professional, personal and practice needs. Building on this heritage, our vision is to be the most trusted professional partner in supporting doctors throughout their lives and careers.  As a mutual organisation, owned by members and run purely for their benefit, our members are at the centre of all we do. As well as providing products and services to our member, we play a broader community role by advocating for improvements in the healthcare system and in quality, safety and professionalism in medicine, through delivering education and research activities.  About the role:  Avant is implementing an integrated business-led data governance function that bridges the divide between business and IT, modernises processes and will be essential to ensuring we meet our strategic imperatives.  This role, reporting to the Data Governance Manager, will act as an advisory and consultative function to assist the business in identifying Critical Data Elements (CDEs) and addressing their data governance requirements.  You will support the implementation of the organisation's Data Governance Framework and standards across business functions, to build trust and value in their data. Confidence in facilitating workshops and initiating, influencing and maintaining positive productive relationships with stakeholders will be essential for success.  Within the role, you will assist Data Owners and Data Stewards understanding and alignment with the Data Governance Framework, policies, practices and regulatory obligations and guidelines relating to data such as CPG235, the privacy act, CPS230.  Key accountabilities: • Support the development, implementation and embedment of the data governance framework, including policies, standards, processes and metrics • Collaborate with key stakeholders across the business, and act as a SME, to ensure understanding and alignment Data Governance framework and regulatory obligations, standards and guidelines relating to data such as CPG235, privacy, CPS230 • Ensure consistency in data governance and management practices across Avant by maintaining a Business Glossary, Data Catalogue and Data Dictionary. • Advocate for better use of data across Avant and contribute to improving the data literacy across the business with knowledge sharing, upskilling others, facilitating governance forum meetings and assisting with projects • Coordinate and lead data quality remediation efforts, championing the management and resolution of data quality issues with operational business leads  To be successful in this role you will have: • 5+ years experience across data governance, data management or data analytics space, including implementing relevant frameworks, policies and standards • Experience in a regulated environment (financial services or insurance essential) • A solid understanding, and experience with Data Management concepts and best practices such as DCAM / DMBOK • Working knowledge of different data governance & management tools and processes • Experience working with customer data • Strong stakeholder management and ability to comfortably work and interact with senior stakeholders across a number of business divisions and domains  At Avant, our people are the centre of everything we do for our members. We offer a range of benefits and opportunities to enable you to make a difference, learn, and grow in your career.  For further information, please contact Sue Allen, Talent Acquisition Specialist on 0429 404 856.

job_description.447: Company Description  Let your passion fly! We’re proud to be one of the world’s leading airlines. Our reputation is built on a long track record of success, an ongoing commitment to our home Hong Kong, and on the delivery of customer service that’s straight from the heart. All of this is possible due to our talented people who share our passion for aviation and our commitment to being the best. Join us and discover just how far you can go!  Role Introduction  We are looking for a People Data, Insights and Policy Analyst who will take a leading role in transforming our team reporting and policy framework capabilities, resulting in further clarity, consistency and data driven insights.  This is a 12-month full-time position based in our regional office in Barangaroo, Sydney. This role will lead a project to review end to end our current ways of working, building fit for future solutions that optimize our data and reporting functionality. This includes, automation of key people metrics reporting/dashboards, defining process mapping, and supporting development of clearer guidelines/playbooks/checklists for People processes.  Key Responsibilities • Define and drives an end-to-end project plan that prioritises scope and timeline to review and document all People processes and practises. • Create transparency of the process to execute such policies and subsequent impact on our reporting needs. • Support any global compliance requests, identifying local risks and driving forward focus areas for improvement across the region. • Play a key role in connecting to a variety of data sources ie supporting integration of data from our payroll systems back to People Hub. • Design end-to-end reporting solutions, with a strong focus on methodology, data integration with existing systems and tools. • Conducting detailed analysis to support improvement and change initiatives that reduce costs, increase utilisation, and improve wellness and fatigue management. • Educating People team colleagues on the use and adaptation of reporting tooling and how to draw meaningful insights from this information.  Requirements • Tertiary qualification and/or extensive work experience in an appropriate discipline. • Demonstrated experience in managing complex data and reporting environments, programs or projects • Proven ability to identify and implement process improvement • Strong proficiency with Excel & working with dataflows • Detail focused and strives for accuracy • Proactive with great communication skills • Ability to put narrative to numbers when communicating with internal stakeholders • Project Management experience preferred  Benefits • Be part of the Cathay Pacific family and join a dynamic team culture working for one of the world’s Top 10 Global Airlines • Make the most of your leave and take advantage of travel industry discounts including flights, hotels, tours and car hire • Hybrid working from Barangaroo in the Sydney CBD  Personal & Application Information  Please apply with a cover letter outlining why you are interested in this role and what makes you stand out from others.  you must have rights to live and work in Australia to apply. Develop predictive models to optimise programmatic advertising campaigns, including ad targeting, bidding strategies, and ad creatives, while leveraging Bayesian techniques for efficiency. Assess and validate the accuracy and reliability of predictive models, using Bayesian diagnostics for model evaluation.  Translate complex modeling insights, Bayesian optimisation results, and diagnostic findings into actionable recommendations for campaign optimization. D. in a quantitative field such as Mathematics, Statistics, Data Science, or related disciplines. Proficient in programming languages such as Python, SQL etc  Strong command of data analysis and machine learning libraries (e.g., pandas, scikit-learn, TensorFlow, PyTorch).  Understanding of statistical concepts and techniques, including A/B testing, attribution modeling, and customer segmentation.  Ideall  y experience with programmatic advertising platforms, tools, and technologies, though not mandatory.  Exceptional problem-solving skills and the ability to tackle complex, open-ended challenges.  Excellent communication and collaboration skills for effective teamwork with cross-functional teams.  Detail-oriented with a passion for continuous learning and improvement.  Benefits: Competitive salary and performance-based bonuses.  Flexible work hours and options for remote work.  Professional development opportunities and training programs.  An innovative and collaborative work environment.  The chance to work on cutting-edge programmatic advertising campaigns that impact the industry. Experience using R and python would be an advantage, but not necessary. • Ability to simplify complex concepts & interpret information by explaining in simple terms and contextually apply results to solve business problems to influencing & negotiate successful outcomes. • Excellent interpersonal skills and a demonstrated ability to employ a variety of communication skills (both in written & verbal form) tailored to the audience. • Solid work ethic. job_description.457: Innovating. Empowering. Delighting. Join the Intuit Australia & Rest of World team as a Staff Business Data Analyst to delight small businesses & accountants through QuickBooks and our ecosystem of attached products.  Intuit HQ is based in Mountain View California where we have been in operations since 1983. We are proud to share that Intuit has consistently appeared in Fortune's top 50 Best companies to work for over the last 5 years. We believe in the power of the individual. The power to do more. To make more. To be more.  The Data Analytics team is looking for a talented Staff Data Analyst to drive GTM initiatives across the Australian & Rest of World businesses. You should be a driven fast learner and high achiever with a passion to continuously learn, grow and deliver well in a high performance and flexible hybrid working environment characterized by speed, collaboration, creativity and fun.  As a Staff Analyst, you will work closely with our GTM Teams to develop insights, lead experimentation, and drive key business results. You will take complex concepts and communicate them to both technical and non-technical leaders in order to effect change for our customers. You will be an instrumental leader in shaping the strategy, working across Marketing, Sales, Intuit AI and Data Engineering to drive an integrated plan to grow and scale our Advisor business.  This is an amazing opportunity to join our passionate team using cutting edge technology and the newest trends in analytics to innovate and challenge the way things are done. You'll be exposed to some of the brightest minds in the tech industry around the globe and empowered to make your own mark!If this sounds like you and you're ready to join our growth journey, we'd love to hear from you!  Responsibilities  This role is a critical partner, leading data and analytics for complex strategic businessinitiatives. • You will be responsible for working across functional groups, self generating hypotheses via data and clearly communicating subsequent insights to senior leaders that drive business impact in a fun team environment. • You will use your business domain knowledge in combination with data and analytics to lead projects, including market/category insights, experiment design, creating dashboards, measuring business results, and analysing customer behaviour. • You will also utilise multiple analytics tools and techniques based on business requirements. Analytics expertise includes (but are not limited to) performance variance testing, funnel/journey reporting, marketing attribution models, A/B and multivariate testing, ROI measurement, statistical analysis,segmentation,and ML modeling (supervised and unsupervised). • You will also rely on strong abilities to access data from various sources, such as relational databases, distributed data sources and, third party data capture tools. • You will create analysis using visualisation tools (e.g. Tableau) to share customized insights with business and analytics partners. • You can prototype data sets used in reporting and analysis. You can also use knowledge of A/B testing to design, implement, and interpret test results using common frameworks. In addition, you will keep a pulse on emerging technologies (such as data exploration, data modeling, visualization and testing) and statistical methods that would make your work more scalable or more efficient for Intuit. • You will marshal resources and seek commitment across multiple functions (such as business stakeholders, data and analytics experts, and IT infrastructure partners) to achieve measurable business outcomes across Marketing, Sales and Operations. • You will also be expected to coach fellow analysts and stakeholders on their craft to help build a great data community and data-driven leaders. • 7+ years of analytics experience working in marketing, sales, web, or other related fields • Highly proficient in SQL, Tableau, and Excel • Experience with programming languages including R or Python • Previous in-depth experience working on SAAS products is a plus. • Excellent problem-solving skills and end to end quantitative thinking • Strong business and commercial acumen: ability to transform the WHAT into the WHY to uncover new opportunities for innovation. • Ability to lead complex strategic initiatives from ideation to execution in a high paced growth environment. • Data storyteller: strong ability to present complex data and insights conciselyto various stakeholders. • Experience building deep customer journeys and marketing funnel reporting, including complex lead journeys and multi-touch attribution models • Statistical knowledge to guide and support A/B testing or other experimentation frameworks, and interpret the results to draw detailed and practical conclusions • Working knowledge of Salesforce is advantageous

job_description.460: Description  About Ashurst Risk Advisory:  Ashurst Risk Advisory was created to respond to client demand and is designed to provide risk expertise that complement the firm's core legal services.  With dedicated teams of legal and risk professionals working side by side, it brings together the technical expertise and critical thinking required to operationalise laws and regulations and help clients to achieve their goals.  After successfully establishing the division in Australia in 2020, our now 100 strong team have developed a market leading reputation and in October 2022 expanded into the UK. To find out more please visit www.ashurst.com  About the role:  As a result of exponential growth our Data & Analytics team is looking to hire a Specialist (equivalent to a Senior Consultant in Big4 consulting) with demonstrated experience in Data Governance.  On a daily basis we work in close collaboration with teams across the Risk Advisory practise and legal teams to focus on how data can be used to deliver a best in class legal led consulting service. We combine our skills to design and deliver data-driven risk management solutions across a vast array of domains from privacy to security to financial crime to name just a few. Some of our work includes: • Assessing the maturity of data governance frameworks • Designing, implementing and embedding data governance frameworks to demonstrate compliance to data management obligations and the adequate management of data risk • Designing and implementing data quality frameworks • Working with clients to document the flow of data from the point of consumption to the point of capture • Supporting clients in the implementation of a data governance tool • Building data pipelines, reporting and governance controls to enable clients to provide and consume data through data sharing agreements • Working with clients to understand their business and data from the bottom up to drive data driven regulatory responses in relation to compliance breaches and remediation activities • Developing algorithms to identify compliance and regulatory risks in client data and use those insights to both proactively alert upon and manage and mitigate those risks using data driven solutions.  Please review the job description attached to the role on our careers site for more detail on the role and what we can offer you.  About you: • You're excited about using your data talents to help solve a diverse range of client problems with new, unique and inventive solutions, and assist in the growth of a unique and 'first to market' practice • You have experience in designing and implementing data governance frameworks • You have experience in documentation of data management policies • You have experience in implementation of data quality frameworks • You have experience in identification of Critical Data Elements, and documentation of data lineage • You have proven experience bringing high quality value to clients through developing data strategies, embedding data governance frameworks, driving insights through analytics and reporting, or creating AI/ML-backed solutions. You're also comfortable clearly communicating with technical and non-technical stakeholders • You're passionate about collaborating with a multi-disciplinary team from across the firm, and have a desire to learn and grow daily • You approach challenging problems with both confidence and humility to put forward your ideas but also empathise with alternate view points • It's desirable if you're experienced and comfortable with the common tools in this space. We use a combination of Alteryx, SQL Server, PowerBI, Tableau and Python but no worries if you're not an expert in these; experience with other common analytics tools is also fine  What makes Ashurst Risk Advisory a great place to work?  We are a team devoted to collaboration, diversity, transparency and innovation. Our vision is to create a unique culture in the consulting market based around teamwork and a structure that offers everyone a voice and the encouragement to help us build the practice. Our ambition is to hire a highly diverse team combining various personalities, cultures and professional backgrounds, and offer them the opportunity to directly deal with clients, take responsibility for business development, drive their careers, and help us in defining our strategy, culture and processes.  We offer award winning Learning & Development and Diversity & Inclusion programs, and a range of benefits including, subsidised gym membership, discounted health insurance, complimentary health and wellbeing support programs, study support, annual bonuses, flexible working, and 26 weeks parental leave, to name a few. job_description.461: If this sounds like the opportunity for you, we would welcome you to apply using the below link:  https://teg.bamboohr.com/careers/527?source=aWQ9MjA%3D  About Ticketek  Ticketek has over 40 years' experience ticketing the biggest live events and venues in Australia. Ticketek sells over 23 million tickets to more than 20,000 events each year, including concerts, sports, theatre, musicals, festivals, exhibitions, experience and family events. A truly digital company, Ticketek is Australia’s number one entertainment events website, and a global leader in ticketing solutions.  The Role  Ticketek operates one of the most advanced ecommerce platforms in Australia, underpinned by one of the largest 1st party data sets. In addition, the latest marketing technology, and an advanced data science and analytics team, have seen us deliver hyper personalisation and machine learning capabilities.  We are now seeking an experienced Digital Analytics & Optimisation Manager to help inform our strategic UX and Digital roadmaps.  You will be responsible for overseeing our optimisation and analytics platforms including our CRO platform, DX Insights platform, and Google Analytics. You will work closely with the Product owners of our User Experience and Digital project streams by providing insights to help prioritisation of our development roadmaps in these areas.  Your focus will be to manage an ongoing program of activity to continually analyse on-site and in-app performance, implement an ongoing testing program, and ultimately identify and lead the implementation of changes that will increase overall conversion rates and revenue. You will provide insight and opportunity to the Product and technology teams to identify problems and opportunities. You will interrogate data and results to identify optimisation opportunities and work with a team of content managers, analysts, designers, and developers to ensure we are maximising both user experience and conversion across our digital assets.  The Person  As the Digital Analytics & Optimisation Manager, you will be responsible for:  Performance Analysis • Develop a deep understanding of the user experience, with a particular focus on Discovery and Purchase, across the website and App through a combination of an intuitive understanding of our platform with data driven insights from analytics including Google Analytics, Clarity and customer research. • Measure datapoints along the user experience and create customer journey mapping frameworks • Collect and analyse data regarding ecommerce performance – tracking and reporting on drop-offs throughout the purchase funnel • Set and maintain ecommerce benchmarks • Derive and circulate data-driven insights to inform UX and digital development streams • Develop dashboards for internal stakeholders to track ecommerce performance • Action insights from our DX Intelligence platform to reduce customer friction points and prioritise our optimisation efforts • Document data flows and missing data points within our analytics platforms  Project Management • Manage the relationship with our external analytics and CRO agency • Project manage our CRO testing roadmap in close collaboration with our CRO agency • Chair our internal UX Working Group • Provide insights to our internal PM teams to help identify and prioritise our UX and Digital dev roadmaps • Work closely with the Product Owner of our UX stream to test and inform future state UX design • Implement performance tracking of new products to understand customer impact • Identify and provide input to the development teams to troubleshoot UX problems  Stakeholder Management • Provide regular reporting and feedback to Senior Management including proposed enhancements, enhancements roadmap, and weekly performance results.  Essential experiences & skills • Minimum 4 years of professional experience in a similar role • Experience delivering personalised on-site user experience • Experience in an Ecommerce environment, across CRO, analytics, optimisation, tagging/tracking and media, • Demonstrated understanding of core eCommerce and martech technologies with the ability to communicate effectively with business, marketing, data, development and technical roles. • Proven experience of using analytics and data to drive user experience and business decision making • Advanced skills with Google Analytics and Google Tag Manager and CRO platforms • Proficient in data management and integration, with experience in data governance and privacy regulations. • Excellent communication skills and developed ability to both manage and work directly with stakeholders.  So, what does Ticketek offer?  At Ticketek all your hard work in helping change the way we interact with clients and customers will not go unnoticed.  In return we support and reward great performance by offering competitive salaries, employee benefits and incentives. • Training and Development • Wellness Wednesday • Flexible Working Arrangements • Birthday Leave! • Gym Membership Perks • Free Advice and Support (EAP) • Flu Vaccinations • Learning Opportunities and support • Company Paid Parental Leave • Complimentary tickets to selected events • Going the Extra Mile (GEM) Awards and Service Awards • Opportunities to support our community and partners  If this sounds like the opportunity for you, we would welcome you to apply using the below link:  https://teg.bamboohr.com/careers/527?source=aWQ9MjA%3D  About TEG  TEG is a global leader in Live Entertainment, Ticketing and Technology. Every day TEG connects fans to experiences and customers with brands. We are proud partners of some of the world’s largest and most iconic venues as well as leading event promoters globally. TEG operates worldwide out of seven country offices and includes Ticketek, Ticketek Marketplace, Ticketek UK, Ticketek New Zealand, Ticketek Malaysia, Ticketek Philippines, Eventopia, Softix, TEG Live, TEG Dainty, TEG Sport, TEG Van Egmond, Laneway Festival, Handsome Tours, SXSW Sydney, TEG Theatrical, MJR Presents, TEG Lifelike Touring, TEG TES Live, Brickman, TEG Rockefeller, Rugby Live, TEG Europe, Propaganda, TEG USA, Qudos Bank Arena, FAN+, VIP NOW and Ovation.  TEG is an equal opportunity employer committed to embracing a diverse and inclusive work environment.  For further information about TEG please go to https://www.teg.com.au/ • Only direct applications will be considered. No recruiters please*

job_description.464: Employment Type: Permanent Full Time  Position Classification: Health Mgr Lvl 1  Remuneration: 81581 - 108532 full time equivalent base salary range (excludes super, leave loading and salary packaging)  Hours Per Week: 38  Requisition ID: REQ436037  Sydney Children's Hospitals Network is the largest paediatric health care entity in Australia. We care for thousands of children each year in our hospitals and in their homes - with one purpose in mind - to help young people live their healthiest lives.  Click here to learn more about our Network  What you'll be doing  This dynamic and fast paced Data Analyst role, which is part of the Costing and Analytics Team, will be responsible for the provision of data and analysis to support the clinical & non-clinical functions of the Network, such as Activity Based Funding (ABF) analysis (e.g. unwarranted clinical variation), key performance indicators (KPIs), clinical service planning, and clinical redesign projects.  Components include: • Comprehensive understanding of data related concepts, including relational database theory & SQL programming. • Provision of accurate, timely & relevant data analysis, interpretation and reports to internal & external stakeholders. • Evaluate and benchmark SCHN performance. • Measure and report against Service Level Agreement (SLA) KPIs. • Develop an understanding of ABF and clinical costing principles and processes.  Overall, the team is responsible for the Activity Based Management, Patient Level Costing, Reporting and Analytic functions for the Network, which supports SCHN staff in the use & interpretation of data results used in the decision making processes for the organisation.  Selection Criteria • Relevant tertiary qualifications in health informatics, information management, Computer Science/Statistics, or related field; or equivalent extensive experience. • Experience in SQL, (preferably SSMS (SQL Server Management Studio), or advanced skills in MS Access) and MS Excel/VBA, with a demonstrated high level analytical skills using multiple data sources and the ability to manipulate large amounts of data. • Highly developed analytical and numerical skills. Experience using R and python would be an advantage, but not necessary. • Ability to simplify complex concepts & interpret information by explaining in simple terms and contextually apply results to solve business problems to influencing & negotiate successful outcomes. • Excellent interpersonal skills and a demonstrated ability to employ a variety of communication skills (both in written & verbal form) tailored to the audience. • Solid work ethic. Able to self-direct, prioritise workload, meet deadlines & manage expectation with minimal supervision, escalating issues as required. • Able to innovate & think laterally to proactively prove & evolve work effort & contribution.  SCHN is an Equal Opportunity Employer that values diversity - we acknowledge the vibrancy that a diverse workforce brings to enhance both our workplace culture and our service delivery to children, young people and their families and carers. We encourage all suitably qualified applicants to apply. If you identify as an Indigenous Australian or as a person with a disability, please contact us if you would like some more information about our recruitment process.  Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people are encouraged to apply. We recognise the value of Aboriginal staff providing health care to Aboriginal children and families that access the services we provide at the Sydney Children's Hospitals Network. Aboriginal job applicants are encouraged to visit the NSW Health Aboriginal Recruitment tool, Stepping Up to assist in preparing your application.  All NSW Health workers are required to have completed a primary course (2 doses) of a COVID-19 vaccine which has been approved or recognised by the Therapeutics Goods Administration (TGA). New applicants must have completed the vaccination course prior to commencement with NSW Health, or provide an approved medical contraindication certificate (IM011 immunisation medical exemption form) certifying the worker cannot have any approved COVID-19 vaccines available in NSW.  Acceptable proof of vaccination is the Australian Immunisation Register (AIR) Immunisation History Statement or AIR COVID-19 Digital Certificate. Booster doses are highly recommended for all health care workers who have completed the primary course of COVID-19 vaccinations. job_description.465: About Agoda  Agoda is an online travel booking platform for accommodations, flights, and more. We build and deploy cutting-edge technology that connects travelers with more than 3.6 million accommodations globally. Based in Asia and part of Booking Holdings, our 6,000+ employees representing 90+ nationalities foster a work environment rich in diversity, creativity, and collaboration. We innovate through a culture of experimentation and ownership, enhancing the ability for our customers to experience the world.  THIS ROLE IS BASED IN BANGKOK, THAILAND (RELOCATION PROVIDED)  About Agoda  Agoda is an online travel booking platform for accommodations, flights, and more. We build and deploy cutting-edge technology that connects travelers with more than 2.5 million accommodations globally. Based in Asia and part of Booking Holdings, our 6,000+ employees representing 90+ nationalities foster a work environment rich in diversity, creativity, and collaboration. We innovate through a culture of experimentation and ownership, enhancing the ability for our customers to experience the world.  Get to Know our Team:  The Supply Analytics team is a team of creative entrepreneurs that develop solutions for Agoda’s accommodation partners and promote Agoda’s top and bottom-line growth. We design tailored business and product solutions with our partners and help them generate measurable value. Members of our team are empowered and supported to grow their market(s) or accounts. We develop win-win relationships and leverage Agoda’s unique accommodations portfolio and tech solutions to bring our partners the advantages they seek. Utilizing our strong brand and resources, we build new channels to increase the visibility of Agoda, introduce more travelers to our great products and service and deliver significant revenues to the overall business.  The Opportunity:  The role sits within the Supply Analytics team under Supply department, where new business ideas, and partnership types are incubated and scaled. We are looking for a BI Analyst whose main focus areas are providing visibility and insights for people-related issues through Business Intelligence tools like Tableau and SQL, managing data warehouses, building ETL processes, and helping build other tools to optimize the business. This role will be involved in strategic projects and work closely with commercial owners and business stakeholders, using data to identify and translate business needs and opportunities into actionable initiatives. You will report directly into the Manager, Senior Manager, or Associate Director of Supply Analytics.  In this Role, you’ll get to: • Translate internal briefs into analytical projects (to include refining the initial brief and asking the ‘right questions’, working through potential hypotheses and storyboarding the output) • Use and analyze data from multiple large-scale data warehouses and present statistically strong analysis to a wide range of business stakeholders • Proactively identify opportunities for growth within supply and the wider business • Drive new analytical initiatives and projects aimed at improving organizational efficiency and shaping Agoda supply • Identify, support, and lead projects aimed at scaling up the way the Supply organization leverages on data, insights, and intelligence • Automate manual operational processes and present back on time savings gained through modernization of business operations  What you’ll Need to Succeed: • 5+ years of experience as a BI Analyst in analytics/insights/strategy • Bachelor’s degree ideally in a business or quantitative subject (e.g. computer science, mathematics, engineering, science, economics or finance) • Hands-on experience with BI & analytics tools (SQL, Tableau, Metabase or PowerBI) • Experience in conducting A/B testing experimentation (a plus) • Good stakeholder management experience. Comfortable presenting to senior leadership and C-suite • Strong experience in finding data insights and provide business recommendation to the business • A good understanding of statistical modelling knowledge or any machine learning technique knowledge is a plus (regression, logistic regression, random forest, etc.) • Excellent skills in presenting and storytelling. • A hacker’s mindset – the ability to build simple but clever and elegant solutions to new problems within significant resource, operational and time constraints through deep understanding of the business, creative problem solving, and a wide range of expertise in data, analytics, automation, programming, and prototyping • Excellent communicator with superior written, verbal, presentation and interpersonal communication skills • Data driven in both decision making and performance measurement • Extreme comfort in ambiguous, fast-paced environment • Ability to multi-task, prioritize and coordinate resources  It’s Great if you Have: • Travel industry / e-commerce / tech / consulting experience  #Singapore #Berlin #Dublin #London #Jakarta #Hongkong #paris #sanfranciso #newyork #austin #seattle #tokyo #shanghai #seoul #sydney #brisbane #melbourne #toronto #moscow #saintpetersburg #kyiv  Equal Opportunity Employer  At Agoda, we pride ourselves on being a company represented by people of all different backgrounds and orientations. job_description.466: • Closing Date: 13 October 2023, 9:00 AM  face2face reference: 591408  Location: Nationwide - Remote  Hours: Full-time  Contract length: 12 Months Contract + 3 x 1 Month (Pending approval)  Entry requirements: Australian Citizen + Ability to obtain Baseline  Pay range: $95.00 – 115.00 p/h inc super  About the role:  The Tertiary Skills and Pathways team is responsible for the unit mapping project, as part of its program of work. Unit mapping uses natural language processing techniques to create a connection between tertiary education learning materials (VET and HE units), and skills taxonomies. Unit mapping helps to identify skills taught in tertiary education, and their potential relationship to occupations and the labour market, to assist in analysis and advice on tertiary education delivery.  The team is working on a demonstration project basis with five key projects to design the end to end process of unit mapping, to continually refine the data science model, and to generate insights on the potential use of mapping outputs. The outputs of models are large, for example one university with approximately 3,000 units can have an output of approximately 30,000 skills mapped. Validation of outputs is a critical part of the mapping process to produce a model and results that are highly accurate.  Duties: • Developing of a comprehensive internal and external validation process for very large data sets, to support improvement of data science models, and the quality of output data sent to partners. This may require an ensemble of approaches, for example statistical sampling, manual and automated approaches to validation. • Managing internal validation processes before outputs are sent to project partners. • Working closely with the data science team to provide feedback for the mapping model development. • Analysing complex model outputs, to derive valuable insights for reporting to project partners, including visualisation techniques. • Providing advice to technical services on interface design for a validation application for project partners.  Required experience/skills: • Demonstrated experience in data analysis and process design, to create replicable data validation processes to improve data output quality. • Excellent analytical skills, with strong attention to detail, and the ability to synthesise and critically analyse large volumes of structured and unstructured data. • Strong skills and experience in data management, in particular how data can be effectively structured, analysed, presented and communicated, to achieve high-quality outcomes. • Excellent communication skills, including the ability to effectively communicate key data insights visually and in written form to a range of diverse stakeholders • Well-developed interpersonal skills, including the ability to work effectively in a multidisciplinary setting.  Desirable experience skills: • Experience in R Shiny, Python, SQL, anduser experience design. • Understanding of, and experience working with tertiary education (HE and/or VET) and/or occupation and labour market data. • Understanding and experience in data science, or related fields. • Experience operating in a policy environment. job_description.467: • Join the Asset Modelling group at Ausgrid as we embark on our exciting transformation journey! • Permanent Full Time | $172,014-$181,807 + 15.5% Super + 1 Monthly Day Off! • Based at our Sydney CBD office | Hybrid Working  Just imagine a future where households and businesses can generate their own energy and sell it back to the grid, ultimately connecting communities and empowering lives. Are you ready to play your part in an evolving industry?  Ausgrid is on an exciting transformation journey and now is the time to be a part of something big. We are proud to service Australia’s east coast, as a leading business in energy distribution, delivering a safe and reliable electricity supply to more than 1.8 million homes – that’s over four million Australians relying on us every day.  Our vision is simple; for our communities to have the power for a resilient, affordable net zero future.  We take pride in knowing that the work we collectively achieve today, will transform the world tomorrow. We value a culture of working and living safely, being customer focussed, commercially minded, collaborative, honest, accountable, and respectful. Our values are not just initiatives driven by leaders; they define the way we work.  Meet our team!  In a world where you spend more hours a week with your work colleagues than your family, it is important to us that you thrive in the team you are in! Energise your career as part of our Asset Modelling team at Ausgrid!  By joining our dynamic Asset Modelling team, you'll be undertaking recognised (award winning) industry-leading analysis supporting our replacement programs and maintenance initiatives, all while driving growth, optimising asset and network performance, and facilitating the transition to a sustainable, net-zero future.  Take the helm in an exciting role that combines cutting-edge modelling, innovative solutions, and thrive in a team with the passion for shaping the future of our industry.  Your new role  As a Data Scientist at Ausgrid, your role is to develop processes that utilise advanced data science techniques and modern systems to analyse data and draw insights to realise business benefits and optimise the balance between asset risk, cost and performance and support the development of models that result in real world outcomes.  Alongside a high performing team of Analysts and Engineers, you will be analysing and forecasting the performance of millions of assets, through billions of calculations and integrate modern and advanced data science techniques to support the development and integration of statistical and financial models used to provide insights and facilitate risk based, and whole of life asset management decision making.  Responsibilities including but not limited to: • Integrate modern and advanced data science techniques to support the development, integration and documentation of asset life and financial models using statistical analysis techniques to assist in asset management decision making and whole of life analysis. • Undertake research and prepare functional and technical specification documentation that enables the development and production of appropriate software, technology solutions, business processes and data models to enable an efficient, repeatable and scalable implementation of these models in Ausgrid’s IT environment. • Maintain an expert level currency in quantitative and probabilistic analysis techniques and the practical application of theoretical principles to asset maintenance, replacement and the optimisation of whole of life decision making. • Provide leadership in the creation and development of innovative individual asset and portfolio level cost benefit initiatives in support of the Company Purpose objective. • In-depth understanding of data integrity issues to allow for built in levels of confidence in modelling and assurance to both internal and external stakeholders. • Establish detailed data specification documentation to define, compile and utilise asset master and transactional data to understand and optimise the balance between asset risk, cost and performance and support the development of models that align to asset class strategies and asset management objectives. • Work with stakeholders across all functions and business units to identify opportunities for leveraging company data, and model output(s) to drive optimal business solutions. • Develop processes that utilise advanced analysis techniques and modern systems to analyse data and draw insights to realise business benefits. • Prepare business cases, presentations and detailed documentation to support the introduction of new work methods, technology, models, datasets and business processes. • Provide technical expertise in the development of data architectures, models and enhancements. • Import, manipulate, conflate, and extract spatial and non-spatial data to support business objectives.  Spark our interest!  Our hiring decisions are not only based on your experience and skills, but we also take into consideration your passion, attitude, and alignment to our core values.  The successful candidate will be degree qualified (Data Science, Statistics, Mathematics, Spatial or Computer Science, Engineering, Finance or Economics) and able to energise us through their skills, demonstrated expert knowledge and experience in various statistical, data mining and machine learning techniques along with their strengths and weaknesses for practical implementation. You will have strong problem solving skills and demonstrated ability to critically analyse systems, processes and software tools and identify appropriate integration strategies and implement solutions, as well as: • Knowledge and experience of statistical computer languages (SAS, Python, SQL, R or equivalent) used to manipulate and transform data into information and enable useful insights to be drawn from large/small and/or technical data sets. • Experience working with and creating data structures and architectures. • Demonstrated ability to mine and analyse data, processes, and technology solutions. • Preparation of business cases, briefs and presentations and detailed documentation to support the introduction of new work methods, technology, models, datasets and business processes. • Ability to liaise with a variety of stakeholders. • High attention to detail and demonstrated personal initiative. • Skills in financial evaluation and optimisation of investment decision making. • Ability to manage multiple tasks and/or projects and prioritising activities. • Demonstrated ability to work both as part of a team and independently. • Strong communicative abilities including written and verbal presentation, negotiation and persuasive skills, and able to deal effectively at senior levels in large organisations. • Ability to create and prepare automated reports (PowerBi, SAS Visual Analytics, or equivalent) that provide validation of model inputs and forecast outputs and assurance to key business stakeholders.  Desirable • Post graduate qualifications in Statistics, Mathematics, Computer and/or Data Science, Finance, Economics or other related business discipline. • Experience and understanding of asset management principles and demonstrated experience in optimising asset risk, expenditure and performance. • Experience in spatial data analytics. • An understanding of electricity networks and related assets. • Experience in monitoring costs and financial impacts across work activities, projects or programs of work.  Grow with Ausgrid  To continue building on our rich heritage, we actively invest in our people’s development through secondments, onsite training, mentoring circles, e-learning, Australian Graduate School of Management programs (UNSW) and study assistance.  It is through our investment in our people that the average tenure across the business is 14 years and our current turnover is sitting at a market competitive rate of just 3.9%.  Ausgrid Perks  Revel in more than just a competitive salary! Our employees enjoy a dynamic range of market leading support and safety services, wellbeing programs, corporate discounts, and flexibility arrangements in many forms.  Our people are paramount to the continued success of Ausgrid, therefore celebrating great work is important to us! It’s not just the big wins that count, we have provided our employees the opportunity to applaud peer successes daily through our Amped Recognition Program. But let’s not forget the major milestones! For those ready to exceed expectations, anticipate a nomination for a CEO award at our formal end of year Award gala.  Belonging at Ausgrid  To deliver the best possible service to our customers we strive towards a workforce that reflects the diverse community that we serve. Ausgrid is committed to creating a diverse and inclusive workforce and we encourage applications from women, people from culturally diverse backgrounds, people with disabilities, people from the LGBTQIA+ community and First Nations people.  Interested, but unsure if you’re the right match? At Ausgrid, we aren’t looking for perfect! If you would like to discuss the opportunity in more detail, please contact the dedicated Talent Advisor for this opportunity on – recruitment@ausgrid.com.au FAO Laura Brown – Senior Talent Advisor.  If you require support with your application/reasonable adjustments for the interview process, we want to hear from you.

As the Head of Data and Analytics, you will lead our data team responsible for managing the operational data of the entire group, as well as analyzing customer transaction data. Benefits  Fostering a collaborative, open environment that's conducive to employee success is the #1 priority at TMGM. • Growth Opportunities - We value your growth as much as we do ours, so we include educational and career growth opportunities at every level. • People-First Values -We believe building a great company happens by hiring great people. Our employees' job satisfaction always comes first. • Shared Success - We offer revenue share opportunities for the right people, allowing our employees to share in company success. • Worldwide Team - Our worldwide team means you'll work with others from all over the globe and gain international experience.

job_description.470: About Future Fund  The Future Fund is Australia's Sovereign Wealth Fund. Our purpose is clear: we invest for the benefit of future generations of Australians.  Decision making is our commercial competitive advantage. Our organisation is home to ambitious, high-performing people who are driven to do meaningful work, grow professionally, support their peers and colleagues, and contribute to the future success of our organisation.  Our ‘One team, One purpose’ philosophy underpins our unique culture and the way we work together. This philosophy extends into all aspects of our organisation and guides how and why we do what we do.  The Opportunity  An exciting opportunity awaits an experienced Senior Analyst to join the IDM Data Operations team. This role is aimed at supporting the Overlays investment team, for whom you will manage upstream investment data management activities. Your in-depth understanding of data analysis, management, tools, models, and the data lifecycle, coupled with your expertise in derivative products (including their valuation and trade life cycles) along with proficiency with the Aladdin platform, will be invaluable in managing investment data for this specialised domain.  Your primary focus will be on daily delivery of data into the Aladdin OMS and ensuring that trading data is both timely and accurate for our Overlays investment team. Key stakeholders to this role are the Overlays team and Investment Operations teams, your ability to drive meaningful and successful relationships with stakeholders is key to success. Your innovative and proactive approach, along with strong statistical skills, will drive data-driven solutions to enhance their experience with the data.  If you are an ambitious professional with a proven background in data analysis and possess expertise in derivative products and lifecycles, along with proficiency in the Aladdin platform, we invite you to apply.  Key Responsibilities  Data Management and Technical Support: Investigate and resolve technical issues related to trades, monitor trading activities, and provide technical expertise on the Aladdin derivatives system. Collaborate with investment teams and technology to ensure accurate processing of trades and settlements. Enhance processes through Aladdin platform improvements.  Operational Service Delivery: Oversee outsourced partners, ensuring high-quality service delivery to downstream consumers. Monitor data delivery, certification, and exception management. Implement market data requirements, drive data quality improvements, and proactively develop solutions to enhance operational efficiency.  Partner and Provider Management: Support oversight of partner delivery, prioritize and manage data service requests. Monitor partner services/products in line with solution parameters. Assist in project and product management of data-related initiatives, fostering effective partner relationships.  About You  1. Technical Proficiency: A strong grasp of the Blackrock Aladdin system, coupled with expertise in derivative securities, trade lifecycles, and market conventions. 2. Analytical Acumen: Proficiency in quantitative analysis and problem-solving, enabling the development of data-driven solutions and insights. 3. Effective Communication: Outstanding interpersonal and communication skills, with the ability to engage stakeholders, convey information, and influence decisions. 4. Professional Attributes: A commitment to professionalism, accuracy, and quality in tasks, along with a proactive, innovative, and adaptable mindset to navigate a dynamic environment.  Life at Future Fund  Our approach to building an inclusive culture is aimed at facilitating impactful, effective and objective decision making. We continue to deepen our understanding of the lived experience of underrepresented groups within our industry.  To continue to expand our knowledge, we actively encourage you to apply to this role and contribute to our collective Purpose. We are better for our differences and support our people in bringing their authentic selves to work. It not only benefits our teams, it means you can focus on what matters most, being you.  Learn more about life at Future Fund by visiting our LinkedIn Life page.

including the ability to manage changing priorities and meeting deadlines • Significant experience in data mining, machine-learning and operations research • Good knowledge of R, SQL and Python; familiarity with Spark, Scala, Java or C++ is an asset • Strong math and analytical skills, with business acumen  Why swipejobs: • A chance to work on a market leading US software product • End to end exposure to the full software development life cycle • Working in a start up environment with modern offices located in North Sydney • A flat organisational structure where everyone is always accessible • Operating in a fast paced and dynamic environment that provides exciting challenges daily • A chance to work on modern technology stack which is cutting edge even for the US • Food provided throughout the day whilst working in the office including a free lunch • Regular social events in and outside the office  If you are talented, driven and interested in joining us in our journey; Your responsibilities will include developing and implementing data governance policies, automating data processes, and working closely with cross-functional teams to drive data-related initiatives.  Key Responsibilities:  Data Governance:  Define and enforce data governance policies and procedures.  Collaborate with stakeholders to establish data quality standards and data management best practices.  Monitor data quality, compliance, and privacy to ensure adherence to industry regulations and internal guidelines.  Create and maintain a data catalog, documenting data assets and their lineage.  Data Automation:  Identify opportunities for automating data-related processes to improve efficiency and accuracy.  Design, develop, and implement automated workflows for data extraction, transformation, and loading (ETL).  Utilize tools and technologies for data integration and orchestration to streamline data workflows.  Troubleshoot and optimize data automation pipelines to ensure smooth operation.  Collaboration and Communication:  Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including data analysts, engineers, and business stakeholders, to gather requirements and deliver data solutions. Data Security and Compliance:  Ensure data security measures are in place, including access controls and encryption, to protect sensitive data. job_description.479: About The Role  An exciting opportunity to join BOQ as a Senior Data Management Analyst during our transformation journey. By joining the digital bank of the future, you will be able to make a difference with integrity and empathy, overseeing the successful and effective analysis of the data quality capability adding significant value to our organisation.  As a Senior Data Management Analyst, you will be working closely with the Group Technology Team that consists of Business Analysts, Developers and Testers. Reporting to the Manager of Data Management, you will be responsible for supporting the execution of data initiatives that enable our bankers to have access to trusted, governed and easily available data which supports their needs.  In this role you will ensure data management practices are conducted in line with statutory, regulatory, audit and risk expectations. Furthermore, you will support operations of the Data Management Framework which includes data principles, policy, standards, and guidelines ensuring their pragmatic and beneficial application to data platforms and the wider data ecosystem. You will also be involved in conducting awareness and training initiatives to create a measurable uplift in data literacy and data handling skills across the bank.  About You  As an experienced data management and analytics professional, you will be a collaborative outcome and people focussed individual who thrives on working in a fast-paced environment. You will have 6+ years of experience working in enterprise data platforms (Data Warehousing, Data Analytics Data Governance or BI) with an ability to manipulate and analyse large amounts of data using SQL queries and map data from source to target.  Alongside your experience working with third party vendors and developing lasting relationships to ensure success, you will have a strong understanding and practical experience in data quality, data management/governance frameworks and methodologies.  About Us  BOQ is one of Australia’s leading regional banks and provides a genuine alternative for Australian financial services customers and employees. Our purpose is to create prosperity for our customers, shareholders and people through empathy, integrity and by making a difference. Our ambition is to be known as the bold challenger bank; with multi-brands that are digitally enabled with a personal touch.  BOQ is passionate about providing opportunities for you to develop your career as we continuously adapt and deliver in a transformational and collaborative environment with a strong focus on community.  BOQ’s Inclusion vision is to foster a workspace that values and leverages difference and creates new possibilities, a place where our people feel confident to bring their best selves to work every day. We embrace difference and believe that our workforce should reflect the customers and communities that we serve.  Since 2021 BOQ Group is recognised as an Employer of Choice for Gender Equality by the Workplace Gender Equality Agency (WGEA).  Our Benefits • Flexible working arrangements • Discounted financial products • Salary sacrificing options • Paid parental leave with no minimum • Paid volunteer days • Purchase annual leave • Discounted private health insurance plan • Employee Assistance Program (EAP) • 5 employee diversity network groups focusing on: First Nations Reconciliation Council, Proudly ME (LGBTIQA+), Multicultural, Gender and Early Career • BOQ Group is a member of Pride in Diversity and a participating organisation in the Australian Workplace Equality Index  How To Apply  To apply for this role please apply via our Careers Page.  The Bank of Queensland is committed to diversity and an inclusive workforce. Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander People are encouraged to apply.  If you are successful for a role with the Bank of Queensland, it is a condition of employment that background screening is completed to ensure that the Bank complies with its obligations under the Anti-Money Laundering and Counter Terrorism Financing Act. These checks may include, but are not limited to: identity, verification, reference checks, criminal background checks, immigration checks, verification of academic qualifications, bankruptcy checks.  Please no agency applications.

We truly believe the right mix of diversity and authenticity will be our winning hand. job_description.484: About Us  Endeavour Group was created in 2020 through the restructure and merger of the Woolworths Group drinks and hospitality businesses. With a strong track record of growth, combined these businesses form the leading customer franchise in drinks and hospitality in Australia.  United behind a common purpose of ‘Creating a more sociable future together’, we are a 28,000+ strong team with more than 1600 stores and 330 hotels nationally, including leading brands such as Dan Murphy’s, BWS and ALH Hotels.  Endeavour Group separated from Woolworths during calendar year 2021 and is well-positioned as an ASX Top 50 Company. Join the team at an exciting time in their evolution!  About The Opportunity  This is a 12 month fixed term contract.  As part of the Data Governance & Privacy team, this role will play a critical part in implementing a robust data governance framework across Endeavour Drinks Group.  With an increasing focus across the group on the use of data to empower decision making and uplift revenue, this role performs a critical function to ensure better understanding, quality, and governance of data.  Drive the delivery of data governance across Endeavour and work with the data governance & privacy team to develop and execute a strategic road map to ensure our data is safe and trusted.  A day in the life of a Data Governance Analyst @ Endeavour ... • Create and conduct governance processes to measure data management and data quality maturity across various domains • Create, update & support policies, standards, and processes related to data management, quality, access, and security are followed in all environments. Create repeatable data management processes within Data Governance & Data Ingestion space • Work with stakeholders to understand, prioritise, and document business and technical needs, and to ensure alignment with DG strategy • Support the implementation of a new data lineage, metadata & reference data management framework and technology solution in partnership with IT. Utilise this solution to identify, initiate and champion improvements in data quality, sustainability and security. • Support the requirement to ensure Endeavour data assets are classified, certified and prioritised to enable our community of users to trust the data they use in their decision making processes. • Work to uplift the group-wide Endeavour data culture and capabilities, alongside other members of the data and Analytics team, • Contribute to the management of a portfolio of data governance initiatives for Endeavour. This includes the development of concepts, business cases, project planning, and delivery. • Improvement in Endeavour data governance framework capability maturity assessment. • Stay abreast of regulatory change and how this may impact on data governance and assist in appropriate responses across Endeavour • Data governance adoption and embedding (governance forums attendance, deliverables, outcomes). • Strength of critical relationships with the group data governance team and Endeavour Stakeholders. • Project initiatives delivered on time, within budget, to agreed scope, with positive stakeholder feedback  What You'll Need To Succeed • 5+ years of experience in a data governance analyst and/or project management role in a data or risk related role within a large organisation or consulting firm. • Experience in implementing frameworks, policies, processes, and transformational agendas in large organisations. • Hands on experience using data governance tools including; Collibra or Ataccama is an added advantage. • Hands-on experience managing enterprise cloud data platform including; GCP or Azure (bigquery, data loss prevention, data catalogue & cloud IAM) an added advantage • Demonstrated experience working in an Agile project delivery model environment. • Eagerness to work in a fun, dynamic, and fast-paced environment. • Exposure to data governance, data information security practices, and cloud databases.  What's in it for you? • Excellent remuneration package and flexible working in every sense. We value our people • Everyday Rewards plus card - access exclusive employee discounts across Woolworths, BigW and Endeavour Group brands (BWS, Dan Murphy’s etc) and 50% off food at ALH venues. • Our innovative ways of working include headspace mornings once a month (no meetings company-wide), opportunity to partner alongside bright minds and genuine investment in leading technologies • Paid learning & development opportunities • Career progression to help you realise your potential. As our business grows so do the opportunities for our people • Access to our Endeavour Group Employee Share Scheme! • Wine education: Bronze, Silver & Gold certifications • Work with an industry-leading team and be a part of one of the most exciting retail transformations in Australia  Grow with Endeavour Group  Bring your spark. Tap into our spirit. That’s the power of Endeavour.  If you want to experience the diverse spirit of drinks and hospitality businesses, here you can tap into Australia’s leading brands including Dan Murphy’s, BWS, ALH, Pinnacle Drinks, Endeavour X and more.  If you have a passion for connecting people with products they love, here you can join an industry that’s deeply embedded in the way Australians socialise, unwind and celebrate.  If you want access to a breadth of career opportunities, here you can enjoy a path that travels between diverse roles and businesses within the Group.  If you’re already asking ‘what’s next for me’ and our industry, here you’ll thrive.  If you want to bring your full self to doing fulfilling work, here you’ll find a culture that’s welcoming, inclusive and responsible.  If you are looking for flexibility, here we encourage our team members to work in ways that meets their work / life commitments and supports their wellbeing.  Come grow with Endeavour where we are passionate about our purpose of creating a more sociable future together, and leaving a positive imprint on our team members and the communities we serve.  If you meet a number of the requirements, but not all, we encourage you to submit your application.  You can learn more about working with us on LinkedIn or via www.wowcareers.com.au #EDG #EGL  Our Talent Acquisition Team and Hiring Leaders kindly request no unsolicited resumes or approaches from Recruitment Agencies. Endeavour Group is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes.
job_description.485: Job Description  Job Title:  Senior Data Scientist - Mathematical and Statistical Modeling with Bayesian Optimisation Expertise  About Us  Join a trailblazing leader in the world of programmatic advertising, dedicated to delivering highly targeted and effective advertising solutions to their clients.  We are seeking a skilled and passionate Data Scientist with expertise in mathematical and statistical modeling, as well as Bayesian optimisation and diagnostics, to join this dynamic team. If you are enthusiastic about harnessing data-driven insights, Bayesian optimisation, and diagnostics to optimize programmatic advertising campaigns, we want to hear from you!  Job Description  As a Data Scientist specialising in mathematical and statistical modeling, with a focus on Bayesian optimisation and diagnostics, you will play a pivotal role in refining our advertising strategies through data analysis and predictive modeling.  Key Responsibilities • Utilise mathematical and statistical modeling techniques, including Bayesian optimisation, to analyse large-scale advertising datasets. • Develop predictive models to optimise programmatic advertising campaigns, including ad targeting, bidding strategies, and ad creatives, while leveraging Bayesian techniques for efficiency. • Collaborate closely with data engineers and analysts to gather, clean, and preprocess advertising data. • Assess and validate the accuracy and reliability of predictive models, using Bayesian diagnostics for model evaluation. • Translate complex modeling insights, Bayesian optimisation results, and diagnostic findings into actionable recommendations for campaign optimization. • Present findings and insights to both technical and non-technical stakeholders using data visualization and clear reports.  Qualifications • Bachelor's, Master's, or Ph.D. in a quantitative field such as Mathematics, Statistics, Data Science, or related disciplines. • Demonstrated experience (3+ years) as a Data Scientist or similar role with a specific focus and expertise in Bayesian methodology and diagnostics. • Proficient in programming languages such as Python, SQL etc • Strong command of data analysis and machine learning libraries (e.g., pandas, scikit-learn, TensorFlow, PyTorch). • Understanding of statistical concepts and techniques, including A/B testing, attribution modeling, and customer segmentation. • Ideally experience with programmatic advertising platforms, tools, and technologies, though not mandatory. • Exceptional problem-solving skills and the ability to tackle complex, open-ended challenges. • Excellent communication and collaboration skills for effective teamwork with cross-functional teams. • Detail-oriented with a passion for continuous learning and improvement.  Benefits • Competitive salary and performance-based bonuses. • Flexible work hours and options for remote work. • Professional development opportunities and training programs. • An innovative and collaborative work environment. • The chance to work on cutting-edge programmatic advertising campaigns that impact the industry.  If you would like to hear more about this position or other Data Science related opportunities, please call Greg - 0487848404 or email me your resume greg@theonset.com.au
job_description.486: About GoSol  GOSOL, IT consulting and Staffing organization, can help you enhance Technology, Digital, Project and Business Transformation. Guided by integrity and trust, we believe in offering an unparalleled experience as your Tech of choice. For businesses, this means providing you with access to the quality solution.  Find us at - https://gosol.com.au/  Job Description  In this role, you will design, build, and maintain batch and real-time data pipelines on On-premises and cloud platforms to ingest data from the various source systems.  Post ingestion, you will be responsible for integrating the data asset in the data model and making the data ready for consumption for the end-user use cases and downstream applications. • Key Responsibilities* Enhance, optimize and maintain existing data ingestion, transformation and extraction pipelines and assets built for reporting and analytics on Cloud (Azure + Databricks) and Big Data Cloudera platform. Work with the Product Owner to understand the priorities and OKRs for the quarter and gather detailed requirements from the initiative owners or program sponsor as per the Epics planned to be delivered in the quarter. Build new and optimized data pipelines, assets to meet the end-user requirements. The Data pipelines must adhere to all the architecture, design and engineering principles. Design the data pipelines and assets to meet non-functional requirements (Security, reliability, performance, maintainability, scalability, and usability). Most importantly, they should be designed to be to keep the compute cost low on Cloud. Data wrangling, Data profiling and data analysis for new datasets ingested from source systems and derived/built from existing datasets with the on-premises and cloud-native tools Functionally understand the Data assets working with various SMEs and apply the transformation rules required to build the target data asset. • Experience and Qualifications* Bachelor's degree in maths, statistics, computer science, information management, finance or economics 7+ years' experience working in Data Engineering and Warehousing. Experience in building fully automated end to end data pipelines using on-premise or cloud based data platforms. Cloud experience Azure based analytics/reporting pipeline Hands on delivery of solutions for Reporting and Analytics use cases. Hands On with advanced SQL on Data Warehouse , Big Data and Data Bricks Experience in data profiling, source-target mappings, ETL development, SQL optimisation, testing and implementation Experience in working effectively on Cloud DWs Knowledgeable in Big Data tools like Spark (python/scala), Hive, Impala, Hue and storage (e.g. HDFS, HBase) Knowledgeable in CICD processes BitBucket/GitHub, Jenkins, Nexus etc. Knowledgeable managing structured and unstructured data types like json, xml, avro Track record of implementing databases and data access middleware and high-volume batch and (near) real-time processing  Only candidates with valid work rights of Australia will be considered. Desirable Skills • Knowledge of Microsoft Azure technologies, and SQL Server Integration Services. • Experience in development of ETL standards and Metadata management. • Experience in SQL Server and Oracle databases. • SQL Scripting and software development capability: e.g., T-SQL, Python, PowerShell, etc.
job_description.488: A fantastic opportunity in a reputable company to work as a Financial Data Analyst  A fantastic opportunity in a reputable company to work as a Financial Data Analyst  About You  You must: • have a relevant degree qualification. • have excellent communication skills, both written and spoken. • have the necessary technical and soft skills to perform the job. • be committed to a career in the industry. • be able to work full-time.  Job Duties • Managing master data, including creation, updates, and deletion. • Analysing current and past financial data • Looking at current financial performance and identifying trends • Preparing reports on the above information and communicating the insights of these reports to the wider business • Suggesting budgets and improvements based on the above information • Developing financial models and providing financial forecasts • Developing initiatives and policies that may improve financial growth • Exploring different investment opportunities • Provide quality assurance of imported data, working with quality assurance analysts if necessary. • Consulting with the management team to develop long-term commercial plans • Commissioning and decommissioning of data sets. • Processing confidential data and information according to guidelines. • Helping develop reports and analysis. • Managing and designing the reporting environment, including data sources, security, and metadata. • Supporting the data warehouse in identifying and revising reporting requirements. • Supporting initiatives for data integrity and normalization. • Assessing tests and implementing new or upgraded software and assisting with strategic decisions on new systems. • Generating reports from single or multiple systems. • Troubleshooting the reporting database environment and reports. • Evaluating changes and updates to source production systems. • Training end-users on new reports and dashboards. As a Data Scientist specialising ML & Forecasting, you will play a key role in leveraging data to develop predictive models, drive insights, and enhance decision-making processes..  Key Responsibilities:  Develop and implement machine learning algorithms and models to solve complex business problems. Build predictive models and time series forecasting solutions to support decision-making and planning processes. Continuously monitor and fine-tune models for optimal performance. Utilize MS SQL Server, Python, and R for data extraction, transformation, and loading (ETL) processes. Optimize data storage and retrieval for efficient analysis. Strong programming skills in Python and R for data analysis, model development, and automation. Experience with Gitlab CI/CD or similar continuous integration/continuous deployment tools. Expertise in data modelling, governance, and documentation. Ability to map and document complex data processes and workflows. Excellent problem-solving and analytical skills. Strong communication and collaboration skills. Self-motivated with the ability to work independently and meet project deadlines.
job_description.490: We are looking for a talented and experienced manager to lead a high-calibre and growing team in planning, implementing and managing the ACMA's data governance lifecycle. Your mandate encompasses the full range of data governance activities including data quality, privacy, security and compliance policies, supporting analytics, data usage and metadata management.  You will be in your element managing a multi-faceted change plan which will include: • providing data governance support for the progressive deployment of advanced analytics including artificial intelligence and machine learning • an evolving 'hub-and-spoke' model with a focus on building data governance capability at all levels of the organisation • embedding and integrating data governance into a fast-paced whole-of-Agency digital transformation program • working across government to promote and support data sharing opportunities.  You will thrive working in close partnership with a broad range of internal and external stakeholders.  This role is perfectly suited for a hands-on and pragmatic senior leader with great people skills and who is motivated to apply their deep subject matter expertise to lifting organisational capability.  To be eligible for employment with the ACMA, applicants must be an Australian citizen.
