job_description.492: About Agoda  Agoda is an online travel booking platform for accommodations, flights, and more. We build and deploy cutting-edge technology that connects travelers with more than 3.6 million accommodations globally. Based in Asia and part of Booking Holdings, our 6,000+ employees representing 90+ nationalities foster a work environment rich in diversity, creativity, and collaboration. We innovate through a culture of experimentation and ownership, enhancing the ability for our customers to experience the world.  Get to Know Our Team  The Data department oversees all of Agoda’s data-related requirements. Our ultimate goal is to enable and increase the use of data in the company through creative approaches and the implementation of powerful resources such as operational and analytical databases, queue systems, BI tools, and data science technology. We hire the brightest minds from around the world to take on this challenge and equip them with the knowledge and tools that contribute to their personal growth and success while supporting our company’s culture of diversity and experimentation. The role the Data team plays at Agoda is critical as business users, product managers, engineers, and many others rely on us to empower their decision making. We are equally dedicated to our customers by improving their search experience with faster results and protecting them from any fraudulent activities. Data is interesting only when you have enough of it, and we have plenty. This is what drives up the challenge as part of the Data department, but also the reward.  The Opportunity  As a Senior Data Analyst, you will be driving our features research in our fraud domain, build experiments to test your hypothesis, and get your hands on experience in ML.  This role will allow you to communicate your findings with the different stakeholders (Product, Devs, and Business) and make an impact at Agoda.  In This Role, You’ll Get to • Apply your expertise in quantitative analysis, data mining, and the presentation of data to understand fraud, how it relates to Agoda’s strategy and products, and how to prevent it • Build advanced predictive models to understand the impact of specific fraudulent behaviors, trends, and patterns • Work closely with cross-functional teams of data and backend engineers, analysts, user researchers, product managers, and designers who are passionate about Agoda’s success • Understand how user fraud affects other consumers of our data, including insights and feature teams, and work across the data landscape to minimize impact and drive influence wherever possible • Communicate data-informed insights and recommendations to key stakeholders, engineering and product partners  What You’ll Need To Succeed • 3+ years of experience in a data driven role in payment fraud detection and prevention , with an understanding of the impact that fraud prevention has on other areas in the company where business and product decisions are made • Extensive experience in detecting and analyzing fraud at the individual transaction level as well as across large data sets • Bachelor’s Degree in science, computer science, statistics, economics, mathematics, a similar quantitative discipline, or equivalent industry experience • Coding skills for analytics and data manipulation (SQL, R, Python, Pandas, Scala) • Experience with data visualization tools such as Tableau or your weapon of choice • Strong analytical and statistical analysis skills in order to extract insights and recommendations • Fluent in English with strong communication skills (both written and verbal)  It’s Great If You Have • Knowledge of machine learning algorithms including classifiers, clustering algorithms, and anomaly detection is a plus  #sanfrancisco #washdc #sydney #london #tokyo #amsterdam #munich #berlin #toronto #vancouver #moscow #dublin #seoul #hcmc #telaviv #taipei #ENG #IT #4  Equal Opportunity Employer  At Agoda, we pride ourselves on being a company represented by people of all different backgrounds and orientations. We prioritize attracting diverse talent and cultivating an inclusive environment that encourages collaboration and innovation. Employment at Agoda is based solely on a person’s merit and qualifications. We are committed to providing equal employment opportunity regardless of sex, age, race, color, national origin, religion, marital status, pregnancy, sexual orientation, gender identity, disability, citizenship, veteran or military status, and other legally protected characteristics.  We will keep your application on file so that we can consider you for future vacancies and you can always ask to have your details removed from the file. For more details please read our privacy policy .  To all recruitment agencies: Agoda does not accept third party resumes. Please do not send resumes to our jobs alias, Agoda employees or any other organization location. Agoda is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes.
job_description.493: Prior experience as an analyst or data scientist, working directly with database-level data, whether formally or self-taught.  The company is seeking a Data Scientist to build with us and our community. Come contribute to our growing body of tools, research, and IP that make blockchain and crypto data more accessible.  Who You Are  You love data and stats. You know some formal statistics, ML, and data exploration techniques, even better if you’ve done network analysis.  You love crypto and DeFi, know the difference between hodling, staking, and yield farming, and you have used both Ethereum and other chains.  You are self-directed. You are insatiably curious. You can be counted on to work through a project, commit and go deep while seeking help when you need it, and propel it forward without hand-holding.  You are fastidious and meticulous in your work. You will put in the time to make an order from chaos. You’ve looked into the eye of Sauron and lived to make a graph. You don’t mind doing the “grunt work” to build up to the full picture, or go as low as it takes? Muckraking? More like fun-making.  You're creative and you aren't afraid to be wrong.  ❄️ You are super comfortable in SQL-like databases (we use Snowflake)  ®️ You are intimately familiar with R for analysis, exploration, and model-building. And you have an opinion about data. table vs dplyr. Python is OK too, but we have a lot of R code, so you need to be comfortable there.  ️ You take pride in your code. It's readable, functional, and reproducible. You commit regularly for all the right reasons.  You can describe a complex problem (or solution) in a way that doesn't put people to sleep and doesn't leave them scratching their heads.  What You'll Work On  Work directly with the company's community, our internal analytics & data platform teams.  Collaborate with other data scientists and analysts to explore, visualize, and validate our data.  Work closely with our marketing team to share what we learn with the world, and educate anyone who wants to learn more.  Support the efforts of our product teams to help transform our apps into more data-driven, web3-connected, powerful experiences for our growing base of thousands of users.  Desired Experience  Experience with Crypto/Blockchain is a requirement.  Prior experience as an analyst or data scientist, working directly with database-level data, whether formally or self-taught.  At least 2 years in a formal data science role, ideally working primarily in R  Experience working with product & marketing teams, developers, and data engineers  Make sure to follow us here to get our most live jobs https://www.linkedin.com/company/cryptorecruit  Cryptorecruit are the worlds leading specialist recruiter for the blockchain/Cryptocurrency industry. We recruit positions from CEO,CTO, Project Manager, Solidity developer, frontend and Backend Blockchain developers to marketing/sales and customer service roles. Please browse our website and at www.cryptorecruit.com to search all our job vacancies.
job_description.494: Why join us? • #1 performance agency in APAC according to Campaign Asia and voted Australia's best Performance Agency by AOY awards 2022 • One of the largest global performance marketing agencies, 3,000+ experts in 68 countries to connect with • Access to progressive leave policies such as Leave+, birthday, anniversary, and leading parental leave policies • A hybrid working model with opportunities for global transfers, internal secondments, and travel. • Reprise for Good: 2x paid volunteering days per year for all APAC team • L&D programs for leadership development, technical courses, and certifications • Wellness programs including access to an EAP and wellness coaching • Agency perks, early finish Fridays, culture club, breakfast, health and wellbeing initiatives.  As the Analytics Manager you will have a key influence in delivering Reprises Analytics Product offering. You will deliver best in class analytics and statistical principles to obtain and collect data across key platforms including Excel, Big Query, GA4, GA360, GTM and Adobe Analytics. This role will partner with our Performance Directors, and our other Product (Craft) teams, to ensure that our clients receive comprehensive data collection plans, streamlined tagging implementation services, strategy analysis and data visualisations to meet their strategic objectives.  About the role: • Work with the Analytics Lead to design and deliver innovative solutions for clients from scoping to execution • Implementation and testing of tags through tag management platforms (GTM) and providing recommendations around the best practises • Ensure client’s data is reliable, actionable and valuable across client business • Managing project timelines and work with Performance Directors to ensure timely and quality work is delivered to clients. • Keeping up to date with industry trends and providing internal POV (Point of View) pieces • Lead client engagement to scope analytical solutions including but not limited to custom measurement frameworks, attribution modelling, predictive modelling, dashboarding, etc. • Leverage statistical models to analyse and determine media/marketing and business performance projections to inform business investment decisions • Assisting in new business pitches/presales activities • Design and deliver with the Analytics Lead, internal training & development programs so that we’re leveraging efficient/best practice usage of analytical tools. • Closely collaborate with other crafts (products) like SEO, Media, and Marketing to make a stronger business impact.  About you: • 3+ years proven experience as a data analyst in a commercial environment • Strong analytical skills with the ability to collect, organise, analyse, and disseminate significant amounts of information with attention to detail and accuracy • Essential experience in GA360, GA4, GTM (Google Tag Manager), Google Data Studio • Big Query and GCP experience will be an additional advantage. • Good to have thinking around attribution and modelling (beneficial but not required.) • Experience with implementing, auditing, and using GMP (Google Marketing Platform) stack. • Experience with Adobe Analytics, SQL, R and/or Python is beneficial though not necessary  Who we are:  Reprise Digital is the world’s largest performance marketing network. We provide comprehensive digital solutions by reimagining performance marketing in line with customer behaviours so that our audiences are interacting with personalised and dynamic content.  Reprise Australia is an equal-opportunity employer and is committed to building a diverse and inclusive workplace. Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples are encouraged to apply.
job_description.495: About Blunomy:  Blunomy is an international strategy consulting firm, dedicated to accelerating the move towards a regenerative society that is decarbonised, circular and inclusive. We do this by partnering with those in the energy supply chain, as well as financial institutions, business and entrepreneurs to ensure the transition of their resources from brown to green.  We have been operating since 2007, previously trading as Enea Consulting, and continue to expand our international team of Blunomists. Our high performing, multidisciplinary team are based across 6 offices: Melbourne, Sydney, Paris, Singapore, Hong Kong and London. We come from a wide variety of backgrounds and experiences, are open minded and focused on the future, united by shared values and are passionate about sustainable development and energy access.  We are looking for a passionate, engaging and ambitious Manager, Data Science to join our team in either Melbourne or Sydney. We invite all of those who want to break the mold to join us to get change done!  About the role:  Data analytics in the energy and climate space is growing at an incredible rate. Blunomy provides data-based solutions to support the energy industry, financial institutions and supply chains through their digitisation, decentralisation and decarbonisation transitions. Our tools support improved energy market operability, automation and planning. We are also developing digital solutions that better measure impact and transition speed, to help decarbonise financial resources.  We are looking for someone who is passionate about energy, climate change and data analytics to do-well-and-do-good by delivering data science products to crack transition challenges. As a Manager, you will be responsible for: • Identify and pursue new business opportunities for the data science team • Managing the end-to-end delivery of the project • Engaging and communicating with the client • Anticipating and managing project risks, timelines, and budget • Managing and leading analysts and senior analysts  In this setting, you will be exposed to the diversity of current energy challenges, leveraging your data and analytical skills to address them. We are always growing the products we deliver but over the last 12 months we have delivered: • Load forecasting: model and predict the evolution of the load on the electrical network. Use machine learning, data analytics and a fair amount of software development to forecast long-term energy consumption, daily energy profiles and Distributed Energy Resources (Electric Vehicles, Battery, Solar PV). • PV connections approval tool: dynamically model the energy network bringing together power flow modelling and machine learning to determine the PV hosting capacity of the local area. Used in production to approve hundreds of PV connection requests a day. • Vegetation management using LiDAR: collect three‑dimensional images of the local network gathered by drone or helicopter. Use machine learning and geometric models to detect and manage vegetation near powerlines. • Bushfire risk modelling: model and compute the network‑related bushfire risk based on fault ignition likelihood. Calculate the consequences of bushfires such as property damage or agricultural loss. • Low-Voltage network mapping: identify errors within the current mapping of the low-voltage network, especially targeting customers whom connection to the network has not been properly recorded. This was performed using outlier detection with out-of-bag predictors.  Depending on the objectives, projects will entail tasks of varying nature. Your first focus will be on projects requiring data analytics capabilities.  About you:  We are looking for a motivated, experienced and passionate person to join our growing team. The right person will have some of the following, and a willingness and ability to learn the rest. • You are passionate about the energy transition and climate change, with a strong interest for energy, environment and/or sustainable development. • Familiarity with Australian energy sector policy, regulation and commercial trends and market dynamics • Knowledge of key industry players and competitors, and demonstrated experience in business development, with a proven track record to identifying, pursuing and winning new opportunities within the sector. • Background in data science or data analytics • Bachelor or Master’s degree in a relevant discipline such Computing Science, Statistics, Mathematics, Energy Systems or Engineering • Functional skills: good verbal and written communication, networking skills, critical thinking, comparative analysis and synthesis capabilities, respect of time constraints, intellectual rigor, curiosity, open mindedness, empathy and team spirit. • Technical skills: strong analytical skills, efficient use of MS Excel and PowerPoint. • Project management skills: proactive, autonomous and flexible attitude, organisational, planning and time management skills, proven experience of stakeholder engagement and management, both external and internal as a leader and builder of teams. • Fluent in English  To be eligible to apply for this position, candidates must be either an Australian citizen or have full working rights in Australia.  Location: Sydney CBD (Hybrid)  Salary: Depending on experience  Work type: Full Time, starting ASAP  Application Process:  In your application process you will be asked the following questions: • Do you have full working rights in Australia? • How many years experience do you have working in the Australian electricity sector? • How many years experience do you have in data analytics roles? • How many years experience do you have in technical sales/business development? • Do you have (consulting) project management experience? If so, how many years? • What are your salary expectations?
job_description.496: EY is a global professional services organization providing advisory, assurance, tax and transaction services. Our Data & Analytics team are looking to hire a Technical Business Analyst.  Key Duties Of The Role Are  Be a part of one of our successful delivery teams and get an opportunity to move into a more consultative role working across various data environments and helping our clients solve their business problems with data.  Be responsible for creating requirement specifications, analyzing requirements, creating visual models, facilitating elicitation sessions and digging around in the data when needed. job_description.497: You are a curious and enthusiastic individual with a true passion for Data.  We are a value-driven team of analytical consultants who translate analytics into meaningful, tangible and actionable commercial solutions for our clients.  Together we can harness the power of analytics and technology to identify solutions for our customers and communities to help build a brighter future and really make a difference. On a day to day basis you will: • Lead a team of analysts and consultants to design and deliver analytical solutions across multiple projects. • Accountable for quality project deliverables and team management. • Supporting the innovation and proto-typing of new product solutions. • Translating insights into meaningful, actionable outcomes for clients. • Engaging with clients to support their execution and implementation of analytical solutions we deliver. • Application of commercial acumen, intellect, business and client understanding to make considered decisions or come to practical conclusions where there is natural ambiguity. • Provide expert knowledge to clients and make recommendations to create value for the client and enhance the relationship between the client and CommBank iQ. • Connecting with and leveraging SMEs across the business to develop the best solution for the client. • Building a team culture of collaboration and support, with career development opportunities in data and analytics. We are open to working with the right candidate to fill any skill gaps during your journey at CommBank. • Proven experience in an analytics environment, within data analytics or data science. • Experience and knowledge of technical analytics, including data preparation, foundational analytics concepts, model development and model training. • High standards of coding experience in SQL (required) and modelling experience in R/Python (desirable). • Commercial acumen to understand business needs and be able suggest the commercial impacts of different analytics solutions or approaches. • Ability to proactively identify, understand and translate strategic business needs for new and existing clients to build lasting partnerships. • Ability to translate complex analytics, insights and or outcomes into presentations written to senior stakeholders. • Experience in project management and leadership, including effective delegation and management of multi-skilled team. • Tertiary qualifications in engineering, mathematics, actuarial studies, statistics, physics, or a related discipline. job_description.499: Job Description  How will I help?  The Group Tech Analytics team supports multiple data analytics platforms that ingest data from a wide range of operational data stores and make it available to end consumers. Unlocking the value of this data is the key to the Westpac transformation journey to a digital bank as well as becoming one of the world’s greatest service companies.  This role is a combination of data architect in the planning of strategic data products/assets and as of technical data modeller for the design and realisation of data Products/Assets over progressive releases which enable higher degree or reusability/scalability, easy maintenance which are highly performing. Working with business user representatives to translate their requirements into robust data structures in both the Westpac Hadoop/Azure Platform as well as the Enterprise Data Warehouse.  Key responsibilities include: • Experience in documenting and designing conceptual, logical, and physical data models with high quality definition. • Publish models using standardised methods and create bespoke communication packs to convey the model content to diverse audiences. • Facilitate workshops to capture the data requirements and design a data model to support the business process/use case • Assess example source content against target models to ensure integrity and alignment with use cases • Communicate the concepts and rules of the data model design and support model users to achieve their goals  What’s in it for me?  You’ll play a significant part of the future of a business that has been around for 200 years. Our purpose is of creating better futures together. So, we’ll back you in the development of your career, internal career prospects, and flexible working. You’ll also keep learning to grown, backed by a fantastic team of people with a can-do, supportive structure. Whatever shape your family takes, we offer generous paid and unpaid parental leave for your nominated primary and support carers. This includes leave to organise adoptions, surrogacy, and foster care arrangements. And we continue to pay your super contributions while you take all the time you need to get your new family settled.  What do I need?  The successful candidate will have: • Logical and physical data modelling in complex environments – spanning Hadoop/Azure and Teradata • Familiarity with Erwin Data Modeler tool, model mart the Web Portal feature. • Experience in banking/financial industry models and designing Data Products, Data Assets and Enterprise data models. • Publish efficient Physical data models based on target data layer which could be Structured, Semi-Structured or Unstructured using Teradata/Hortonworks and Azure Synapse analytics. • Proficient in data analysis, data profiling using SQL or other tools. • Understanding of e2e processing of a data in an analytics environment  What is it like to work there?  We aim to provide one big, supportive team to help us achieve our purpose of creating better futures together. With us you'll discover new ways of working, and an exciting range of roles to showcase your skills. As an equal opportunity employer, we’re proud to have created a culture where people can be their best, in an environment that values diversity and flexibility and one where everyone belongs.  How do I apply?  Start here. Just click on the APPLY button.  As part of our commitment to creating a diverse and inclusive workplace, this role is open to experienced candidates seeking a discussion around workplace flexibility. We invite candidates of all ages, genders, sexual orientation, cultural backgrounds, people with disability, neurodiverse individuals, and Indigenous Australians to apply. If an adjustment is required to assist you during our recruitment process, please email talentacquisition@westpac.com.au  Do you need reasonable adjustments during the recruitment process?  At Westpac we are committed to providing a supportive culture and creating inclusive and accessible workplaces, branches, products and services for our customers, employees, and community.  We can provide reasonable adjustments for individuals with disability and/or neurodiversity. If you require an adjustment to be made during the recruitment process at any stage, please call 1800 655 592 Option 1.2 or email talentacquisition@westpac.com.au

Our business has more than 1,600 retail stores and 340 hotels powered by a team of 28,000 people. Our brands include BWS, Dan Murphy’s, Jimmy Brings, Langtons, Shorty’s Liquor, Pinnacle Drinks and ALH hotels Our purpose is to create a more sociable future, together. We work as one team to contribute to the communities we serve and collaborate with our partners to help build a better industry. We recognise how important our people are in helping us to achieve our ambition and we champion individuality and value fairness, inclusion and diversity.  The Advanced Analytics Team is an Enterprise function within Endeavour, with capabilities across data governance & privacy, data engineering & platforms, data analytics and data science. We are a passionate team of data enthusiasts with a mission to empower Endeavour to achieve its ambitions through data driven insights.  About Us  Endeavour Group runs Australia’s leading retail drinks and licenced hotel network across Australia. We are an ASX50 business with more than 1,600 retail stores and 340 hotels powered by a team of 28,000 people. Our brands include BWS, Dan Murphy’s, Jimmy Brings, Langtons, Shorty’s Liquor, Pinnacle Drinks and ALH hotels Our purpose is to create a more sociable future, together. We’re all about bringing people together to create great experiences and memorable moments. We do the right thing - build our business sustainably, act responsibly and embrace technology. We work as one team to contribute to the communities we serve and collaborate with our partners to help build a better industry. We recognise how important our people are in helping us to achieve our ambition and we champion individuality and value fairness, inclusion and diversity.  The Role The Analytics & Reporting Manager - Transformation is responsible for bringing our analytics and reporting standards and best practice to the Transformation program. The role sits in the Advanced Analytics team, however for day to day delivery is embedded in the Transformation program. This role will work closely with Advanced Analytics to understand our standards and will work closely with the Transformation stream leads to understand their needs and then to recruit, allocate resources and guide delivery to our standards, ensuring that delivery meets the transformation program requirements and is in line with our Advanced Analytics enterprise architecture and standards.  This is a hands-on role, where you will form strong trusted relationships with both the Transformation program and Advanced Analytics team.  About You  You are a capability expert in the analytics and reporting domain and act as a servant leader for your team. You will coach, mentor, support and upskill the team to ensure that we have the capability necessary to deliver value through the delivery teams.  You value quality and will drive the adherence to standards to ensure quality delivery of the capability across the transformation program.  You’re customer focused and passionate about being part of a tribe of great people and you actively contribute to your workplace community.  With a growth mindset, you orient around doing what’s meaningful, purposeful and delivers value. You’re excited about being part of a data-led transformation at one of Australia’s biggest companies.  You’re curious and empathetic. You have an eye for the bigger picture while also ensuring the details are in order. You deal with complexity by collaborating with colleagues, listening to customers, testing ideas and continuously learning. You take authorship for what you create.  Direct reports You will have a team of analytics and reporting resources (e.g. data engineers, data analysts) who are embedded across the various transformation streams, ensuring that the programs deliver their analytics and reporting requirements in line with our Enterprise standards and platforms.  A day in the life as an Analytics and Reporting Manager @ Endeavour • Analytics and reporting business partner in the transformation program, understanding the analytics needs of the programs and supporting those programs to deliver these capabilities in line with our enterprise architecture and standards • Recruitment, line management, delivery team allocation and capability uplift, where required, of the data engineering, analytics and reporting resources, providing skills to build data, analytics and reporting deliverables on our Enterprise Data Platform • Team line management (including performance reviews), career pathway support and mentoring • Actively coach, mentor, support & upskill team to improve performance, reinforce continuous improvement and guide career progression • Ensure that team are delivering value in their assigned delivery teams • Understand our Advanced Analytics standards, tools and platforms and upskill your team to follow those standards • Maintain connection with Advanced Analytics COE and Practices/Chapters, ensuring alignment with our Enterprise Data Architecture, Standards, Platforms and tools • Remove impediments from the team • Recruit, onboard and offboard the team to/from Endeavour Group • Stay abreast of work allocated to the team to understand improvement possibilities and/or sharing between team members, and challenges facing team members • Facilitate discussion to resolve conflict within the team members • Set objectives for the team and track/report using defined standards • Reinforce Endeavour’s Agile & Scrum values and principles • Responsible for ensuring Data Engineering, Analytics & Reporting chapter norms and standards are understood and followed by their members • Enables close cooperation across all Practices & Chapters in Endeavour • Participate when required Inception workshops, to enable decomposition and planning • Coach team members in the capability discipline to be empowered and self-organized • Assists transformation streams when they require recruitment for Data engineering and analytics capabilities  What You'll Need To Suceed • 10+ years experience in data engineering, analytics or a similar capability • 2+ years leadership capability with a proven track record leading high performance teams • Advanced knowledge of data and analytics industry frameworks and professional standards • Experience in Technology delivery, waterfall and agile • An in-depth understanding of common databases and data structures • Experience working with big data cloud platforms (Azure, Google Cloud Platform, AWS) • Experience working with visualisation tools such as Tableau • Experience delivering technology or analytics projects in a large, complex enterprise  What's in it for you? • Excellent remuneration package and flexible working in every sense. We value our people • Everyday Rewards plus card - access exclusive employee discounts across Woolworths, BigW and Endeavour Group brands (BWS, Dan Murphy’s etc) and 50% off food at ALH venues. • Our innovative ways of working include headspace mornings once a month (no meetings company-wide), opportunity to partner alongside bright minds and genuine investment in leading technologies • Paid learning & development opportunities • Career progression to help you realise your potential. As our business grows so do the opportunities for our people • Access to our Endeavour Group Employee Share Scheme! • Wine education: Bronze, Silver & Gold certifications • Work with an industry-leading team and be a part of one of the most exciting retail transformations in Australia  Grow with Endeavour Group Bring your spark. Tap into our spirit. That’s the power of Endeavour.  If you want to experience the diverse spirit of drinks and hospitality businesses, here you can tap into Australia’s leading brands including Dan Murphy’s, BWS, ALH, Pinnacle Drinks, Endeavour X and more.  If you have a passion for connecting people with products they love, here you can join an industry that’s deeply embedded in the way Australians socialise, unwind and celebrate.  If you want access to a breadth of career opportunities, here you can enjoy a path that travels between diverse roles and businesses within the Group.  If you’re already asking ‘what’s next for me’ and our industry, here you’ll thrive.  If you want to bring your full self to doing fulfilling work, here you’ll find a culture that’s welcoming, inclusive and responsible.  If you are looking for flexibility, here we encourage our team members to work in ways that meets their work / life commitments and supports their wellbeing.  Come grow with Endeavour where we are passionate about our purpose of creating a more sociable future together, and leaving a positive imprint on our team members and the communities we serve. You can learn more about working with us on LinkedIn or via www.wowcareers.com.au/endeavour/ #EGL #EDG Our Talent Acquisition Team and Hiring Leaders kindly request no unsolicited resumes or approaches from Recruitment Agencies. job_description.505: Innovating. Empowering. Delighting. Join the Intuit Australia & Rest of World team as a Staff Business Data Analyst to delight small businesses & accountants through QuickBooks and our ecosystem of attached products.  Intuit HQ is based in Mountain View California where we have been in operations since 1983. We are proud to share that Intuit has consistently appeared in Fortune’s top 50 Best companies to work for over the last 5 years. We believe in the power of the individual. The power to do more. To make more. To be more.  The Data Analytics team is looking for a talented Staff Data Analyst to drive GTM initiatives across the Australian & Rest of World businesses. You should be a driven fast learner and high achiever with a passion to continuously learn, grow and deliver well in a high performance and flexible hybrid working environment characterized by speed, collaboration, creativity and fun.  As a Staff Analyst, you will work closely with our GTM Teams to develop insights, lead experimentation, and drive key business results. You will take complex concepts and communicate them to both technical and non-technical leaders in order to effect change for our customers. You will be an instrumental leader in shaping the strategy, working across Marketing, Sales, Intuit AI and Data Engineering to drive an integrated plan to grow and scale our Advisor business.  This is an amazing opportunity to join our passionate team using cutting edge technology and the newest trends in analytics to innovate and challenge the way things are done. You’ll be exposed to some of the brightest minds in the tech industry around the globe and empowered to make your own mark!If this sounds like you and you’re ready to join our growth journey, we’d love to hear from you! Responsibilities  This role is a critical partner, leading data and analytics for complex strategic businessinitiatives. • You will be responsible for working across functional groups, self generating hypotheses via data and clearly communicating subsequent insights to senior leaders that drive business impact in a fun team environment. • You will use your business domain knowledge in combination with data and analytics to lead projects, including market/category insights, experiment design, creating dashboards, measuring business results, and analysing customer behaviour. • You will also utilise multiple analytics tools and techniques based on business requirements. Analytics expertise includes (but are not limited to) performance variance testing, funnel/journey reporting, marketing attribution models, A/B and multivariate testing, ROI measurement, statistical analysis,segmentation,and ML modeling (supervised and unsupervised). • You will also rely on strong abilities to access data from various sources, such as relational databases, distributed data sources and, third party data capture tools. • You will create analysis using visualisation tools (e.g. Tableau) to share customized insights with business and analytics partners. • You can prototype data sets used in reporting and analysis. You can also use knowledge of A/B testing to design, implement, and interpret test results using common frameworks. In addition, you will keep a pulse on emerging technologies (such as data exploration, data modeling, visualization and testing) and statistical methods that would make your work more scalable or more efficient for Intuit. • You will marshal resources and seek commitment across multiple functions (such as business stakeholders, data and analytics experts, and IT infrastructure partners) to achieve measurable business outcomes across Marketing, Sales and Operations. • You will also be expected to coach fellow analysts and stakeholders on their craft to help build a great data community and data-driven leaders.
job_description.506: • Experience Hybrid. Work from the office or home in a rhythm that suits you • Permanent role based in Sydney or Melbourne.  We're REA  REA Group is not your average digital business. From humble beginnings in a garage in Melbourne’s east in 1995, we have grown into a leading global digital business, specialising in property.  With bold and ambitious goals, we are changing the way the world experiences property. No matter where you're at on your property journey, we're here to help with every step - whether that's finding or financing your next home.  Our people are the key to our success. At the heart of everything we do, is a thriving culture centred around high performance and care. We are purpose driven and collaborative, which drives innovation and our ability to make a real impact. As such, we’re proud to be named in Australia’s “Top 5” Best Workplaces two years in a row, as well as being recognised as a Best Workplace for Women.  Where the team fits in  REA is evolving how it leverages data and technology to deliver benefits for customers. After the acquisition of Hometrack Australia in May-18 (recently re-branded into PropTrack). Since this time the business has continued to grow, underpinned by an expanding set of services and capabilities we bring to our customers.  PropTrack’s commercial team is the face of the PropTrack business with its customers. The Data Analyst role sits within the Client Analytics function within the commercial team. The Client analytics team has become an important, unique and in demand offering of PropTrack in market, as a result we are now looking for an experienced data & analytics professional who can interface with our customers to help consult and solve analytical problems.  What the role is all about • Liaising and working collaboratively with PropTrack’s customers to help solve analytical business problems. • Working with customers on tasks from a wide breadth of analytical domains including modelling, data mining/analysis, reporting and data visualisation. • Presenting complex analytical outputs and results to all levels of an organisation. • Working with commercial leads and account managers to support client requests and working across a wide range of teams within REA to service these requests. • Bringing domain expertise to help in the design and build of new products and solutions to support PropTrack’s property analytics products, platforms and custom solutions in line with the growth strategy • Building a deep understanding of PropTrack’s products and enabling clients to optimise and make the best use of PropTrack’s current data analytics products and platforms (eg AVM, HTV, HPB). • Building deep relationship with key stakeholders within the Financial Services clients (Senior Management to analyst levels)  Who we’re looking for • Technical knowledge- Understanding of common analytical techniques such as sampling and experience of working in a data-rich environment with data mining techniques and predictive analytics, with use of tools such as SQL, R, Python. Knowledge in common data visualisation tools such as tableau is also high desirable. • Domain Knowledge - A deep understanding of several or all of the following: data analytics, the property market, property data, property valuations, home lending and retail banking. • Commercial orientation – Commercially savvy, able to bring the best outcomes for the benefit of PropTrack business and clients alike. • Creative and analytical thinker - An ability to work through complex problems collaboratively, and to find practical and viable solutions to meet client needs and wants. • Client Focus - A mind-set that is always client first, and a proven track record in managing customer experience initiatives. • Relationship Influencer – the ability to build strong relationships with peers within in organisations, to solve problems and perspective of clients for mutually beneficial outcomes.  The REA experience  The physical, mental, emotional and financial health of our people is something we’ll never stop caring about. This is a place to learn and grow. We’re committed to your development – both professionally and personally. Your experience with us is something we take seriously.  We offer: • A hybrid and flexible approach to working - https://rea.to/hybrid-working • Flexible parental leave offering for primary and secondary carers • Programs to support mental, emotional, financial and physical health & wellbeing • Our Because We Care program offers employees volunteering leave, community grants, matched payroll giving and our Community Café donates 100% of revenue to charity. • Hack Days so you can bring your big ideas to life • Performance recognition programs because hard work should never go unnoticed  Our commitment to Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion  We are committed to providing a working environment that embraces and values diversity, equity and inclusion. We believe teams with diverse ideas and experiences are more creative, more eﬀective and fuel disruptive thinking - be it cultural and ethnic backgrounds, gender identity, disability, age, sexual orientation, or any other identity or lived experience. We know diverse teams are critical to maintaining our success and driving new business opportunities. If you've got the skills, dedication and enthusiasm to learn but don't necessarily meet every single point on the job description, please still get in touch.  If you like the sound of us, then we think you should apply today. We're proud to be Circle Back Initiative Employer and we commit to respond to every applicant. While we're looking at your application, and preparing to come back to you with an update, why not get to know us a bit more through our various social channels?

Fed up with the increased cost you’re spending on fuel?  Why waste time and money, when you could have a flexible hybrid arrangement?  What a nice change, huh?  Not only this, but enjoy the satisfaction of knowing that your data insights will directly impact this Non-For-Profit’s mission for the positive; to upskill and coach individuals to sustain small businesses, and provide support to Indigenous communities.  If you want to use your data insights experience to make a real change in the community, step right up.  Your New Gig  This Non-For-Profit is continuously growing, and as an Applied Data Analyst, you’ll be joining for 6 weeks, as a key player in a project to promote business process improvement.  You’ll be working on multiple business problems, however you’ll have a significant focus on leveraging and analysing data surrounding the customer journey. You’ll need to identify and communicate key insights and areas of attrition to leaders, with the goal to minimise customer drop-out rates and help overall lead conversion.  If you’re a lover of data who likes to get hands-on and dig deep to find the “why”, then this is the fun bit!  You won’t just be reporting your insights, you’ll be a part of the problem-solving process. You’ll be brainstorming hypotheses, testing them with different processes and solutions, and delivering your insights accordingly.  If you’re not an expert in extracting data – no worries, you’ll be working with a Business Analyst who will provide you with the necessary data to get the job done.  As a result of your work, you’ll help this organisation deliver its services to hundreds more in need.  If you happen to also utilise the Six Sigma methodology, this will help. If not, they’ll coach you through it!  Next Steps  If you have a CV, click apply to be immediately considered.  If you don’t have an up-to-date CV, but are still keen, let’s have a further chat.  Contact me, Olivia Ellerman via one of the following channels:  LinkedIn: linkedin.com/in/oliviaellerman/  Email: oellerman@rarekind.com.au
job_description.508: WiseTech Global is a world-leading software company building software for the global logistics industry. We are united in our mission to create breakthrough products that enable and empower those who own and operate the supply chains of the world. More than 18,000 logistics organizations use our software solutions, including 24 of the top 25 global freight forwarders and 41 of the top 50 global third-party logistics providers.  We’re an engineer-led company focusing on building secure, scalable products. Therefore, data analytics is critical to the function of the international supply chain.  As a Sydney or Melbourne-based data analyst, you will be responsible for designing and building data models to enhance analytics and performance reporting and optimizing data flow and collection for cross-functional teams.  About the role:  By joining the team, you will be responsible for analyzing available data sources and giving recommendations on data integration and processing, building data models for predictive and prescriptive analytics, investigating, and interpreting data, and building prototypes for analytics reports.  If you are self-directed and are comfortable supporting the data needs of the business, systems, and products - this role is for you!  Key responsibilities: • Communicating with stakeholders to understand and write technical and business requirements for use cases. • Statistical analysis of data in multiple data sources, creating data profiles. • Identifying and implementing data quality control processes that prompt correction in the source systems where required. • Developing data models, flows, datasets, and views that are efficient and meaningful representations of data. • Designing reporting solutions and building prototypes. • Communicating and coordinating effectively with data owners, product people, and other stakeholders to ensure models and results are well understood and incorporated into their business processes. • Developing and implementing testing plans for data transformations, maintaining data definition and technical documentation. • Driving awareness and providing expertise on the use of analytics tools and concepts, providing training and effectively communicating with multiple stakeholders. • Analysing existing data governance and privacy requirements and identifying areas for improvement.  To be successful in this role, you will have: • 2-6 years of commercial experience in a similar role • Strong understanding of business analysis methodologies and techniques, including requirements gathering, process modelling, and documentation • Experience of working with notebooks • Deep understanding of databases • Experience in Data Design work • Expertise in Microsoft BI stack (MS SQL, SSIS, SSAS, Power BI, OLAP) • Experience working with SQL and visualization tools like Tableau or Power BI, • Basic Python skills • Experience with Statistical Modelling • Practical knowledge of data warehousing concepts • Knowledge of Data Governance concepts, industry best practices, and principles • Solid SQL experience, authoring complex queries and DDL, working with execution plans • Basic knowledge of machine learning (E.g. Spark ML or Python ML)  Before you apply:  From time to time, WiseTech Global may use external service providers to assist us with assessing applications, including background checks, on our behalf. Accordingly, by applying for this role and providing your personal information to WiseTech Global, you consent to WiseTech Global providing this information to our external service providers who are required to treat such information with strict confidentiality in line with privacy and data protection laws and regulations.
job_description.509: About Us  Big Red Group is the leading experience network in ANZ. A powerful connector that provides experience partners with quality customers and the industry with trusted intelligence and comprehensive support.  Australian owned, Big Red Group operates respected consumer experience brands RedBalloon AU/NZ, Adrenaline and Experience OZ alongside an expansive range of B2B channels and a suite of industry products and services to support experience partners with growth and capability.  With a purpose to 'shift the way people experience life' Big Red Group are on a journey to shift the tide of consumption. Encouraging people to choose 'stories over stuff' at every opportunity. And, on track to deliver an experience every second by 2030.  The Role:  We currently have an opening for a Senior Data Analyst in our centralised data team supporting our marketing teams. This person will play a key role in enabling the marketing teams to make data informed decisions and drive growth.  What will I be doing? • You’ll work closely with Product when we build new features to ensure we are measuring the right things and build a better product that customers love to use. • You’ll support our Marketing team to understand how our marketing is impacting performance and help us to improve the way we spend our marketing dollars. • You’ll be the driving force behind our experimentation agenda by analysing how successful the experiments were and work closely with the Product team to suggest new testing opportunities. • You’ll dive into the data to support our personalisation and website optimisation teams create great customer experiences that influence our metrics that matter. • You’ll be an integral part of the team and will help to improve digital & data literacy across the business.  What are we looking for? • A keen interest in web analytics and trends in digital marketing • Experience working with web data. eg. GA, Segment, Snowplow • Experience working with performance marketing data eg. Google Ads, Facebook Ads • Experience with SQL & Data Warehouses. Eg. Snowflake, Bigquery Redshift • Experience with Reporting or Visualisation Tools eg. Tabluea, Power BI, Looker etc  What else would be of interest? • Experience with the full modern data stack • Experience with data modelling tools eg. dbt, stored procedures, Airflow • Experience with statistical analysis eg. A/B testing, T-Tests, regression • Experience with Statistical Programming eg. Python,  Why work for us? • Our dedication is to provide a workplace you choose to return every day. • Community - ESG commitment, paid community days, Fast Company 'Brands that matter', weekly Community Lunch in our offices, Volunteering • Connection - organised experiences, quarterly roadshows, offsites, social & sports events • Investing in you - 30 days work anywhere, Leadership Development, Talent Academy's, Mentors, Paid Parental Leave, Wellness support • Your Workplace - Hybrid flexible, Sydney & GC offices, 2022 AFR Best Place to Work, 2021 Australian Employer of choice, Top 20% most engaged workplaces in Australia
job_description.510: The main responsibilities of this role include - • Assist in the preparation of reports and building complex data models • Devise new data collection and analysis processes • Work with key stakeholders to priorities information needs • Analyse results and report findings to the business • Identify and interpret trends or patterns in complex data sets • Develop strategies to optimise the quality of statistical results • Maintain database • Research background materials, including relevant economic and financial data • Assist in the development of long-range financial forecasts and related budgets  The Successful Applicant  The Successful Applicant will have the following - • Bachelors degree in Business / Commerce or related discipline • Ideally 1-3 years of experience, however, will also consider graduates straight from University • Intermediate Excel skills • Strong analytic skills and problem solving • Strong communication skills • Proficient in Power BI (preferred)  What's on Offer • New office currently being built • Opportunity to develop and enhance career • flexible working arrangements • Work closely with the CFO • Attractive remuneration and bonus • Flexible working arrangements
job_description.511: We are looking for someone who is passionate about optimising data and using their analytical skills to further the mission of Compassion Australia. This role is a full-time temporary 12-month contract and will be performed in a hybrid arrangement...  Compassion Australia's headquarters is in Newcastle but we have offices across Australia. We are open to receiving applications Australia-wide for this position. • Purpose driven organisation • Hybrid work, with a genuine mix of office and work from home • Salary Packaging Options available - maximise your take-home pay!  Our Impact As part of a global network of more than 40 countries, Compassion Australia is a Christian charity with over 70 years’ experience working with children living in extreme poverty. Compassion is Christ-centred, child-focused, and church-based, and exists to release children from poverty in Jesus’ name. With our partners, we serve over 2.2 million children in more than 25 countries around the world.  Compassion Australia has a goal to further maximise our reach and extend to new areas and supporter groups.  About the Role Compassion is a Christian organisation, and it is important that the successful candidate supports our values and Statement of Faith.  Reporting to the Head of Projects, Research and Analytics, the Data Analyst effectively identifies relevant and available data sources and implements methods to gather, interpret and report data. You will contribute significantly by having a strong understanding of data modeling, analysis approaches, and translating complex information into reportable and usable knowlegde. You will also be assisting in ensuring the quality of the systems and tools used and monitoring its effectiveness to ensure decisions at Compassion Australia are data-informed. The role will require strong collaboration and stakeholder management across internal and external groups. You will be adding value to the works of Compassion through being detail-oriented, methodical, and analytical in your approaches.  About You • You are methodical in your thought process and have successfully applied that capability to perform tasks effectively and achieve results. • You are analytical in your approach; you find ease in identifying information or variances and have the ability to translate data and communicate solutions. • You are highly organised and have excellent ability to prioritise work to meet deadlines. • You are passionate about continuous improvement, always seeking to better processes and frameworks to increase efficiency. • You enjoy cross-departmental collaboration and have excellent interpersonal communication. • You have strong knowledge of data modelling techniques, reporting packages and analytical methodologies • Intermediate query skills - SQL, R, Python • Intermediate experience in ETL tools • Experience in database solutions – Azure Synapse, Snowflake • Experience in data visualisation applications – Power BI, Tableau • You have well-developed experience applying knowledge gained through analysis to solving business and process problems.  For a full copy of the Position Description, please contact our People and Culture Team via email at peopleandculture@compassion.com.au  How to Apply  If you would like to be considered for this position, submit your application by clicking “Apply Now”. • You are required to respond to the screening questions • Submit a cover letter outlining why you are interested in this role and how your background, and experience will enable you to successfully fulfill this role • Submit a concise resume outlining your qualifications and employment history.  Applications close at 11:59pm AEST 26 October 2023. Early applications are encouraged, and the position may be filled prior to the closing date.  If you have any questions regarding this position, please contact our People and Culture Team via email at peopleandculture@compassion.com.au.
job_description.512: Introduction At IBM, work is more than a job - it's a calling: To build. To design. To code. To consult. To think along with clients and sell. To make markets. To invent. To collaborate. Not just to do something better, but to attempt things you've never thought possible. Are you ready to lead in this new era of technology and solve some of the world's most challenging problems? If so, lets talk.  Your Role and Responsibilities We are currently recruiting Data Engineer -Big Data for 18 month fixed term contract, based in Sydney. You will be part of a Data Engineer team that is responsible for supporting Data Ingestion, Data Transformation and data analysis. As a Data Engineer your responsibilities include – • Develop design documents and review technical documents from Solution Architects for projects in the cards and collections domain and manage the alignment of the program’s architecture to the Bank’s Enterprise Architecture and as per Westpac WDP standards. • Define technical user stories and track the development activities of the team members • Lead the technical design process coordinating the various stakeholders from business and towards an agreed solution. • Experience and Knowledge of Agile and Scrum Process and coordinate with distributed teams • Design and build deliverables to ensure traceability of the built solution to the architectural principles and business objectives. • Resolve technical issues during system integration testing and post implementation, address the technical and operational challenges faced by the team. • Participate in client meetings to communicate status or give demos. • Be keenly aware of timelines and budgeting to deliver in a timely manner.  Required Technical and Professional Expertise To ensure success in the role you will possess the following skills – • Minimum 10 years of experience as Data Engineer with expert and leadership level skills in HIVE, Spark, Scala, PySpark, Solr, HBase, Kafka, Spark streaming • Experienced in writing robust and efficient code in HIVE, Spark, Scala, PySpark, Solr, Kafka, HBase, Spark streaming, Unix in Cloudera environment. • Good knowledge and experience in Business lending domain (in Banking) • Should have domain knowledge in personal loans, secured car loans, android pay and mobile wallets. • Good understanding and experience in DevOps – CI/CD tools like Git, Jenkins, Bitbucket • Build using Maven, Gradle tools • Good understanding on schedulers like Control M, Crontab. • Experience on tools like Pycharm, Putty, WinScp, Confluence, Jira • Should be proficient in DevOps methodologies and tools  Preferred Technical and Professional Expertise As Above

As part of this role you will verify that business names and opening hours are correct. With this job you can plan your days around this highly flexible working schedule, work weekends or late evenings, all from the comfort of your own office.  The flexibility of our roles minimizes the impact on your daily routine.  So, whether you are a student looking to earn as you learn, a retiree looking for a new challenge a part-time / full time professional or a work from home parent, Peroptyx has the right role for you!  Ideal Candidate • Fluent in English. • Excellent research skills. • Excellent local knowledge of your home country. • Good understanding and general knowledge of the geography and culture of Australia. • Analytical mindset.
