job_description.517: Senior Data Analyst, Product Analytics  12-Month Contract  We believe that we are better together, and at Tripadvisor we welcome you for who you are. Our workplace is for everyone, as is our people powered platform. At Tripadvisor, we want you to bring your unique perspective and experiences, so we can collectively revolutionize travel and together find the good out there.  Tripadvisor is looking for an experienced data analyst to join our dynamic and fast paced Product Analytics Team on our Viator brand, home to over 300K bookable experiences worldwide. As a member of this team, you will have the opportunity to work on a wide range of complex and interesting business problems and have access to huge data sets. You will present your finding to Senior Leadership and be able to observe the impact of your work in real time as you help the company grow. This is a great opportunity to make your mark on a growing brand in the Tripadvisor family strongly recovering post Covid-19.  We are seeking a Senior Analyst, Product Analytics who has the analytical skills and business knowledge to support numerous end users from an analytics and measurement perspective and is looking to join a fast-growing all-star team dedicated to providing the highest quality data driven insights. • Lead analysis/reporting of current business operating metrics, focused on developing the capability to provide insight into Tripadvisor's products and improving Tripadvisor's understanding of its market-by-market customer propositions and competitor positioning. • Provide timely insights and analytical support to different internal stakeholders to support effective business decision-making, including Product, Marketing, Supply and Business Development. • Create concepts, justify business cases and manage the implementation of changes to the website experience to improve customer engagement and value metrics. • Employ/automate reporting tools to measure customer interaction (such as acquisition of members, engagement metrics, and member and user value) and competitor positioning. (such as reach and page impression growth, content feature set, and marketing activities) • Lead analysis of consumer and member behavior across the websites, using web analytics tools and internal warehouse data to identify source of traffic and which areas of the site, content and functionality users are engaging in. • Identify key success indicators and determine best practices for measurement and reporting. • Lead product experimental design like A/B or Multi-variate test to identify opportunity for product optimization and improve business KPIs. • Assist with ad hoc queries and provide analytical support to our fast-growing business as it evolves. What we are looking for? • 3-5 years of experience in an analytical role (ideal backgrounds include: a similar business analyst role at a web company, a data-based consulting role, or other data strategy type positions) • Bachelor's Degree in an analytical field (math, economics, engineering, statistics, etc), Master's Degree a plus • Excellent problem-solving and analytical skills, involving data analysis, experimental design and predictive modeling • Ability to work with large dataset and summarize findings in a clear format • Combine creative and pragmatic use of insight and data with attention to detail • Proficient in Excel, SQL, R/Python, Tableau and a few other useful tools of the data trade • Proactive not reactive, with ability to work independently in a fast-paced environment • Ability to take in loose requirements, work independently, ask smart questions, and produce high quality actionable insights • Confident with learning new tools, technologies, and methodologies • Ability to work at all levels including senior management; and across multiple functions/departments • Small company experience with hands on / can-do mindset is an advantage • Some programming/scripting ability a huge plus • Experience with statistical packages such as SAS, R, SPSS, etc. a plus We strive to create an accessible and inclusive experience for all candidates. If you need a reasonable accommodation during the application or the recruiting process, please make sure to reach out to your individual recruiter or our team at recruitment@tripadvisor.com.  #LI-JZ1  #Viator
job_description.518: Join our dynamic and fast-growing real estate company as our Data Analyst!  We are a leading organisation in the real estate sector with an extensive franchise network across the country. Our company values excellence, teamwork, and innovation, and we are committed to fostering a positive and collaborative work environment.  We are seeking a talented and motivated individual to join our team to play a crucial role in transforming raw data into actionable insights that drive strategic decisions and enhance operational efficiency. You will work closely with various teams within the organisation to gather, analyse, and visualise data and provide valuable insights that inform business strategies.  Responsibilities include: • Identify data sources and gather relevant data from various internal systems and external sources. • Clean, validate, and preprocess data to ensure accuracy and consistency, addressing any data quality issues. • Utilise statistical techniques and advanced analytics to extract meaningful insights from complex data. • Identify trends, patterns, and correlations within the data, offering insights that support decision-making processes. • Developing and maintaining databases, and data systems – reorganising data in a readable format. • Analysing local, national, and global trends that impact both the organisation and the industry. • Preparing reports for the CEO & Head of Growth. • Provide consolidated franchise performance reports on gross numbers via CRM data. • Preparing final analysis reports for stakeholders to understand the data-analysis steps, enabling them to make important decisions based on various facts and trends.  The successful candidate will have: • Proven experience as a data analyst or in a similar role, with excellent data interpretation. • Knowledge of the real estate industry is a bonus, with the ability to understand industry-specific trends and concepts. • Strong team player with the ability to collaborate effectively and contribute to a positive work • environment. • Detail-oriented with an eye for accuracy and consistency. • Proactive and self-motivated with the ability to take initiative and drive projects forward.
job_description.519: About Index Exchange:  Index is a global advertising marketplace enabling media owners to grow their revenue by helping marketers reach consumers across every screen. We’re a proud industry pioneer with nearly 20 years of experience accelerating the evolution of ad technology for the world’s leading experience-makers.  We are all in on video this year. We recently rebuilt our platform from the ground up specifically for this new channel, allowing our customers to transact across every device and screen as efficiently as possible. We’re reimagining streaming TV, and it has become one of the fastest growing areas of our business.  Index is an exciting and fast-paced place to work, and our company is built on our values of change, support, learning and teaching, trust, and intention. You will be able to feed your ambition, lean into trust & transparency, and feel genuine support from your colleagues here.  We pride ourselves on our independence and openness, not only in our technology, but in our teams, too. Our diverse and inclusive culture celebrates how we can leverage our unique differences to help drive Index forward.  We have more than 550 Indexers around the globe dedicated to building a safe and transparent marketplace that provides a trusted experience for consumers, and we’re looking for talented professionals to help take us to the next level.  Are you ready to join the programmatic evolution?  Reporting to the Manager, Commercial Insights, the Data Analyst will support and drive objectives of the Commercial Insights team, partnering with our commercial business partners to drive revenue and growth through data insights.  What We’re Looking For: • Critical thinker: Logical and concise with a strong sense of urgency, understanding the larger story behind each release/product. • Problem solver: Experience working with teams and collaborating across groups to achieve desired results. • Independent: Comfort with ambiguity and self-starter with an aptitude for defining new processes. Resourceful. • Passionate: You are curious and love experimenting with different approaches to find the most efficient solution to a problem. • Storyteller: You can find and tell a story when looking at numbers and graphs • Experienced: Minimum 2-3 years working experience; 0-1 years in programmatic advertising preferred.  Here’s What You’ll be Doing: • Become an expert in Index’s data. Build and maintain efficient data solutions for the commercial business, utilising our primary BI tool, Looker. • Drive incremental growth for Index’s customers by uncovering and delivering proactive analysis and meaningful insights to our account management teams for Index’s clients, across publishers, DSPs and buyers. • Provide client-facing analytics for a selection of key premium publisher accounts in APAC, partnering with the account team, attending meetings and quarterly reviews, and identifying revenue growth opportunities via data analysis. • Design and build dashboards to quantify and monitor releases and initiatives • Provide analytics support and empower internal teams with knowledge and resources by delivering a range of analysis, insights, and reporting for commercial teams, via a queue-based system. • Drive initiatives to increase revenue and/or improve operations, utilising Index’s internal software and reporting systems such as Looker, Confluence and Salesforce. • Have a leading role in strategic programs, to drive incremental revenue and improve efficiency for the business. • Provide comprehensive summaries on analysis, releases, and outcomes to key stakeholders • Be inquisitive and explore opportunities for automation of recurring and time consuming tasks, using creativity and programming language skills. • Collaborate and learn from analytics team members across the globe.  Here's What You Need: • Bachelor’s degree in Mathematics, Economics, Finance or a similar quantitative discipline combined with a minimum of 2-3 years of experience performing the responsibilities outlined above, or an equivalent combination of education, training and experience. • Ability to build consensus and relationships among partners and team members. • Strong ability to organize effectively, solve problems, make confident conclusions quickly, thoughtfully, and communicate clearly • Strong analytical mind and a keen interest in conducting research, interpreting data and translating to insights for various audiences. • Ability to be curious with data and translate it into meaningful insights. • Experience or an interest in working within the ad technology industry. • Advanced proficiency in Microsoft Excel. • Knowledge of SQL for querying databases. • Experience with BI tools such as Redash and Looker considered an asset. • Knowledge of digital advertising industry, participants, technologies, and advertising ecosystems considered an asset • Japanese language skills a plus  Why You’ll Love Working Here: • Comprehensive health, dental, and vision plans at no cost to you • Time off and flexible work schedules • Stock options and equity packages • Generous parental leave • Monthly wellness stipend plus fitness discounts and quarterly wellness group activities • Community engagement opportunities and donation-matching program • Annual virtual company retreats and regular community-led team events • One day off per year to volunteer • A workplace that supports a diverse, equitable, and inclusive environment – learn more here  Notification  Index Exchange is aware that there have been recent scams directed toward candidates regarding job interviews and offers.  Please be vigilant and do not accept interview requests, job offers, or other hiring-related documents from anyone other than our dedicated recruitment team, from the domain of @indexexchange.com. Our interview process consists of several steps, including phone screens and video interviews. We do not conduct interviews via an email questionnaire or request money at any point in the process.  If you do receive these requests, please let us know immediately at: report.scam@indexexchange.com.  Equal employment opportunity  At Index Exchange, we believe that successful products are built by teams just as diverse as the audience who uses them. As such, we are committed to equal employment opportunities. We celebrate diversity of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity or expression, or veteran status. Additionally, we realize that diversity is deeper than any status or classification—diversity is the human experience. For those who show grit, passion, and humility—Index will welcome you.  Accessibility for applicants with disabilities  Index Exchange is committed to working with and providing access and reasonable accommodations to applicants with disabilities. Please let us know if you’d like to request a reasonable accommodation.  #LI-MF1  #LI-Hybrid
job_description.520: Reporting to the **Head of Operations**, you will play a vital role in optimising the success of our customers on the FoodByUs platform, both buyers and suppliers. You will collaborate with various departments, including sales, operations, and marketing, to identify opportunities for improvement and implement data-driven solutions.
job_description.521: • Permanent role based in either Sydney or Melbourne  We're REA  REA Group is not your average digital business. From humble beginnings in a garage in Melbourne’s east in 1995, we have grown into a leading global digital business, specialising in property.  With bold and ambitious goals, we are changing the way the world experiences property. No matter where you're at on your property journey, we're here to help with every step - whether that's finding or financing your next home.  Our people are the key to our success. At the heart of everything we do, is a thriving culture centred around high performance and care. We are purpose driven and collaborative, which drives innovation and our ability to make a real impact. As such, we’re proud to be named in Australia’s “Top 5” Best Workplaces two years in a row, as well as being recognised as a Best Workplace for Women.  Where the team fits in  It’s an exciting time to be part of Financial Services. You will be part of a team working together to solve unique challenges, like how to better connect Australian property seekers with finance and mortgage advice.  The Financial Services purpose is to offer home finance and other financial services to those using realestate.com.au for their property search. Given the opportunity of the size of that audience, the FS vision is to integrate a consumer’s property search with finance though a world class digital seamless process.  This will be achieved by building innovative consumer search and property finance application experiences that integrate the mortgage distribution channels of digital, phone and face to face. The financial services team is accountable for strategy development and execution, working with our banking and mortgage broker partners to build our capability and product offerings, leading sales management and engaging across the other lines of business in REA.  What the role is all about • Be a key team member in the finance and data analytics team for Financial Services • Prepare and deliver accurate reporting and analysis to track business performance with insights and action • Provide ad-hoc support and analysis, ranging from key performance indicators, trend analysis, conversion performance to market and competitor analysis • Ability to work across multiple systems and utilise various tools – Excel, Powerpoint, dashboards • Support the Data & Insights Manager in day-to-day deliverables and be able to work cross-functionally and establish relationships across Financial Services. • Stakeholder management – ability to listen to others, tailor to the audience, collaborate and partner to achieve the best commercial outcomes • Be flexible to meet dynamic and evolving business environment and needs • Work well in a team environment and contribute to wider team & organisation culture  Who we’re looking for • 1-3 years of experience working in an analytical role – industry environment in a commercial capacity • Strong initiative, willingness to take ownership and a team player • High attention to detail with tenacity to problem solve • Advanced Excel skills and comfortable working with data to surface insights • Interested in career progression in either data analytics or commercial finance • Demonstrated commercial acumen and stakeholder management • Relevant tertiary qualifications  Additional skills and experience that would be highly desirable: • Commercial finance or a FP&A background working towards CPA or CA • Data visualisation & dashboarding experience (Tableau or similar) • Experience using SQL or BigQuery • Mortgage broking industry experience, banking or sales organisation  The REA experience  The physical, mental, emotional and financial health of our people is something we’ll never stop caring about. This is a place to learn and grow. We’re committed to your development – both professionally and personally. Your experience with us is something we take seriously.  We offer: • A hybrid and flexible approach to working - https://rea.to/hybrid-working • Flexible parental leave offering for primary and secondary carers • Programs to support mental, emotional, financial and physical health & wellbeing • Our Because We Care program offers employees volunteering leave, community grants, matched payroll giving and our Community Café donates 100% of revenue to charity. • Hack Days so you can bring your big ideas to life • Performance recognition programs because hard work should never go unnoticed  Our commitment to Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion  We are committed to providing a working environment that embraces and values diversity, equity and inclusion. We believe teams with diverse ideas and experiences are more creative, more eﬀective and fuel disruptive thinking - be it cultural and ethnic backgrounds, gender identity, disability, age, sexual orientation, or any other identity or lived experience. We know diverse teams are critical to maintaining our success and driving new business opportunities. If you like the sound of us, then we think you should apply today. We're proud to be Circle Back Initiative Employer and we commit to respond to every applicant. job_description.522: Job description  We are looking for a Data Analyst to be part of our Analytics team, whose objective is to help continue the ongoing HelloFresh growth!  Reporting through to the Associate Director, Data Science:  You will... • Provide analytics on a variety of growth and marketing topics, including customer acquisition, marketing mix, retention and monetisation. • Improve our analytics capability: identify inefficiencies and gaps within our analytics process and work to streamline and improve the way the team operates. • Exemplify best practice: develop processes, analysis methodologies and dashboards to increase efficiency and consistency within the wider growth functions. • Enable data-driveness for better decisions making: create innovative solutions that enable colleagues to easily track, report and identify trends and opportunities. • Identify growth opportunities: analyse business performance to identify opportunities to invest marketing budget more efficiently. • Use your technical skills: quickly learn about our data infrastructure, extract and aggregate data with complex SQL queries, and make clear summaries for stakeholders in Google Sheets or apply advanced analytics methodologies using Python/R where appropriate  You have/ are... • Minimum 3 years experience in a similar role. • Excellent analytical skills, including working with large data sets • Excellent knowledge of Google Sheets/Excel, SQL (Tableau is a plus) • Working knowledge of Python • Strong organisational skills with a proven ability to manage multiple projects and deadlines • An aspiration to drive optimal decision making and maximum productivity • A logical way of working and high attention to detail • The ability to document findings in a clear and concise way, and present them to key stakeholders • An analytical degree; experience in analytics, data science or marketing is a plus • Passion for HelloFresh and the desire to be part of an extremely fast-paced business  What You'll Get In Return... • Heavily discounted HelloFresh boxes (70% off) • High level of responsibility from day one • A position designed with room for evolution • Working with a fun, energetic and supportive team  Start date: Immediately - Can wait notice period  Duration: Full time role. You must have the right to work full-time in Australia.  Location: Chippendale Head Office - Hybrid working model  #LI-Hybrid
job_description.523: Hello. We are EssenceMediacom. GroupM’s newest and largest agency, committed to delivering marketing breakthroughs for brands. We have disrupted the old models across media, creative, innovation and analytics to find new opportunities for advertisers and deliver truly integrated media solutions. Born out of two pioneering agencies, EssenceMediacom fuses Essence’s performance, data, analytics and creative technology DNA with MediaCom’s scaled multichannel audience planning and strategic media expertise.  This role sits at a pivotal crossroads of client and product solutions. As a Data Analyst, you will be responsible for supporting internal teams on data and analysis projects providing data driven recommendation and insights. This will involve the management of internal stakeholders to drive maximum value of your client’s media mix and new insights developed for smarter planning and business management.  Reporting of the role  This role reports to the Advanced Analytics Manager  3 best things about the job: • An enjoyable environment that combines the best of your skills whilst at the same time being part of the largest marketing services group in the world • Working within a network of 100+ analysts worldwide in areas such as statistics, econometrics, optimisation, machine learning, programming, marketing mix modelling, causal analysis, attribution modelling and predictive modelling or forecasting • Work diversity that involves liaising with internal and external stakeholders across a range of disciplines, solving business problems for clients  Measures of success  In three months, you would have: • You will be up to speed with the Advanced Analytics team value proposition and able to articulate this confidently. • You will have started to build relationships with the key decision makers in the team and agency. • You will be able to build data sets for modelling related work including data manipulation, data cleansing, and organisation.  In six months, you would have: • Provided structured data to your line manager • Be confident using our available range of tools and software to organise and visualise data • Started to work on your own allocated projects and ad hoc requests  In 12 months, you would have: • Become a key support for your line manager and peers • Fully work on a project under your line manager’s guidance from start to end including delivery of results • Nominated champion in your area of expertise  What you will need: • A degree ideally in a STEM related subject. Candidates with relevant degrees and demonstrated coding skills will also be considered. • Experience working across either Media, Marketing, Consultancy, Business Analytics would be beneficial. • Proficiency in SQL, R, Python, data science segmentation/prediction algorithms would be beneficial. • Experience with data visualization tools (e.g., Tableau, Power BI) • Exceptional verbal, written, communication skills with an analytical mind set. • An excellent work ethic, problem solving and proficient time management skills. • Able to work to deadlines in a fast-paced agency environment. • Have a passion for learning and work effectively in a team environment. • MS Office skills with advance knowledge in Excel. Apply now and send your CV via the link!

job_description.525: Data Analyst / Consultant  A National Data & Analytics consultancy based out of Sydney is looking for Consultants/Analysts, with a strong background in Data & Analytics, machine learning and data science to help grow their practice.  This is an exciting opportunity for someone with 0.5 to 5 years’ experience in the industry, that is looking to further develop their skills and tech capability through training and exposure to project based work. You will need to have exceptionally strong SQL skills and a mathematical logical mind.  In this role, you will gain exposure to Python, Power BI, Azure, Databricks, Tableau, AWS, UiPath and Power Automate, to name a few.  We’d love to hear from you, if you have: • Ability to work with complex data structures • Exceptionally strong SQL skills • Python skills • Strong understanding of Data Visualisation with tools like Power BI or Tableau • Mathematical and logical thinking with an understanding of business processes • Bachelor’s degree, preferably in Science, Engineering, Computing, Business or Finance field • At least 0.5 to 5 years of relevant industry experience • Exceptional critical thinking skills and problem-solving skills • An analytical mind with excellent data collection and analysis skills • A commitment to ongoing learning and development • High attention to detail with excellent interpersonal and communication skills (verbal and written) - ensuring all communications are clear, succinct and audience appropriate  In this role, you will be responsible for (but not limited to): • Support current and new projects for clients or internally, meeting with clients prior to actual professional engagement to determine requirements • Gathering data from multiple sources and pursuing data that is late in delivery • Cleansing data, troubleshooting, fixing errors and identifying discrepancies in data • Providing input to project planning, status and review meetings • Contributing to the design and development of innovative solutions • Analysing requirements within companies and giving independent and objective advice on the use of technologies • Identifying and evaluating inefficiencies and recommend optimal solutions • Designing, testing, installing and monitoring new systems • Ensuring the conceptual completeness of the technical solutions • Analysing and interpreting data to unearth weaknesses and problems, and comprehend the causes  If you have some of these skills and an enthusiasm for learning then click apply as we want to hear from you.
job_description.526: ING, Australia's most recommended bank is on the hunt for an experienced "Data Analysts"to join our high performing Customer Insights team.  You'll be responsible for producing comprehensive deep-dive analyses, and delivering these actionable insights to key stakeholders using impactful visualisation and presentation techniques. Our ideal candidate will be passionate about data, and its ability to strengthen narrative. This love of data and an understanding of how customers tick are essential in this role.  You'll be instrumental across all stages of analysis, including, but not limited to, planning, forecasting, behavioural investigation, research integration, and across all stages of the customer lifecycle and value management.  You'll be an integral part of our Customer Insights team, which is the CoE for the analytics function, for our retail bank.  The CI team is also a strategic partner for the business, equipping our stakeholders with data and insights to help identify, assess and quantify opportunities and outcomes, drive decisions, as well as to understand their impacts. What You'll Do  Integrating internal and external data sources to maximise the insights derived (examples of external data sources include quantitative research; government data sources such as APRA, RBA; external data agencies such as Nielsen; ABS/population).  Working with key stakeholders across the business to understand and clarify their business problems and propose investigative approaches to support decision-making.  Developing analytics to understand behaviours including customer behaviour, channel use, customer segments, product value, social media and lifetime value and presenting these insights and recommended actions in an engaging way.  Managing data discovery and manipulation, working and transforming customer / business data to improve usability and assess the quality and viability of the intended research. What we're looking for Demonstrated experience as Data analyst with hands-on in SQL, PowerBI and reporting. Advanced working knowledge of MS SQL / Teradata, SAS (Enterprise Guide and SAS Macros) and Excel. Experience with Python, the Google Cloud Platform environment and R are desirable, but not essential. Highly analytical, problem solving, lateral thinking and interpretive skills  About Us  At ING, we want to make life simpler and more worthwhile – for everyone who banks with us, for the people who work with us, and the community at large, too.  When you come to work at ING, you're joining a modern and progressive team where individuality isn't just accepted, it's encouraged. You'll be surrounded by people who are friendly, inclusive and respectful, who want you to reach your potential. It's one of the many reasons we're proud to be an Employer of Choice for Gender Equality.  We give people the freedom to take risks, stay curious and think differently, and seek new and better ways to make things happen. We're here to help you get ahead.  And with our global network, there's plenty of scope to take your career in new directions, perhaps even ones you've never considered.  People of all ages, sexual orientations, cultures and backgrounds are welcome to apply – likewise if you're an indigenous Australian, or you're living with a disability, or you have family or caring responsibilities. Sound like the kind of place you'd feel at home? We'd love to hear from you.  (One last thing, ING operates a direct talent sourcing model. So no agency introductions, please.) #J-18808-Ljbffr
job_description.527: Primary Details Time Type: Full time  Worker Type: Employee  The opportunity • Engage with businesses to help mature their data management practices by fostering development and collaboration amongst data stewards and coaching them in the use of data governance tools and processes. • Sydney, NSW (flexible) • Permanent, full-time position Your new role:  In this role you will work closely with data stewards, senior management and business units to drive the development and adoption of policy and governance processes. This will include assisting with policy formation, raising awareness and education and driving cultural change into the organization.  Primary Responsibilities will include: • Engaging with and supporting business and technical data stewards so that they are clear on their role and how to execute their responsibilities. • Facilitating activities across the data steward network to promote collaboration and address cross-functional issues. • Working with key partners in Risk, Security, Privacy, and other Data Governance colleagues to align communication and coordination of initiatives that affect data stewards. • Organising and running events to promote the data steward community. • Playing a key role in developing data governance processes and guidelines, and in policy formation. • Providing insight on the impact of regulatory, policy and operational change. • Driving cultural change into all parts of the organization. • Keeping abreast of developments, trends and best practices in data governance and management. Your story so far  To be successful in this role you will have a sound understanding of organisation change management and leadership practices in policy, cultural or transformation initiatives, as well as a natural affinity for reaching out and engaging with people across an organisation. An understanding of data management principles and practices and their implementation would help, as well as familiarity with methods and software tools used in governance processes and/or measurement and analysis. Your experience is having worked alongside management to drive and foster a culture of continuous improvement, motivation, collaboration, empowerment and buy-in across the business and other functions.  Required skills and experience: • Change management and communications to lead a business audience to adopt new process • Knowledge and understanding of implementing data stewardship principles and practices, and dealing with accountability, ownership, classification and roles and responsibilities. • Critical thinking to make data driven decisions backed with strong problem-solving skills to address data related issues and challenges. • Strong verbal, written and visualization skills to communicate effectively with stakeholders, including partner businesses, stewards and other teams, on data processes, practices and having an impact in driving cultural change. • Proficient in conducting audits and ensuring compliance with data governance policies and regulations are followed. • Strong business acumen to understand QBE's businesses and how data governance aligns to and is used to support the same. • Additional experience in the insurance industry will be a plus. • Ability to adapt to the evolving data management needs and requirements, and keeping abreast with changing principles and industry regulations. • Collaboration with other parties to establish and enforce data governance policies and promote cultural change. About QBE  We can never really predict what's around the corner, but at QBE we're asking the right questions to enable a more resilient future - helping those around us build strength and embrace change to their advantage.  We're an international insurer that's building momentum towards realising our vision of becoming the most consistent and innovative risk partner.  And our people will be at the centre of our success. We're proud to work together, and encourage each other enable resilience for our customers, our environment, our economies and our communities.  With more than more than 11,000 people working across 27 countries, we're big enough to make a real impact, but small enough to provide a friendly workplace, where people are down-to-earth, passionate and kind.  We believe this is our moment - what if it was yours too?  Your career at QBE - let's make it happen!  Benefits  QBE is an employer of choice amongst Australian insurers, offering a great range of benefits which enable you to bring your best self to work; including competitive salaries and bonus structures, hybrid working for the flexibility of working from home and the office, super matching and generous leave allowances.  In addition to this, we also offer flexible parental leave for both parents and additional support services for our diverse community of employees. We've won many awards highlighting our strong culture and values, reinforcing our family and community focus.  Apply now  APPLY NOW and let's make it happen!  Applications close on 12th October 2023 at 11:55pm AEST.  Successful applicants will need to complete work rights, police and credit checks through our online provider as a condition of employment. QBE recognise the value of diverse perspectives and experience. We are committed to an inclusive workplace where everyone feels valued and respected for who they are. If we can provide support with access requirements, alternative work arrangements or you would like to connect with one of our networks please contact us at recruitment@qbe.com  Application Close Date: 12/10/2023 11:59 PM  How to Apply:  To submit your application, click "Apply" and follow the step by step process. Primary purpose of the role: The Data Quality Analyst is responsible for understanding data quality as well as supporting the Data Management Tools that manage our metadata management, data lineage and data quality monitoring. Essential requirements: • Pre-employment checks. • Tertiary qualification plus at least 4 years experience in a data role. • Sound knowledge of data analysis, knowing SQL is an advantage, advanced Excel, to cleanse and manipulate data, and/or build reports  Typical experience: • Hands on experience in Data Mining, built or defined Data Quality rules in a line of business either writing SQL Scripts or using tools such as Informatica Data Quality; or • A broad range of experience in data analysis applications in complex information system environments; or • Experience working on and sound understanding of data lakes, data warehouses, and data marts; or • Experience in the creation and maintenance of data dictionaries, management of metadata, and/or maintenance of master and reference data; and • Experience as a workshops contributor with demonstrable experience building strong relationships with peers, stakeholders, and working with them to deliver relevant data analysis and/or actionable business insights and solutions that create value. The initial focus of the role will be to lead the HCM system implementation including readiness and preparation of P&C data and processes and lead P&C SME’s in defining business rules and liaising with ERP Program Lead on system configuration. Post implementation the role will be accountable for ongoing systems management and support, data integrity and governance and P&C reporting. You will work closely with the Senior Manager Operations to ensure all aspects of data are accurate and in accordance with relevant legislative requirements.  Key Responsibilities • P&C SME/Project Manager for Implementation of new HRIS (Workday) • SME for all current P&C systems and responsible for monitoring and managing ongoing upgrades and co-ordination with all relevant stakeholders. • Lead development and implementation of governance for systems and people data, ensuring all relevant parties are collaborated with. Perform regular data quality audits and ensure ongoing governance adherence. • Provide key stakeholder support and user training as a systems super user. • Maintain and develop all systems including but not limited to permissions architecture, system maintenance, system testing, data checking, user access and fault finding and resolution. • Focus on continuous improvement for both systems and data to enable the P&C team to add value, create self-service and uplift data capabilities. • Partner with third party providers for all aspects of contractual agreement, system maintenance, upgrades etc. and work with them to gain the best optimisation, user experience and system adoption possible. • Ensure the on-time delivery of all current scheduled P&C metrics (both automated and manual) and review current state vs future state requirements. • Develop and implement a P&C dashboard to provide reporting and analytics against end user needs whilst driving standardisation and medium of delivery. job_description.533: Hi, we’re PEXA  Every time a house is bought, sold or refinanced in Australia your lawyer, conveyancer and lender will most likely use a digital platform to settle your property, this is where we come in. PEXA’s world-first digital settlement platform has revolutionised the way we exchange property in Australia helping over 20,000 people a week safely settle their homes. And this is just the beginning. Our data and insights are helping organisations unlock the intel they need to drive change and possibilities.  Since starting our journey in 2010, we now employ a team of over 1,000 people working across multiple continents. We’re still growing, innovating and looking ahead, but behind our greatest achievements, there is a team of curious creators and big thinkers. That’s why, we’re looking for ambitious people like yourself to join the team.  About The Role  Are you passionate about sustainability and the environment? Cape is a fintech servicing small to mid sized businesses with a corporate card offering that is powered up by an expense management platform to allow you to set controls and rules around spend, putting businesses back in control of their cash.  We are a diverse team, made up of Tech Aficionados, Financial Services gurus, FinTech veterans and  Tech Newcomers all with one purpose in mind, we are passionate about what we do, we love to share our ideas and collaboration is our driving force.  Exciting times lie ahead, Cape is currently in the beta testing phase and we are full steam ahead with developing our platform. You’ve caught us at a good time as we have successfully secured a 33.1 million dollar fundraise and are currently in the process of our next round. Our best work is yet to come and we want you to be a part of this journey. Cape is not only product focused, we are also devoted to our people.  We value an impeccable culture, a team who are on a mission to make a real impact, steered by our core values ‘SAVE’,  About the role  As a Customer Business Analyst at Cape, you will assist with the end to end risk assessment of our customers both during the onboarding process and on an ongoing basis.You will see first hand and learn how to develop and implement a sophisticated decision engine. You will help with setting up Underwriting  Cases, inputting data and ensuring Cape has a clean Audit trial of the decisions that we are making. On top of this, you will produce dashboards and reports to drive decisions on process improvements.  On any given day you will • Review cases and ensure all data is available for an UW to complete the case; • Use third party tools and integrations to gather data and ensure our systems are processing them correctly. • Assist in ‘Anti-Money Laundering’ and ‘Know Your Customer’ requirements and escalate matters as needed • Build reports and dashboard on our risk key metrics and present to stakeholders  What you need to be successful • An analytical mindset whereby you use data to inform your decision making process • Design and implement monitoring dashboards to track risk performance and customer experience • An eager to learn about credit underwriting and the fintech industry  Nice to Haves • Graduate or still studying a business, finance or related field • Understanding of excel, SQL and BI tools to build out reports  Benefits: Our people are our number one priority. For this reason, we’re committed to supporting and rewarding our amazing team for their ongoing commitment and contribution. We offer a variety of perks and benefits to support you, your friends and your family: • Flexibility & Balance: Although we love what we do, we also appreciate (and support) the fact that life happens outside of work. We pride ourselves in our forward thinking hybrid working practices and are here to support you in defining what ‘flexible working’ means for you, your family and your lifestyle. • Did someone say an extra week of leave? That’s right! We’re all about supporting you to find the time to do what you love, whether that’s traveling, being with family or just taking a few days to yourself. All full-time employees get to enjoy 25 days of annual leave a year! • Workplace set-up: Regardless of where you’re based we are committed to set you up to do amazing things. This means that we provide you with state of the art technology and equipment to suit your needs from day dot! Obviously this also includes a great collection of Cape merch! • Ongoing Education & Resources: *We’re all about growth mindset and appreciate that individually and as a team we’re always learning. We have partnered with some amazing providers that will support your growth needs. Beyond this, we provide you with designated time in your week to dive into the tools and resources that we have available. • Grow your Career: *Cape’s well and truly found its feet, but it’s still a young company, which means there is plenty of career growth and development for you! Plus we were the winners of  Wealth and Finance International’s Fintech of the Year Award for 2022, in addition to being listed by Fintechmagazine.com as one of the top 5 fintechs to watchout for in 2022 as well as being nominated by HackerNoon for Fintech startup on the year 2022.  Life at Cape:  Cape HQ is located on the beautiful beachfront of Manly. You get the benefits of watching the waves at your desk, eating lunch on the beach and knocking off work to finish your day with a surf.  But hey, if that’s not your vibe or maybe you don’t even live in Sydney, we fully support those who wish to work remotely. In fact we have Cape-iens situated all around the globe. At Cape we encourage you to work in a manner which best suits you and your lifestyle.  Come and Join Our Team  If you’re looking to join a company who are striving for change, passionate about new technologies and get excited about the prospect of building innovative products to change the face of Fintech and challenge incumbent “Big Banks” then come join us!  Cape is an equal opportunity, inclusive company, we are committed to creating a diverse environment for all our employees. We encourage candidates of any nationality, age, background, disability and gender identity to apply. If you have a disability or special need that requires accommodation, please let us know, we are happy to adjust the recruitment process to suit your needs. Cape has proudly teamed up with Project F to actively support gender balanced hiring within the tech sector.  Job Type: Full-time  Salary: $62,569.21 – $85,552.25 per year  Benefits: • Employee stock purchase plan • Extended annual leave • Paid volunteer leave • Professional development assistance • Visa sponsorship • Work from home  Schedule: • 8 hour shift  Ability to commute/relocate: • Manly, NSW 2095: Reliably commute or planning to relocate before starting work (Required)  Work Authorisation: • Australia (Preferred)  Getting Down Under Partners with 482jobs.com for our sponsored job listings. 482Jobs.com is the world’s largest job board dedicated to advertising Sponsored Jobs In Australia. Additionally, becoming well-versed in the modern data and analytics technology stack, particularly focusing on Google Analytics, AppsFlyer, Snowplow, Tableau, and Looker (Data Studio).  ✅ Gathering, refining, and scrutinizing marketing data to extract invaluable insights and detect trends.  ✅ Formulating and managing dashboards and reports that monitor essential key performance indicators (KPIs) pertinent to marketing campaigns.  ✅ Furnishing regular performance reports to stakeholders, accentuating significant discoveries and actionable recommendations.  ✅ Conducting A/B testing and multivariate analysis to optimize ad creatives, targeting approaches, and bidding strategies.  ✅ Analyzing user behaviors spanning marketing channels to pinpoint possibilities for enhancing conversion rates.  ✅ Tracking and reporting funnel performance metrics encompassing acquisition, activation, retention, and revenue.  ✅ Collaborating closely with cross-functional teams to implement strategies aimed at enhancing funnel efficiency.  ✅ Safeguarding data precision and integrity by executing data governance procedures and conducting regular data audits.  ✅ Formulating actionable insights and suggestions grounded in data analysis to endorse strategic decision-making. job_description.556: UTS has a bold vision to be a world-leading university of technology, in which data and analytics are used for continuous improvement. We are a dynamic and innovative university in central Sydney, ranked the top young university in Australia. As analytics move into the mainstream, UTS is preparing its graduates and staff for the workplaces of today and tomorrow.  About Us  UTS Graduate School of Health was established to address the emerging needs of a range of health professions. It provides innovative, practice-based education and high impact research. The School is committed to producing career-ready graduates. Integrated problem-based learning, simulated environments and interdisciplinary workshops are used to help students apply the theory they learn and build their considerable skill set.  At the UTS Graduate School of Health we provide innovative, practice-based orthoptics education and high impact research that promotes excellence in eye healthcare.  About the Role  The Data Scientist will bring the technical and interpersonal skills to work with chief investigators on the NHMRC grant on a variety of projects in clinical vision research. S/he can expect to be significantly developing skillsets including machine learning, statistics data visualization, storytelling with data, and knowledge mapping. This position also provides a unique opportunity to work on various leading-edge projects, and to assist in transferring their innovative tools into mainstream use.  With examples, please outline in a separate document how you meet the following five (5) key selection criteria points: • Passionate about data, and in understanding the end goals • Ability to plan and multitask across projects • Data science programming: track record in using a common data-science programming language and to yield insight from diverse data sources (e.g. Python, R, use of third party APIs) • Bachelor or Master’s Degree in Data Science or a quantitative field • A portfolio of projects evidencing your skills and experience initiating/working on real world analytics problems. What worked, and what did you learn?  Remuneration  Base Salary: $110,790 to $126,178 pa (HEW 8)  This role attracts 17% superannuation (pension) in addition to the base salary.  UTS staff also benefit from a wide range of Employee Benefits include flexible work practices, child care centres, generous parental leave and salary packaging opportunities.  This position is full time and the appointment will be made on a fixed term basis for 2 years.  How to Apply  Please click the Apply link to be taken to the UTS website. Here you can download:  • full details of the application process;  • a copy of the position statement; and  • information on remuneration, benefits, terms and conditions  Please ensure that the file name for each document submitted includes IRC257922 and your name  Specific enquiries or issues with your application may be directed to Amelia Costain in the UTS Recruitment Team via recruitment@uts.edu.au  Closing Date: Tuesday 31st October 2023 at 11:59pm (AEST)  Applicants must have current and valid work rights in Australia for the duration of the contract.  Accessibility  UTS Recruitment care about digital accessibility. If there is any content in our advertising that you have struggled with, please make us aware so that we can make our information accessible to all.  In addition, if you have a disability that requires adjustment to the recruitment process or an alternative application pathway please contact recruitment@uts.edu.au for assistance.  UTS is recognised widely as supporting inclusivity and diversity through our Wingara Indigenous Employment Strategy, Social Impact Framework and UTS Access and Inclusion Plan. Cited as a WGEA Employer of Choice since the inception of the award, we were among the first Australian institutions to receive the Athena SWAN Bronze Accreditation for our commitment to action addressing gender equity in the STEMM disciplines.  We welcome applications from women, Indigenous Australians, people with disability, those who identify as LGBTIQ and applicants from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds.
job_description.557: Job Description  Reporting into our Associate Director of Data Science, as a Senior Business Intelligence Analyst you will play a pivotal role in transforming, analysing, and interpreting our marketing data to inform strategic decisions. This role exists to optimise return on investment (ROI) for each of our marketing campaigns by bridging the gap between marketing initiatives and measurable business outcomes. You will lead a team of analytics professionals, ensuring that data analytics capabilities are leveraged effectively across our in-house marketing department.  We are looking for a dynamic and engaging senior analyst who is passionate about fostering a data-driven culture within HelloFresh to enable more effective decision-making processes through advanced analytics and team leadership whilst you work to transform raw data into actionable insights. These insights contribute to enhancing customer engagement, improving sales performance, and increasing our market share. Ultimately, this role adds value by contributing to the financial sustainability and competitive advantage of The HelloFresh Group. This role is ‘hands-on’ and will individually contribute to delivering outcomes including completing analyses, building tools, and developing models.  What you'll do... • Develop and execute analytics strategies to align with marketing and business objectives • Lead and mentor a team of 3 analytics professionals • Foster cross-functional collaboration with business units and tech teams • Manage the lifecycle of analytics projects, ensuring alignment with business needs • Implement quality measures for data and analytics models • Translate and present complex data insights to senior stakeholders • Regularly assess and report on the impact of analytics initiatives • Provide guidance on A/B testing  What you'll bring... • A Bachelor's Degree in a related field (Data Science, Economics, Marketing Analytics, Engineering, Statistics etc) • Hands on SQL & Python experience • An advanced level of Excel/Google Sheets • Experience in project management, with an ability to manage and prioritise multiple projects simultaneously • Hands on experience using Tableau or other data visualisation tools • Previous experience working with a Marketing Team and A/B testing  What you get in return… • Significant discount on our meal kits, 70% off from your first day • HelloFresh Academies, monthly internal learning & development • Working flexibility available with a work from home hybrid • A diverse and vibrant international environment • A guaranteed steep learning curve & boost for your career • Access to Headspace  Start Date: ASAP  Duration: Full time role. You must have the right to work full-time in Australia/New Zealand.  Location: Chippendale Head Office, Sydney  #LI-hybrid

job_description.560: About MONEYME: MONEYME is a leading Australian FinTech disruptor on course to become the #1 challenger to the major banks. With a focus on innovation, we fund Australians’ ambitions with market-leading speed and seamless customer experiences. Leveraging AI and advanced, cloud-based technology, we offer highly automated credit products across personal, auto and real estate finance. Our core brands MONEYME and SocietyOne reflect digital-first experiences that meet, and exceed, the expectations of ‘Generation Now’. Our culture is young, fresh, energetic and we continually challenge the status quo… we’re nothing like your traditional finance institution. We have recently been certified as Great Place To Work. We’re proud to have built a culture where people feel heard, cared for, and empowered to push boundaries. We wouldn’t be able to continually improve and grow as a company without our diverse and exceptional team. In 2022 we started heavily investing in the MONEYME brand with the ambition to be a household name in the near future. What we are looking for: We are looking for a Data Analyst to assist building and evolving market leading BI capabilities in our Data Intelligence team. The Data Intelligence team is responsible for managing MONEYME's data reporting and data modelling. The primary roles are to; perform analysis on complicated business problems and develop maintainable reports/dashboards for internal stakeholders. Responsibilities for this position include:  Understanding technical reporting requirements and translate them into effective data models and PowerBI dashboards. Collaborating with key stakeholders and support the team in driving initiatives. Conducting business-oriented data analysis on credit decisioning, credit risk and collections. Providing regular updates on insights found in analytics projects. Participation of analysis on our AI applications.  To be successful in this role you must have the following:  Highly analytical with attention to detail. Experience in data manipulation and visualization tools like SQL Server, Python, PowerBI or similar. Hands-on experience in analytics and development/ tracking of KPI's. Solid written and oral communication skills – ability to articulate insights to diverse stakeholders and influence outcomes. Solid presentation skills – ability to digest complex information and explain in logical and simple terms. Experience in consumer lending would be an advantage, but we also consider other backgrounds.  What's in it for you: MONEYME’s employees and culture are core to who we are. We know that without a high-performing and engaged Team MONEYME, we will not achieve our ambitious goals for the future. We are proud to offer a collaborative and fun work environment. MONEYME is an equal opportunity employer and we value diversity, equity, and inclusion. We are committed to creating a diverse and inclusive workplace and encourage applicants from all backgrounds to apply. We believe that the unique contribution of our employees is a key driver of our success. We stand together – our diversity and inclusion give us an edge.
job_description.561: We are looking for an experienced Senior Analytics Engineer to join the growing Enterprise Data Team (MData). MData's aspiration is that data underpins the delivery of exceptional consumer experiences and enables retailers, suppliers and Metcash to better run and grow their businesses. It is a central team that is enabling data to be a strategic, accessible and valued asset across the Metcash Group supporting data & insights, analytics and ML/AI across business units. With the demand for data and insights continuing to grow, we are a looking for an energetic, Senior Analytical Engineer focused delivery of BI Solutions, managing data and ensuring its availability, reliability, and accessibility for use by data analysts, BI developer and other digital solutions.  As a Senior Analytic Engineer, you will be responsible for designing, developing, and implementing business intelligence solutions using Microsoft data technologies. You will collaborate closely with stakeholders, business analysts, and Azure Data engineers to understand requirements, gather data from various sources, and transform it into core enterprise standard data models that can be used for self-service datasets, deliver meaningful insights and visually appealing reports and dashboards.  What you'll do • Develop and maintain end-to-end BI Data modelling solutions, including PBI Datasets, Azure Synapse Data Models, deployment pipelines and PBI dashboards and reports • Collaborate with business analysts and stakeholders to gather requirements and translate them into technical specification e.g., conceptual and logical data models. • Contribute to the definition and structure of data extraction, transformation, and loading [ETL] processes to integrate data from diverse sources into Power BI • Develop complex Enterprise data models using DAX (Data Analysis Expressions) and optimise performance for large enterprise scale datasets • Implement BI data governance and security best practices, ensuring data accuracy, integrity, and confidentiality • Collaborate with the data engineering and solution architect team as well as the broader IT Team to identify and resolve data quality issues and opportunities for optimising BI platforms  What you'll bring • Proven experience as a Senior BI Data Modeller, with a strong portfolio of successful Power BI Projects, data modelling methodologies and data integration • Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to translate complex business requirements into technical solutions • Experience as a Business Intelligence developer or Analytical engineer in data warehousing space • Experience with data governance, security, and compliance best practices • Ability to coach and help develop skills across other team members • Bachelor's degree in computer science, information systems, or a related field • Proficient in Microsoft Power BI, including Power Query, DAX, power automate and Azure synapse Analytics • Advance PBI Data model's optimisation skills using external tools e.g., DAX Studio, Tabular Editor, ALM Toolkit and solid experience on Azure Data & Analytics SaaS technology framework  What we can offer • Hybrid working - flexibility is in our DNA. • Free on-site parking and close to public transport • An extra week of annual leave after your first year as part of our Fifth Week program, and the opportunity to purchase annual leave to help you recharge. • Our Met Health wellbeing program is designed to help you enjoy work/life balance and get the most out of life. • Access to 12 paid weeks of gender-equal parental leave for primary carers, and three weeks for partners  We're all about celebrating success, and we're proud to be a WGEA Employer of Choice for Equity, an accredited Flex Ready workplace, and a Gold Standard Mental Health First Aid skilled workplace.  If you're a tech-savvy thinker with a love for local communities, you'll discover a fulfilling career and an opportunity to redefine the future of independent business.  Make your Mark!  #LN-SO1  #INSO
job_description.562: About Tabcorp  Tabcorp is Australia's leading gambling entertainment company, renowned for our world-class brands including TAB, Sky Racing, and MAX. It’s an exciting moment in our history – a new era of Tabcorp. We’re bringing industry-leading products and services to our customers, leading with integrity, and creating value for our shareholders and industry partners by breaking into new horizons.  What You'll Do  As a Senior Digital Analyst you’ll join our Data & Analytics Centre of Excellence which is a game-changing hub of innovation and insights that is tasked with developing cutting-edge data and analytics solutions that tackle complex business challenges head-on.  Your role will be to partner with our Digital and Product teams to champion digital data analytics, support major digital initiatives and deliver insights that improve performance and create leading products and services. Therefore, you will: • develop digital insights leading to new and improved app and website features; • partner with developers on Adobe and Google Analytics initiatives; • drive digital engagement and growth through personalisation and tagging strategies; • analyze data to identify trends, understand user journeys, improve conversion funnels, and identify drop-off / pain points for customers; and • lead A/B Testing to evaluate effectiveness of digital marketing, web/app changes and conversion rate tests.  What you’ll bring  As a Senior Digital Analyst, you’ll have demonstrated experience in digital analytics role where you have developed a range of skills and experiences including: • strong experience developing strategies to drive digital engagement and growth across websites and apps; • experience in data analytics and exposure to website and mobile app development processes; • strong experience with Adobe Analytics or equivalent software (such as Google Analytics); • experience partnering with a range of stakeholders including product teams and software developers; and • ability to write and develop specifications for web and app tracking implementation. job_description.572: Careers That Change Lives  Be a part of a company that thinks differently to solve problems to deliver meaningful innovations. We have an opportunity for a talented Business Intelligence and Data Analytics Principal / Specialist to join our Australia & New Zealand (ANZ) Commercial Excellence team in a role to provide the key connections to IT, Global Data teams and our commercial Operating Units.  A Day in the Life  Reporting into the Director, Business Development and Strategy, this is an exciting and newly created opportunity, providing the mechanisms to enable all ANZ commercial Operating Unit teams to implement data driven decision making and resource allocation.  This successful individual will be the liaison to the Asia Pacific, Business Intelligence and Data team and will enable key initiatives identified by the ANZ and APAC Commercial Excellence team. He/she will be a business partner providing a point of contact for all commercial Operating Units to initiate, design, co-create and deliver Business Intelligence initiatives that support growth & efficiencies and increase customer satisfaction.  Key responsibilities include: • Providing business partnership between all commercial teams, functional teams and the BI and Data team • Driving ANZ design input to create reliable, easy to use system, BI and/or analytical tools to sales reporting, market analytics and inventory health analysis • Executing analysis through presenting to ANZ / APAC / Global stakeholders • Standardizing and simplifying Sales Reporting delivering comprehensive value and a consistent high-quality user experience • Developing and maintaining a central repository of data, insights, tools and expertise to enable Operating Units, i.e. OUs (independent of scope and scale of OU) to make data driven decisions (sample) • Resource allocation • Segmentation • SFE • Contract KPIs tracking / ROI analysis • Market economics • Contract and ROI analysis • Training and coaching commercial stakeholders on how to leverage BI tools, reports and insights and how to leverage in meaningful review processes • Finding / developing / building / maintaining local data sources to capture key market and customer trends (incl. consistent and timely market share metric). • Maintaining reporting system, verifying the accuracy of the data, and acting as liaison with information technology in identifying and resolving problems • Understanding complex business challenges, develop hypotheses, integrate internal and external data sources, analyze them using cutting edge machine learning and statistical modelling techniques to uncover causality and synthesizing insights. • Assisting CRM enablement and commercial capabilities through developing measurement scheme and its execution for their SFE initiatives. • Supporting IT system or technologies launch and replacement with BI requirements delivery. • Providing administrative support to the sales function such as preparing sales and/or expense forecasts, budgets, and quotas; coordinating sales meetings; etc. • Conducting statistical analysis on sales data and information to ensure optimal sales execution and attainment of growth objectives. • Analyzing market competition, e.g. NPI / GTM • Translating and visualizing local customer and market insights into actionable insights, e.g. segmentation, profiling and targeting • Coaching tools, & reviewing processes to stakeholders in OUs - integrating into commercial capabilities training • Closely working with PMO to ensure that all BI initiatives are appropriately entered into the PMO, prioritized and resourced.  Must Have • Bachelor's degree (or related) in Information Technology, Mathematics, Statistic, Engineering or Science and a minimum of 7 years relevant experience • Preferably 3+ years of relevant work experience in BI and Advanced Analytics area. • Data analysis skills with ability to understand complex models and business processes. • Hands on experience Visualization Tools such as Tableau or Power BI.  Good to Have • Salesforce.com Administrator/Advanced Administrator experience and knowledge of Medtronic systems (e.g. SAP) • Experiences on Excel, R/Python, Alteryx, SharePoint, etc... • Ability to work effectively in a matrix organization • Experience in working in large complex BI projects and/or IT system launch project • Data science, statistical analysis, ad-hoc advanced analytics, Machine/Deep Learning, AI • Experience on data processing tools such as Excel (Pivot), R, Python, Alteryx • Experience on SalesForceDotCom (SFDC), Snowflake, SQL basics • Strong business acumen and can recognize problems, opportunities and provide value-added business solutions • Able to work independently and manage multiple task assignments • Communicate various stakeholders effectively with respect to achieve the goals. • Fluent in English for business communication / presentation / reporting • Experience on biomedical systems or working for medical / pharmaceutical companies • Superior sales or marketing experience  Our Offer:  In our 5th Tenet of our Mission, we recognize the personal worth of employees by providing an employment framework that allows personal satisfaction in work accomplished, security, advancement opportunity, and means to share in the company's success.  We believe in rewarding our staff with a complete package of benefits designed to support them at every career and life stage. As a result, our employees have access to the following benefits, to name a few: • Range of on-demand online health and wellness training resources, apps, videos, and communities • We invest in professional training and development for employees at all levels. • Our Employee Resource Groups (ERG)- foster awareness and inclusion in the workplace. • Various insurance benefits include life and disability, salary continuances and salary sacrifice • We have generous employee referral programs, corporate discount programs, leave benefits, and more!  About Medtronic  Together, we can change healthcare worldwide. At Medtronic, we push the limits of what technology can do to help alleviate pain, restore health and extend life. We challenge ourselves and each other to make tomorrow better than yesterday. It is what makes this an exciting and rewarding place to be.  We can accelerate and advance our ability to create meaningful innovations - but we will only succeed with the right people on our team. Let's work together to address universal healthcare needs and improve patients' lives. Help us shape the future.  Additional Information • Posting Date: Sep 27, 2023 • Travel: No
job_description.573: Hi! And thanks for stopping by!  We’re MYOB, a business management platform designed to unleash the potential of businesses across Australia and New Zealand! As the #originalstartup, our roots are in finance and accounting software, but today we are so much more. We help our Aussie and Kiwi customers unleash their full potential, giving them the tools to Start, Survive and Succeed: all in the one place.  We’re always on the hunt for those who bring a different perspective, diversity of thought and the drive to make our culture even better. Take your career to a new dimension at MYOB.  About the Team  Our Unified marketing team is here to drive un-believe-able results for the business. They create demand in market for MYOB and engage AU & NZ businesses when it matters most to either acquire or retain them. They’re dedicated to delivering value for our customers by understanding their business pain points, and needs and ensuring we deliver them value at every stage of their journey.  Are you passionate about utilising data to drive strategic marketing decisions? Do you have a curiosity for extracting insights from complex datasets and turning them into practical recommendations? If so, we have an exciting opportunity for you to join our marketing team as a Marketing Performance Analyst.  About the Role  As a Marketing Performance Analyst, you will play a crucial role in supporting our marketing team by analysing data, tracking program performance, and providing strategic insights. Your focus will be on optimising channel effectiveness, enhancing marketing program outcomes, and contributing to the overall success of our marketing efforts. Reporting to the Marketing Analytics and Performance Manager, you will collaborate with various team members across the organisation, including marketing leaders, cross-functional teams, and external partners.  Key Responsibilities  - Conduct in-depth tactical data analysis across marketing channels, identifying areas for process improvement and implementing metrics from engagement to conversion across segments.  - Mine and analyse data from multiple sources to track the performance of marketing programs against key performance indicators, offering insights to drive optimisation.  - Monitor and analyse performance throughout the marketing and sales funnel, pinpointing opportunities for enhancement.  - Collaborate with marketing, sales, revenue operations, and finance teams to contribute to quarterly and annual forecasts and performance modelling.  - Develop and implement regular reporting and data visualisations to communicate insights to senior leaders, enhancing self-serve analytics across the marketing function.  - Stay up-to-date with the latest web analytics tools and technologies, making recommendations for new tools that can improve web performance monitoring.  About You  - Deep understanding of data analytics across multiple channels.  - Strong operational experience in systems, processes, and technologies.  - Profound understanding of B2B marketing and sales strategies.  - Proven experience in website analytics, preferably in e-commerce or digital marketing environments, with expertise in Google Analytics, including configuration and reporting.  - Proven experience with various data platforms and tools, including Google Analytics, Microsoft Power BI, CRM systems (e.g., Salesforce or HubSpot), Microsoft Excel, and SQL for data analysis.  - Ability to extract insights from extensive data volumes to inform customer acquisition and retention strategies.  - Prior experience in creating dashboards and reports to convey findings to diverse audiences.  - Familiarity with business databases and data warehouses (e.g., Snowflake) is desirable.  Skills and Competencies  - Commercial savvy and business insight.  - Proficiency in data analysis and insights generation.  - Effective communication and collaboration skills.  - Passion for getting results through data-driven decisions.  - Ability to work successfully in a cross-functional team environment.  Our Culture & Benefits  Our values have stood the test of time. If you want to work and collaborate where opinions are valued, and your ideas can make a difference, come to a place where Your Work Matters.     See what it's like to work at MYOB and what we're all about.     Do your best work in a flexible work environment, right down to financial assistance to set up your home office…it’s called Flexperience, and it’s designed by you and your team!     Our partnership with Smiling Mind helps support the wellbeing of our team members and customers     Drive your own learning via conferences, in-house training, LinkedIn Learning, study assistance and a strong focus on leaders creating a learning environment     A multitude of leave options including up to an additional four weeks of purchased leave, generous parental leave, domestic violence leave, transgender leave, volunteer leave, study leave, plus more!     Communities built around ‘Wellness’, ‘Belonging’ and the ‘Planet’ where you can make a meaningful contribution     Access to best-in-class discounts and vouchers from leading retailers, and a lot more.  We are proud to be a Circle Back Initiative Employer and we commit to responding to every applicant.  MYOB are an equal opportunity employer and we champion diversity. Don’t meet every single requirement of this role? Still apply! Research tells us that that women and underrepresented groups are less likely to apply unless they meet every single requirement. At MYOB we believe that the right hire is someone who makes an addition to our culture, rather than someone who fits in and conforms to our status quo. Moving to ‘Culture Add’ means adding team members who not only value MYOBs standards and workplace culture, but also bring an aspect of diversity that positively contributes to MYOB. So, if you’re excited about this role, or about MYOB, we’d still love to hear from you!

The Data Scientist role involves working on complex Data Science and AI initiatives that generate substantial business value, potentially including informal leadership responsibilities. These initiatives span from prototypes to scaled data science assets integrated into core business processes.  What you'll do • Contribute to best practices and thought leadership within the Data Science & AI community • Assist with the development of models and algorithms for optimal performance and risk management • Be a part of our evolution of Suncorp's Data Science & AI ecosystem, including platform integration • Work on technically complex AI projects with significant business impact • Prototyping to fully integrated, scaled data science assets in core business processes • Scaling AI initiatives and supporting data science endeavours company-wide  What you'll bring • 2+ years of experience in Data Science, AI, or related fields is required • Ability to discern current and emerging best practices, differentiating hype from efficacy • Ability to use Python or large language models • Bachelor's degree in a technical field (e.g., data science, machine learning, statistics, actuarial, engineering, mathematics) is mandatory • Commitment to team and Suncorp Data Science & AI community success • Pragmatic approach balancing technical excellence with resource constraints • Proficiency in holistic data science solution design, integrating technical expertise with innovative approaches • Skill in solving analytical challenges without prior patterns • Knowledge and practical experience in applying diverse Data Science and AI techniques for financial services solutions • Versatility across various work modes, from rapid innovation to project delivery  What we can offer you • A range of flexible working and leave options, including 20 weeks paid parental leave, 4 weeks paid secondary carer parental leave and unlimited paid emergency response leave • Discounts and offers on a range of retail favourite stores as well as banking and insurance products • Invest in your brighter future with ongoing study support and career development programs • Give back to our communities with payroll giving, donation matching and paid volunteer leave • Prioritise your work/life balance with our robust employee assistance program and dedicated employee council  Advertised: 05 Oct 2023 AUS Eastern Daylight Time Applications close: 26 Oct 2023 AUS Eastern Daylight Time  Don't
